116 /// isExactlyValue - We don't rely on operator== working on double values, as
117 /// it returns true for things that are clearly not equal, like -0.0 and 0.0.
118 /// As such, this method can be used to do an exact bit-for-bit comparison of
119 /// two floating point values.
120 bool ConstantFPSDNode::isExactlyValue(const APFloat& V) const {
121  return getValueAPF().bitwiseIsEqual(V);
122 }
123 
124 bool ConstantFPSDNode::isValueValidForType(EVT VT,
125  const APFloat& Val) {
126  assert(VT.isFloatingPoint() && "Can only convert between FP types");
127 
128  // convert modifies in place, so make a copy.
129  APFloat Val2 = APFloat(Val);
130  bool losesInfo;
131  (void) Val2.convert(SelectionDAG::EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT),
132  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven,
133  &losesInfo);
134  return !losesInfo;
135 }

141 bool ISD::isConstantSplatVector(const SDNode *N, APInt &SplatVal) {
142  if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR) {
143  unsigned EltSize =
144  N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType().getSizeInBits();
145  if (auto *Op0 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(0))) {
146  SplatVal = Op0->getAPIntValue().trunc(EltSize);
147  return true;
148  }
149  if (auto *Op0 = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N->getOperand(0))) {
150  SplatVal = Op0->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt().trunc(EltSize);
151  return true;
152  }
153  }
154 
155  auto *BV = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(N);
156  if (!BV)
157  return false;
158 
159  APInt SplatUndef;
160  unsigned SplatBitSize;
161  bool HasUndefs;
162  unsigned EltSize = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType().getSizeInBits();
163  return BV->isConstantSplat(SplatVal, SplatUndef, SplatBitSize, HasUndefs,
164  EltSize) &&
165  EltSize == SplatBitSize;
166 }
167 
168 // FIXME: AllOnes and AllZeros duplicate a lot of code. Could these be
169 // specializations of the more general isConstantSplatVector()?
170 
171 bool ISD::isConstantSplatVectorAllOnes(const SDNode *N, bool BuildVectorOnly) {
172  // Look through a bit convert.
173  while (N->getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST)
174  N = N->getOperand(0).getNode();
175 
176  if (!BuildVectorOnly && N->getOpcode() == ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR) {
177  APInt SplatVal;
178  return isConstantSplatVector(N, SplatVal) && SplatVal.isAllOnes();
179  }
180 
181  if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::BUILD_VECTOR) return false;
182 
183  unsigned i = 0, e = N->getNumOperands();
184 
185  // Skip over all of the undef values.
186  while (i != e && N->getOperand(i).isUndef())
187  ++i;
188 
189  // Do not accept an all-undef vector.
190  if (i == e) return false;
191 
192  // Do not accept build_vectors that aren't all constants or which have non-~0
193  // elements. We have to be a bit careful here, as the type of the constant
194  // may not be the same as the type of the vector elements due to type
195  // legalization (the elements are promoted to a legal type for the target and
196  // a vector of a type may be legal when the base element type is not).
197  // We only want to check enough bits to cover the vector elements, because
198  // we care if the resultant vector is all ones, not whether the individual
199  // constants are.
200  SDValue NotZero = N->getOperand(i);
201  unsigned EltSize = N->getValueType(0).getScalarSizeInBits();
202  if (ConstantSDNode *CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(NotZero)) {
203  if (CN->getAPIntValue().countTrailingOnes() < EltSize)
204  return false;
205  } else if (ConstantFPSDNode *CFPN = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(NotZero)) {
206  if (CFPN->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt().countTrailingOnes() < EltSize)
207  return false;
208  } else
209  return false;
210 
211  // Okay, we have at least one ~0 value, check to see if the rest match or are
212  // undefs. Even with the above element type twiddling, this should be OK, as
213  // the same type legalization should have applied to all the elements.
214  for (++i; i != e; ++i)
215  if (N->getOperand(i) != NotZero && !N->getOperand(i).isUndef())
216  return false;
217  return true;
218 }
219 
220 bool ISD::isConstantSplatVectorAllZeros(const SDNode *N, bool BuildVectorOnly) {
221  // Look through a bit convert.
222  while (N->getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST)
223  N = N->getOperand(0).getNode();
224 
225  if (!BuildVectorOnly && N->getOpcode() == ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR) {
226  APInt SplatVal;
227  return isConstantSplatVector(N, SplatVal) && SplatVal.isZero();
228  }
229 
230  if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::BUILD_VECTOR) return false;
231 
232  bool IsAllUndef = true;
233  for (const SDValue &Op : N->op_values()) {
234  if (Op.isUndef())
235  continue;
236  IsAllUndef = false;
237  // Do not accept build_vectors that aren't all constants or which have non-0
238  // elements. We have to be a bit careful here, as the type of the constant
239  // may not be the same as the type of the vector elements due to type
240  // legalization (the elements are promoted to a legal type for the target
241  // and a vector of a type may be legal when the base element type is not).
242  // We only want to check enough bits to cover the vector elements, because
243  // we care if the resultant vector is all zeros, not whether the individual
244  // constants are.
245  unsigned EltSize = N->getValueType(0).getScalarSizeInBits();
246  if (ConstantSDNode *CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)) {
247  if (CN->getAPIntValue().countTrailingZeros() < EltSize)
248  return false;
249  } else if (ConstantFPSDNode *CFPN = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op)) {
250  if (CFPN->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt().countTrailingZeros() < EltSize)
251  return false;
252  } else
253  return false;
254  }
255 
256  // Do not accept an all-undef vector.
257  if (IsAllUndef)
258  return false;
259  return true;
260 }

263  return isConstantSplatVectorAllOnes(N, /*BuildVectorOnly*/ true);

266 bool ISD::isBuildVectorAllZeros(const SDNode *N) {
267  return isConstantSplatVectorAllZeros(N, /*BuildVectorOnly*/ true);

270 bool ISD::isBuildVectorOfConstantSDNodes(const SDNode *N) {
271  if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::BUILD_VECTOR)
272  return false;
273 
274  for (const SDValue &Op : N->op_values()) {
275  if (Op.isUndef())
276  continue;
277  if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(Op))
278  return false;
279  }
280  return true;
281 }

283 bool ISD::isBuildVectorOfConstantFPSDNodes(const SDNode *N) {
284  if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::BUILD_VECTOR)
285  return false;
286 
287  for (const SDValue &Op : N->op_values()) {
288  if (Op.isUndef())
289  continue;
290  if (!isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op))
291  return false;
292  }
293  return true;
294 }

296 bool ISD::isVectorShrinkable(const SDNode *N, unsigned NewEltSize,
297  bool Signed) {
298  assert(N->getValueType(0).isVector() && "Expected a vector!");
299 
300  unsigned EltSize = N->getValueType(0).getScalarSizeInBits();
301  if (EltSize <= NewEltSize)
302  return false;
303 
304  if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND) {
305  return (N->getOperand(0).getValueType().getScalarSizeInBits() <=
306  NewEltSize) &&
307  !Signed;
308  }
309  if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND) {
310  return (N->getOperand(0).getValueType().getScalarSizeInBits() <=
311  NewEltSize) &&
312  Signed;
313  }
314  if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::BUILD_VECTOR)
315  return false;
316 
317  for (const SDValue &Op : N->op_values()) {
318  if (Op.isUndef())
319  continue;
320  if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(Op))
321  return false;
322 
323  APInt C = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)->getAPIntValue().trunc(EltSize);
324  if (Signed && C.trunc(NewEltSize).sext(EltSize) != C)
325  return false;
326  if (!Signed && C.trunc(NewEltSize).zext(EltSize) != C)
327  return false;
328  }
329 
330  return true;
331 }
332 
333 bool ISD::allOperandsUndef(const SDNode *N) {
334  // Return false if the node has no operands.
335  // This is "logically inconsistent" with the definition of "all" but
336  // is probably the desired behavior.
337  if (N->getNumOperands() == 0)
338  return false;
339  return all_of(N->op_values(), [](SDValue Op) { return Op.isUndef(); });
340 }

342 bool ISD::isFreezeUndef(const SDNode *N) {
343  return N->getOpcode() == ISD::FREEZE && N->getOperand(0).isUndef();
344 }
345 
346 bool ISD::matchUnaryPredicate(SDValue Op,
347  std::function<bool(ConstantSDNode *)> Match,
348  bool AllowUndefs) {
349  // FIXME: Add support for scalar UNDEF cases?
350  if (auto *Cst = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op))
351  return Match(Cst);
352 
353  // FIXME: Add support for vector UNDEF cases?
354  if (ISD::BUILD_VECTOR != Op.getOpcode() &&
355  ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR != Op.getOpcode())
356  return false;
357 
358  EVT SVT = Op.getValueType().getScalarType();
359  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Op.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
360  if (AllowUndefs && Op.getOperand(i).isUndef()) {
361  if (!Match(nullptr))
362  return false;
363  continue;
364  }
365 
366  auto *Cst = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(i));
367  if (!Cst || Cst->getValueType(0) != SVT || !Match(Cst))
368  return false;
369  }
370  return true;
371 }
372 
373 bool ISD::matchBinaryPredicate(
374  SDValue LHS, SDValue RHS,
375  std::function<bool(ConstantSDNode *, ConstantSDNode *)> Match,
376  bool AllowUndefs, bool AllowTypeMismatch) {
377  if (!AllowTypeMismatch && LHS.getValueType() != RHS.getValueType())
378  return false;
379 
380  // TODO: Add support for scalar UNDEF cases?
381  if (auto *LHSCst = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(LHS))
382  if (auto *RHSCst = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS))
383  return Match(LHSCst, RHSCst);
384 
385  // TODO: Add support for vector UNDEF cases?
386  if (LHS.getOpcode() != RHS.getOpcode() ||
387  (LHS.getOpcode() != ISD::BUILD_VECTOR &&
388  LHS.getOpcode() != ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR))
389  return false;
390 
391  EVT SVT = LHS.getValueType().getScalarType();
392  for (unsigned i = 0, e = LHS.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
393  SDValue LHSOp = LHS.getOperand(i);
394  SDValue RHSOp = RHS.getOperand(i);
395  bool LHSUndef = AllowUndefs && LHSOp.isUndef();
396  bool RHSUndef = AllowUndefs && RHSOp.isUndef();
397  auto *LHSCst = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(LHSOp);
398  auto *RHSCst = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHSOp);
399  if ((!LHSCst && !LHSUndef) || (!RHSCst && !RHSUndef))
400  return false;
401  if (!AllowTypeMismatch && (LHSOp.getValueType() != SVT ||
402  LHSOp.getValueType() != RHSOp.getValueType()))
403  return false;
404  if (!Match(LHSCst, RHSCst))
405  return false;
406  }
407  return true;
408 }

410 ISD::NodeType ISD::getVecReduceBaseOpcode(unsigned VecReduceOpcode) {
411  switch (VecReduceOpcode) {
412  default:
413  llvm_unreachable("Expected VECREDUCE opcode");
414  case ISD::VECREDUCE_FADD:
415  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FADD:
416  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FADD:
417  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SEQ_FADD:
418  return ISD::FADD;
419  case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMUL:
420  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FMUL:
421  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FMUL:
422  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SEQ_FMUL:
423  return ISD::FMUL;
424  case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD:
425  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_ADD:
426  return ISD::ADD;
427  case ISD::VECREDUCE_MUL:
428  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_MUL:
429  return ISD::MUL;
430  case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND:
431  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_AND:
432  return ISD::AND;
433  case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR:
434  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_OR:
435  return ISD::OR;
436  case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR:
437  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_XOR:
438  return ISD::XOR;
439  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX:
440  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SMAX:
441  return ISD::SMAX;
442  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN:
443  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SMIN:
444  return ISD::SMIN;
445  case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX:
446  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_UMAX:
447  return ISD::UMAX;
448  case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN:
449  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_UMIN:
450  return ISD::UMIN;
451  case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMAX:
452  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FMAX:
453  return ISD::FMAXNUM;
454  case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMIN:
455  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FMIN:
456  return ISD::FMINNUM;
457  }
458 }

544 ISD::NodeType ISD::getExtForLoadExtType(bool IsFP, ISD::LoadExtType ExtType) {
545  switch (ExtType) {
546  case ISD::EXTLOAD:
547  return IsFP ? ISD::FP_EXTEND : ISD::ANY_EXTEND;
548  case ISD::SEXTLOAD:
549  return ISD::SIGN_EXTEND;
550  case ISD::ZEXTLOAD:
551  return ISD::ZERO_EXTEND;
552  default:
553  break;
554  }
555 
556  llvm_unreachable("Invalid LoadExtType");
557 }
558 
559 ISD::CondCode ISD::getSetCCSwappedOperands(ISD::CondCode Operation) {
560  // To perform this operation, we just need to swap the L and G bits of the
561  // operation.
562  unsigned OldL = (Operation >> 2) & 1;
563  unsigned OldG = (Operation >> 1) & 1;
564  return ISD::CondCode((Operation & ~6) | // Keep the N, U, E bits
565  (OldL << 1) | // New G bit
566  (OldG << 2)); // New L bit.
567 }
568 
569 static ISD::CondCode getSetCCInverseImpl(ISD::CondCode Op, bool isIntegerLike) {
570  unsigned Operation = Op;
571  if (isIntegerLike)
572  Operation ^= 7; // Flip L, G, E bits, but not U.
573  else
574  Operation ^= 15; // Flip all of the condition bits.
575 
576  if (Operation > ISD::SETTRUE2)
577  Operation &= ~8; // Don't let N and U bits get set.
578 
579  return ISD::CondCode(Operation);
580 }
581 
582 ISD::CondCode ISD::getSetCCInverse(ISD::CondCode Op, EVT Type) {
583  return getSetCCInverseImpl(Op, Type.isInteger());
584 }
585 
586 ISD::CondCode ISD::GlobalISel::getSetCCInverse(ISD::CondCode Op,
587  bool isIntegerLike) {
588  return getSetCCInverseImpl(Op, isIntegerLike);
589 }
590 
591 /// For an integer comparison, return 1 if the comparison is a signed operation
592 /// and 2 if the result is an unsigned comparison. Return zero if the operation
593 /// does not depend on the sign of the input (setne and seteq).
594 static int isSignedOp(ISD::CondCode Opcode) {
595  switch (Opcode) {
596  default: llvm_unreachable("Illegal integer setcc operation!");
597  case ISD::SETEQ:
598  case ISD::SETNE: return 0;
599  case ISD::SETLT:
600  case ISD::SETLE:
601  case ISD::SETGT:
602  case ISD::SETGE: return 1;
603  case ISD::SETULT:
604  case ISD::SETULE:
605  case ISD::SETUGT:
606  case ISD::SETUGE: return 2;
607  }
608 }
609 
610 ISD::CondCode ISD::getSetCCOrOperation(ISD::CondCode Op1, ISD::CondCode Op2,
611  EVT Type) {
612  bool IsInteger = Type.isInteger();
613  if (IsInteger && (isSignedOp(Op1) | isSignedOp(Op2)) == 3)
614  // Cannot fold a signed integer setcc with an unsigned integer setcc.
615  return ISD::SETCC_INVALID;
616 
617  unsigned Op = Op1 | Op2; // Combine all of the condition bits.
618 
619  // If the N and U bits get set, then the resultant comparison DOES suddenly
620  // care about orderedness, and it is true when ordered.
621  if (Op > ISD::SETTRUE2)
622  Op &= ~16; // Clear the U bit if the N bit is set.
623 
624  // Canonicalize illegal integer setcc's.
625  if (IsInteger && Op == ISD::SETUNE) // e.g. SETUGT | SETULT
626  Op = ISD::SETNE;
627 
628  return ISD::CondCode(Op);
629 }
630 
631 ISD::CondCode ISD::getSetCCAndOperation(ISD::CondCode Op1, ISD::CondCode Op2,
632  EVT Type) {
633  bool IsInteger = Type.isInteger();
634  if (IsInteger && (isSignedOp(Op1) | isSignedOp(Op2)) == 3)
635  // Cannot fold a signed setcc with an unsigned setcc.
636  return ISD::SETCC_INVALID;
637 
638  // Combine all of the condition bits.
639  ISD::CondCode Result = ISD::CondCode(Op1 & Op2);
640 
641  // Canonicalize illegal integer setcc's.
642  if (IsInteger) {
643  switch (Result) {
644  default: break;
645  case ISD::SETUO : Result = ISD::SETFALSE; break; // SETUGT & SETULT
646  case ISD::SETOEQ: // SETEQ & SETU[LG]E
647  case ISD::SETUEQ: Result = ISD::SETEQ ; break; // SETUGE & SETULE
648  case ISD::SETOLT: Result = ISD::SETULT ; break; // SETULT & SETNE
649  case ISD::SETOGT: Result = ISD::SETUGT ; break; // SETUGT & SETNE
650  }
651  }
652 
653  return Result;
654 }

696 /// If this is an SDNode with special info, add this info to the NodeID data.
697 static void AddNodeIDCustom(FoldingSetNodeID &ID, const SDNode *N) {
698  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
699  case ISD::TargetExternalSymbol:
700  case ISD::ExternalSymbol:
701  case ISD::MCSymbol:
702  llvm_unreachable("Should only be used on nodes with operands");
703  default: break; // Normal nodes don't need extra info.
704  case ISD::TargetConstant:
705  case ISD::Constant: {
706  const ConstantSDNode *C = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N);
707  ID.AddPointer(C->getConstantIntValue());
708  ID.AddBoolean(C->isOpaque());
709  break;
710  }
711  case ISD::TargetConstantFP:
712  case ISD::ConstantFP:
713  ID.AddPointer(cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N)->getConstantFPValue());
714  break;
715  case ISD::TargetGlobalAddress:
716  case ISD::GlobalAddress:
717  case ISD::TargetGlobalTLSAddress:
718  case ISD::GlobalTLSAddress: {
719  const GlobalAddressSDNode *GA = cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(N);
720  ID.AddPointer(GA->getGlobal());
721  ID.AddInteger(GA->getOffset());
722  ID.AddInteger(GA->getTargetFlags());
723  break;
724  }
725  case ISD::BasicBlock:
726  ID.AddPointer(cast<BasicBlockSDNode>(N)->getBasicBlock());
727  break;
728  case ISD::Register:
729  ID.AddInteger(cast<RegisterSDNode>(N)->getReg());
730  break;
731  case ISD::RegisterMask:
732  ID.AddPointer(cast<RegisterMaskSDNode>(N)->getRegMask());
733  break;
734  case ISD::SRCVALUE:
735  ID.AddPointer(cast<SrcValueSDNode>(N)->getValue());
736  break;
737  case ISD::FrameIndex:
738  case ISD::TargetFrameIndex:
739  ID.AddInteger(cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(N)->getIndex());
740  break;
741  case ISD::LIFETIME_START:
742  case ISD::LIFETIME_END:
743  if (cast<LifetimeSDNode>(N)->hasOffset()) {
744  ID.AddInteger(cast<LifetimeSDNode>(N)->getSize());
745  ID.AddInteger(cast<LifetimeSDNode>(N)->getOffset());
746  }
747  break;
748  case ISD::PSEUDO_PROBE:
749  ID.AddInteger(cast<PseudoProbeSDNode>(N)->getGuid());
750  ID.AddInteger(cast<PseudoProbeSDNode>(N)->getIndex());
751  ID.AddInteger(cast<PseudoProbeSDNode>(N)->getAttributes());
752  break;
753  case ISD::JumpTable:
754  case ISD::TargetJumpTable:
755  ID.AddInteger(cast<JumpTableSDNode>(N)->getIndex());
756  ID.AddInteger(cast<JumpTableSDNode>(N)->getTargetFlags());
757  break;
758  case ISD::ConstantPool:
759  case ISD::TargetConstantPool: {
760  const ConstantPoolSDNode *CP = cast<ConstantPoolSDNode>(N);
761  ID.AddInteger(CP->getAlign().value());
762  ID.AddInteger(CP->getOffset());
763  if (CP->isMachineConstantPoolEntry())
764  CP->getMachineCPVal()->addSelectionDAGCSEId(ID);
765  else
766  ID.AddPointer(CP->getConstVal());
767  ID.AddInteger(CP->getTargetFlags());
768  break;
769  }
770  case ISD::TargetIndex: {
771  const TargetIndexSDNode *TI = cast<TargetIndexSDNode>(N);
772  ID.AddInteger(TI->getIndex());
773  ID.AddInteger(TI->getOffset());
774  ID.AddInteger(TI->getTargetFlags());
775  break;
776  }
777  case ISD::LOAD: {
778  const LoadSDNode *LD = cast<LoadSDNode>(N);
779  ID.AddInteger(LD->getMemoryVT().getRawBits());
780  ID.AddInteger(LD->getRawSubclassData());
781  ID.AddInteger(LD->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
782  ID.AddInteger(LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
783  break;
784  }
785  case ISD::STORE: {
786  const StoreSDNode *ST = cast<StoreSDNode>(N);
787  ID.AddInteger(ST->getMemoryVT().getRawBits());
788  ID.AddInteger(ST->getRawSubclassData());
789  ID.AddInteger(ST->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
790  ID.AddInteger(ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
791  break;
792  }
793  case ISD::VP_LOAD: {
794  const VPLoadSDNode *ELD = cast<VPLoadSDNode>(N);
795  ID.AddInteger(ELD->getMemoryVT().getRawBits());
796  ID.AddInteger(ELD->getRawSubclassData());
797  ID.AddInteger(ELD->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
798  ID.AddInteger(ELD->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
799  break;
800  }
801  case ISD::VP_STORE: {
802  const VPStoreSDNode *EST = cast<VPStoreSDNode>(N);
803  ID.AddInteger(EST->getMemoryVT().getRawBits());
804  ID.AddInteger(EST->getRawSubclassData());
805  ID.AddInteger(EST->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
806  ID.AddInteger(EST->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
807  break;
808  }
809  case ISD::EXPERIMENTAL_VP_STRIDED_LOAD: {
810  const VPStridedLoadSDNode *SLD = cast<VPStridedLoadSDNode>(N);
811  ID.AddInteger(SLD->getMemoryVT().getRawBits());
812  ID.AddInteger(SLD->getRawSubclassData());
813  ID.AddInteger(SLD->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
814  break;
815  }
816  case ISD::EXPERIMENTAL_VP_STRIDED_STORE: {
817  const VPStridedStoreSDNode *SST = cast<VPStridedStoreSDNode>(N);
818  ID.AddInteger(SST->getMemoryVT().getRawBits());
819  ID.AddInteger(SST->getRawSubclassData());
820  ID.AddInteger(SST->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
821  break;
822  }
823  case ISD::VP_GATHER: {
824  const VPGatherSDNode *EG = cast<VPGatherSDNode>(N);
825  ID.AddInteger(EG->getMemoryVT().getRawBits());
826  ID.AddInteger(EG->getRawSubclassData());
827  ID.AddInteger(EG->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
828  ID.AddInteger(EG->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
829  break;
830  }
831  case ISD::VP_SCATTER: {
832  const VPScatterSDNode *ES = cast<VPScatterSDNode>(N);
833  ID.AddInteger(ES->getMemoryVT().getRawBits());
834  ID.AddInteger(ES->getRawSubclassData());
835  ID.AddInteger(ES->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
836  ID.AddInteger(ES->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
837  break;
838  }
839  case ISD::MLOAD: {
840  const MaskedLoadSDNode *MLD = cast<MaskedLoadSDNode>(N);
841  ID.AddInteger(MLD->getMemoryVT().getRawBits());
842  ID.AddInteger(MLD->getRawSubclassData());
843  ID.AddInteger(MLD->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
844  ID.AddInteger(MLD->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
845  break;
846  }
847  case ISD::MSTORE: {
848  const MaskedStoreSDNode *MST = cast<MaskedStoreSDNode>(N);
849  ID.AddInteger(MST->getMemoryVT().getRawBits());
850  ID.AddInteger(MST->getRawSubclassData());
851  ID.AddInteger(MST->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
852  ID.AddInteger(MST->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
853  break;
854  }
855  case ISD::MGATHER: {
856  const MaskedGatherSDNode *MG = cast<MaskedGatherSDNode>(N);
857  ID.AddInteger(MG->getMemoryVT().getRawBits());
858  ID.AddInteger(MG->getRawSubclassData());
859  ID.AddInteger(MG->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
860  ID.AddInteger(MG->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
861  break;
862  }
863  case ISD::MSCATTER: {
864  const MaskedScatterSDNode *MS = cast<MaskedScatterSDNode>(N);
865  ID.AddInteger(MS->getMemoryVT().getRawBits());
866  ID.AddInteger(MS->getRawSubclassData());
867  ID.AddInteger(MS->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
868  ID.AddInteger(MS->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
869  break;
870  }
871  case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP:
872  case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_WITH_SUCCESS:
873  case ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP:
874  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD:
875  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB:
876  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND:
877  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_CLR:
878  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR:
879  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR:
880  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND:
881  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN:
882  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX:
883  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN:
884  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX:
885  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD:
886  case ISD::ATOMIC_STORE: {
887  const AtomicSDNode *AT = cast<AtomicSDNode>(N);
888  ID.AddInteger(AT->getMemoryVT().getRawBits());
889  ID.AddInteger(AT->getRawSubclassData());
890  ID.AddInteger(AT->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
891  ID.AddInteger(AT->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
892  break;
893  }
894  case ISD::PREFETCH: {
895  const MemSDNode *PF = cast<MemSDNode>(N);
896  ID.AddInteger(PF->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
897  ID.AddInteger(PF->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
898  break;
899  }
900  case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE: {
901  const ShuffleVectorSDNode *SVN = cast<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(N);
902  for (unsigned i = 0, e = N->getValueType(0).getVectorNumElements();
903  i != e; ++i)
904  ID.AddInteger(SVN->getMaskElt(i));
905  break;
906  }
907  case ISD::TargetBlockAddress:
908  case ISD::BlockAddress: {
909  const BlockAddressSDNode *BA = cast<BlockAddressSDNode>(N);
910  ID.AddPointer(BA->getBlockAddress());
911  ID.AddInteger(BA->getOffset());
912  ID.AddInteger(BA->getTargetFlags());
913  break;
914  }
915  case ISD::AssertAlign:
916  ID.AddInteger(cast<AssertAlignSDNode>(N)->getAlign().value());
917  break;
918  } // end switch (N->getOpcode())
919 
920  // Target specific memory nodes could also have address spaces and flags
921  // to check.
922  if (N->isTargetMemoryOpcode()) {
923  const MemSDNode *MN = cast<MemSDNode>(N);
924  ID.AddInteger(MN->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
925  ID.AddInteger(MN->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
926  }
927 }

929 /// AddNodeIDNode - Generic routine for adding a nodes info to the NodeID
930 /// data.
931 static void AddNodeIDNode(FoldingSetNodeID &ID, const SDNode *N) {
932  AddNodeIDOpcode(ID, N->getOpcode());
933  // Add the return value info.
934  AddNodeIDValueTypes(ID, N->getVTList());
935  // Add the operand info.
936  AddNodeIDOperands(ID, N->ops());
937 
938  // Handle SDNode leafs with special info.
939  AddNodeIDCustom(ID, N);
940 }

946 /// doNotCSE - Return true if CSE should not be performed for this node.
947 static bool doNotCSE(SDNode *N) {
948  if (N->getValueType(0) == MVT::Glue)
949  return true; // Never CSE anything that produces a flag.
950 
951  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
952  default: break;
953  case ISD::HANDLENODE:
954  case ISD::EH_LABEL:
955  return true; // Never CSE these nodes.
956  }
957 
958  // Check that remaining values produced are not flags.
959  for (unsigned i = 1, e = N->getNumValues(); i != e; ++i)
960  if (N->getValueType(i) == MVT::Glue)
961  return true; // Never CSE anything that produces a flag.
962 
963  return false;
964 }
965 
966 /// RemoveDeadNodes - This method deletes all unreachable nodes in the
967 /// SelectionDAG.
968 void SelectionDAG::RemoveDeadNodes() {
969  // Create a dummy node (which is not added to allnodes), that adds a reference
970  // to the root node, preventing it from being deleted.
971  HandleSDNode Dummy(getRoot());
972 
973  SmallVector<SDNode*, 128> DeadNodes;
974 
975  // Add all obviously-dead nodes to the DeadNodes worklist.
976  for (SDNode &Node : allnodes())
977  if (Node.use_empty())
978  DeadNodes.push_back(&Node);
979 
980  RemoveDeadNodes(DeadNodes);
981 
982  // If the root changed (e.g. it was a dead load, update the root).
983  setRoot(Dummy.getValue());
984 }
985 
986 /// RemoveDeadNodes - This method deletes the unreachable nodes in the
987 /// given list, and any nodes that become unreachable as a result.
988 void SelectionDAG::RemoveDeadNodes(SmallVectorImpl<SDNode *> &DeadNodes) {
989 
990  // Process the worklist, deleting the nodes and adding their uses to the
991  // worklist.
992  while (!DeadNodes.empty()) {
993  SDNode *N = DeadNodes.pop_back_val();
994  // Skip to next node if we've already managed to delete the node. This could
995  // happen if replacing a node causes a node previously added to the node to
996  // be deleted.
997  if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::DELETED_NODE)
998  continue;
999 
1000  for (DAGUpdateListener *DUL = UpdateListeners; DUL; DUL = DUL->Next)
1001  DUL->NodeDeleted(N, nullptr);
1002 
1003  // Take the node out of the appropriate CSE map.
1004  RemoveNodeFromCSEMaps(N);
1005 
1006  // Next, brutally remove the operand list. This is safe to do, as there are
1007  // no cycles in the graph.
1008  for (SDNode::op_iterator I = N->op_begin(), E = N->op_end(); I != E; ) {
1009  SDUse &Use = *I++;
1010  SDNode *Operand = Use.getNode();
1011  Use.set(SDValue());
1012 
1013  // Now that we removed this operand, see if there are no uses of it left.
1014  if (Operand->use_empty())
1015  DeadNodes.push_back(Operand);
1016  }
1017 
1018  DeallocateNode(N);
1019  }
1020 }
1021 
1022 void SelectionDAG::RemoveDeadNode(SDNode *N){
1023  SmallVector<SDNode*, 16> DeadNodes(1, N);
1024 
1025  // Create a dummy node that adds a reference to the root node, preventing
1026  // it from being deleted. (This matters if the root is an operand of the
1027  // dead node.)
1028  HandleSDNode Dummy(getRoot());
1029 
1030  RemoveDeadNodes(DeadNodes);
1031 }
1032 
1033 void SelectionDAG::DeleteNode(SDNode *N) {
1034  // First take this out of the appropriate CSE map.
1035  RemoveNodeFromCSEMaps(N);
1036 
1037  // Finally, remove uses due to operands of this node, remove from the
1038  // AllNodes list, and delete the node.
1039  DeleteNodeNotInCSEMaps(N);
1040 }
1041 
1042 void SelectionDAG::DeleteNodeNotInCSEMaps(SDNode *N) {
1043  assert(N->getIterator() != AllNodes.begin() &&
1044  "Cannot delete the entry node!");
1045  assert(N->use_empty() && "Cannot delete a node that is not dead!");
1046 
1047  // Drop all of the operands and decrement used node's use counts.
1048  N->DropOperands();
1049 
1050  DeallocateNode(N);
1051 }
1052 
1053 void SDDbgInfo::add(SDDbgValue *V, bool isParameter) {
1054  assert(!(V->isVariadic() && isParameter));
1055  if (isParameter)
1056  ByvalParmDbgValues.push_back(V);
1057  else
1058  DbgValues.push_back(V);
1059  for (const SDNode *Node : V->getSDNodes())
1060  if (Node)
1061  DbgValMap[Node].push_back(V);
1062 }
1063 
1064 void SDDbgInfo::erase(const SDNode *Node) {
1065  DbgValMapType::iterator I = DbgValMap.find(Node);
1066  if (I == DbgValMap.end())
1067  return;
1068  for (auto &Val: I->second)
1069  Val->setIsInvalidated();
1070  DbgValMap.erase(I);
1071 }
1072 
1073 void SelectionDAG::DeallocateNode(SDNode *N) {
1074  // If we have operands, deallocate them.
1075  removeOperands(N);
1076 
1077  NodeAllocator.Deallocate(AllNodes.remove(N));
1078 
1079  // Set the opcode to DELETED_NODE to help catch bugs when node
1080  // memory is reallocated.
1081  // FIXME: There are places in SDag that have grown a dependency on the opcode
1082  // value in the released node.
1083  __asan_unpoison_memory_region(&N->NodeType, sizeof(N->NodeType));
1084  N->NodeType = ISD::DELETED_NODE;
1085 
1086  // If any of the SDDbgValue nodes refer to this SDNode, invalidate
1087  // them and forget about that node.
1088  DbgInfo->erase(N);
1089 
1090  // Invalidate extra info.
1091  SDEI.erase(N);
1092 }
1093 
1094 #ifndef NDEBUG
1095 /// VerifySDNode - Check the given SDNode. Aborts if it is invalid.
1096 static void VerifySDNode(SDNode *N) {
1097  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
1098  default:
1099  break;
1100  case ISD::BUILD_PAIR: {
1101  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
1102  assert(N->getNumValues() == 1 && "Too many results!");
1103  assert(!VT.isVector() && (VT.isInteger() || VT.isFloatingPoint()) &&
1104  "Wrong return type!");
1105  assert(N->getNumOperands() == 2 && "Wrong number of operands!");
1106  assert(N->getOperand(0).getValueType() == N->getOperand(1).getValueType() &&
1107  "Mismatched operand types!");
1108  assert(N->getOperand(0).getValueType().isInteger() == VT.isInteger() &&
1109  "Wrong operand type!");
1110  assert(VT.getSizeInBits() == 2 * N->getOperand(0).getValueSizeInBits() &&
1111  "Wrong return type size");
1112  break;
1113  }
1114  case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: {
1115  assert(N->getNumValues() == 1 && "Too many results!");
1116  assert(N->getValueType(0).isVector() && "Wrong return type!");
1117  assert(N->getNumOperands() == N->getValueType(0).getVectorNumElements() &&
1118  "Wrong number of operands!");
1119  EVT EltVT = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
1120  for (const SDUse &Op : N->ops()) {
1121  assert((Op.getValueType() == EltVT ||
1122  (EltVT.isInteger() && Op.getValueType().isInteger() &&
1123  EltVT.bitsLE(Op.getValueType()))) &&
1124  "Wrong operand type!");
1125  assert(Op.getValueType() == N->getOperand(0).getValueType() &&
1126  "Operands must all have the same type");
1127  }
1128  break;
1129  }
1130  }
1131 }
1132 #endif // NDEBUG
1133 
1134 /// Insert a newly allocated node into the DAG.
1135 ///
1136 /// Handles insertion into the all nodes list and CSE map, as well as
1137 /// verification and other common operations when a new node is allocated.
1138 void SelectionDAG::InsertNode(SDNode *N) {
1139  AllNodes.push_back(N);
1140 #ifndef NDEBUG
1141  N->PersistentId = NextPersistentId++;
1142  VerifySDNode(N);
1143 #endif
1144  for (DAGUpdateListener *DUL = UpdateListeners; DUL; DUL = DUL->Next)
1145  DUL->NodeInserted(N);
1146 }
1147 
1148 /// RemoveNodeFromCSEMaps - Take the specified node out of the CSE map that
1149 /// correspond to it. This is useful when we're about to delete or repurpose
1150 /// the node. We don't want future request for structurally identical nodes
1151 /// to return N anymore.
1152 bool SelectionDAG::RemoveNodeFromCSEMaps(SDNode *N) {
1153  bool Erased = false;
1154  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
1155  case ISD::HANDLENODE: return false; // noop.
1156  case ISD::CONDCODE:
1157  assert(CondCodeNodes[cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N)->get()] &&
1158  "Cond code doesn't exist!");
1159  Erased = CondCodeNodes[cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N)->get()] != nullptr;
1160  CondCodeNodes[cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N)->get()] = nullptr;
1161  break;
1162  case ISD::ExternalSymbol:
1163  Erased = ExternalSymbols.erase(cast<ExternalSymbolSDNode>(N)->getSymbol());
1164  break;
1165  case ISD::TargetExternalSymbol: {
1166  ExternalSymbolSDNode *ESN = cast<ExternalSymbolSDNode>(N);
1167  Erased = TargetExternalSymbols.erase(std::pair<std::string, unsigned>(
1168  ESN->getSymbol(), ESN->getTargetFlags()));
1169  break;
1170  }
1171  case ISD::MCSymbol: {
1172  auto *MCSN = cast<MCSymbolSDNode>(N);
1173  Erased = MCSymbols.erase(MCSN->getMCSymbol());
1174  break;
1175  }
1176  case ISD::VALUETYPE: {
1177  EVT VT = cast<VTSDNode>(N)->getVT();
1178  if (VT.isExtended()) {
1179  Erased = ExtendedValueTypeNodes.erase(VT);
1180  } else {
1181  Erased = ValueTypeNodes[VT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy] != nullptr;
1182  ValueTypeNodes[VT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy] = nullptr;
1183  }
1184  break;
1185  }
1186  default:
1187  // Remove it from the CSE Map.
1188  assert(N->getOpcode() != ISD::DELETED_NODE && "DELETED_NODE in CSEMap!");
1189  assert(N->getOpcode() != ISD::EntryToken && "EntryToken in CSEMap!");
1190  Erased = CSEMap.RemoveNode(N);
1191  break;
1192  }
1193 #ifndef NDEBUG
1194  // Verify that the node was actually in one of the CSE maps, unless it has a
1195  // flag result (which cannot be CSE'd) or is one of the special cases that are
1196  // not subject to CSE.
1197  if (!Erased && N->getValueType(N->getNumValues()-1) != MVT::Glue &&
1198  !N->isMachineOpcode() && !doNotCSE(N)) {
1199  N->dump(this);
1200  dbgs() << "\n";
1201  llvm_unreachable("Node is not in map!");
1202  }
1203 #endif
1204  return Erased;
1205 }
1206 
1207 /// AddModifiedNodeToCSEMaps - The specified node has been removed from the CSE
1208 /// maps and modified in place. Add it back to the CSE maps, unless an identical
1209 /// node already exists, in which case transfer all its users to the existing
1210 /// node. This transfer can potentially trigger recursive merging.
1211 void
1212 SelectionDAG::AddModifiedNodeToCSEMaps(SDNode *N) {
1213  // For node types that aren't CSE'd, just act as if no identical node
1214  // already exists.
1215  if (!doNotCSE(N)) {
1216  SDNode *Existing = CSEMap.GetOrInsertNode(N);
1217  if (Existing != N) {
1218  // If there was already an existing matching node, use ReplaceAllUsesWith
1219  // to replace the dead one with the existing one. This can cause
1220  // recursive merging of other unrelated nodes down the line.
1221  ReplaceAllUsesWith(N, Existing);
1222 
1223  // N is now dead. Inform the listeners and delete it.
1224  for (DAGUpdateListener *DUL = UpdateListeners; DUL; DUL = DUL->Next)
1225  DUL->NodeDeleted(N, Existing);
1226  DeleteNodeNotInCSEMaps(N);
1227  return;
1228  }
1229  }
1230 
1231  // If the node doesn't already exist, we updated it. Inform listeners.
1232  for (DAGUpdateListener *DUL = UpdateListeners; DUL; DUL = DUL->Next)
1233  DUL->NodeUpdated(N);
1234 }
1235 
1236 /// FindModifiedNodeSlot - Find a slot for the specified node if its operands
1237 /// were replaced with those specified. If this node is never memoized,
1238 /// return null, otherwise return a pointer to the slot it would take. If a
1239 /// node already exists with these operands, the slot will be non-null.
1240 SDNode *SelectionDAG::FindModifiedNodeSlot(SDNode *N, SDValue Op,
1241  void *&InsertPos) {
1242  if (doNotCSE(N))
1243  return nullptr;
1244 
1245  SDValue Ops[] = { Op };
1246  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
1247  AddNodeIDNode(ID, N->getOpcode(), N->getVTList(), Ops);
1248  AddNodeIDCustom(ID, N);
1249  SDNode *Node = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, SDLoc(N), InsertPos);
1250  if (Node)
1251  Node->intersectFlagsWith(N->getFlags());
1252  return Node;
1253 }

1256 /// were replaced with those specified. If this node is never memoized,
1257 /// return null, otherwise return a pointer to the slot it would take. If a
1258 /// node already exists with these operands, the slot will be non-null.
1259 SDNode *SelectionDAG::FindModifiedNodeSlot(SDNode *N,
1260  SDValue Op1, SDValue Op2,

1263  return nullptr;
1264 
1265  SDValue Ops[] = { Op1, Op2 };

1268  AddNodeIDCustom(ID, N);
1269  SDNode *Node = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, SDLoc(N), InsertPos);
1270  if (Node)
1271  Node->intersectFlagsWith(N->getFlags());
1272  return Node;
1273 }

1341 void SelectionDAG::allnodes_clear() {
1342  assert(&*AllNodes.begin() == &EntryNode);
1343  AllNodes.remove(AllNodes.begin());
1344  while (!AllNodes.empty())
1345  DeallocateNode(&AllNodes.front());
1346 #ifndef NDEBUG
1347  NextPersistentId = 0;
1348 #endif
1349 }
1350 
1351 SDNode *SelectionDAG::FindNodeOrInsertPos(const FoldingSetNodeID &ID,
1352  void *&InsertPos) {
1353  SDNode *N = CSEMap.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
1354  if (N) {
1355  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
1356  default: break;
1357  case ISD::Constant:
1358  case ISD::ConstantFP:
1359  llvm_unreachable("Querying for Constant and ConstantFP nodes requires "
1360  "debug location. Use another overload.");
1361  }
1362  }
1363  return N;
1364 }
1365 
1366 SDNode *SelectionDAG::FindNodeOrInsertPos(const FoldingSetNodeID &ID,
1367  const SDLoc &DL, void *&InsertPos) {
1368  SDNode *N = CSEMap.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
1369  if (N) {
1370  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
1371  case ISD::Constant:
1372  case ISD::ConstantFP:
1373  // Erase debug location from the node if the node is used at several
1374  // different places. Do not propagate one location to all uses as it
1375  // will cause a worse single stepping debugging experience.
1376  if (N->getDebugLoc() != DL.getDebugLoc())
1377  N->setDebugLoc(DebugLoc());
1378  break;
1379  default:
1380  // When the node's point of use is located earlier in the instruction
1381  // sequence than its prior point of use, update its debug info to the
1382  // earlier location.
1383  if (DL.getIROrder() && DL.getIROrder() < N->getIROrder())
1384  N->setDebugLoc(DL.getDebugLoc());
1385  break;
1386  }
1387  }
1388  return N;
1389 }
1390 
1391 void SelectionDAG::clear() {
1392  allnodes_clear();
1393  OperandRecycler.clear(OperandAllocator);
1394  OperandAllocator.Reset();
1395  CSEMap.clear();
1396 
1397  ExtendedValueTypeNodes.clear();
1398  ExternalSymbols.clear();
1399  TargetExternalSymbols.clear();
1400  MCSymbols.clear();
1401  SDEI.clear();
1402  std::fill(CondCodeNodes.begin(), CondCodeNodes.end(),
1403  static_cast<CondCodeSDNode*>(nullptr));
1404  std::fill(ValueTypeNodes.begin(), ValueTypeNodes.end(),
1405  static_cast<SDNode*>(nullptr));
1406 
1407  EntryNode.UseList = nullptr;
1408  InsertNode(&EntryNode);
1409  Root = getEntryNode();
1410  DbgInfo->clear();
1411 }

1413 SDValue SelectionDAG::getFPExtendOrRound(SDValue Op, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT) {
1414  return VT.bitsGT(Op.getValueType())
1415  ? getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, DL, VT, Op)
1416  : getNode(ISD::FP_ROUND, DL, VT, Op,
1417  getIntPtrConstant(0, DL, /*isTarget=*/true));
1418 }

1420 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue>
1421 SelectionDAG::getStrictFPExtendOrRound(SDValue Op, SDValue Chain,
1422  const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT) {
1423  assert(!VT.bitsEq(Op.getValueType()) &&
1424  "Strict no-op FP extend/round not allowed.");
1425  SDValue Res =
1426  VT.bitsGT(Op.getValueType())
1427  ? getNode(ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND, DL, {VT, MVT::Other}, {Chain, Op})
1428  : getNode(ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND, DL, {VT, MVT::Other},
1429  {Chain, Op, getIntPtrConstant(0, DL)});
1430 
1431  return std::pair<SDValue, SDValue>(Res, SDValue(Res.getNode(), 1));
1432 }

1452 SDValue SelectionDAG::getBoolExtOrTrunc(SDValue Op, const SDLoc &SL, EVT VT,
1453  EVT OpVT) {

1455  return getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SL, VT, Op);

1458  return getNode(TLI->getExtendForContent(BType), SL, VT, Op);

1461 SDValue SelectionDAG::getZeroExtendInReg(SDValue Op, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT) {
1462  EVT OpVT = Op.getValueType();
1463  assert(VT.isInteger() && OpVT.isInteger() &&
1464  "Cannot getZeroExtendInReg FP types");
1465  assert(VT.isVector() == OpVT.isVector() &&
1466  "getZeroExtendInReg type should be vector iff the operand "
1467  "type is vector!");
1468  assert((!VT.isVector() ||
1469  VT.getVectorElementCount() == OpVT.getVectorElementCount()) &&
1470  "Vector element counts must match in getZeroExtendInReg");
1471  assert(VT.bitsLE(OpVT) && "Not extending!");
1472  if (OpVT == VT)
1473  return Op;
1474  APInt Imm = APInt::getLowBitsSet(OpVT.getScalarSizeInBits(),
1475  VT.getScalarSizeInBits());
1476  return getNode(ISD::AND, DL, OpVT, Op, getConstant(Imm, DL, OpVT));
1477 }

1481  // might delegate to TLI to check pointer signedness.
1482  return getZExtOrTrunc(Op, DL, VT);
1483 }

1525 SDValue SelectionDAG::getBoolConstant(bool V, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
1526  EVT OpVT) {
1527  if (!V)
1528  return getConstant(0, DL, VT);
1529 
1530  switch (TLI->getBooleanContents(OpVT)) {
1531  case TargetLowering::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent:
1532  case TargetLowering::UndefinedBooleanContent:
1533  return getConstant(1, DL, VT);
1534  case TargetLowering::ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent:
1535  return getAllOnesConstant(DL, VT);
1536  }
1537  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected boolean content enum!");
1538 }

1540 SDValue SelectionDAG::getConstant(uint64_t Val, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
1541  bool isT, bool isO) {
1542  EVT EltVT = VT.getScalarType();
1543  assert((EltVT.getSizeInBits() >= 64 ||
1544  (uint64_t)((int64_t)Val >> EltVT.getSizeInBits()) + 1 < 2) &&
1545  "getConstant with a uint64_t value that doesn't fit in the type!");
1546  return getConstant(APInt(EltVT.getSizeInBits(), Val), DL, VT, isT, isO);
1547 }
1548 
1549 SDValue SelectionDAG::getConstant(const APInt &Val, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
1550  bool isT, bool isO) {
1551  return getConstant(*ConstantInt::get(*Context, Val), DL, VT, isT, isO);
1552 }
1553 
1554 SDValue SelectionDAG::getConstant(const ConstantInt &Val, const SDLoc &DL,
1555  EVT VT, bool isT, bool isO) {
1556  assert(VT.isInteger() && "Cannot create FP integer constant!");
1557 
1558  EVT EltVT = VT.getScalarType();
1559  const ConstantInt *Elt = &Val;
1560 
1561  // In some cases the vector type is legal but the element type is illegal and
1562  // needs to be promoted, for example v8i8 on ARM. In this case, promote the
1563  // inserted value (the type does not need to match the vector element type).
1564  // Any extra bits introduced will be truncated away.
1565  if (VT.isVector() && TLI->getTypeAction(*getContext(), EltVT) ==
1566  TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger) {
1567  EltVT = TLI->getTypeToTransformTo(*getContext(), EltVT);
1568  APInt NewVal = Elt->getValue().zextOrTrunc(EltVT.getSizeInBits());
1569  Elt = ConstantInt::get(*getContext(), NewVal);
1570  }
1571  // In other cases the element type is illegal and needs to be expanded, for
1572  // example v2i64 on MIPS32. In this case, find the nearest legal type, split
1573  // the value into n parts and use a vector type with n-times the elements.
1574  // Then bitcast to the type requested.
1575  // Legalizing constants too early makes the DAGCombiner's job harder so we
1576  // only legalize if the DAG tells us we must produce legal types.
1577  else if (NewNodesMustHaveLegalTypes && VT.isVector() &&
1578  TLI->getTypeAction(*getContext(), EltVT) ==
1579  TargetLowering::TypeExpandInteger) {
1580  const APInt &NewVal = Elt->getValue();
1581  EVT ViaEltVT = TLI->getTypeToTransformTo(*getContext(), EltVT);
1582  unsigned ViaEltSizeInBits = ViaEltVT.getSizeInBits();
1583 
1584  // For scalable vectors, try to use a SPLAT_VECTOR_PARTS node.
1585  if (VT.isScalableVector()) {
1586  assert(EltVT.getSizeInBits() % ViaEltSizeInBits == 0 &&
1587  "Can only handle an even split!");
1588  unsigned Parts = EltVT.getSizeInBits() / ViaEltSizeInBits;
1589 
1590  SmallVector<SDValue, 2> ScalarParts;
1591  for (unsigned i = 0; i != Parts; ++i)
1592  ScalarParts.push_back(getConstant(
1593  NewVal.extractBits(ViaEltSizeInBits, i * ViaEltSizeInBits), DL,
1594  ViaEltVT, isT, isO));
1595 
1596  return getNode(ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR_PARTS, DL, VT, ScalarParts);
1597  }
1598 
1599  unsigned ViaVecNumElts = VT.getSizeInBits() / ViaEltSizeInBits;
1600  EVT ViaVecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*getContext(), ViaEltVT, ViaVecNumElts);
1601 
1602  // Check the temporary vector is the correct size. If this fails then
1603  // getTypeToTransformTo() probably returned a type whose size (in bits)
1604  // isn't a power-of-2 factor of the requested type size.
1605  assert(ViaVecVT.getSizeInBits() == VT.getSizeInBits());
1606 
1607  SmallVector<SDValue, 2> EltParts;
1608  for (unsigned i = 0; i < ViaVecNumElts / VT.getVectorNumElements(); ++i)
1609  EltParts.push_back(getConstant(
1610  NewVal.extractBits(ViaEltSizeInBits, i * ViaEltSizeInBits), DL,
1611  ViaEltVT, isT, isO));
1612 
1613  // EltParts is currently in little endian order. If we actually want
1614  // big-endian order then reverse it now.
1615  if (getDataLayout().isBigEndian())
1616  std::reverse(EltParts.begin(), EltParts.end());
1617 
1618  // The elements must be reversed when the element order is different
1619  // to the endianness of the elements (because the BITCAST is itself a
1620  // vector shuffle in this situation). However, we do not need any code to
1621  // perform this reversal because getConstant() is producing a vector
1622  // splat.
1623  // This situation occurs in MIPS MSA.
1624 
1625  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
1626  for (unsigned i = 0, e = VT.getVectorNumElements(); i != e; ++i)
1627  llvm::append_range(Ops, EltParts);
1628 
1629  SDValue V =
1630  getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VT, getBuildVector(ViaVecVT, DL, Ops));
1631  return V;
1632  }
1633 
1634  assert(Elt->getBitWidth() == EltVT.getSizeInBits() &&
1635  "APInt size does not match type size!");
1636  unsigned Opc = isT ? ISD::TargetConstant : ISD::Constant;
1637  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
1638  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opc, getVTList(EltVT), std::nullopt);
1639  ID.AddPointer(Elt);
1640  ID.AddBoolean(isO);
1641  void *IP = nullptr;
1642  SDNode *N = nullptr;
1643  if ((N = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, DL, IP)))
1644  if (!VT.isVector())
1645  return SDValue(N, 0);
1646 
1647  if (!N) {
1648  N = newSDNode<ConstantSDNode>(isT, isO, Elt, EltVT);
1649  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
1650  InsertNode(N);
1651  NewSDValueDbgMsg(SDValue(N, 0), "Creating constant: ", this);
1652  }
1653 
1654  SDValue Result(N, 0);
1655  if (VT.isVector())
1656  Result = getSplat(VT, DL, Result);
1657  return Result;
1658 }
1659 
1660 SDValue SelectionDAG::getIntPtrConstant(uint64_t Val, const SDLoc &DL,
1661  bool isTarget) {
1662  return getConstant(Val, DL, TLI->getPointerTy(getDataLayout()), isTarget);
1663 }

1677 SDValue SelectionDAG::getConstantFP(const APFloat &V, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,

1681 
1682 SDValue SelectionDAG::getConstantFP(const ConstantFP &V, const SDLoc &DL,
1683  EVT VT, bool isTarget) {
1684  assert(VT.isFloatingPoint() && "Cannot create integer FP constant!");
1685 
1686  EVT EltVT = VT.getScalarType();
1687 
1688  // Do the map lookup using the actual bit pattern for the floating point
1689  // value, so that we don't have problems with 0.0 comparing equal to -0.0, and
1690  // we don't have issues with SNANs.
1691  unsigned Opc = isTarget ? ISD::TargetConstantFP : ISD::ConstantFP;
1692  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
1693  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opc, getVTList(EltVT), std::nullopt);
1694  ID.AddPointer(&V);
1695  void *IP = nullptr;
1696  SDNode *N = nullptr;
1697  if ((N = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, DL, IP)))
1698  if (!VT.isVector())
1699  return SDValue(N, 0);
1700 
1701  if (!N) {
1702  N = newSDNode<ConstantFPSDNode>(isTarget, &V, EltVT);
1703  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
1704  InsertNode(N);
1705  }
1706 
1707  SDValue Result(N, 0);
1708  if (VT.isVector())
1709  Result = getSplat(VT, DL, Result);
1710  NewSDValueDbgMsg(Result, "Creating fp constant: ", this);
1711  return Result;
1712 }
1713 
1714 SDValue SelectionDAG::getConstantFP(double Val, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
1715  bool isTarget) {
1716  EVT EltVT = VT.getScalarType();
1717  if (EltVT == MVT::f32)
1718  return getConstantFP(APFloat((float)Val), DL, VT, isTarget);
1719  if (EltVT == MVT::f64)
1720  return getConstantFP(APFloat(Val), DL, VT, isTarget);
1721  if (EltVT == MVT::f80 || EltVT == MVT::f128 || EltVT == MVT::ppcf128 ||
1722  EltVT == MVT::f16 || EltVT == MVT::bf16) {
1723  bool Ignored;
1724  APFloat APF = APFloat(Val);
1725  APF.convert(EVTToAPFloatSemantics(EltVT), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven,
1726  &Ignored);
1727  return getConstantFP(APF, DL, VT, isTarget);
1728  }
1729  llvm_unreachable("Unsupported type in getConstantFP");
1730 }
1731 
1732 SDValue SelectionDAG::getGlobalAddress(const GlobalValue *GV, const SDLoc &DL,
1733  EVT VT, int64_t Offset, bool isTargetGA,
1734  unsigned TargetFlags) {
1735  assert((TargetFlags == 0 || isTargetGA) &&
1736  "Cannot set target flags on target-independent globals");
1737 
1738  // Truncate (with sign-extension) the offset value to the pointer size.
1739  unsigned BitWidth = getDataLayout().getPointerTypeSizeInBits(GV->getType());
1740  if (BitWidth < 64)
1741  Offset = SignExtend64(Offset, BitWidth);
1742 
1743  unsigned Opc;
1744  if (GV->isThreadLocal())
1745  Opc = isTargetGA ? ISD::TargetGlobalTLSAddress : ISD::GlobalTLSAddress;
1746  else
1747  Opc = isTargetGA ? ISD::TargetGlobalAddress : ISD::GlobalAddress;
1748 
1749  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
1750  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opc, getVTList(VT), std::nullopt);
1751  ID.AddPointer(GV);
1752  ID.AddInteger(Offset);
1753  ID.AddInteger(TargetFlags);
1754  void *IP = nullptr;
1755  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, DL, IP))
1756  return SDValue(E, 0);
1757 
1758  auto *N = newSDNode<GlobalAddressSDNode>(
1759  Opc, DL.getIROrder(), DL.getDebugLoc(), GV, VT, Offset, TargetFlags);
1760  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
1761  InsertNode(N);
1762  return SDValue(N, 0);
1763 }

1943 SDValue SelectionDAG::getStepVector(const SDLoc &DL, EVT ResVT, APInt StepVal) {
1944  assert(ResVT.getScalarSizeInBits() == StepVal.getBitWidth());
1945  if (ResVT.isScalableVector())
1946  return getNode(
1947  ISD::STEP_VECTOR, DL, ResVT,
1948  getTargetConstant(StepVal, DL, ResVT.getVectorElementType()));
1949 
1950  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> OpsStepConstants;
1951  for (uint64_t i = 0; i < ResVT.getVectorNumElements(); i++)
1952  OpsStepConstants.push_back(
1953  getConstant(StepVal * i, DL, ResVT.getVectorElementType()));
1954  return getBuildVector(ResVT, DL, OpsStepConstants);
1955 }
1956 
1957 /// Swaps the values of N1 and N2. Swaps all indices in the shuffle mask M that
1958 /// point at N1 to point at N2 and indices that point at N2 to point at N1.
1959 static void commuteShuffle(SDValue &N1, SDValue &N2, MutableArrayRef<int> M) {
1960  std::swap(N1, N2);
1961  ShuffleVectorSDNode::commuteMask(M);
1962 }
1963 
1964 SDValue SelectionDAG::getVectorShuffle(EVT VT, const SDLoc &dl, SDValue N1,
1965  SDValue N2, ArrayRef<int> Mask) {
1966  assert(VT.getVectorNumElements() == Mask.size() &&
1967  "Must have the same number of vector elements as mask elements!");
1968  assert(VT == N1.getValueType() && VT == N2.getValueType() &&
1969  "Invalid VECTOR_SHUFFLE");
1970 
1971  // Canonicalize shuffle undef, undef -> undef
1972  if (N1.isUndef() && N2.isUndef())
1973  return getUNDEF(VT);
1974 
1975  // Validate that all indices in Mask are within the range of the elements
1976  // input to the shuffle.
1977  int NElts = Mask.size();
1978  assert(llvm::all_of(Mask,
1979  [&](int M) { return M < (NElts * 2) && M >= -1; }) &&
1980  "Index out of range");
1981 
1982  // Copy the mask so we can do any needed cleanup.
1983  SmallVector<int, 8> MaskVec(Mask);
1984 
1985  // Canonicalize shuffle v, v -> v, undef
1986  if (N1 == N2) {
1987  N2 = getUNDEF(VT);
1988  for (int i = 0; i != NElts; ++i)
1989  if (MaskVec[i] >= NElts) MaskVec[i] -= NElts;
1990  }
1991 
1992  // Canonicalize shuffle undef, v -> v, undef. Commute the shuffle mask.
1993  if (N1.isUndef())
1994  commuteShuffle(N1, N2, MaskVec);
1995 
1996  if (TLI->hasVectorBlend()) {
1997  // If shuffling a splat, try to blend the splat instead. We do this here so
1998  // that even when this arises during lowering we don't have to re-handle it.
1999  auto BlendSplat = [&](BuildVectorSDNode *BV, int Offset) {
2000  BitVector UndefElements;
2001  SDValue Splat = BV->getSplatValue(&UndefElements);
2002  if (!Splat)
2003  return;
2004 
2005  for (int i = 0; i < NElts; ++i) {
2006  if (MaskVec[i] < Offset || MaskVec[i] >= (Offset + NElts))
2007  continue;
2008 
2009  // If this input comes from undef, mark it as such.
2010  if (UndefElements[MaskVec[i] - Offset]) {
2011  MaskVec[i] = -1;
2012  continue;
2013  }
2014 
2015  // If we can blend a non-undef lane, use that instead.
2016  if (!UndefElements[i])
2017  MaskVec[i] = i + Offset;
2018  }
2019  };
2020  if (auto *N1BV = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(N1))
2021  BlendSplat(N1BV, 0);
2022  if (auto *N2BV = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(N2))
2023  BlendSplat(N2BV, NElts);
2024  }
2025 
2026  // Canonicalize all index into lhs, -> shuffle lhs, undef
2027  // Canonicalize all index into rhs, -> shuffle rhs, undef
2028  bool AllLHS = true, AllRHS = true;
2029  bool N2Undef = N2.isUndef();
2030  for (int i = 0; i != NElts; ++i) {
2031  if (MaskVec[i] >= NElts) {
2032  if (N2Undef)
2033  MaskVec[i] = -1;
2034  else
2035  AllLHS = false;
2036  } else if (MaskVec[i] >= 0) {
2037  AllRHS = false;
2038  }
2039  }
2040  if (AllLHS && AllRHS)
2041  return getUNDEF(VT);
2042  if (AllLHS && !N2Undef)
2043  N2 = getUNDEF(VT);
2044  if (AllRHS) {
2045  N1 = getUNDEF(VT);
2046  commuteShuffle(N1, N2, MaskVec);
2047  }
2048  // Reset our undef status after accounting for the mask.
2049  N2Undef = N2.isUndef();
2050  // Re-check whether both sides ended up undef.
2051  if (N1.isUndef() && N2Undef)
2052  return getUNDEF(VT);
2053 
2054  // If Identity shuffle return that node.
2055  bool Identity = true, AllSame = true;
2056  for (int i = 0; i != NElts; ++i) {
2057  if (MaskVec[i] >= 0 && MaskVec[i] != i) Identity = false;
2058  if (MaskVec[i] != MaskVec[0]) AllSame = false;
2059  }
2060  if (Identity && NElts)
2061  return N1;
2062 
2063  // Shuffling a constant splat doesn't change the result.
2064  if (N2Undef) {
2065  SDValue V = N1;
2066 
2067  // Look through any bitcasts. We check that these don't change the number
2068  // (and size) of elements and just changes their types.
2069  while (V.getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST)
2070  V = V->getOperand(0);
2071 
2072  // A splat should always show up as a build vector node.
2073  if (auto *BV = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(V)) {
2074  BitVector UndefElements;
2075  SDValue Splat = BV->getSplatValue(&UndefElements);
2076  // If this is a splat of an undef, shuffling it is also undef.
2077  if (Splat && Splat.isUndef())
2078  return getUNDEF(VT);
2079 
2080  bool SameNumElts =
2081  V.getValueType().getVectorNumElements() == VT.getVectorNumElements();
2082 
2083  // We only have a splat which can skip shuffles if there is a splatted
2084  // value and no undef lanes rearranged by the shuffle.
2085  if (Splat && UndefElements.none()) {
2086  // Splat of <x, x, ..., x>, return <x, x, ..., x>, provided that the
2087  // number of elements match or the value splatted is a zero constant.
2088  if (SameNumElts)
2089  return N1;
2090  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Splat))
2091  if (C->isZero())
2092  return N1;
2093  }
2094 
2095  // If the shuffle itself creates a splat, build the vector directly.
2096  if (AllSame && SameNumElts) {
2097  EVT BuildVT = BV->getValueType(0);
2098  const SDValue &Splatted = BV->getOperand(MaskVec[0]);
2099  SDValue NewBV = getSplatBuildVector(BuildVT, dl, Splatted);
2100 
2101  // We may have jumped through bitcasts, so the type of the
2102  // BUILD_VECTOR may not match the type of the shuffle.
2103  if (BuildVT != VT)
2104  NewBV = getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, VT, NewBV);
2105  return NewBV;
2106  }
2107  }
2108  }
2109 
2110  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
2111  SDValue Ops[2] = { N1, N2 };
2112  AddNodeIDNode(ID, ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE, getVTList(VT), Ops);
2113  for (int i = 0; i != NElts; ++i)
2114  ID.AddInteger(MaskVec[i]);
2115 
2116  void* IP = nullptr;
2117  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, dl, IP))
2118  return SDValue(E, 0);
2119 
2120  // Allocate the mask array for the node out of the BumpPtrAllocator, since
2121  // SDNode doesn't have access to it. This memory will be "leaked" when
2122  // the node is deallocated, but recovered when the NodeAllocator is released.
2123  int *MaskAlloc = OperandAllocator.Allocate<int>(NElts);
2124  llvm::copy(MaskVec, MaskAlloc);
2125 
2126  auto *N = newSDNode<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(VT, dl.getIROrder(),
2127  dl.getDebugLoc(), MaskAlloc);
2128  createOperands(N, Ops);
2129 
2130  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
2131  InsertNode(N);
2132  SDValue V = SDValue(N, 0);
2133  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
2134  return V;
2135 }
2136 
2137 SDValue SelectionDAG::getCommutedVectorShuffle(const ShuffleVectorSDNode &SV) {
2138  EVT VT = SV.getValueType(0);
2139  SmallVector<int, 8> MaskVec(SV.getMask());
2140  ShuffleVectorSDNode::commuteMask(MaskVec);
2141 
2142  SDValue Op0 = SV.getOperand(0);
2143  SDValue Op1 = SV.getOperand(1);
2144  return getVectorShuffle(VT, SDLoc(&SV), Op1, Op0, MaskVec);
2145 }

2250 SDValue SelectionDAG::getBitcast(EVT VT, SDValue V) {
2251  if (VT == V.getValueType())
2252  return V;
2253 
2254  return getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SDLoc(V), VT, V);
2255 }

2257 SDValue SelectionDAG::getAddrSpaceCast(const SDLoc &dl, EVT VT, SDValue Ptr,
2258  unsigned SrcAS, unsigned DestAS) {
2259  SDValue Ops[] = {Ptr};
2260  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
2261  AddNodeIDNode(ID, ISD::ADDRSPACECAST, getVTList(VT), Ops);
2262  ID.AddInteger(SrcAS);
2263  ID.AddInteger(DestAS);
2264 
2265  void *IP = nullptr;
2266  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, dl, IP))
2267  return SDValue(E, 0);
2268 
2269  auto *N = newSDNode<AddrSpaceCastSDNode>(dl.getIROrder(), dl.getDebugLoc(),
2270  VT, SrcAS, DestAS);
2271  createOperands(N, Ops);
2272 
2273  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
2274  InsertNode(N);
2275  return SDValue(N, 0);
2276 }

2292 SDValue SelectionDAG::expandVAArg(SDNode *Node) {
2293  SDLoc dl(Node);
2294  const TargetLowering &TLI = getTargetLoweringInfo();
2295  const Value *V = cast<SrcValueSDNode>(Node->getOperand(2))->getValue();
2296  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
2297  SDValue Tmp1 = Node->getOperand(0);
2298  SDValue Tmp2 = Node->getOperand(1);
2299  const MaybeAlign MA(Node->getConstantOperandVal(3));
2300 
2301  SDValue VAListLoad = getLoad(TLI.getPointerTy(getDataLayout()), dl, Tmp1,
2302  Tmp2, MachinePointerInfo(V));
2303  SDValue VAList = VAListLoad;
2304 
2305  if (MA && *MA > TLI.getMinStackArgumentAlignment()) {
2306  VAList = getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VAList.getValueType(), VAList,
2307  getConstant(MA->value() - 1, dl, VAList.getValueType()));
2308 
2309  VAList =
2310  getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VAList.getValueType(), VAList,
2311  getConstant(-(int64_t)MA->value(), dl, VAList.getValueType()));
2312  }
2313 
2314  // Increment the pointer, VAList, to the next vaarg
2315  Tmp1 = getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VAList.getValueType(), VAList,
2316  getConstant(getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(
2317  VT.getTypeForEVT(*getContext())),
2318  dl, VAList.getValueType()));
2319  // Store the incremented VAList to the legalized pointer
2320  Tmp1 =
2321  getStore(VAListLoad.getValue(1), dl, Tmp1, Tmp2, MachinePointerInfo(V));
2322  // Load the actual argument out of the pointer VAList
2323  return getLoad(VT, dl, Tmp1, VAList, MachinePointerInfo());
2324 }
2325 
2326 SDValue SelectionDAG::expandVACopy(SDNode *Node) {
2327  SDLoc dl(Node);
2328  const TargetLowering &TLI = getTargetLoweringInfo();
2329  // This defaults to loading a pointer from the input and storing it to the
2330  // output, returning the chain.
2331  const Value *VD = cast<SrcValueSDNode>(Node->getOperand(3))->getValue();
2332  const Value *VS = cast<SrcValueSDNode>(Node->getOperand(4))->getValue();
2333  SDValue Tmp1 =
2334  getLoad(TLI.getPointerTy(getDataLayout()), dl, Node->getOperand(0),
2335  Node->getOperand(2), MachinePointerInfo(VS));
2336  return getStore(Tmp1.getValue(1), dl, Tmp1, Node->getOperand(1),
2337  MachinePointerInfo(VD));
2338 }
2339 
2340 Align SelectionDAG::getReducedAlign(EVT VT, bool UseABI) {
2341  const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout();
2342  Type *Ty = VT.getTypeForEVT(*getContext());
2343  Align RedAlign = UseABI ? DL.getABITypeAlign(Ty) : DL.getPrefTypeAlign(Ty);
2344 
2345  if (TLI->isTypeLegal(VT) || !VT.isVector())
2346  return RedAlign;
2347 
2348  const TargetFrameLowering *TFI = MF->getSubtarget().getFrameLowering();
2349  const Align StackAlign = TFI->getStackAlign();
2350 
2351  // See if we can choose a smaller ABI alignment in cases where it's an
2352  // illegal vector type that will get broken down.
2353  if (RedAlign > StackAlign) {
2354  EVT IntermediateVT;
2355  MVT RegisterVT;
2356  unsigned NumIntermediates;
2357  TLI->getVectorTypeBreakdown(*getContext(), VT, IntermediateVT,
2358  NumIntermediates, RegisterVT);
2359  Ty = IntermediateVT.getTypeForEVT(*getContext());
2360  Align RedAlign2 = UseABI ? DL.getABITypeAlign(Ty) : DL.getPrefTypeAlign(Ty);
2361  if (RedAlign2 < RedAlign)
2362  RedAlign = RedAlign2;
2363  }
2364 
2365  return RedAlign;
2366 }

2368 SDValue SelectionDAG::CreateStackTemporary(TypeSize Bytes, Align Alignment) {
2369  MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF->getFrameInfo();
2370  const TargetFrameLowering *TFI = MF->getSubtarget().getFrameLowering();
2371  int StackID = 0;
2372  if (Bytes.isScalable())
2373  StackID = TFI->getStackIDForScalableVectors();
2374  // The stack id gives an indication of whether the object is scalable or
2375  // not, so it's safe to pass in the minimum size here.
2376  int FrameIdx = MFI.CreateStackObject(Bytes.getKnownMinValue(), Alignment,
2377  false, nullptr, StackID);
2378  return getFrameIndex(FrameIdx, TLI->getFrameIndexTy(getDataLayout()));
2379 }

2381 SDValue SelectionDAG::CreateStackTemporary(EVT VT, unsigned minAlign) {
2382  Type *Ty = VT.getTypeForEVT(*getContext());
2383  Align StackAlign =
2384  std::max(getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlign(Ty), Align(minAlign));
2385  return CreateStackTemporary(VT.getStoreSize(), StackAlign);
2386 }
2387 
2388 SDValue SelectionDAG::CreateStackTemporary(EVT VT1, EVT VT2) {
2389  TypeSize VT1Size = VT1.getStoreSize();
2390  TypeSize VT2Size = VT2.getStoreSize();
2391  assert(VT1Size.isScalable() == VT2Size.isScalable() &&
2392  "Don't know how to choose the maximum size when creating a stack "
2393  "temporary");
2394  TypeSize Bytes = VT1Size.getKnownMinValue() > VT2Size.getKnownMinValue()
2395  ? VT1Size
2396  : VT2Size;
2397 
2398  Type *Ty1 = VT1.getTypeForEVT(*getContext());
2399  Type *Ty2 = VT2.getTypeForEVT(*getContext());
2400  const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout();
2401  Align Align = std::max(DL.getPrefTypeAlign(Ty1), DL.getPrefTypeAlign(Ty2));
2402  return CreateStackTemporary(Bytes, Align);
2403 }
2404 
2405 SDValue SelectionDAG::FoldSetCC(EVT VT, SDValue N1, SDValue N2,
2406  ISD::CondCode Cond, const SDLoc &dl) {
2407  EVT OpVT = N1.getValueType();
2408 
2409  // These setcc operations always fold.
2410  switch (Cond) {
2411  default: break;
2412  case ISD::SETFALSE:
2413  case ISD::SETFALSE2: return getBoolConstant(false, dl, VT, OpVT);
2414  case ISD::SETTRUE:
2415  case ISD::SETTRUE2: return getBoolConstant(true, dl, VT, OpVT);
2416 
2417  case ISD::SETOEQ:
2418  case ISD::SETOGT:
2419  case ISD::SETOGE:
2420  case ISD::SETOLT:
2421  case ISD::SETOLE:
2422  case ISD::SETONE:
2423  case ISD::SETO:
2424  case ISD::SETUO:
2425  case ISD::SETUEQ:
2426  case ISD::SETUNE:
2427  assert(!OpVT.isInteger() && "Illegal setcc for integer!");
2428  break;
2429  }
2430 
2431  if (OpVT.isInteger()) {
2432  // For EQ and NE, we can always pick a value for the undef to make the
2433  // predicate pass or fail, so we can return undef.
2434  // Matches behavior in llvm::ConstantFoldCompareInstruction.
2435  // icmp eq/ne X, undef -> undef.
2436  if ((N1.isUndef() || N2.isUndef()) &&
2437  (Cond == ISD::SETEQ || Cond == ISD::SETNE))
2438  return getUNDEF(VT);
2439 
2440  // If both operands are undef, we can return undef for int comparison.
2441  // icmp undef, undef -> undef.
2442  if (N1.isUndef() && N2.isUndef())
2443  return getUNDEF(VT);
2444 
2445  // icmp X, X -> true/false
2446  // icmp X, undef -> true/false because undef could be X.
2447  if (N1 == N2)
2448  return getBoolConstant(ISD::isTrueWhenEqual(Cond), dl, VT, OpVT);
2449  }
2450 
2451  if (ConstantSDNode *N2C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N2)) {
2452  const APInt &C2 = N2C->getAPIntValue();
2453  if (ConstantSDNode *N1C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N1)) {
2454  const APInt &C1 = N1C->getAPIntValue();
2455 
2456  return getBoolConstant(ICmpInst::compare(C1, C2, getICmpCondCode(Cond)),
2457  dl, VT, OpVT);
2458  }
2459  }
2460 
2461  auto *N1CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N1);
2462  auto *N2CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N2);
2463 
2464  if (N1CFP && N2CFP) {
2465  APFloat::cmpResult R = N1CFP->getValueAPF().compare(N2CFP->getValueAPF());
2466  switch (Cond) {
2467  default: break;
2468  case ISD::SETEQ: if (R==APFloat::cmpUnordered)
2469  return getUNDEF(VT);
2470  [[fallthrough]];
2471  case ISD::SETOEQ: return getBoolConstant(R==APFloat::cmpEqual, dl, VT,
2472  OpVT);
2473  case ISD::SETNE: if (R==APFloat::cmpUnordered)
2474  return getUNDEF(VT);
2475  [[fallthrough]];
2476  case ISD::SETONE: return getBoolConstant(R==APFloat::cmpGreaterThan ||
2477  R==APFloat::cmpLessThan, dl, VT,
2478  OpVT);
2479  case ISD::SETLT: if (R==APFloat::cmpUnordered)
2480  return getUNDEF(VT);
2481  [[fallthrough]];
2482  case ISD::SETOLT: return getBoolConstant(R==APFloat::cmpLessThan, dl, VT,
2483  OpVT);
2484  case ISD::SETGT: if (R==APFloat::cmpUnordered)
2485  return getUNDEF(VT);
2486  [[fallthrough]];
2487  case ISD::SETOGT: return getBoolConstant(R==APFloat::cmpGreaterThan, dl,
2488  VT, OpVT);
2489  case ISD::SETLE: if (R==APFloat::cmpUnordered)
2490  return getUNDEF(VT);
2491  [[fallthrough]];
2492  case ISD::SETOLE: return getBoolConstant(R==APFloat::cmpLessThan ||
2493  R==APFloat::cmpEqual, dl, VT,
2494  OpVT);
2495  case ISD::SETGE: if (R==APFloat::cmpUnordered)
2496  return getUNDEF(VT);
2497  [[fallthrough]];
2498  case ISD::SETOGE: return getBoolConstant(R==APFloat::cmpGreaterThan ||
2499  R==APFloat::cmpEqual, dl, VT, OpVT);
2500  case ISD::SETO: return getBoolConstant(R!=APFloat::cmpUnordered, dl, VT,
2501  OpVT);
2502  case ISD::SETUO: return getBoolConstant(R==APFloat::cmpUnordered, dl, VT,
2503  OpVT);
2504  case ISD::SETUEQ: return getBoolConstant(R==APFloat::cmpUnordered ||
2505  R==APFloat::cmpEqual, dl, VT,
2506  OpVT);
2507  case ISD::SETUNE: return getBoolConstant(R!=APFloat::cmpEqual, dl, VT,
2508  OpVT);
2509  case ISD::SETULT: return getBoolConstant(R==APFloat::cmpUnordered ||
2510  R==APFloat::cmpLessThan, dl, VT,
2511  OpVT);
2512  case ISD::SETUGT: return getBoolConstant(R==APFloat::cmpGreaterThan ||
2513  R==APFloat::cmpUnordered, dl, VT,
2514  OpVT);
2515  case ISD::SETULE: return getBoolConstant(R!=APFloat::cmpGreaterThan, dl,
2516  VT, OpVT);
2517  case ISD::SETUGE: return getBoolConstant(R!=APFloat::cmpLessThan, dl, VT,
2518  OpVT);
2519  }
2520  } else if (N1CFP && OpVT.isSimple() && !N2.isUndef()) {
2521  // Ensure that the constant occurs on the RHS.
2522  ISD::CondCode SwappedCond = ISD::getSetCCSwappedOperands(Cond);
2523  if (!TLI->isCondCodeLegal(SwappedCond, OpVT.getSimpleVT()))
2524  return SDValue();
2525  return getSetCC(dl, VT, N2, N1, SwappedCond);
2526  } else if ((N2CFP && N2CFP->getValueAPF().isNaN()) ||
2527  (OpVT.isFloatingPoint() && (N1.isUndef() || N2.isUndef()))) {
2528  // If an operand is known to be a nan (or undef that could be a nan), we can
2529  // fold it.
2530  // Choosing NaN for the undef will always make unordered comparison succeed
2531  // and ordered comparison fails.
2532  // Matches behavior in llvm::ConstantFoldCompareInstruction.
2533  switch (ISD::getUnorderedFlavor(Cond)) {
2534  default:
2535  llvm_unreachable("Unknown flavor!");
2536  case 0: // Known false.
2537  return getBoolConstant(false, dl, VT, OpVT);
2538  case 1: // Known true.
2539  return getBoolConstant(true, dl, VT, OpVT);
2540  case 2: // Undefined.
2541  return getUNDEF(VT);
2542  }
2543  }
2544 
2545  // Could not fold it.
2546  return SDValue();
2547 }
2548 
2549 /// SignBitIsZero - Return true if the sign bit of Op is known to be zero. We
2550 /// use this predicate to simplify operations downstream.
2551 bool SelectionDAG::SignBitIsZero(SDValue Op, unsigned Depth) const {
2552  unsigned BitWidth = Op.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
2553  return MaskedValueIsZero(Op, APInt::getSignMask(BitWidth), Depth);
2554 }
2555 
2556 /// MaskedValueIsZero - Return true if 'V & Mask' is known to be zero. We use
2557 /// this predicate to simplify operations downstream. Mask is known to be zero
2558 /// for bits that V cannot have.
2559 bool SelectionDAG::MaskedValueIsZero(SDValue V, const APInt &Mask,
2560  unsigned Depth) const {
2561  return Mask.isSubsetOf(computeKnownBits(V, Depth).Zero);
2562 }
2563 
2564 /// MaskedValueIsZero - Return true if 'V & Mask' is known to be zero in
2565 /// DemandedElts. We use this predicate to simplify operations downstream.
2566 /// Mask is known to be zero for bits that V cannot have.
2567 bool SelectionDAG::MaskedValueIsZero(SDValue V, const APInt &Mask,
2568  const APInt &DemandedElts,
2569  unsigned Depth) const {
2570  return Mask.isSubsetOf(computeKnownBits(V, DemandedElts, Depth).Zero);
2571 }
2572 
2573 /// MaskedVectorIsZero - Return true if 'Op' is known to be zero in
2574 /// DemandedElts. We use this predicate to simplify operations downstream.
2575 bool SelectionDAG::MaskedVectorIsZero(SDValue V, const APInt &DemandedElts,
2576  unsigned Depth /* = 0 */) const {
2577  return computeKnownBits(V, DemandedElts, Depth).isZero();
2578 }
2579 
2580 /// MaskedValueIsAllOnes - Return true if '(Op & Mask) == Mask'.
2581 bool SelectionDAG::MaskedValueIsAllOnes(SDValue V, const APInt &Mask,
2582  unsigned Depth) const {
2583  return Mask.isSubsetOf(computeKnownBits(V, Depth).One);
2584 }
2585 
2586 APInt SelectionDAG::computeVectorKnownZeroElements(SDValue Op,
2587  const APInt &DemandedElts,
2588  unsigned Depth) const {
2589  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
2590  assert(VT.isVector() && !VT.isScalableVector() && "Only for fixed vectors!");
2591 
2592  unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
2593  assert(DemandedElts.getBitWidth() == NumElts && "Unexpected demanded mask.");
2594 
2595  APInt KnownZeroElements = APInt::getNullValue(NumElts);
2596  for (unsigned EltIdx = 0; EltIdx != NumElts; ++EltIdx) {
2597  if (!DemandedElts[EltIdx])
2598  continue; // Don't query elements that are not demanded.
2599  APInt Mask = APInt::getOneBitSet(NumElts, EltIdx);
2600  if (MaskedVectorIsZero(Op, Mask, Depth))
2601  KnownZeroElements.setBit(EltIdx);
2602  }
2603  return KnownZeroElements;
2604 }
2605 
2606 /// isSplatValue - Return true if the vector V has the same value
2607 /// across all DemandedElts. For scalable vectors, we don't know the
2608 /// number of lanes at compile time. Instead, we use a 1 bit APInt
2609 /// to represent a conservative value for all lanes; that is, that
2610 /// one bit value is implicitly splatted across all lanes.
2611 bool SelectionDAG::isSplatValue(SDValue V, const APInt &DemandedElts,
2612  APInt &UndefElts, unsigned Depth) const {
2613  unsigned Opcode = V.getOpcode();
2614  EVT VT = V.getValueType();
2615  assert(VT.isVector() && "Vector type expected");
2616  assert((!VT.isScalableVector() || DemandedElts.getBitWidth() == 1) &&
2617  "scalable demanded bits are ignored");
2618 
2619  if (!DemandedElts)
2620  return false; // No demanded elts, better to assume we don't know anything.
2621 
2622  if (Depth >= MaxRecursionDepth)
2623  return false; // Limit search depth.
2624 
2625  // Deal with some common cases here that work for both fixed and scalable
2626  // vector types.
2627  switch (Opcode) {
2628  case ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR:
2629  UndefElts = V.getOperand(0).isUndef()
2630  ? APInt::getAllOnes(DemandedElts.getBitWidth())
2631  : APInt(DemandedElts.getBitWidth(), 0);
2632  return true;
2633  case ISD::ADD:
2634  case ISD::SUB:
2635  case ISD::AND:
2636  case ISD::XOR:
2637  case ISD::OR: {
2638  APInt UndefLHS, UndefRHS;
2639  SDValue LHS = V.getOperand(0);
2640  SDValue RHS = V.getOperand(1);
2641  if (isSplatValue(LHS, DemandedElts, UndefLHS, Depth + 1) &&
2642  isSplatValue(RHS, DemandedElts, UndefRHS, Depth + 1)) {
2643  UndefElts = UndefLHS | UndefRHS;
2644  return true;
2645  }
2646  return false;
2647  }
2648  case ISD::ABS:
2649  case ISD::TRUNCATE:
2650  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
2651  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
2652  return isSplatValue(V.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, UndefElts, Depth + 1);
2653  default:
2654  if (Opcode >= ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END || Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN ||
2655  Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN || Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID)
2656  return TLI->isSplatValueForTargetNode(V, DemandedElts, UndefElts, *this,
2657  Depth);
2658  break;
2659 }
2660 
2661  // We don't support other cases than those above for scalable vectors at
2662  // the moment.
2663  if (VT.isScalableVector())
2664  return false;
2665 
2666  unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
2667  assert(NumElts == DemandedElts.getBitWidth() && "Vector size mismatch");
2668  UndefElts = APInt::getZero(NumElts);
2669 
2670  switch (Opcode) {
2671  case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: {
2672  SDValue Scl;
2673  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
2674  SDValue Op = V.getOperand(i);
2675  if (Op.isUndef()) {
2676  UndefElts.setBit(i);
2677  continue;
2678  }
2679  if (!DemandedElts[i])
2680  continue;
2681  if (Scl && Scl != Op)
2682  return false;
2683  Scl = Op;
2684  }
2685  return true;
2686  }
2687  case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE: {
2688  // Check if this is a shuffle node doing a splat or a shuffle of a splat.
2689  APInt DemandedLHS = APInt::getNullValue(NumElts);
2690  APInt DemandedRHS = APInt::getNullValue(NumElts);
2691  ArrayRef<int> Mask = cast<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(V)->getMask();
2692  for (int i = 0; i != (int)NumElts; ++i) {
2693  int M = Mask[i];
2694  if (M < 0) {
2695  UndefElts.setBit(i);
2696  continue;
2697  }
2698  if (!DemandedElts[i])
2699  continue;
2700  if (M < (int)NumElts)
2701  DemandedLHS.setBit(M);
2702  else
2703  DemandedRHS.setBit(M - NumElts);
2704  }
2705 
2706  // If we aren't demanding either op, assume there's no splat.
2707  // If we are demanding both ops, assume there's no splat.
2708  if ((DemandedLHS.isZero() && DemandedRHS.isZero()) ||
2709  (!DemandedLHS.isZero() && !DemandedRHS.isZero()))
2710  return false;
2711 
2712  // See if the demanded elts of the source op is a splat or we only demand
2713  // one element, which should always be a splat.
2714  // TODO: Handle source ops splats with undefs.
2715  auto CheckSplatSrc = [&](SDValue Src, const APInt &SrcElts) {
2716  APInt SrcUndefs;
2717  return (SrcElts.countPopulation() == 1) ||
2718  (isSplatValue(Src, SrcElts, SrcUndefs, Depth + 1) &&
2719  (SrcElts & SrcUndefs).isZero());
2720  };
2721  if (!DemandedLHS.isZero())
2722  return CheckSplatSrc(V.getOperand(0), DemandedLHS);
2723  return CheckSplatSrc(V.getOperand(1), DemandedRHS);
2724  }
2725  case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: {
2726  // Offset the demanded elts by the subvector index.
2727  SDValue Src = V.getOperand(0);
2728  // We don't support scalable vectors at the moment.
2729  if (Src.getValueType().isScalableVector())
2730  return false;
2731  uint64_t Idx = V.getConstantOperandVal(1);
2732  unsigned NumSrcElts = Src.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
2733  APInt UndefSrcElts;
2734  APInt DemandedSrcElts = DemandedElts.zext(NumSrcElts).shl(Idx);
2735  if (isSplatValue(Src, DemandedSrcElts, UndefSrcElts, Depth + 1)) {
2736  UndefElts = UndefSrcElts.extractBits(NumElts, Idx);
2737  return true;
2738  }
2739  break;
2740  }
2741  case ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
2742  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
2743  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG: {
2744  // Widen the demanded elts by the src element count.
2745  SDValue Src = V.getOperand(0);
2746  // We don't support scalable vectors at the moment.
2747  if (Src.getValueType().isScalableVector())
2748  return false;
2749  unsigned NumSrcElts = Src.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
2750  APInt UndefSrcElts;
2751  APInt DemandedSrcElts = DemandedElts.zext(NumSrcElts);
2752  if (isSplatValue(Src, DemandedSrcElts, UndefSrcElts, Depth + 1)) {
2753  UndefElts = UndefSrcElts.trunc(NumElts);
2754  return true;
2755  }
2756  break;
2757  }
2758  case ISD::BITCAST: {
2759  SDValue Src = V.getOperand(0);
2760  EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
2761  unsigned SrcBitWidth = SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
2762  unsigned BitWidth = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
2763 
2764  // Ignore bitcasts from unsupported types.
2765  // TODO: Add fp support?
2766  if (!SrcVT.isVector() || !SrcVT.isInteger() || !VT.isInteger())
2767  break;
2768 
2769  // Bitcast 'small element' vector to 'large element' vector.
2770  if ((BitWidth % SrcBitWidth) == 0) {
2771  // See if each sub element is a splat.
2772  unsigned Scale = BitWidth / SrcBitWidth;
2773  unsigned NumSrcElts = SrcVT.getVectorNumElements();
2774  APInt ScaledDemandedElts =
2775  APIntOps::ScaleBitMask(DemandedElts, NumSrcElts);
2776  for (unsigned I = 0; I != Scale; ++I) {
2777  APInt SubUndefElts;
2778  APInt SubDemandedElt = APInt::getOneBitSet(Scale, I);
2779  APInt SubDemandedElts = APInt::getSplat(NumSrcElts, SubDemandedElt);
2780  SubDemandedElts &= ScaledDemandedElts;
2781  if (!isSplatValue(Src, SubDemandedElts, SubUndefElts, Depth + 1))
2782  return false;
2783  // TODO: Add support for merging sub undef elements.
2784  if (!SubUndefElts.isZero())
2785  return false;
2786  }
2787  return true;
2788  }
2789  break;
2790  }
2791  }
2792 
2793  return false;
2794 }
2795 
2796 /// Helper wrapper to main isSplatValue function.
2797 bool SelectionDAG::isSplatValue(SDValue V, bool AllowUndefs) const {
2798  EVT VT = V.getValueType();
2799  assert(VT.isVector() && "Vector type expected");
2800 
2801  APInt UndefElts;
2802  // Since the number of lanes in a scalable vector is unknown at compile time,
2803  // we track one bit which is implicitly broadcast to all lanes. This means
2804  // that all lanes in a scalable vector are considered demanded.
2805  APInt DemandedElts
2806  = APInt::getAllOnes(VT.isScalableVector() ? 1 : VT.getVectorNumElements());
2807  return isSplatValue(V, DemandedElts, UndefElts) &&
2808  (AllowUndefs || !UndefElts);
2809 }
2810 
2811 SDValue SelectionDAG::getSplatSourceVector(SDValue V, int &SplatIdx) {
2812  V = peekThroughExtractSubvectors(V);
2813 
2814  EVT VT = V.getValueType();
2815  unsigned Opcode = V.getOpcode();
2816  switch (Opcode) {
2817  default: {
2818  APInt UndefElts;
2819  // Since the number of lanes in a scalable vector is unknown at compile time,
2820  // we track one bit which is implicitly broadcast to all lanes. This means
2821  // that all lanes in a scalable vector are considered demanded.
2822  APInt DemandedElts
2823  = APInt::getAllOnes(VT.isScalableVector() ? 1 : VT.getVectorNumElements());
2824 
2825  if (isSplatValue(V, DemandedElts, UndefElts)) {
2826  if (VT.isScalableVector()) {
2827  // DemandedElts and UndefElts are ignored for scalable vectors, since
2828  // the only supported cases are SPLAT_VECTOR nodes.
2829  SplatIdx = 0;
2830  } else {
2831  // Handle case where all demanded elements are UNDEF.
