2832  if (DemandedElts.isSubsetOf(UndefElts)) {
2833  SplatIdx = 0;
2834  return getUNDEF(VT);
2835  }
2836  SplatIdx = (UndefElts & DemandedElts).countTrailingOnes();
2837  }
2838  return V;
2839  }
2840  break;
2841  }
2842  case ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR:
2843  SplatIdx = 0;
2844  return V;
2845  case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE: {
2846  assert(!VT.isScalableVector());
2847  // Check if this is a shuffle node doing a splat.
2848  // TODO - remove this and rely purely on SelectionDAG::isSplatValue,
2849  // getTargetVShiftNode currently struggles without the splat source.
2850  auto *SVN = cast<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(V);
2851  if (!SVN->isSplat())
2852  break;
2853  int Idx = SVN->getSplatIndex();
2854  int NumElts = V.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
2855  SplatIdx = Idx % NumElts;
2856  return V.getOperand(Idx / NumElts);
2857  }
2858  }
2859 
2860  return SDValue();
2861 }
2862 
2863 SDValue SelectionDAG::getSplatValue(SDValue V, bool LegalTypes) {
2864  int SplatIdx;
2865  if (SDValue SrcVector = getSplatSourceVector(V, SplatIdx)) {
2866  EVT SVT = SrcVector.getValueType().getScalarType();
2867  EVT LegalSVT = SVT;
2868  if (LegalTypes && !TLI->isTypeLegal(SVT)) {
2869  if (!SVT.isInteger())
2870  return SDValue();
2871  LegalSVT = TLI->getTypeToTransformTo(*getContext(), LegalSVT);
2872  if (LegalSVT.bitsLT(SVT))
2873  return SDValue();
2874  }
2875  return getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SDLoc(V), LegalSVT, SrcVector,
2876  getVectorIdxConstant(SplatIdx, SDLoc(V)));
2877  }
2878  return SDValue();
2879 }
2880 
2881 const APInt *
2882 SelectionDAG::getValidShiftAmountConstant(SDValue V,
2883  const APInt &DemandedElts) const {
2884  assert((V.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL || V.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL ||
2885  V.getOpcode() == ISD::SRA) &&
2886  "Unknown shift node");
2887  unsigned BitWidth = V.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
2888  if (ConstantSDNode *SA = isConstOrConstSplat(V.getOperand(1), DemandedElts)) {
2889  // Shifting more than the bitwidth is not valid.
2890  const APInt &ShAmt = SA->getAPIntValue();
2891  if (ShAmt.ult(BitWidth))
2892  return &ShAmt;
2893  }
2894  return nullptr;
2895 }
2896 
2897 const APInt *SelectionDAG::getValidMinimumShiftAmountConstant(
2898  SDValue V, const APInt &DemandedElts) const {
2899  assert((V.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL || V.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL ||
2900  V.getOpcode() == ISD::SRA) &&
2901  "Unknown shift node");
2902  if (const APInt *ValidAmt = getValidShiftAmountConstant(V, DemandedElts))
2903  return ValidAmt;
2904  unsigned BitWidth = V.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
2905  auto *BV = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(V.getOperand(1));
2906  if (!BV)
2907  return nullptr;
2908  const APInt *MinShAmt = nullptr;
2909  for (unsigned i = 0, e = BV->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
2910  if (!DemandedElts[i])
2911  continue;
2912  auto *SA = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(BV->getOperand(i));
2913  if (!SA)
2914  return nullptr;
2915  // Shifting more than the bitwidth is not valid.
2916  const APInt &ShAmt = SA->getAPIntValue();
2917  if (ShAmt.uge(BitWidth))
2918  return nullptr;
2919  if (MinShAmt && MinShAmt->ule(ShAmt))
2920  continue;
2921  MinShAmt = &ShAmt;
2922  }
2923  return MinShAmt;
2924 }
2925 
2926 const APInt *SelectionDAG::getValidMaximumShiftAmountConstant(
2927  SDValue V, const APInt &DemandedElts) const {
2928  assert((V.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL || V.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL ||
2929  V.getOpcode() == ISD::SRA) &&
2930  "Unknown shift node");
2931  if (const APInt *ValidAmt = getValidShiftAmountConstant(V, DemandedElts))
2932  return ValidAmt;
2933  unsigned BitWidth = V.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
2934  auto *BV = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(V.getOperand(1));
2935  if (!BV)
2936  return nullptr;
2937  const APInt *MaxShAmt = nullptr;
2938  for (unsigned i = 0, e = BV->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
2939  if (!DemandedElts[i])
2940  continue;
2941  auto *SA = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(BV->getOperand(i));
2942  if (!SA)
2943  return nullptr;
2944  // Shifting more than the bitwidth is not valid.
2945  const APInt &ShAmt = SA->getAPIntValue();
2946  if (ShAmt.uge(BitWidth))
2947  return nullptr;
2948  if (MaxShAmt && MaxShAmt->uge(ShAmt))
2949  continue;
2950  MaxShAmt = &ShAmt;
2951  }
2952  return MaxShAmt;
2953 }
2954 
2955 /// Determine which bits of Op are known to be either zero or one and return
2956 /// them in Known. For vectors, the known bits are those that are shared by
2957 /// every vector element.
2958 KnownBits SelectionDAG::computeKnownBits(SDValue Op, unsigned Depth) const {
2959  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
2960 
2961  // Since the number of lanes in a scalable vector is unknown at compile time,
2962  // we track one bit which is implicitly broadcast to all lanes. This means
2963  // that all lanes in a scalable vector are considered demanded.
2964  APInt DemandedElts = VT.isFixedLengthVector()
2965  ? APInt::getAllOnes(VT.getVectorNumElements())
2966  : APInt(1, 1);
2967  return computeKnownBits(Op, DemandedElts, Depth);
2968 }
2969 
2970 /// Determine which bits of Op are known to be either zero or one and return
2971 /// them in Known. The DemandedElts argument allows us to only collect the known
2972 /// bits that are shared by the requested vector elements.
2973 KnownBits SelectionDAG::computeKnownBits(SDValue Op, const APInt &DemandedElts,
2974  unsigned Depth) const {
2975  unsigned BitWidth = Op.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
2976 
2977  KnownBits Known(BitWidth); // Don't know anything.
2978 
2979  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)) {
2980  // We know all of the bits for a constant!
2981  return KnownBits::makeConstant(C->getAPIntValue());
2982  }
2983  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op)) {
2984  // We know all of the bits for a constant fp!
2985  return KnownBits::makeConstant(C->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt());
2986  }
2987 
2988  if (Depth >= MaxRecursionDepth)
2989  return Known; // Limit search depth.
2990 
2991  KnownBits Known2;
2992  unsigned NumElts = DemandedElts.getBitWidth();
2993  assert((!Op.getValueType().isFixedLengthVector() ||
2994  NumElts == Op.getValueType().getVectorNumElements()) &&
2995  "Unexpected vector size");
2996 
2997  if (!DemandedElts)
2998  return Known; // No demanded elts, better to assume we don't know anything.
2999 
3000  unsigned Opcode = Op.getOpcode();
3001  switch (Opcode) {
3002  case ISD::MERGE_VALUES:
3003  return computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(Op.getResNo()), DemandedElts,
3004  Depth + 1);
3005  case ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR: {
3006  SDValue SrcOp = Op.getOperand(0);
3007  assert(SrcOp.getValueSizeInBits() >= BitWidth &&
3008  "Expected SPLAT_VECTOR implicit truncation");
3009  // Implicitly truncate the bits to match the official semantics of
3010  // SPLAT_VECTOR.
3011  Known = computeKnownBits(SrcOp, Depth + 1).trunc(BitWidth);
3012  break;
3013  }
3014  case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR:
3015  assert(!Op.getValueType().isScalableVector());
3016  // Collect the known bits that are shared by every demanded vector element.
3017  Known.Zero.setAllBits(); Known.One.setAllBits();
3018  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Op.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
3019  if (!DemandedElts[i])
3020  continue;
3021 
3022  SDValue SrcOp = Op.getOperand(i);
3023  Known2 = computeKnownBits(SrcOp, Depth + 1);
3024 
3025  // BUILD_VECTOR can implicitly truncate sources, we must handle this.
3026  if (SrcOp.getValueSizeInBits() != BitWidth) {
3027  assert(SrcOp.getValueSizeInBits() > BitWidth &&
3028  "Expected BUILD_VECTOR implicit truncation");
3029  Known2 = Known2.trunc(BitWidth);
3030  }
3031 
3032  // Known bits are the values that are shared by every demanded element.
3033  Known = KnownBits::commonBits(Known, Known2);
3034 
3035  // If we don't know any bits, early out.
3036  if (Known.isUnknown())
3037  break;
3038  }
3039  break;
3040  case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE: {
3041  assert(!Op.getValueType().isScalableVector());
3042  // Collect the known bits that are shared by every vector element referenced
3043  // by the shuffle.
3044  APInt DemandedLHS, DemandedRHS;
3045  const ShuffleVectorSDNode *SVN = cast<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(Op);
3046  assert(NumElts == SVN->getMask().size() && "Unexpected vector size");
3047  if (!getShuffleDemandedElts(NumElts, SVN->getMask(), DemandedElts,
3048  DemandedLHS, DemandedRHS))
3049  break;
3050 
3051  // Known bits are the values that are shared by every demanded element.
3052  Known.Zero.setAllBits(); Known.One.setAllBits();
3053  if (!!DemandedLHS) {
3054  SDValue LHS = Op.getOperand(0);
3055  Known2 = computeKnownBits(LHS, DemandedLHS, Depth + 1);
3056  Known = KnownBits::commonBits(Known, Known2);
3057  }
3058  // If we don't know any bits, early out.
3059  if (Known.isUnknown())
3060  break;
3061  if (!!DemandedRHS) {
3062  SDValue RHS = Op.getOperand(1);
3063  Known2 = computeKnownBits(RHS, DemandedRHS, Depth + 1);
3064  Known = KnownBits::commonBits(Known, Known2);
3065  }
3066  break;
3067  }
3068  case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS: {
3069  if (Op.getValueType().isScalableVector())
3070  break;
3071  // Split DemandedElts and test each of the demanded subvectors.
3072  Known.Zero.setAllBits(); Known.One.setAllBits();
3073  EVT SubVectorVT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
3074  unsigned NumSubVectorElts = SubVectorVT.getVectorNumElements();
3075  unsigned NumSubVectors = Op.getNumOperands();
3076  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumSubVectors; ++i) {
3077  APInt DemandedSub =
3078  DemandedElts.extractBits(NumSubVectorElts, i * NumSubVectorElts);
3079  if (!!DemandedSub) {
3080  SDValue Sub = Op.getOperand(i);
3081  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Sub, DemandedSub, Depth + 1);
3082  Known = KnownBits::commonBits(Known, Known2);
3083  }
3084  // If we don't know any bits, early out.
3085  if (Known.isUnknown())
3086  break;
3087  }
3088  break;
3089  }
3090  case ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR: {
3091  if (Op.getValueType().isScalableVector())
3092  break;
3093  // Demand any elements from the subvector and the remainder from the src its
3094  // inserted into.
3095  SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
3096  SDValue Sub = Op.getOperand(1);
3097  uint64_t Idx = Op.getConstantOperandVal(2);
3098  unsigned NumSubElts = Sub.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
3099  APInt DemandedSubElts = DemandedElts.extractBits(NumSubElts, Idx);
3100  APInt DemandedSrcElts = DemandedElts;
3101  DemandedSrcElts.insertBits(APInt::getZero(NumSubElts), Idx);
3102 
3103  Known.One.setAllBits();
3104  Known.Zero.setAllBits();
3105  if (!!DemandedSubElts) {
3106  Known = computeKnownBits(Sub, DemandedSubElts, Depth + 1);
3107  if (Known.isUnknown())
3108  break; // early-out.
3109  }
3110  if (!!DemandedSrcElts) {
3111  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Src, DemandedSrcElts, Depth + 1);
3112  Known = KnownBits::commonBits(Known, Known2);
3113  }
3114  break;
3115  }
3116  case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: {
3117  // Offset the demanded elts by the subvector index.
3118  SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
3119  // Bail until we can represent demanded elements for scalable vectors.
3120  if (Op.getValueType().isScalableVector() || Src.getValueType().isScalableVector())
3121  break;
3122  uint64_t Idx = Op.getConstantOperandVal(1);
3123  unsigned NumSrcElts = Src.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
3124  APInt DemandedSrcElts = DemandedElts.zext(NumSrcElts).shl(Idx);
3125  Known = computeKnownBits(Src, DemandedSrcElts, Depth + 1);
3126  break;
3127  }
3128  case ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR: {
3129  if (Op.getValueType().isScalableVector())
3130  break;
3131  // We know about scalar_to_vector as much as we know about it source,
3132  // which becomes the first element of otherwise unknown vector.
3133  if (DemandedElts != 1)
3134  break;
3135 
3136  SDValue N0 = Op.getOperand(0);
3137  Known = computeKnownBits(N0, Depth + 1);
3138  if (N0.getValueSizeInBits() != BitWidth)
3139  Known = Known.trunc(BitWidth);
3140 
3141  break;
3142  }
3143  case ISD::BITCAST: {
3144  if (Op.getValueType().isScalableVector())
3145  break;
3146 
3147  SDValue N0 = Op.getOperand(0);
3148  EVT SubVT = N0.getValueType();
3149  unsigned SubBitWidth = SubVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
3150 
3151  // Ignore bitcasts from unsupported types.
3152  if (!(SubVT.isInteger() || SubVT.isFloatingPoint()))
3153  break;
3154 
3155  // Fast handling of 'identity' bitcasts.
3156  if (BitWidth == SubBitWidth) {
3157  Known = computeKnownBits(N0, DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3158  break;
3159  }
3160 
3161  bool IsLE = getDataLayout().isLittleEndian();
3162 
3163  // Bitcast 'small element' vector to 'large element' scalar/vector.
3164  if ((BitWidth % SubBitWidth) == 0) {
3165  assert(N0.getValueType().isVector() && "Expected bitcast from vector");
3166 
3167  // Collect known bits for the (larger) output by collecting the known
3168  // bits from each set of sub elements and shift these into place.
3169  // We need to separately call computeKnownBits for each set of
3170  // sub elements as the knownbits for each is likely to be different.
3171  unsigned SubScale = BitWidth / SubBitWidth;
3172  APInt SubDemandedElts(NumElts * SubScale, 0);
3173  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i)
3174  if (DemandedElts[i])
3175  SubDemandedElts.setBit(i * SubScale);
3176 
3177  for (unsigned i = 0; i != SubScale; ++i) {
3178  Known2 = computeKnownBits(N0, SubDemandedElts.shl(i),
3179  Depth + 1);
3180  unsigned Shifts = IsLE ? i : SubScale - 1 - i;
3181  Known.insertBits(Known2, SubBitWidth * Shifts);
3182  }
3183  }
3184 
3185  // Bitcast 'large element' scalar/vector to 'small element' vector.
3186  if ((SubBitWidth % BitWidth) == 0) {
3187  assert(Op.getValueType().isVector() && "Expected bitcast to vector");
3188 
3189  // Collect known bits for the (smaller) output by collecting the known
3190  // bits from the overlapping larger input elements and extracting the
3191  // sub sections we actually care about.
3192  unsigned SubScale = SubBitWidth / BitWidth;
3193  APInt SubDemandedElts =
3194  APIntOps::ScaleBitMask(DemandedElts, NumElts / SubScale);
3195  Known2 = computeKnownBits(N0, SubDemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3196 
3197  Known.Zero.setAllBits(); Known.One.setAllBits();
3198  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i)
3199  if (DemandedElts[i]) {
3200  unsigned Shifts = IsLE ? i : NumElts - 1 - i;
3201  unsigned Offset = (Shifts % SubScale) * BitWidth;
3202  Known = KnownBits::commonBits(Known,
3203  Known2.extractBits(BitWidth, Offset));
3204  // If we don't know any bits, early out.
3205  if (Known.isUnknown())
3206  break;
3207  }
3208  }
3209  break;
3210  }
3211  case ISD::AND:
3212  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3213  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3214 
3215  Known &= Known2;
3216  break;
3217  case ISD::OR:
3218  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3219  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3220 
3221  Known |= Known2;
3222  break;
3223  case ISD::XOR:
3224  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3225  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3226 
3227  Known ^= Known2;
3228  break;
3229  case ISD::MUL: {
3230  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3231  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3232  bool SelfMultiply = Op.getOperand(0) == Op.getOperand(1);
3233  // TODO: SelfMultiply can be poison, but not undef.
3234  if (SelfMultiply)
3235  SelfMultiply &= isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(
3236  Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, false, Depth + 1);
3237  Known = KnownBits::mul(Known, Known2, SelfMultiply);
3238 
3239  // If the multiplication is known not to overflow, the product of a number
3240  // with itself is non-negative. Only do this if we didn't already computed
3241  // the opposite value for the sign bit.
3242  if (Op->getFlags().hasNoSignedWrap() &&
3243  Op.getOperand(0) == Op.getOperand(1) &&
3244  !Known.isNegative())
3245  Known.makeNonNegative();
3246  break;
3247  }
3248  case ISD::MULHU: {
3249  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3250  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3251  Known = KnownBits::mulhu(Known, Known2);
3252  break;
3253  }
3254  case ISD::MULHS: {
3255  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3256  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3257  Known = KnownBits::mulhs(Known, Known2);
3258  break;
3259  }
3260  case ISD::UMUL_LOHI: {
3261  assert((Op.getResNo() == 0 || Op.getResNo() == 1) && "Unknown result");
3262  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3263  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3264  bool SelfMultiply = Op.getOperand(0) == Op.getOperand(1);
3265  if (Op.getResNo() == 0)
3266  Known = KnownBits::mul(Known, Known2, SelfMultiply);
3267  else
3268  Known = KnownBits::mulhu(Known, Known2);
3269  break;
3270  }
3271  case ISD::SMUL_LOHI: {
3272  assert((Op.getResNo() == 0 || Op.getResNo() == 1) && "Unknown result");
3273  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3274  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3275  bool SelfMultiply = Op.getOperand(0) == Op.getOperand(1);
3276  if (Op.getResNo() == 0)
3277  Known = KnownBits::mul(Known, Known2, SelfMultiply);
3278  else
3279  Known = KnownBits::mulhs(Known, Known2);
3280  break;
3281  }
3282  case ISD::AVGCEILU: {
3283  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3284  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3285  Known = Known.zext(BitWidth + 1);
3286  Known2 = Known2.zext(BitWidth + 1);
3287  KnownBits One = KnownBits::makeConstant(APInt(1, 1));
3288  Known = KnownBits::computeForAddCarry(Known, Known2, One);
3289  Known = Known.extractBits(BitWidth, 1);
3290  break;
3291  }
3292  case ISD::SELECT:
3293  case ISD::VSELECT:
3294  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(2), DemandedElts, Depth+1);
3295  // If we don't know any bits, early out.
3296  if (Known.isUnknown())
3297  break;
3298  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth+1);
3299 
3300  // Only known if known in both the LHS and RHS.
3301  Known = KnownBits::commonBits(Known, Known2);
3302  break;
3303  case ISD::SELECT_CC:
3304  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(3), DemandedElts, Depth+1);
3305  // If we don't know any bits, early out.
3306  if (Known.isUnknown())
3307  break;
3308  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(2), DemandedElts, Depth+1);
3309 
3310  // Only known if known in both the LHS and RHS.
3311  Known = KnownBits::commonBits(Known, Known2);
3312  break;
3313  case ISD::SMULO:
3314  case ISD::UMULO:
3315  if (Op.getResNo() != 1)
3316  break;
3317  // The boolean result conforms to getBooleanContents.
3318  // If we know the result of a setcc has the top bits zero, use this info.
3319  // We know that we have an integer-based boolean since these operations
3320  // are only available for integer.
3321  if (TLI->getBooleanContents(Op.getValueType().isVector(), false) ==
3322  TargetLowering::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent &&
3323  BitWidth > 1)
3324  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(1);
3325  break;
3326  case ISD::SETCC:
3327  case ISD::SETCCCARRY:
3328  case ISD::STRICT_FSETCC:
3329  case ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS: {
3330  unsigned OpNo = Op->isStrictFPOpcode() ? 1 : 0;
3331  // If we know the result of a setcc has the top bits zero, use this info.
3332  if (TLI->getBooleanContents(Op.getOperand(OpNo).getValueType()) ==
3333  TargetLowering::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent &&
3334  BitWidth > 1)
3335  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(1);
3336  break;
3337  }
3338  case ISD::SHL:
3339  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3340  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3341  Known = KnownBits::shl(Known, Known2);
3342 
3343  // Minimum shift low bits are known zero.
3344  if (const APInt *ShMinAmt =
3345  getValidMinimumShiftAmountConstant(Op, DemandedElts))
3346  Known.Zero.setLowBits(ShMinAmt->getZExtValue());
3347  break;
3348  case ISD::SRL:
3349  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3350  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3351  Known = KnownBits::lshr(Known, Known2);
3352 
3353  // Minimum shift high bits are known zero.
3354  if (const APInt *ShMinAmt =
3355  getValidMinimumShiftAmountConstant(Op, DemandedElts))
3356  Known.Zero.setHighBits(ShMinAmt->getZExtValue());
3357  break;
3358  case ISD::SRA:
3359  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3360  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3361  Known = KnownBits::ashr(Known, Known2);
3362  // TODO: Add minimum shift high known sign bits.
3363  break;
3364  case ISD::FSHL:
3365  case ISD::FSHR:
3366  if (ConstantSDNode *C = isConstOrConstSplat(Op.getOperand(2), DemandedElts)) {
3367  unsigned Amt = C->getAPIntValue().urem(BitWidth);
3368 
3369  // For fshl, 0-shift returns the 1st arg.
3370  // For fshr, 0-shift returns the 2nd arg.
3371  if (Amt == 0) {
3372  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(Opcode == ISD::FSHL ? 0 : 1),
3373  DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3374  break;
3375  }
3376 
3377  // fshl: (X << (Z % BW)) | (Y >> (BW - (Z % BW)))
3378  // fshr: (X << (BW - (Z % BW))) | (Y >> (Z % BW))
3379  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3380  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3381  if (Opcode == ISD::FSHL) {
3382  Known.One <<= Amt;
3383  Known.Zero <<= Amt;
3384  Known2.One.lshrInPlace(BitWidth - Amt);
3385  Known2.Zero.lshrInPlace(BitWidth - Amt);
3386  } else {
3387  Known.One <<= BitWidth - Amt;
3388  Known.Zero <<= BitWidth - Amt;
3389  Known2.One.lshrInPlace(Amt);
3390  Known2.Zero.lshrInPlace(Amt);
3391  }
3392  Known.One |= Known2.One;
3393  Known.Zero |= Known2.Zero;
3394  }
3395  break;
3396  case ISD::SHL_PARTS:
3397  case ISD::SRA_PARTS:
3398  case ISD::SRL_PARTS: {
3399  assert((Op.getResNo() == 0 || Op.getResNo() == 1) && "Unknown result");
3400 
3401  // Collect lo/hi source values and concatenate.
3402  unsigned LoBits = Op.getOperand(0).getScalarValueSizeInBits();
3403  unsigned HiBits = Op.getOperand(1).getScalarValueSizeInBits();
3404  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3405  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3406  Known = Known2.concat(Known);
3407 
3408  // Collect shift amount.
3409  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(2), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3410 
3411  if (Opcode == ISD::SHL_PARTS)
3412  Known = KnownBits::shl(Known, Known2);
3413  else if (Opcode == ISD::SRA_PARTS)
3414  Known = KnownBits::ashr(Known, Known2);
3415  else // if (Opcode == ISD::SRL_PARTS)
3416  Known = KnownBits::lshr(Known, Known2);
3417 
3418  // TODO: Minimum shift low/high bits are known zero.
3419 
3420  if (Op.getResNo() == 0)
3421  Known = Known.extractBits(LoBits, 0);
3422  else
3423  Known = Known.extractBits(HiBits, LoBits);
3424  break;
3425  }
3426  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: {
3427  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3428  EVT EVT = cast<VTSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))->getVT();
3429  Known = Known.sextInReg(EVT.getScalarSizeInBits());
3430  break;
3431  }
3432  case ISD::CTTZ:
3433  case ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF: {
3434  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3435  // If we have a known 1, its position is our upper bound.
3436  unsigned PossibleTZ = Known2.countMaxTrailingZeros();
3437  unsigned LowBits = llvm::bit_width(PossibleTZ);
3438  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(LowBits);
3439  break;
3440  }
3441  case ISD::CTLZ:
3442  case ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF: {
3443  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3444  // If we have a known 1, its position is our upper bound.
3445  unsigned PossibleLZ = Known2.countMaxLeadingZeros();
3446  unsigned LowBits = llvm::bit_width(PossibleLZ);
3447  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(LowBits);
3448  break;
3449  }
3450  case ISD::CTPOP: {
3451  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3452  // If we know some of the bits are zero, they can't be one.
3453  unsigned PossibleOnes = Known2.countMaxPopulation();
3454  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(llvm::bit_width(PossibleOnes));
3455  break;
3456  }
3457  case ISD::PARITY: {
3458  // Parity returns 0 everywhere but the LSB.
3459  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(1);
3460  break;
3461  }
3462  case ISD::LOAD: {
3463  LoadSDNode *LD = cast<LoadSDNode>(Op);
3464  const Constant *Cst = TLI->getTargetConstantFromLoad(LD);
3465  if (ISD::isNON_EXTLoad(LD) && Cst) {
3466  // Determine any common known bits from the loaded constant pool value.
3467  Type *CstTy = Cst->getType();
3468  if ((NumElts * BitWidth) == CstTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() &&
3469  !Op.getValueType().isScalableVector()) {
3470  // If its a vector splat, then we can (quickly) reuse the scalar path.
3471  // NOTE: We assume all elements match and none are UNDEF.
3472  if (CstTy->isVectorTy()) {
3473  if (const Constant *Splat = Cst->getSplatValue()) {
3474  Cst = Splat;
3475  CstTy = Cst->getType();
3476  }
3477  }
3478  // TODO - do we need to handle different bitwidths?
3479  if (CstTy->isVectorTy() && BitWidth == CstTy->getScalarSizeInBits()) {
3480  // Iterate across all vector elements finding common known bits.
3481  Known.One.setAllBits();
3482  Known.Zero.setAllBits();
3483  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
3484  if (!DemandedElts[i])
3485  continue;
3486  if (Constant *Elt = Cst->getAggregateElement(i)) {
3487  if (auto *CInt = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Elt)) {
3488  const APInt &Value = CInt->getValue();
3489  Known.One &= Value;
3490  Known.Zero &= ~Value;
3491  continue;
3492  }
3493  if (auto *CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Elt)) {
3494  APInt Value = CFP->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt();
3495  Known.One &= Value;
3496  Known.Zero &= ~Value;
3497  continue;
3498  }
3499  }
3500  Known.One.clearAllBits();
3501  Known.Zero.clearAllBits();
3502  break;
3503  }
3504  } else if (BitWidth == CstTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits()) {
3505  if (auto *CInt = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Cst)) {
3506  Known = KnownBits::makeConstant(CInt->getValue());
3507  } else if (auto *CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Cst)) {
3508  Known =
3509  KnownBits::makeConstant(CFP->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt());
3510  }
3511  }
3512  }
3513  } else if (ISD::isZEXTLoad(Op.getNode()) && Op.getResNo() == 0) {
3514  // If this is a ZEXTLoad and we are looking at the loaded value.
3515  EVT VT = LD->getMemoryVT();
3516  unsigned MemBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
3517  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(MemBits);
3518  } else if (const MDNode *Ranges = LD->getRanges()) {
3519  EVT VT = LD->getValueType(0);
3520 
3521  // TODO: Handle for extending loads
3522  if (LD->getExtensionType() == ISD::NON_EXTLOAD) {
3523  if (VT.isVector()) {
3524  // Handle truncation to the first demanded element.
3525  // TODO: Figure out which demanded elements are covered
3526  if (DemandedElts != 1 || !getDataLayout().isLittleEndian())
3527  break;
3528 
3529  // Handle the case where a load has a vector type, but scalar memory
3530  // with an attached range.
3531  EVT MemVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
3532  KnownBits KnownFull(MemVT.getSizeInBits());
3533 
3534  computeKnownBitsFromRangeMetadata(*Ranges, KnownFull);
3535  Known = KnownFull.trunc(BitWidth);
3536  } else
3537  computeKnownBitsFromRangeMetadata(*Ranges, Known);
3538  }
3539  }
3540  break;
3541  }
3542  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG: {
3543  if (Op.getValueType().isScalableVector())
3544  break;
3545  EVT InVT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
3546  APInt InDemandedElts = DemandedElts.zext(InVT.getVectorNumElements());
3547  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), InDemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3548  Known = Known.zext(BitWidth);
3549  break;
3550  }
3551  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND: {
3552  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3553  Known = Known.zext(BitWidth);
3554  break;
3555  }
3556  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG: {
3557  if (Op.getValueType().isScalableVector())
3558  break;
3559  EVT InVT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
3560  APInt InDemandedElts = DemandedElts.zext(InVT.getVectorNumElements());
3561  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), InDemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3562  // If the sign bit is known to be zero or one, then sext will extend
3563  // it to the top bits, else it will just zext.
3564  Known = Known.sext(BitWidth);
3565  break;
3566  }
3567  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND: {
3568  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3569  // If the sign bit is known to be zero or one, then sext will extend
3570  // it to the top bits, else it will just zext.
3571  Known = Known.sext(BitWidth);
3572  break;
3573  }
3574  case ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG: {
3575  if (Op.getValueType().isScalableVector())
3576  break;
3577  EVT InVT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
3578  APInt InDemandedElts = DemandedElts.zext(InVT.getVectorNumElements());
3579  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), InDemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3580  Known = Known.anyext(BitWidth);
3581  break;
3582  }
3583  case ISD::ANY_EXTEND: {
3584  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3585  Known = Known.anyext(BitWidth);
3586  break;
3587  }
3588  case ISD::TRUNCATE: {
3589  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3590  Known = Known.trunc(BitWidth);
3591  break;
3592  }
3593  case ISD::AssertZext: {
3594  EVT VT = cast<VTSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))->getVT();
3595  APInt InMask = APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, VT.getSizeInBits());
3596  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3597  Known.Zero |= (~InMask);
3598  Known.One &= (~Known.Zero);
3599  break;
3600  }
3601  case ISD::AssertAlign: {
3602  unsigned LogOfAlign = Log2(cast<AssertAlignSDNode>(Op)->getAlign());
3603  assert(LogOfAlign != 0);
3604 
3605  // TODO: Should use maximum with source
3606  // If a node is guaranteed to be aligned, set low zero bits accordingly as
3607  // well as clearing one bits.
3608  Known.Zero.setLowBits(LogOfAlign);
3609  Known.One.clearLowBits(LogOfAlign);
3610  break;
3611  }
3612  case ISD::FGETSIGN:
3613  // All bits are zero except the low bit.
3614  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(1);
3615  break;
3616  case ISD::USUBO:
3617  case ISD::SSUBO:
3618  case ISD::SUBCARRY:
3619  case ISD::SSUBO_CARRY:
3620  if (Op.getResNo() == 1) {
3621  // If we know the result of a setcc has the top bits zero, use this info.
3622  if (TLI->getBooleanContents(Op.getOperand(0).getValueType()) ==
3623  TargetLowering::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent &&
3624  BitWidth > 1)
3625  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(1);
3626  break;
3627  }
3628  [[fallthrough]];
3629  case ISD::SUB:
3630  case ISD::SUBC: {
3631  assert(Op.getResNo() == 0 &&
3632  "We only compute knownbits for the difference here.");
3633 
3634  // TODO: Compute influence of the carry operand.
3635  if (Opcode == ISD::SUBCARRY || Opcode == ISD::SSUBO_CARRY)
3636  break;
3637 
3638  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3639  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3640  Known = KnownBits::computeForAddSub(/* Add */ false, /* NSW */ false,
3641  Known, Known2);
3642  break;
3643  }
3644  case ISD::UADDO:
3645  case ISD::SADDO:
3646  case ISD::ADDCARRY:
3647  case ISD::SADDO_CARRY:
3648  if (Op.getResNo() == 1) {
3649  // If we know the result of a setcc has the top bits zero, use this info.
3650  if (TLI->getBooleanContents(Op.getOperand(0).getValueType()) ==
3651  TargetLowering::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent &&
3652  BitWidth > 1)
3653  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(1);
3654  break;
3655  }
3656  [[fallthrough]];
3657  case ISD::ADD:
3658  case ISD::ADDC:
3659  case ISD::ADDE: {
3660  assert(Op.getResNo() == 0 && "We only compute knownbits for the sum here.");
3661 
3662  // With ADDE and ADDCARRY, a carry bit may be added in.
3663  KnownBits Carry(1);
3664  if (Opcode == ISD::ADDE)
3665  // Can't track carry from glue, set carry to unknown.
3666  Carry.resetAll();
3667  else if (Opcode == ISD::ADDCARRY || Opcode == ISD::SADDO_CARRY)
3668  // TODO: Compute known bits for the carry operand. Not sure if it is worth
3669  // the trouble (how often will we find a known carry bit). And I haven't
3670  // tested this very much yet, but something like this might work:
3671  // Carry = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(2), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3672  // Carry = Carry.zextOrTrunc(1, false);
3673  Carry.resetAll();
3674  else
3675  Carry.setAllZero();
3676 
3677  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3678  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3679  Known = KnownBits::computeForAddCarry(Known, Known2, Carry);
3680  break;
3681  }
3682  case ISD::UDIV: {
3683  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3684  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3685  Known = KnownBits::udiv(Known, Known2);
3686  break;
3687  }
3688  case ISD::SREM: {
3689  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3690  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3691  Known = KnownBits::srem(Known, Known2);
3692  break;
3693  }
3694  case ISD::UREM: {
3695  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3696  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3697  Known = KnownBits::urem(Known, Known2);
3698  break;
3699  }
3700  case ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT: {
3701  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), Depth+1);
3702  const unsigned Index = Op.getConstantOperandVal(1);
3703  const unsigned EltBitWidth = Op.getValueSizeInBits();
3704 
3705  // Remove low part of known bits mask
3706  Known.Zero = Known.Zero.getHiBits(Known.getBitWidth() - Index * EltBitWidth);
3707  Known.One = Known.One.getHiBits(Known.getBitWidth() - Index * EltBitWidth);
3708 
3709  // Remove high part of known bit mask
3710  Known = Known.trunc(EltBitWidth);
3711  break;
3712  }
3713  case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT: {
3714  SDValue InVec = Op.getOperand(0);
3715  SDValue EltNo = Op.getOperand(1);
3716  EVT VecVT = InVec.getValueType();
3717  // computeKnownBits not yet implemented for scalable vectors.
3718  if (VecVT.isScalableVector())
3719  break;
3720  const unsigned EltBitWidth = VecVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
3721  const unsigned NumSrcElts = VecVT.getVectorNumElements();
3722 
3723  // If BitWidth > EltBitWidth the value is anyext:ed. So we do not know
3724  // anything about the extended bits.
3725  if (BitWidth > EltBitWidth)
3726  Known = Known.trunc(EltBitWidth);
3727 
3728  // If we know the element index, just demand that vector element, else for
3729  // an unknown element index, ignore DemandedElts and demand them all.
3730  APInt DemandedSrcElts = APInt::getAllOnes(NumSrcElts);
3731  auto *ConstEltNo = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(EltNo);
3732  if (ConstEltNo && ConstEltNo->getAPIntValue().ult(NumSrcElts))
3733  DemandedSrcElts =
3734  APInt::getOneBitSet(NumSrcElts, ConstEltNo->getZExtValue());
3735 
3736  Known = computeKnownBits(InVec, DemandedSrcElts, Depth + 1);
3737  if (BitWidth > EltBitWidth)
3738  Known = Known.anyext(BitWidth);
3739  break;
3740  }
3741  case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT: {
3742  if (Op.getValueType().isScalableVector())
3743  break;
3744 
3745  // If we know the element index, split the demand between the
3746  // source vector and the inserted element, otherwise assume we need
3747  // the original demanded vector elements and the value.
3748  SDValue InVec = Op.getOperand(0);
3749  SDValue InVal = Op.getOperand(1);
3750  SDValue EltNo = Op.getOperand(2);
3751  bool DemandedVal = true;
3752  APInt DemandedVecElts = DemandedElts;
3753  auto *CEltNo = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(EltNo);
3754  if (CEltNo && CEltNo->getAPIntValue().ult(NumElts)) {
3755  unsigned EltIdx = CEltNo->getZExtValue();
3756  DemandedVal = !!DemandedElts[EltIdx];
3757  DemandedVecElts.clearBit(EltIdx);
3758  }
3759  Known.One.setAllBits();
3760  Known.Zero.setAllBits();
3761  if (DemandedVal) {
3762  Known2 = computeKnownBits(InVal, Depth + 1);
3763  Known = KnownBits::commonBits(Known, Known2.zextOrTrunc(BitWidth));
3764  }
3765  if (!!DemandedVecElts) {
3766  Known2 = computeKnownBits(InVec, DemandedVecElts, Depth + 1);
3767  Known = KnownBits::commonBits(Known, Known2);
3768  }
3769  break;
3770  }
3771  case ISD::BITREVERSE: {
3772  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3773  Known = Known2.reverseBits();
3774  break;
3775  }
3776  case ISD::BSWAP: {
3777  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3778  Known = Known2.byteSwap();
3779  break;
3780  }
3781  case ISD::ABS: {
3782  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3783  Known = Known2.abs();
3784  break;
3785  }
3786  case ISD::USUBSAT: {
3787  // The result of usubsat will never be larger than the LHS.
3788  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3789  Known.Zero.setHighBits(Known2.countMinLeadingZeros());
3790  break;
3791  }
3792  case ISD::UMIN: {
3793  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3794  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3795  Known = KnownBits::umin(Known, Known2);
3796  break;
3797  }
3798  case ISD::UMAX: {
3799  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3800  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3801  Known = KnownBits::umax(Known, Known2);
3802  break;
3803  }
3804  case ISD::SMIN:
3805  case ISD::SMAX: {
3806  // If we have a clamp pattern, we know that the number of sign bits will be
3807  // the minimum of the clamp min/max range.
3808  bool IsMax = (Opcode == ISD::SMAX);
3809  ConstantSDNode *CstLow = nullptr, *CstHigh = nullptr;
3810  if ((CstLow = isConstOrConstSplat(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts)))
3811  if (Op.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == (IsMax ? ISD::SMIN : ISD::SMAX))
3812  CstHigh =
3813  isConstOrConstSplat(Op.getOperand(0).getOperand(1), DemandedElts);
3814  if (CstLow && CstHigh) {
3815  if (!IsMax)
3816  std::swap(CstLow, CstHigh);
3817 
3818  const APInt &ValueLow = CstLow->getAPIntValue();
3819  const APInt &ValueHigh = CstHigh->getAPIntValue();
3820  if (ValueLow.sle(ValueHigh)) {
3821  unsigned LowSignBits = ValueLow.getNumSignBits();
3822  unsigned HighSignBits = ValueHigh.getNumSignBits();
3823  unsigned MinSignBits = std::min(LowSignBits, HighSignBits);
3824  if (ValueLow.isNegative() && ValueHigh.isNegative()) {
3825  Known.One.setHighBits(MinSignBits);
3826  break;
3827  }
3828  if (ValueLow.isNonNegative() && ValueHigh.isNonNegative()) {
3829  Known.Zero.setHighBits(MinSignBits);
3830  break;
3831  }
3832  }
3833  }
3834 
3835  Known = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3836  Known2 = computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
3837  if (IsMax)
3838  Known = KnownBits::smax(Known, Known2);
3839  else
3840  Known = KnownBits::smin(Known, Known2);
3841 
3842  // For SMAX, if CstLow is non-negative we know the result will be
3843  // non-negative and thus all sign bits are 0.
3844  // TODO: There's an equivalent of this for smin with negative constant for
3845  // known ones.
3846  if (IsMax && CstLow) {
3847  const APInt &ValueLow = CstLow->getAPIntValue();
3848  if (ValueLow.isNonNegative()) {
3849  unsigned SignBits = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), Depth + 1);
3850  Known.Zero.setHighBits(std::min(SignBits, ValueLow.getNumSignBits()));
3851  }
3852  }
3853 
3854  break;
3855  }
3856  case ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT: {
3857  // FP_TO_UINT_SAT produces an unsigned value that fits in the saturating VT.
3858  EVT VT = cast<VTSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))->getVT();
3859  Known.Zero |= APInt::getBitsSetFrom(BitWidth, VT.getScalarSizeInBits());
3860  break;
3861  }
3862  case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_WITH_SUCCESS:
3863  if (Op.getResNo() == 1) {
3864  // The boolean result conforms to getBooleanContents.
3865  // If we know the result of a setcc has the top bits zero, use this info.
3866  // We know that we have an integer-based boolean since these operations
3867  // are only available for integer.
3868  if (TLI->getBooleanContents(Op.getValueType().isVector(), false) ==
3869  TargetLowering::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent &&
3870  BitWidth > 1)
3871  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(1);
3872  break;
3873  }
3874  [[fallthrough]];
3875  case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP:
3876  case ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP:
3877  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD:
3878  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB:
3879  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND:
3880  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_CLR:
3881  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR:
3882  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR:
3883  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND:
3884  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN:
3885  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX:
3886  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN:
3887  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX:
3888  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD: {
3889  unsigned MemBits =
3890  cast<AtomicSDNode>(Op)->getMemoryVT().getScalarSizeInBits();
3891  // If we are looking at the loaded value.
3892  if (Op.getResNo() == 0) {
3893  if (TLI->getExtendForAtomicOps() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND)
3894  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(MemBits);
3895  }
3896  break;
3897  }
3898  case ISD::FrameIndex:
3899  case ISD::TargetFrameIndex:
3900  TLI->computeKnownBitsForFrameIndex(cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(Op)->getIndex(),
3901  Known, getMachineFunction());
3902  break;
3903 
3904  default:
3905  if (Opcode < ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END)
3906  break;
3907  [[fallthrough]];
3908  case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN:
3909  case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN:
3910  case ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID:
3911  // TODO: Probably okay to remove after audit; here to reduce change size
3912  // in initial enablement patch for scalable vectors
3913  if (Op.getValueType().isScalableVector())
3914  break;
3915 
3916  // Allow the target to implement this method for its nodes.
3917  TLI->computeKnownBitsForTargetNode(Op, Known, DemandedElts, *this, Depth);
3918  break;
3919  }
3920 
3921  assert(!Known.hasConflict() && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
3922  return Known;
3923 }
3924 
3925 SelectionDAG::OverflowKind SelectionDAG::computeOverflowKind(SDValue N0,
3926  SDValue N1) const {
3927  // X + 0 never overflow
3928  if (isNullConstant(N1))
3929  return OFK_Never;
3930 
3931  KnownBits N1Known = computeKnownBits(N1);
3932  if (N1Known.Zero.getBoolValue()) {
3933  KnownBits N0Known = computeKnownBits(N0);
3934 
3935  bool overflow;
3936  (void)N0Known.getMaxValue().uadd_ov(N1Known.getMaxValue(), overflow);
3937  if (!overflow)
3938  return OFK_Never;
3939  }
3940 
3941  // mulhi + 1 never overflow
3942  if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::UMUL_LOHI && N0.getResNo() == 1 &&
3943  (N1Known.getMaxValue() & 0x01) == N1Known.getMaxValue())
3944  return OFK_Never;
3945 
3946  if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::UMUL_LOHI && N1.getResNo() == 1) {
3947  KnownBits N0Known = computeKnownBits(N0);
3948 
3949  if ((N0Known.getMaxValue() & 0x01) == N0Known.getMaxValue())
3950  return OFK_Never;
3951  }
3952 
3953  return OFK_Sometime;
3954 }
3955 
3956 bool SelectionDAG::isKnownToBeAPowerOfTwo(SDValue Val) const {
3957  EVT OpVT = Val.getValueType();
3958  unsigned BitWidth = OpVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
3959 
3960  // Is the constant a known power of 2?
3961  if (ConstantSDNode *Const = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Val))
3962  return Const->getAPIntValue().zextOrTrunc(BitWidth).isPowerOf2();
3963 
3964  // A left-shift of a constant one will have exactly one bit set because
3965  // shifting the bit off the end is undefined.
3966  if (Val.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) {
3967  auto *C = isConstOrConstSplat(Val.getOperand(0));
3968  if (C && C->getAPIntValue() == 1)
3969  return true;
3970  }
3971 
3972  // Similarly, a logical right-shift of a constant sign-bit will have exactly
3973  // one bit set.
3974  if (Val.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL) {
3975  auto *C = isConstOrConstSplat(Val.getOperand(0));
3976  if (C && C->getAPIntValue().isSignMask())
3977  return true;
3978  }
3979 
3980  // Are all operands of a build vector constant powers of two?
3981  if (Val.getOpcode() == ISD::BUILD_VECTOR)
3982  if (llvm::all_of(Val->ops(), [BitWidth](SDValue E) {
3983  if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(E))
3984  return C->getAPIntValue().zextOrTrunc(BitWidth).isPowerOf2();
3985  return false;
3986  }))
3987  return true;
3988 
3989  // Is the operand of a splat vector a constant power of two?
3990  if (Val.getOpcode() == ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR)
3991  if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Val->getOperand(0)))
3992  if (C->getAPIntValue().zextOrTrunc(BitWidth).isPowerOf2())
3993  return true;
3994 
3995  // vscale(power-of-two) is a power-of-two for some targets
3996  if (Val.getOpcode() == ISD::VSCALE &&
3997  getTargetLoweringInfo().isVScaleKnownToBeAPowerOfTwo() &&
3998  isKnownToBeAPowerOfTwo(Val.getOperand(0)))
3999  return true;
4000 
4001  // More could be done here, though the above checks are enough
4002  // to handle some common cases.
4003 
4004  // Fall back to computeKnownBits to catch other known cases.
4005  KnownBits Known = computeKnownBits(Val);
4006  return (Known.countMaxPopulation() == 1) && (Known.countMinPopulation() == 1);
4007 }
4008 
4009 unsigned SelectionDAG::ComputeNumSignBits(SDValue Op, unsigned Depth) const {
4010  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
4011 
4012  // Since the number of lanes in a scalable vector is unknown at compile time,
4013  // we track one bit which is implicitly broadcast to all lanes. This means
4014  // that all lanes in a scalable vector are considered demanded.
4015  APInt DemandedElts = VT.isFixedLengthVector()
4016  ? APInt::getAllOnes(VT.getVectorNumElements())
4017  : APInt(1, 1);
4018  return ComputeNumSignBits(Op, DemandedElts, Depth);
4019 }
4020 
4021 unsigned SelectionDAG::ComputeNumSignBits(SDValue Op, const APInt &DemandedElts,
4022  unsigned Depth) const {
4023  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
4024  assert((VT.isInteger() || VT.isFloatingPoint()) && "Invalid VT!");
4025  unsigned VTBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
4026  unsigned NumElts = DemandedElts.getBitWidth();
4027  unsigned Tmp, Tmp2;
4028  unsigned FirstAnswer = 1;
4029 
4030  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)) {
4031  const APInt &Val = C->getAPIntValue();
4032  return Val.getNumSignBits();
4033  }
4034 
4035  if (Depth >= MaxRecursionDepth)
4036  return 1; // Limit search depth.
4037 
4038  if (!DemandedElts)
4039  return 1; // No demanded elts, better to assume we don't know anything.
4040 
4041  unsigned Opcode = Op.getOpcode();
4042  switch (Opcode) {
4043  default: break;
4044  case ISD::AssertSext:
4045  Tmp = cast<VTSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))->getVT().getSizeInBits();
4046  return VTBits-Tmp+1;
4047  case ISD::AssertZext:
4048  Tmp = cast<VTSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))->getVT().getSizeInBits();
4049  return VTBits-Tmp;
4050  case ISD::MERGE_VALUES:
4051  return ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(Op.getResNo()), DemandedElts,
4052  Depth + 1);
4053  case ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR: {
4054  // Check if the sign bits of source go down as far as the truncated value.
4055  unsigned NumSrcBits = Op.getOperand(0).getValueSizeInBits();
4056  unsigned NumSrcSignBits = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), Depth + 1);
4057  if (NumSrcSignBits > (NumSrcBits - VTBits))
4058  return NumSrcSignBits - (NumSrcBits - VTBits);
4059  break;
4060  }
4061  case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR:
4062  assert(!VT.isScalableVector());
4063  Tmp = VTBits;
4064  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Op.getNumOperands(); (i < e) && (Tmp > 1); ++i) {
4065  if (!DemandedElts[i])
4066  continue;
4067 
4068  SDValue SrcOp = Op.getOperand(i);
4069  Tmp2 = ComputeNumSignBits(SrcOp, Depth + 1);
4070 
4071  // BUILD_VECTOR can implicitly truncate sources, we must handle this.
4072  if (SrcOp.getValueSizeInBits() != VTBits) {
4073  assert(SrcOp.getValueSizeInBits() > VTBits &&
4074  "Expected BUILD_VECTOR implicit truncation");
4075  unsigned ExtraBits = SrcOp.getValueSizeInBits() - VTBits;
4076  Tmp2 = (Tmp2 > ExtraBits ? Tmp2 - ExtraBits : 1);
4077  }
4078  Tmp = std::min(Tmp, Tmp2);
4079  }
4080  return Tmp;
4081 
4082  case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE: {
4083  // Collect the minimum number of sign bits that are shared by every vector
4084  // element referenced by the shuffle.
4085  APInt DemandedLHS, DemandedRHS;
4086  const ShuffleVectorSDNode *SVN = cast<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(Op);
4087  assert(NumElts == SVN->getMask().size() && "Unexpected vector size");
4088  if (!getShuffleDemandedElts(NumElts, SVN->getMask(), DemandedElts,
4089  DemandedLHS, DemandedRHS))
4090  return 1;
4091 
4092  Tmp = std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max();
4093  if (!!DemandedLHS)
4094  Tmp = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedLHS, Depth + 1);
4095  if (!!DemandedRHS) {
4096  Tmp2 = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedRHS, Depth + 1);
4097  Tmp = std::min(Tmp, Tmp2);
4098  }
4099  // If we don't know anything, early out and try computeKnownBits fall-back.
4100  if (Tmp == 1)
4101  break;
4102  assert(Tmp <= VTBits && "Failed to determine minimum sign bits");
4103  return Tmp;
4104  }
4105 
4106  case ISD::BITCAST: {
4107  if (VT.isScalableVector())
4108  break;
4109  SDValue N0 = Op.getOperand(0);
4110  EVT SrcVT = N0.getValueType();
4111  unsigned SrcBits = SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
4112 
4113  // Ignore bitcasts from unsupported types..
4114  if (!(SrcVT.isInteger() || SrcVT.isFloatingPoint()))
4115  break;
4116 
4117  // Fast handling of 'identity' bitcasts.
4118  if (VTBits == SrcBits)
4119  return ComputeNumSignBits(N0, DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
4120 
4121  bool IsLE = getDataLayout().isLittleEndian();
4122 
4123  // Bitcast 'large element' scalar/vector to 'small element' vector.
4124  if ((SrcBits % VTBits) == 0) {
4125  assert(VT.isVector() && "Expected bitcast to vector");
4126 
4127  unsigned Scale = SrcBits / VTBits;
4128  APInt SrcDemandedElts =
4129  APIntOps::ScaleBitMask(DemandedElts, NumElts / Scale);
4130 
4131  // Fast case - sign splat can be simply split across the small elements.
4132  Tmp = ComputeNumSignBits(N0, SrcDemandedElts, Depth + 1);
4133  if (Tmp == SrcBits)
4134  return VTBits;
4135 
4136  // Slow case - determine how far the sign extends into each sub-element.
4137  Tmp2 = VTBits;
4138  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i)
4139  if (DemandedElts[i]) {
4140  unsigned SubOffset = i % Scale;
4141  SubOffset = (IsLE ? ((Scale - 1) - SubOffset) : SubOffset);
4142  SubOffset = SubOffset * VTBits;
4143  if (Tmp <= SubOffset)
4144  return 1;
4145  Tmp2 = std::min(Tmp2, Tmp - SubOffset);
4146  }
4147  return Tmp2;
4148  }
4149  break;
4150  }
4151 
4152  case ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT:
4153  // FP_TO_SINT_SAT produces a signed value that fits in the saturating VT.
4154  Tmp = cast<VTSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))->getVT().getScalarSizeInBits();
4155  return VTBits - Tmp + 1;
4156  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
4157  Tmp = VTBits - Op.getOperand(0).getScalarValueSizeInBits();
4158  return ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth+1) + Tmp;
4159  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG:
4160  // Max of the input and what this extends.
4161  Tmp = cast<VTSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))->getVT().getScalarSizeInBits();
4162  Tmp = VTBits-Tmp+1;
4163  Tmp2 = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth+1);
4164  return std::max(Tmp, Tmp2);
4165  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG: {
4166  if (VT.isScalableVector())
4167  break;
4168  SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
4169  EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
4170  APInt DemandedSrcElts = DemandedElts.zext(SrcVT.getVectorNumElements());
4171  Tmp = VTBits - SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
4172  return ComputeNumSignBits(Src, DemandedSrcElts, Depth+1) + Tmp;
4173  }
4174  case ISD::SRA:
4175  Tmp = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
4176  // SRA X, C -> adds C sign bits.
4177  if (const APInt *ShAmt =
4178  getValidMinimumShiftAmountConstant(Op, DemandedElts))
4179  Tmp = std::min<uint64_t>(Tmp + ShAmt->getZExtValue(), VTBits);
4180  return Tmp;
4181  case ISD::SHL:
4182  if (const APInt *ShAmt =
4183  getValidMaximumShiftAmountConstant(Op, DemandedElts)) {
4184  // shl destroys sign bits, ensure it doesn't shift out all sign bits.
4185  Tmp = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
4186  if (ShAmt->ult(Tmp))
4187  return Tmp - ShAmt->getZExtValue();
4188  }
4189  break;
4190  case ISD::AND:
4191  case ISD::OR:
4192  case ISD::XOR: // NOT is handled here.
4193  // Logical binary ops preserve the number of sign bits at the worst.
4194  Tmp = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth+1);
4195  if (Tmp != 1) {
4196  Tmp2 = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth+1);
4197  FirstAnswer = std::min(Tmp, Tmp2);
4198  // We computed what we know about the sign bits as our first
4199  // answer. Now proceed to the generic code that uses
4200  // computeKnownBits, and pick whichever answer is better.
4201  }
4202  break;
4203 
4204  case ISD::SELECT:
4205  case ISD::VSELECT:
4206  Tmp = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth+1);
4207  if (Tmp == 1) return 1; // Early out.
4208  Tmp2 = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(2), DemandedElts, Depth+1);
4209  return std::min(Tmp, Tmp2);
4210  case ISD::SELECT_CC:
4211  Tmp = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(2), DemandedElts, Depth+1);
4212  if (Tmp == 1) return 1; // Early out.
4213  Tmp2 = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(3), DemandedElts, Depth+1);
4214  return std::min(Tmp, Tmp2);
4215 
4216  case ISD::SMIN:
4217  case ISD::SMAX: {
4218  // If we have a clamp pattern, we know that the number of sign bits will be
4219  // the minimum of the clamp min/max range.
4220  bool IsMax = (Opcode == ISD::SMAX);
4221  ConstantSDNode *CstLow = nullptr, *CstHigh = nullptr;
4222  if ((CstLow = isConstOrConstSplat(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts)))
4223  if (Op.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == (IsMax ? ISD::SMIN : ISD::SMAX))
4224  CstHigh =
4225  isConstOrConstSplat(Op.getOperand(0).getOperand(1), DemandedElts);
4226  if (CstLow && CstHigh) {
4227  if (!IsMax)
4228  std::swap(CstLow, CstHigh);
4229  if (CstLow->getAPIntValue().sle(CstHigh->getAPIntValue())) {
4230  Tmp = CstLow->getAPIntValue().getNumSignBits();
4231  Tmp2 = CstHigh->getAPIntValue().getNumSignBits();
4232  return std::min(Tmp, Tmp2);
4233  }
4234  }
4235 
4236  // Fallback - just get the minimum number of sign bits of the operands.
4237  Tmp = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
4238  if (Tmp == 1)
4239  return 1; // Early out.
4240  Tmp2 = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
4241  return std::min(Tmp, Tmp2);
4242  }
4243  case ISD::UMIN:
4244  case ISD::UMAX:
4245  Tmp = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
4246  if (Tmp == 1)
4247  return 1; // Early out.
4248  Tmp2 = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
4249  return std::min(Tmp, Tmp2);
4250  case ISD::SADDO:
4251  case ISD::UADDO:
4252  case ISD::SADDO_CARRY:
4253  case ISD::ADDCARRY:
4254  case ISD::SSUBO:
4255  case ISD::USUBO:
4256  case ISD::SSUBO_CARRY:
4257  case ISD::SUBCARRY:
4258  case ISD::SMULO:
4259  case ISD::UMULO:
4260  if (Op.getResNo() != 1)
4261  break;
4262  // The boolean result conforms to getBooleanContents. Fall through.
4263  // If setcc returns 0/-1, all bits are sign bits.
4264  // We know that we have an integer-based boolean since these operations
4265  // are only available for integer.
4266  if (TLI->getBooleanContents(VT.isVector(), false) ==
4267  TargetLowering::ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent)
4268  return VTBits;
4269  break;
4270  case ISD::SETCC:
4271  case ISD::SETCCCARRY:
4272  case ISD::STRICT_FSETCC:
4273  case ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS: {
4274  unsigned OpNo = Op->isStrictFPOpcode() ? 1 : 0;
4275  // If setcc returns 0/-1, all bits are sign bits.
4276  if (TLI->getBooleanContents(Op.getOperand(OpNo).getValueType()) ==
4277  TargetLowering::ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent)
4278  return VTBits;
4279  break;
4280  }
4281  case ISD::ROTL:
4282  case ISD::ROTR:
4283  Tmp = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
4284 
4285  // If we're rotating an 0/-1 value, then it stays an 0/-1 value.
4286  if (Tmp == VTBits)
4287  return VTBits;
4288 
4289  if (ConstantSDNode *C =
4290  isConstOrConstSplat(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts)) {
4291  unsigned RotAmt = C->getAPIntValue().urem(VTBits);
4292 
4293  // Handle rotate right by N like a rotate left by 32-N.
4294  if (Opcode == ISD::ROTR)
4295  RotAmt = (VTBits - RotAmt) % VTBits;
4296 
4297  // If we aren't rotating out all of the known-in sign bits, return the
4298  // number that are left. This handles rotl(sext(x), 1) for example.
4299  if (Tmp > (RotAmt + 1)) return (Tmp - RotAmt);
4300  }
4301  break;
4302  case ISD::ADD:
4303  case ISD::ADDC:
4304  // Add can have at most one carry bit. Thus we know that the output
4305  // is, at worst, one more bit than the inputs.
4306  Tmp = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
4307  if (Tmp == 1) return 1; // Early out.
4308 
4309  // Special case decrementing a value (ADD X, -1):
4310  if (ConstantSDNode *CRHS =
4311  isConstOrConstSplat(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts))
4312  if (CRHS->isAllOnes()) {
4313  KnownBits Known =
4314  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
4315 
4316  // If the input is known to be 0 or 1, the output is 0/-1, which is all
4317  // sign bits set.
4318  if ((Known.Zero | 1).isAllOnes())
4319  return VTBits;
4320 
4321  // If we are subtracting one from a positive number, there is no carry
4322  // out of the result.
4323  if (Known.isNonNegative())
4324  return Tmp;
4325  }
4326 
4327  Tmp2 = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
4328  if (Tmp2 == 1) return 1; // Early out.
4329  return std::min(Tmp, Tmp2) - 1;
4330  case ISD::SUB:
4331  Tmp2 = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
4332  if (Tmp2 == 1) return 1; // Early out.
4333 
4334  // Handle NEG.
4335  if (ConstantSDNode *CLHS =
4336  isConstOrConstSplat(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts))
4337  if (CLHS->isZero()) {
4338  KnownBits Known =
4339  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
4340  // If the input is known to be 0 or 1, the output is 0/-1, which is all
4341  // sign bits set.
4342  if ((Known.Zero | 1).isAllOnes())
4343  return VTBits;
4344 
4345  // If the input is known to be positive (the sign bit is known clear),
4346  // the output of the NEG has the same number of sign bits as the input.
4347  if (Known.isNonNegative())
4348  return Tmp2;
4349 
4350  // Otherwise, we treat this like a SUB.
4351  }
4352 
4353  // Sub can have at most one carry bit. Thus we know that the output
4354  // is, at worst, one more bit than the inputs.
4355  Tmp = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
4356  if (Tmp == 1) return 1; // Early out.
4357  return std::min(Tmp, Tmp2) - 1;
4358  case ISD::MUL: {
4359  // The output of the Mul can be at most twice the valid bits in the inputs.
4360  unsigned SignBitsOp0 = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), Depth + 1);
4361  if (SignBitsOp0 == 1)
4362  break;
4363  unsigned SignBitsOp1 = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(1), Depth + 1);
4364  if (SignBitsOp1 == 1)
4365  break;
4366  unsigned OutValidBits =
4367  (VTBits - SignBitsOp0 + 1) + (VTBits - SignBitsOp1 + 1);
4368  return OutValidBits > VTBits ? 1 : VTBits - OutValidBits + 1;
4369  }
4370  case ISD::SREM:
4371  // The sign bit is the LHS's sign bit, except when the result of the
4372  // remainder is zero. The magnitude of the result should be less than or
4373  // equal to the magnitude of the LHS. Therefore, the result should have
4374  // at least as many sign bits as the left hand side.
4375  return ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
4376  case ISD::TRUNCATE: {
4377  // Check if the sign bits of source go down as far as the truncated value.
4378  unsigned NumSrcBits = Op.getOperand(0).getScalarValueSizeInBits();
4379  unsigned NumSrcSignBits = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), Depth + 1);
4380  if (NumSrcSignBits > (NumSrcBits - VTBits))
4381  return NumSrcSignBits - (NumSrcBits - VTBits);
4382  break;
4383  }
4384  case ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT: {
4385  if (VT.isScalableVector())
4386  break;
4387  const int KnownSign = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), Depth+1);
4388  const int BitWidth = Op.getValueSizeInBits();
4389  const int Items = Op.getOperand(0).getValueSizeInBits() / BitWidth;
4390 
4391  // Get reverse index (starting from 1), Op1 value indexes elements from
4392  // little end. Sign starts at big end.
4393  const int rIndex = Items - 1 - Op.getConstantOperandVal(1);
4394 
4395  // If the sign portion ends in our element the subtraction gives correct
4396  // result. Otherwise it gives either negative or > bitwidth result
4397  return std::clamp(KnownSign - rIndex * BitWidth, 0, BitWidth);
4398  }
4399  case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT: {
4400  if (VT.isScalableVector())
4401  break;
4402  // If we know the element index, split the demand between the
4403  // source vector and the inserted element, otherwise assume we need
4404  // the original demanded vector elements and the value.
4405  SDValue InVec = Op.getOperand(0);
4406  SDValue InVal = Op.getOperand(1);
4407  SDValue EltNo = Op.getOperand(2);
4408  bool DemandedVal = true;
4409  APInt DemandedVecElts = DemandedElts;
4410  auto *CEltNo = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(EltNo);
4411  if (CEltNo && CEltNo->getAPIntValue().ult(NumElts)) {
4412  unsigned EltIdx = CEltNo->getZExtValue();
4413  DemandedVal = !!DemandedElts[EltIdx];
4414  DemandedVecElts.clearBit(EltIdx);
4415  }
4416  Tmp = std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max();
4417  if (DemandedVal) {
4418  // TODO - handle implicit truncation of inserted elements.
4419  if (InVal.getScalarValueSizeInBits() != VTBits)
4420  break;
4421  Tmp2 = ComputeNumSignBits(InVal, Depth + 1);
4422  Tmp = std::min(Tmp, Tmp2);
4423  }
4424  if (!!DemandedVecElts) {
4425  Tmp2 = ComputeNumSignBits(InVec, DemandedVecElts, Depth + 1);
4426  Tmp = std::min(Tmp, Tmp2);
4427  }
4428  assert(Tmp <= VTBits && "Failed to determine minimum sign bits");
4429  return Tmp;
4430  }
4431  case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT: {
4432  assert(!VT.isScalableVector());
4433  SDValue InVec = Op.getOperand(0);
4434  SDValue EltNo = Op.getOperand(1);
4435  EVT VecVT = InVec.getValueType();
4436  // ComputeNumSignBits not yet implemented for scalable vectors.
4437  if (VecVT.isScalableVector())
4438  break;
4439  const unsigned BitWidth = Op.getValueSizeInBits();
4440  const unsigned EltBitWidth = Op.getOperand(0).getScalarValueSizeInBits();
4441  const unsigned NumSrcElts = VecVT.getVectorNumElements();
4442 
4443  // If BitWidth > EltBitWidth the value is anyext:ed, and we do not know
4444  // anything about sign bits. But if the sizes match we can derive knowledge
4445  // about sign bits from the vector operand.
4446  if (BitWidth != EltBitWidth)
4447  break;
4448 
4449  // If we know the element index, just demand that vector element, else for
4450  // an unknown element index, ignore DemandedElts and demand them all.
4451  APInt DemandedSrcElts = APInt::getAllOnes(NumSrcElts);
4452  auto *ConstEltNo = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(EltNo);
4453  if (ConstEltNo && ConstEltNo->getAPIntValue().ult(NumSrcElts))
4454  DemandedSrcElts =
4455  APInt::getOneBitSet(NumSrcElts, ConstEltNo->getZExtValue());
4456 
4457  return ComputeNumSignBits(InVec, DemandedSrcElts, Depth + 1);
4458  }
4459  case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: {
4460  // Offset the demanded elts by the subvector index.
4461  SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
4462  // Bail until we can represent demanded elements for scalable vectors.
4463  if (Src.getValueType().isScalableVector())
4464  break;
4465  uint64_t Idx = Op.getConstantOperandVal(1);
4466  unsigned NumSrcElts = Src.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
4467  APInt DemandedSrcElts = DemandedElts.zext(NumSrcElts).shl(Idx);
4468  return ComputeNumSignBits(Src, DemandedSrcElts, Depth + 1);
4469  }
4470  case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS: {
4471  if (VT.isScalableVector())
4472  break;
4473  // Determine the minimum number of sign bits across all demanded
4474  // elts of the input vectors. Early out if the result is already 1.
4475  Tmp = std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max();
4476  EVT SubVectorVT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
4477  unsigned NumSubVectorElts = SubVectorVT.getVectorNumElements();
4478  unsigned NumSubVectors = Op.getNumOperands();
4479  for (unsigned i = 0; (i < NumSubVectors) && (Tmp > 1); ++i) {
4480  APInt DemandedSub =
4481  DemandedElts.extractBits(NumSubVectorElts, i * NumSubVectorElts);
4482  if (!DemandedSub)
4483  continue;
4484  Tmp2 = ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(i), DemandedSub, Depth + 1);
4485  Tmp = std::min(Tmp, Tmp2);
4486  }
4487  assert(Tmp <= VTBits && "Failed to determine minimum sign bits");
4488  return Tmp;
4489  }
4490  case ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR: {
4491  if (VT.isScalableVector())
4492  break;
4493  // Demand any elements from the subvector and the remainder from the src its
4494  // inserted into.
4495  SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
4496  SDValue Sub = Op.getOperand(1);
4497  uint64_t Idx = Op.getConstantOperandVal(2);
4498  unsigned NumSubElts = Sub.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
4499  APInt DemandedSubElts = DemandedElts.extractBits(NumSubElts, Idx);
4500  APInt DemandedSrcElts = DemandedElts;
4501  DemandedSrcElts.insertBits(APInt::getZero(NumSubElts), Idx);
4502 
4503  Tmp = std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max();
4504  if (!!DemandedSubElts) {
4505  Tmp = ComputeNumSignBits(Sub, DemandedSubElts, Depth + 1);
4506  if (Tmp == 1)
4507  return 1; // early-out
4508  }
4509  if (!!DemandedSrcElts) {
4510  Tmp2 = ComputeNumSignBits(Src, DemandedSrcElts, Depth + 1);
4511  Tmp = std::min(Tmp, Tmp2);
4512  }
4513  assert(Tmp <= VTBits && "Failed to determine minimum sign bits");
4514  return Tmp;
4515  }
4516  case ISD::LOAD: {
4517  LoadSDNode *LD = cast<LoadSDNode>(Op);
4518  if (const MDNode *Ranges = LD->getRanges()) {
4519  if (DemandedElts != 1)
4520  break;
4521 
4522  ConstantRange CR = getConstantRangeFromMetadata(*Ranges);
4523  if (VTBits > CR.getBitWidth()) {
4524  switch (LD->getExtensionType()) {
4525  case ISD::SEXTLOAD:
4526  CR = CR.signExtend(VTBits);
4527  break;
4528  case ISD::ZEXTLOAD:
4529  CR = CR.zeroExtend(VTBits);
4530  break;
4531  default:
4532  break;
4533  }
4534  }
4535 
4536  if (VTBits != CR.getBitWidth())
4537  break;
4538  return std::min(CR.getSignedMin().getNumSignBits(),
4539  CR.getSignedMax().getNumSignBits());
4540  }
4541 
4542  break;
4543  }
4544  case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP:
4545  case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_WITH_SUCCESS:
4546  case ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP:
4547  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD:
4548  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB:
4549  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND:
4550  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_CLR:
4551  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR:
4552  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR:
4553  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND:
4554  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN:
4555  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX:
4556  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN:
4557  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX:
4558  case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD: {
4559  Tmp = cast<AtomicSDNode>(Op)->getMemoryVT().getScalarSizeInBits();
4560  // If we are looking at the loaded value.
4561  if (Op.getResNo() == 0) {
4562  if (Tmp == VTBits)
4563  return 1; // early-out
4564  if (TLI->getExtendForAtomicOps() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND)
4565  return VTBits - Tmp + 1;
4566  if (TLI->getExtendForAtomicOps() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND)
4567  return VTBits - Tmp;
4568  }
4569  break;
4570  }
4571  }
4572 
4573  // If we are looking at the loaded value of the SDNode.
4574  if (Op.getResNo() == 0) {
4575  // Handle LOADX separately here. EXTLOAD case will fallthrough.
4576  if (LoadSDNode *LD = dyn_cast<LoadSDNode>(Op)) {
4577  unsigned ExtType = LD->getExtensionType();
4578  switch (ExtType) {
4579  default: break;
4580  case ISD::SEXTLOAD: // e.g. i16->i32 = '17' bits known.
4581  Tmp = LD->getMemoryVT().getScalarSizeInBits();
4582  return VTBits - Tmp + 1;
4583  case ISD::ZEXTLOAD: // e.g. i16->i32 = '16' bits known.
4584  Tmp = LD->getMemoryVT().getScalarSizeInBits();
4585  return VTBits - Tmp;
4586  case ISD::NON_EXTLOAD:
4587  if (const Constant *Cst = TLI->getTargetConstantFromLoad(LD)) {
4588  // We only need to handle vectors - computeKnownBits should handle
4589  // scalar cases.
4590  Type *CstTy = Cst->getType();
4591  if (CstTy->isVectorTy() && !VT.isScalableVector() &&
4592  (NumElts * VTBits) == CstTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() &&
4593  VTBits == CstTy->getScalarSizeInBits()) {
4594  Tmp = VTBits;
4595  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
4596  if (!DemandedElts[i])
4597  continue;
4598  if (Constant *Elt = Cst->getAggregateElement(i)) {
4599  if (auto *CInt = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Elt)) {
4600  const APInt &Value = CInt->getValue();
4601  Tmp = std::min(Tmp, Value.getNumSignBits());
4602  continue;
4603  }
4604  if (auto *CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Elt)) {
4605  APInt Value = CFP->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt();
4606  Tmp = std::min(Tmp, Value.getNumSignBits());
4607  continue;
4608  }
4609  }
4610  // Unknown type. Conservatively assume no bits match sign bit.
4611  return 1;
4612  }
4613  return Tmp;
4614  }
4615  }
4616  break;
4617  }
4618  }
4619  }
4620 
4621  // Allow the target to implement this method for its nodes.
4622  if (Opcode >= ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END ||
4623  Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN ||
4624  Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN ||
4625  Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID) {
4626  // TODO: This can probably be removed once target code is audited. This
4627  // is here purely to reduce patch size and review complexity.
4628  if (!VT.isScalableVector()) {
4629  unsigned NumBits =
4630  TLI->ComputeNumSignBitsForTargetNode(Op, DemandedElts, *this, Depth);
4631  if (NumBits > 1)
4632  FirstAnswer = std::max(FirstAnswer, NumBits);
4633  }
4634  }
4635 
4636  // Finally, if we can prove that the top bits of the result are 0's or 1's,
4637  // use this information.
4638  KnownBits Known = computeKnownBits(Op, DemandedElts, Depth);
4639  return std::max(FirstAnswer, Known.countMinSignBits());
4640 }
4641 
4642 unsigned SelectionDAG::ComputeMaxSignificantBits(SDValue Op,
4643  unsigned Depth) const {
4644  unsigned SignBits = ComputeNumSignBits(Op, Depth);
4645  return Op.getScalarValueSizeInBits() - SignBits + 1;
4646 }
4647 
4648 unsigned SelectionDAG::ComputeMaxSignificantBits(SDValue Op,
4649  const APInt &DemandedElts,
4650  unsigned Depth) const {
4651  unsigned SignBits = ComputeNumSignBits(Op, DemandedElts, Depth);
4652  return Op.getScalarValueSizeInBits() - SignBits + 1;
4653 }
4654 
4655 bool SelectionDAG::isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(SDValue Op, bool PoisonOnly,
4656  unsigned Depth) const {
4657  // Early out for FREEZE.
4658  if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::FREEZE)
4659  return true;
4660 
4661  // TODO: Assume we don't know anything for now.
4662  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
4663  if (VT.isScalableVector())
4664  return false;
4665 
4666  APInt DemandedElts = VT.isVector()
4667  ? APInt::getAllOnes(VT.getVectorNumElements())
4668  : APInt(1, 1);
4669  return isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(Op, DemandedElts, PoisonOnly, Depth);
4670 }
4671 
4672 bool SelectionDAG::isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(SDValue Op,
4673  const APInt &DemandedElts,
4674  bool PoisonOnly,
4675  unsigned Depth) const {
4676  unsigned Opcode = Op.getOpcode();
4677 
4678  // Early out for FREEZE.
4679  if (Opcode == ISD::FREEZE)
4680  return true;
4681 
4682  if (Depth >= MaxRecursionDepth)
4683  return false; // Limit search depth.
4684 
4685  if (isIntOrFPConstant(Op))
4686  return true;
4687 
4688  switch (Opcode) {
4689  case ISD::VALUETYPE:
4690  case ISD::FrameIndex:
4691  case ISD::TargetFrameIndex:
4692  return true;
4693 
4694  case ISD::UNDEF:
4695  return PoisonOnly;
4696 
4697  case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR:
4698  // NOTE: BUILD_VECTOR has implicit truncation of wider scalar elements -
4699  // this shouldn't affect the result.
4700  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Op.getNumOperands(); i < e; ++i) {
4701  if (!DemandedElts[i])
4702  continue;
4703  if (!isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(Op.getOperand(i), PoisonOnly,
4704  Depth + 1))
4705  return false;
4706  }
4707  return true;
4708 
4709  // TODO: Search for noundef attributes from library functions.
4710 
4711  // TODO: Pointers dereferenced by ISD::LOAD/STORE ops are noundef.
4712 
4713  default:
4714  // Allow the target to implement this method for its nodes.
4715  if (Opcode >= ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END || Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN ||
4716  Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN || Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID)
4717  return TLI->isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoisonForTargetNode(
4718  Op, DemandedElts, *this, PoisonOnly, Depth);
4719  break;
4720  }
4721 
4722  // If Op can't create undef/poison and none of its operands are undef/poison
4723  // then Op is never undef/poison.
4724  // NOTE: TargetNodes should handle this in themselves in
4725  // isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoisonForTargetNode.
4726  return !canCreateUndefOrPoison(Op, PoisonOnly, /*ConsiderFlags*/ true,
4727  Depth) &&
4728  all_of(Op->ops(), [&](SDValue V) {
4729  return isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(V, PoisonOnly, Depth + 1);
4730  });
4731 }
4732 
4733 bool SelectionDAG::canCreateUndefOrPoison(SDValue Op, bool PoisonOnly,
4734  bool ConsiderFlags,
4735  unsigned Depth) const {
4736  // TODO: Assume we don't know anything for now.
4737  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
4738  if (VT.isScalableVector())
4739  return true;
4740 
4741  APInt DemandedElts = VT.isVector()
4742  ? APInt::getAllOnes(VT.getVectorNumElements())
4743  : APInt(1, 1);
4744  return canCreateUndefOrPoison(Op, DemandedElts, PoisonOnly, ConsiderFlags,
4745  Depth);
4746 }
4747 
4748 bool SelectionDAG::canCreateUndefOrPoison(SDValue Op, const APInt &DemandedElts,
4749  bool PoisonOnly, bool ConsiderFlags,
4750  unsigned Depth) const {
4751  // TODO: Assume we don't know anything for now.
4752  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
4753  if (VT.isScalableVector())
4754  return true;
4755 
4756  unsigned Opcode = Op.getOpcode();
4757  switch (Opcode) {
4758  case ISD::AssertSext:
4759  case ISD::AssertZext:
4760  case ISD::FREEZE:
4761  case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS:
4762  case ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR:
4763  case ISD::AND:
4764  case ISD::OR:
4765  case ISD::XOR:
4766  case ISD::ROTL:
4767  case ISD::ROTR:
4768  case ISD::FSHL:
4769  case ISD::FSHR:
4770  case ISD::BSWAP:
4771  case ISD::CTPOP:
4772  case ISD::BITREVERSE:
4773  case ISD::PARITY:
4774  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
4775  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
4776  case ISD::TRUNCATE:
4777  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG:
4778  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
4779  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
4780  case ISD::BITCAST:
4781  case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR:
4782  case ISD::BUILD_PAIR:
4783  return false;
4784 
4785  case ISD::ADD:
4786  case ISD::SUB:
4787  case ISD::MUL:
4788  // Matches hasPoisonGeneratingFlags().
4789  return ConsiderFlags && (Op->getFlags().hasNoSignedWrap() ||
4790  Op->getFlags().hasNoUnsignedWrap());
4791 
4792  case ISD::SHL:
4793  // If the max shift amount isn't in range, then the shift can create poison.
4794  if (!getValidMaximumShiftAmountConstant(Op, DemandedElts))
4795  return true;
4796 
4797  // Matches hasPoisonGeneratingFlags().
4798  return ConsiderFlags && (Op->getFlags().hasNoSignedWrap() ||
4799  Op->getFlags().hasNoUnsignedWrap());
4800 
4801  default:
4802  // Allow the target to implement this method for its nodes.
4803  if (Opcode >= ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END || Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN ||
4804  Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN || Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID)
4805  return TLI->canCreateUndefOrPoisonForTargetNode(
4806  Op, DemandedElts, *this, PoisonOnly, ConsiderFlags, Depth);
4807  break;
4808  }
4809 
4810  // Be conservative and return true.
4811  return true;
4812 }
4813 
4814 bool SelectionDAG::isBaseWithConstantOffset(SDValue Op) const {
4815  if ((Op.getOpcode() != ISD::ADD && Op.getOpcode() != ISD::OR) ||
4816  !isa<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1)))
4817  return false;
4818 
4819  if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::OR &&
4820  !MaskedValueIsZero(Op.getOperand(0), Op.getConstantOperandAPInt(1)))
4821  return false;
4822 
4823  return true;
4824 }
4825 
4826 bool SelectionDAG::isKnownNeverNaN(SDValue Op, bool SNaN, unsigned Depth) const {
4827  // If we're told that NaNs won't happen, assume they won't.
4828  if (getTarget().Options.NoNaNsFPMath || Op->getFlags().hasNoNaNs())
4829  return true;
4830 
4831  if (Depth >= MaxRecursionDepth)
4832  return false; // Limit search depth.
4833 
4834  // If the value is a constant, we can obviously see if it is a NaN or not.
4835  if (const ConstantFPSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op)) {
4836  return !C->getValueAPF().isNaN() ||
4837  (SNaN && !C->getValueAPF().isSignaling());
4838  }
4839 
4840  unsigned Opcode = Op.getOpcode();
4841  switch (Opcode) {
4842  case ISD::FADD:
4843  case ISD::FSUB:
4844  case ISD::FMUL:
4845  case ISD::FDIV:
4846  case ISD::FREM:
4847  case ISD::FSIN:
4848  case ISD::FCOS:
4849  case ISD::FMA:
4850  case ISD::FMAD: {
4851  if (SNaN)
4852  return true;
4853  // TODO: Need isKnownNeverInfinity
4854  return false;
4855  }
4856  case ISD::FCANONICALIZE:
4857  case ISD::FEXP:
4858  case ISD::FEXP2:
4859  case ISD::FTRUNC:
4860  case ISD::FFLOOR:
4861  case ISD::FCEIL:
4862  case ISD::FROUND:
4863  case ISD::FROUNDEVEN:
4864  case ISD::FRINT:
4865  case ISD::FNEARBYINT: {
4866  if (SNaN)
4867  return true;
4868  return isKnownNeverNaN(Op.getOperand(0), SNaN, Depth + 1);
4869  }
4870  case ISD::FABS:
4871  case ISD::FNEG:
4872  case ISD::FCOPYSIGN: {
4873  return isKnownNeverNaN(Op.getOperand(0), SNaN, Depth + 1);
4874  }
4875  case ISD::SELECT:
4876  return isKnownNeverNaN(Op.getOperand(1), SNaN, Depth + 1) &&
4877  isKnownNeverNaN(Op.getOperand(2), SNaN, Depth + 1);
4878  case ISD::FP_EXTEND:
4879  case ISD::FP_ROUND: {
4880  if (SNaN)
4881  return true;
4882  return isKnownNeverNaN(Op.getOperand(0), SNaN, Depth + 1);
4883  }
4884  case ISD::SINT_TO_FP:
4885  case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
4886  return true;
4887  case ISD::FSQRT: // Need is known positive
4888  case ISD::FLOG:
4889  case ISD::FLOG2:
4890  case ISD::FLOG10:
4891  case ISD::FPOWI:
4892  case ISD::FPOW: {
4893  if (SNaN)
4894  return true;
4895  // TODO: Refine on operand
4896  return false;
4897  }
4898  case ISD::FMINNUM:
4899  case ISD::FMAXNUM: {
4900  // Only one needs to be known not-nan, since it will be returned if the
4901  // other ends up being one.
4902  return isKnownNeverNaN(Op.getOperand(0), SNaN, Depth + 1) ||
4903  isKnownNeverNaN(Op.getOperand(1), SNaN, Depth + 1);
4904  }
4905  case ISD::FMINNUM_IEEE:
4906  case ISD::FMAXNUM_IEEE: {
4907  if (SNaN)
4908  return true;
4909  // This can return a NaN if either operand is an sNaN, or if both operands
4910  // are NaN.
4911  return (isKnownNeverNaN(Op.getOperand(0), false, Depth + 1) &&
4912  isKnownNeverSNaN(Op.getOperand(1), Depth + 1)) ||
4913  (isKnownNeverNaN(Op.getOperand(1), false, Depth + 1) &&
4914  isKnownNeverSNaN(Op.getOperand(0), Depth + 1));
4915  }
4916  case ISD::FMINIMUM:
4917  case ISD::FMAXIMUM: {
4918  // TODO: Does this quiet or return the origina NaN as-is?
4919  return isKnownNeverNaN(Op.getOperand(0), SNaN, Depth + 1) &&
4920  isKnownNeverNaN(Op.getOperand(1), SNaN, Depth + 1);
4921  }
4922  case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT: {
4923  return isKnownNeverNaN(Op.getOperand(0), SNaN, Depth + 1);
4924  }
4925  case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: {
4926  for (const SDValue &Opnd : Op->ops())
4927  if (!isKnownNeverNaN(Opnd, SNaN, Depth + 1))
4928  return false;
4929  return true;
4930  }
4931  default:
4932  if (Opcode >= ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END ||
4933  Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN ||
4934  Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN ||
4935  Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID) {
4936  return TLI->isKnownNeverNaNForTargetNode(Op, *this, SNaN, Depth);
4937  }
4938 
4939  return false;
