4940  }
4941 }
4942 
4943 bool SelectionDAG::isKnownNeverZeroFloat(SDValue Op) const {
4944  assert(Op.getValueType().isFloatingPoint() &&
4945  "Floating point type expected");
4946 
4947  // If the value is a constant, we can obviously see if it is a zero or not.
4948  if (const ConstantFPSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op))
4949  return !C->isZero();
4950 
4951  // Return false if we find any zero in a vector.
4952  if (Op->getOpcode() == ISD::BUILD_VECTOR ||
4953  Op->getOpcode() == ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR) {
4954  for (const SDValue &OpVal : Op->op_values()) {
4955  if (OpVal.isUndef())
4956  return false;
4957  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(OpVal))
4958  if (C->isZero())
4959  return false;
4960  }
4961  return true;
4962  }
4963  return false;
4964 }
4965 
4966 bool SelectionDAG::isKnownNeverZero(SDValue Op) const {
4967  assert(!Op.getValueType().isFloatingPoint() &&
4968  "Floating point types unsupported - use isKnownNeverZeroFloat");
4969 
4970  // If the value is a constant, we can obviously see if it is a zero or not.
4971  if (ISD::matchUnaryPredicate(Op,
4972  [](ConstantSDNode *C) { return !C->isZero(); }))
4973  return true;
4974 
4975  // TODO: Recognize more cases here.
4976  switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
4977  default: break;
4978  case ISD::OR:
4979  if (isKnownNeverZero(Op.getOperand(1)) ||
4980  isKnownNeverZero(Op.getOperand(0)))
4981  return true;
4982  break;
4983  }
4984 
4985  return false;
4986 }
4987 
4988 bool SelectionDAG::isEqualTo(SDValue A, SDValue B) const {
4989  // Check the obvious case.
4990  if (A == B) return true;
4991 
4992  // For for negative and positive zero.
4993  if (const ConstantFPSDNode *CA = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(A))
4994  if (const ConstantFPSDNode *CB = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(B))
4995  if (CA->isZero() && CB->isZero()) return true;
4996 
4997  // Otherwise they may not be equal.
4998  return false;
4999 }
5000 
5001 // Only bits set in Mask must be negated, other bits may be arbitrary.
5002 SDValue llvm::getBitwiseNotOperand(SDValue V, SDValue Mask, bool AllowUndefs) {
5003  if (isBitwiseNot(V, AllowUndefs))
5004  return V.getOperand(0);
5005 
5006  // Handle any_extend (not (truncate X)) pattern, where Mask only sets
5007  // bits in the non-extended part.
5008  ConstantSDNode *MaskC = isConstOrConstSplat(Mask);
5009  if (!MaskC || V.getOpcode() != ISD::ANY_EXTEND)
5010  return SDValue();
5011  SDValue ExtArg = V.getOperand(0);
5012  if (ExtArg.getScalarValueSizeInBits() >=
5013  MaskC->getAPIntValue().getActiveBits() &&
5014  isBitwiseNot(ExtArg, AllowUndefs) &&
5015  ExtArg.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE &&
5016  ExtArg.getOperand(0).getOperand(0).getValueType() == V.getValueType())
5017  return ExtArg.getOperand(0).getOperand(0);
5018  return SDValue();
5019 }
5020 
5021 static bool haveNoCommonBitsSetCommutative(SDValue A, SDValue B) {
5022  // Match masked merge pattern (X & ~M) op (Y & M)
5023  // Including degenerate case (X & ~M) op M
5024  auto MatchNoCommonBitsPattern = [&](SDValue Not, SDValue Mask,
5025  SDValue Other) {
5026  if (SDValue NotOperand =
5027  getBitwiseNotOperand(Not, Mask, /* AllowUndefs */ true)) {
5028  if (Other == NotOperand)
5029  return true;
5030  if (Other->getOpcode() == ISD::AND)
5031  return NotOperand == Other->getOperand(0) ||
5032  NotOperand == Other->getOperand(1);
5033  }
5034  return false;
5035  };
5036  if (A->getOpcode() == ISD::AND)
5037  return MatchNoCommonBitsPattern(A->getOperand(0), A->getOperand(1), B) ||
5038  MatchNoCommonBitsPattern(A->getOperand(1), A->getOperand(0), B);
5039  return false;
5040 }
5041 
5042 // FIXME: unify with llvm::haveNoCommonBitsSet.
5043 bool SelectionDAG::haveNoCommonBitsSet(SDValue A, SDValue B) const {
5044  assert(A.getValueType() == B.getValueType() &&
5045  "Values must have the same type");
5046  if (haveNoCommonBitsSetCommutative(A, B) ||
5047  haveNoCommonBitsSetCommutative(B, A))
5048  return true;
5049  return KnownBits::haveNoCommonBitsSet(computeKnownBits(A),
5050  computeKnownBits(B));
5051 }

5053 static SDValue FoldSTEP_VECTOR(const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT, SDValue Step,
5054  SelectionDAG &DAG) {
5055  if (cast<ConstantSDNode>(Step)->isZero())
5056  return DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT);
5057 
5058  return SDValue();
5059 }
5060 
5061 static SDValue FoldBUILD_VECTOR(const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
5062  ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops,
5063  SelectionDAG &DAG) {
5064  int NumOps = Ops.size();
5065  assert(NumOps != 0 && "Can't build an empty vector!");
5066  assert(!VT.isScalableVector() &&
5067  "BUILD_VECTOR cannot be used with scalable types");
5068  assert(VT.getVectorNumElements() == (unsigned)NumOps &&
5069  "Incorrect element count in BUILD_VECTOR!");
5070 
5071  // BUILD_VECTOR of UNDEFs is UNDEF.
5072  if (llvm::all_of(Ops, [](SDValue Op) { return Op.isUndef(); }))
5073  return DAG.getUNDEF(VT);
5074 
5075  // BUILD_VECTOR of seq extract/insert from the same vector + type is Identity.
5076  SDValue IdentitySrc;
5077  bool IsIdentity = true;
5078  for (int i = 0; i != NumOps; ++i) {
5079  if (Ops[i].getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT ||
5080  Ops[i].getOperand(0).getValueType() != VT ||
5081  (IdentitySrc && Ops[i].getOperand(0) != IdentitySrc) ||
5082  !isa<ConstantSDNode>(Ops[i].getOperand(1)) ||
5083  cast<ConstantSDNode>(Ops[i].getOperand(1))->getAPIntValue() != i) {
5084  IsIdentity = false;
5085  break;
5086  }
5087  IdentitySrc = Ops[i].getOperand(0);
5088  }
5089  if (IsIdentity)
5090  return IdentitySrc;
5091 
5092  return SDValue();
5093 }
5094 
5095 /// Try to simplify vector concatenation to an input value, undef, or build
5096 /// vector.
5097 static SDValue foldCONCAT_VECTORS(const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
5098  ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops,
5099  SelectionDAG &DAG) {
5100  assert(!Ops.empty() && "Can't concatenate an empty list of vectors!");
5101  assert(llvm::all_of(Ops,
5102  [Ops](SDValue Op) {
5103  return Ops[0].getValueType() == Op.getValueType();
5104  }) &&
5105  "Concatenation of vectors with inconsistent value types!");
5106  assert((Ops[0].getValueType().getVectorElementCount() * Ops.size()) ==
5107  VT.getVectorElementCount() &&
5108  "Incorrect element count in vector concatenation!");
5109 
5110  if (Ops.size() == 1)
5111  return Ops[0];
5112 
5113  // Concat of UNDEFs is UNDEF.
5114  if (llvm::all_of(Ops, [](SDValue Op) { return Op.isUndef(); }))
5115  return DAG.getUNDEF(VT);
5116 
5117  // Scan the operands and look for extract operations from a single source
5118  // that correspond to insertion at the same location via this concatenation:
5119  // concat (extract X, 0*subvec_elts), (extract X, 1*subvec_elts), ...
5120  SDValue IdentitySrc;
5121  bool IsIdentity = true;
5122  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Ops.size(); i != e; ++i) {
5123  SDValue Op = Ops[i];
5124  unsigned IdentityIndex = i * Op.getValueType().getVectorMinNumElements();
5125  if (Op.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR ||
5126  Op.getOperand(0).getValueType() != VT ||
5127  (IdentitySrc && Op.getOperand(0) != IdentitySrc) ||
5128  Op.getConstantOperandVal(1) != IdentityIndex) {
5129  IsIdentity = false;
5130  break;
5131  }
5132  assert((!IdentitySrc || IdentitySrc == Op.getOperand(0)) &&
5133  "Unexpected identity source vector for concat of extracts");
5134  IdentitySrc = Op.getOperand(0);
5135  }
5136  if (IsIdentity) {
5137  assert(IdentitySrc && "Failed to set source vector of extracts");
5138  return IdentitySrc;
5139  }
5140 
5141  // The code below this point is only designed to work for fixed width
5142  // vectors, so we bail out for now.
5143  if (VT.isScalableVector())
5144  return SDValue();
5145 
5146  // A CONCAT_VECTOR with all UNDEF/BUILD_VECTOR operands can be
5147  // simplified to one big BUILD_VECTOR.
5148  // FIXME: Add support for SCALAR_TO_VECTOR as well.
5149  EVT SVT = VT.getScalarType();
5150  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Elts;
5151  for (SDValue Op : Ops) {
5152  EVT OpVT = Op.getValueType();
5153  if (Op.isUndef())
5154  Elts.append(OpVT.getVectorNumElements(), DAG.getUNDEF(SVT));
5155  else if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::BUILD_VECTOR)
5156  Elts.append(Op->op_begin(), Op->op_end());
5157  else
5158  return SDValue();
5159  }
5160 
5161  // BUILD_VECTOR requires all inputs to be of the same type, find the
5162  // maximum type and extend them all.
5163  for (SDValue Op : Elts)
5164  SVT = (SVT.bitsLT(Op.getValueType()) ? Op.getValueType() : SVT);
5165 
5166  if (SVT.bitsGT(VT.getScalarType())) {
5167  for (SDValue &Op : Elts) {
5168  if (Op.isUndef())
5169  Op = DAG.getUNDEF(SVT);
5170  else
5171  Op = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo().isZExtFree(Op.getValueType(), SVT)
5172  ? DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Op, DL, SVT)
5173  : DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(Op, DL, SVT);
5174  }
5175  }
5176 
5177  SDValue V = DAG.getBuildVector(VT, DL, Elts);
5178  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "New node fold concat vectors: ", &DAG);
5179  return V;
5180 }
5181 
5182 /// Gets or creates the specified node.
5183 SDValue SelectionDAG::getNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT) {
5184  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5185  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opcode, getVTList(VT), std::nullopt);
5186  void *IP = nullptr;
5187  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, DL, IP))
5188  return SDValue(E, 0);
5189 
5190  auto *N = newSDNode<SDNode>(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(), DL.getDebugLoc(),
5191  getVTList(VT));
5192  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
5193 
5194  InsertNode(N);
5195  SDValue V = SDValue(N, 0);
5196  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
5197  return V;
5198 }
5199 
5200 SDValue SelectionDAG::getNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
5201  SDValue Operand) {
5202  SDNodeFlags Flags;
5203  if (Inserter)
5204  Flags = Inserter->getFlags();
5205  return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, Operand, Flags);
5206 }
5207 
5208 SDValue SelectionDAG::getNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
5209  SDValue Operand, const SDNodeFlags Flags) {
5210  assert(Operand.getOpcode() != ISD::DELETED_NODE &&
5211  "Operand is DELETED_NODE!");
5212  // Constant fold unary operations with an integer constant operand. Even
5213  // opaque constant will be folded, because the folding of unary operations
5214  // doesn't create new constants with different values. Nevertheless, the
5215  // opaque flag is preserved during folding to prevent future folding with
5216  // other constants.
5217  if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Operand)) {
5218  const APInt &Val = C->getAPIntValue();
5219  switch (Opcode) {
5220  default: break;
5221  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
5222  return getConstant(Val.sextOrTrunc(VT.getSizeInBits()), DL, VT,
5223  C->isTargetOpcode(), C->isOpaque());
5224  case ISD::TRUNCATE:
5225  if (C->isOpaque())
5226  break;
5227  [[fallthrough]];
5228  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
5229  return getConstant(Val.zextOrTrunc(VT.getSizeInBits()), DL, VT,
5230  C->isTargetOpcode(), C->isOpaque());
5231  case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
5232  // Some targets like RISCV prefer to sign extend some types.
5233  if (TLI->isSExtCheaperThanZExt(Operand.getValueType(), VT))
5234  return getConstant(Val.sextOrTrunc(VT.getSizeInBits()), DL, VT,
5235  C->isTargetOpcode(), C->isOpaque());
5236  return getConstant(Val.zextOrTrunc(VT.getSizeInBits()), DL, VT,
5237  C->isTargetOpcode(), C->isOpaque());
5238  case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
5239  case ISD::SINT_TO_FP: {
5240  APFloat apf(EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT),
5241  APInt::getZero(VT.getSizeInBits()));
5242  (void)apf.convertFromAPInt(Val,
5243  Opcode==ISD::SINT_TO_FP,
5244  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
5245  return getConstantFP(apf, DL, VT);
5246  }
5247  case ISD::BITCAST:
5248  if (VT == MVT::f16 && C->getValueType(0) == MVT::i16)
5249  return getConstantFP(APFloat(APFloat::IEEEhalf(), Val), DL, VT);
5250  if (VT == MVT::f32 && C->getValueType(0) == MVT::i32)
5251  return getConstantFP(APFloat(APFloat::IEEEsingle(), Val), DL, VT);
5252  if (VT == MVT::f64 && C->getValueType(0) == MVT::i64)
5253  return getConstantFP(APFloat(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), Val), DL, VT);
5254  if (VT == MVT::f128 && C->getValueType(0) == MVT::i128)
5255  return getConstantFP(APFloat(APFloat::IEEEquad(), Val), DL, VT);
5256  break;
5257  case ISD::ABS:
5258  return getConstant(Val.abs(), DL, VT, C->isTargetOpcode(),
5259  C->isOpaque());
5260  case ISD::BITREVERSE:
5261  return getConstant(Val.reverseBits(), DL, VT, C->isTargetOpcode(),
5262  C->isOpaque());
5263  case ISD::BSWAP:
5264  return getConstant(Val.byteSwap(), DL, VT, C->isTargetOpcode(),
5265  C->isOpaque());
5266  case ISD::CTPOP:
5267  return getConstant(Val.countPopulation(), DL, VT, C->isTargetOpcode(),
5268  C->isOpaque());
5269  case ISD::CTLZ:
5270  case ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
5271  return getConstant(Val.countLeadingZeros(), DL, VT, C->isTargetOpcode(),
5272  C->isOpaque());
5273  case ISD::CTTZ:
5274  case ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
5275  return getConstant(Val.countTrailingZeros(), DL, VT, C->isTargetOpcode(),
5276  C->isOpaque());
5277  case ISD::FP16_TO_FP:
5278  case ISD::BF16_TO_FP: {
5279  bool Ignored;
5280  APFloat FPV(Opcode == ISD::FP16_TO_FP ? APFloat::IEEEhalf()
5281  : APFloat::BFloat(),
5282  (Val.getBitWidth() == 16) ? Val : Val.trunc(16));
5283 
5284  // This can return overflow, underflow, or inexact; we don't care.
5285  // FIXME need to be more flexible about rounding mode.
5286  (void)FPV.convert(EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT),
5287  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &Ignored);
5288  return getConstantFP(FPV, DL, VT);
5289  }
5290  case ISD::STEP_VECTOR: {
5291  if (SDValue V = FoldSTEP_VECTOR(DL, VT, Operand, *this))
5292  return V;
5293  break;
5294  }
5295  }
5296  }
5297 
5298  // Constant fold unary operations with a floating point constant operand.
5299  if (ConstantFPSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Operand)) {
5300  APFloat V = C->getValueAPF(); // make copy
5301  switch (Opcode) {
5302  case ISD::FNEG:
5303  V.changeSign();
5304  return getConstantFP(V, DL, VT);
5305  case ISD::FABS:
5306  V.clearSign();
5307  return getConstantFP(V, DL, VT);
5308  case ISD::FCEIL: {
5309  APFloat::opStatus fs = V.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmTowardPositive);
5310  if (fs == APFloat::opOK || fs == APFloat::opInexact)
5311  return getConstantFP(V, DL, VT);
5312  break;
5313  }
5314  case ISD::FTRUNC: {
5315  APFloat::opStatus fs = V.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmTowardZero);
5316  if (fs == APFloat::opOK || fs == APFloat::opInexact)
5317  return getConstantFP(V, DL, VT);
5318  break;
5319  }
5320  case ISD::FFLOOR: {
5321  APFloat::opStatus fs = V.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmTowardNegative);
5322  if (fs == APFloat::opOK || fs == APFloat::opInexact)
5323  return getConstantFP(V, DL, VT);
5324  break;
5325  }
5326  case ISD::FP_EXTEND: {
5327  bool ignored;
5328  // This can return overflow, underflow, or inexact; we don't care.
5329  // FIXME need to be more flexible about rounding mode.
5330  (void)V.convert(EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT),
5331  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &ignored);
5332  return getConstantFP(V, DL, VT);
5333  }
5334  case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
5335  case ISD::FP_TO_UINT: {
5336  bool ignored;
5337  APSInt IntVal(VT.getSizeInBits(), Opcode == ISD::FP_TO_UINT);
5338  // FIXME need to be more flexible about rounding mode.
5339  APFloat::opStatus s =
5340  V.convertToInteger(IntVal, APFloat::rmTowardZero, &ignored);
5341  if (s == APFloat::opInvalidOp) // inexact is OK, in fact usual
5342  break;
5343  return getConstant(IntVal, DL, VT);
5344  }
5345  case ISD::BITCAST:
5346  if (VT == MVT::i16 && C->getValueType(0) == MVT::f16)
5347  return getConstant((uint16_t)V.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue(), DL, VT);
5348  if (VT == MVT::i16 && C->getValueType(0) == MVT::bf16)
5349  return getConstant((uint16_t)V.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue(), DL, VT);
5350  if (VT == MVT::i32 && C->getValueType(0) == MVT::f32)
5351  return getConstant((uint32_t)V.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue(), DL, VT);
5352  if (VT == MVT::i64 && C->getValueType(0) == MVT::f64)
5353  return getConstant(V.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue(), DL, VT);
5354  break;
5355  case ISD::FP_TO_FP16:
5356  case ISD::FP_TO_BF16: {
5357  bool Ignored;
5358  // This can return overflow, underflow, or inexact; we don't care.
5359  // FIXME need to be more flexible about rounding mode.
5360  (void)V.convert(Opcode == ISD::FP_TO_FP16 ? APFloat::IEEEhalf()
5361  : APFloat::BFloat(),
5362  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &Ignored);
5363  return getConstant(V.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue(), DL, VT);
5364  }
5365  }
5366  }
5367 
5368  // Constant fold unary operations with a vector integer or float operand.
5369  switch (Opcode) {
5370  default:
5371  // FIXME: Entirely reasonable to perform folding of other unary
5372  // operations here as the need arises.
5373  break;
5374  case ISD::FNEG:
5375  case ISD::FABS:
5376  case ISD::FCEIL:
5377  case ISD::FTRUNC:
5378  case ISD::FFLOOR:
5379  case ISD::FP_EXTEND:
5380  case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
5381  case ISD::FP_TO_UINT:
5382  case ISD::TRUNCATE:
5383  case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
5384  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
5385  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
5386  case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
5387  case ISD::SINT_TO_FP:
5388  case ISD::ABS:
5389  case ISD::BITREVERSE:
5390  case ISD::BSWAP:
5391  case ISD::CTLZ:
5392  case ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
5393  case ISD::CTTZ:
5394  case ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
5395  case ISD::CTPOP: {
5396  SDValue Ops = {Operand};
5397  if (SDValue Fold = FoldConstantArithmetic(Opcode, DL, VT, Ops))
5398  return Fold;
5399  }
5400  }
5401 
5402  unsigned OpOpcode = Operand.getNode()->getOpcode();
5403  switch (Opcode) {
5404  case ISD::STEP_VECTOR:
5405  assert(VT.isScalableVector() &&
5406  "STEP_VECTOR can only be used with scalable types");
5407  assert(OpOpcode == ISD::TargetConstant &&
5408  VT.getVectorElementType() == Operand.getValueType() &&
5409  "Unexpected step operand");
5410  break;
5411  case ISD::FREEZE:
5412  assert(VT == Operand.getValueType() && "Unexpected VT!");
5413  if (isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(Operand, /*PoisonOnly*/ false,
5414  /*Depth*/ 1))
5415  return Operand;
5416  break;
5417  case ISD::TokenFactor:
5418  case ISD::MERGE_VALUES:
5419  case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS:
5420  return Operand; // Factor, merge or concat of one node? No need.
5421  case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: {
5422  // Attempt to simplify BUILD_VECTOR.
5423  SDValue Ops[] = {Operand};
5424  if (SDValue V = FoldBUILD_VECTOR(DL, VT, Ops, *this))
5425  return V;
5426  break;
5427  }
5428  case ISD::FP_ROUND: llvm_unreachable("Invalid method to make FP_ROUND node");
5429  case ISD::FP_EXTEND:
5430  assert(VT.isFloatingPoint() &&
5431  Operand.getValueType().isFloatingPoint() && "Invalid FP cast!");
5432  if (Operand.getValueType() == VT) return Operand; // noop conversion.
5433  assert((!VT.isVector() ||
5434  VT.getVectorElementCount() ==
5435  Operand.getValueType().getVectorElementCount()) &&
5436  "Vector element count mismatch!");
5437  assert(Operand.getValueType().bitsLT(VT) &&
5438  "Invalid fpext node, dst < src!");
5439  if (Operand.isUndef())
5440  return getUNDEF(VT);
5441  break;
5442  case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
5443  case ISD::FP_TO_UINT:
5444  if (Operand.isUndef())
5445  return getUNDEF(VT);
5446  break;
5447  case ISD::SINT_TO_FP:
5448  case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
5449  // [us]itofp(undef) = 0, because the result value is bounded.
5450  if (Operand.isUndef())
5451  return getConstantFP(0.0, DL, VT);
5452  break;
5453  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
5454  assert(VT.isInteger() && Operand.getValueType().isInteger() &&
5455  "Invalid SIGN_EXTEND!");
5456  assert(VT.isVector() == Operand.getValueType().isVector() &&
5457  "SIGN_EXTEND result type type should be vector iff the operand "
5458  "type is vector!");
5459  if (Operand.getValueType() == VT) return Operand; // noop extension
5460  assert((!VT.isVector() ||
5461  VT.getVectorElementCount() ==
5462  Operand.getValueType().getVectorElementCount()) &&
5463  "Vector element count mismatch!");
5464  assert(Operand.getValueType().bitsLT(VT) &&
5465  "Invalid sext node, dst < src!");
5466  if (OpOpcode == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND || OpOpcode == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND)
5467  return getNode(OpOpcode, DL, VT, Operand.getOperand(0));
5468  if (OpOpcode == ISD::UNDEF)
5469  // sext(undef) = 0, because the top bits will all be the same.
5470  return getConstant(0, DL, VT);
5471  break;
5472  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
5473  assert(VT.isInteger() && Operand.getValueType().isInteger() &&
5474  "Invalid ZERO_EXTEND!");
5475  assert(VT.isVector() == Operand.getValueType().isVector() &&
5476  "ZERO_EXTEND result type type should be vector iff the operand "
5477  "type is vector!");
5478  if (Operand.getValueType() == VT) return Operand; // noop extension
5479  assert((!VT.isVector() ||
5480  VT.getVectorElementCount() ==
5481  Operand.getValueType().getVectorElementCount()) &&
5482  "Vector element count mismatch!");
5483  assert(Operand.getValueType().bitsLT(VT) &&
5484  "Invalid zext node, dst < src!");
5485  if (OpOpcode == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND) // (zext (zext x)) -> (zext x)
5486  return getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, VT, Operand.getOperand(0));
5487  if (OpOpcode == ISD::UNDEF)
5488  // zext(undef) = 0, because the top bits will be zero.
5489  return getConstant(0, DL, VT);
5490  break;
5491  case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
5492  assert(VT.isInteger() && Operand.getValueType().isInteger() &&
5493  "Invalid ANY_EXTEND!");
5494  assert(VT.isVector() == Operand.getValueType().isVector() &&
5495  "ANY_EXTEND result type type should be vector iff the operand "
5496  "type is vector!");
5497  if (Operand.getValueType() == VT) return Operand; // noop extension
5498  assert((!VT.isVector() ||
5499  VT.getVectorElementCount() ==
5500  Operand.getValueType().getVectorElementCount()) &&
5501  "Vector element count mismatch!");
5502  assert(Operand.getValueType().bitsLT(VT) &&
5503  "Invalid anyext node, dst < src!");
5504 
5505  if (OpOpcode == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND || OpOpcode == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND ||
5506  OpOpcode == ISD::ANY_EXTEND)
5507  // (ext (zext x)) -> (zext x) and (ext (sext x)) -> (sext x)
5508  return getNode(OpOpcode, DL, VT, Operand.getOperand(0));
5509  if (OpOpcode == ISD::UNDEF)
5510  return getUNDEF(VT);
5511 
5512  // (ext (trunc x)) -> x
5513  if (OpOpcode == ISD::TRUNCATE) {
5514  SDValue OpOp = Operand.getOperand(0);
5515  if (OpOp.getValueType() == VT) {
5516  transferDbgValues(Operand, OpOp);
5517  return OpOp;
5518  }
5519  }
5520  break;
5521  case ISD::TRUNCATE:
5522  assert(VT.isInteger() && Operand.getValueType().isInteger() &&
5523  "Invalid TRUNCATE!");
5524  assert(VT.isVector() == Operand.getValueType().isVector() &&
5525  "TRUNCATE result type type should be vector iff the operand "
5526  "type is vector!");
5527  if (Operand.getValueType() == VT) return Operand; // noop truncate
5528  assert((!VT.isVector() ||
5529  VT.getVectorElementCount() ==
5530  Operand.getValueType().getVectorElementCount()) &&
5531  "Vector element count mismatch!");
5532  assert(Operand.getValueType().bitsGT(VT) &&
5533  "Invalid truncate node, src < dst!");
5534  if (OpOpcode == ISD::TRUNCATE)
5535  return getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VT, Operand.getOperand(0));
5536  if (OpOpcode == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND || OpOpcode == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND ||
5537  OpOpcode == ISD::ANY_EXTEND) {
5538  // If the source is smaller than the dest, we still need an extend.
5539  if (Operand.getOperand(0).getValueType().getScalarType()
5540  .bitsLT(VT.getScalarType()))
5541  return getNode(OpOpcode, DL, VT, Operand.getOperand(0));
5542  if (Operand.getOperand(0).getValueType().bitsGT(VT))
5543  return getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VT, Operand.getOperand(0));
5544  return Operand.getOperand(0);
5545  }
5546  if (OpOpcode == ISD::UNDEF)
5547  return getUNDEF(VT);
5548  if (OpOpcode == ISD::VSCALE && !NewNodesMustHaveLegalTypes)
5549  return getVScale(DL, VT, Operand.getConstantOperandAPInt(0));
5550  break;
5551  case ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
5552  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
5553  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
5554  assert(VT.isVector() && "This DAG node is restricted to vector types.");
5555  assert(Operand.getValueType().bitsLE(VT) &&
5556  "The input must be the same size or smaller than the result.");
5557  assert(VT.getVectorMinNumElements() <
5558  Operand.getValueType().getVectorMinNumElements() &&
5559  "The destination vector type must have fewer lanes than the input.");
5560  break;
5561  case ISD::ABS:
5562  assert(VT.isInteger() && VT == Operand.getValueType() &&
5563  "Invalid ABS!");
5564  if (OpOpcode == ISD::UNDEF)
5565  return getConstant(0, DL, VT);
5566  break;
5567  case ISD::BSWAP:
5568  assert(VT.isInteger() && VT == Operand.getValueType() &&
5569  "Invalid BSWAP!");
5570  assert((VT.getScalarSizeInBits() % 16 == 0) &&
5571  "BSWAP types must be a multiple of 16 bits!");
5572  if (OpOpcode == ISD::UNDEF)
5573  return getUNDEF(VT);
5574  // bswap(bswap(X)) -> X.
5575  if (OpOpcode == ISD::BSWAP)
5576  return Operand.getOperand(0);
5577  break;
5578  case ISD::BITREVERSE:
5579  assert(VT.isInteger() && VT == Operand.getValueType() &&
5580  "Invalid BITREVERSE!");
5581  if (OpOpcode == ISD::UNDEF)
5582  return getUNDEF(VT);
5583  break;
5584  case ISD::BITCAST:
5585  assert(VT.getSizeInBits() == Operand.getValueSizeInBits() &&
5586  "Cannot BITCAST between types of different sizes!");
5587  if (VT == Operand.getValueType()) return Operand; // noop conversion.
5588  if (OpOpcode == ISD::BITCAST) // bitconv(bitconv(x)) -> bitconv(x)
5589  return getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VT, Operand.getOperand(0));
5590  if (OpOpcode == ISD::UNDEF)
5591  return getUNDEF(VT);
5592  break;
5593  case ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR:
5594  assert(VT.isVector() && !Operand.getValueType().isVector() &&
5595  (VT.getVectorElementType() == Operand.getValueType() ||
5596  (VT.getVectorElementType().isInteger() &&
5597  Operand.getValueType().isInteger() &&
5598  VT.getVectorElementType().bitsLE(Operand.getValueType()))) &&
5599  "Illegal SCALAR_TO_VECTOR node!");
5600  if (OpOpcode == ISD::UNDEF)
5601  return getUNDEF(VT);
5602  // scalar_to_vector(extract_vector_elt V, 0) -> V, top bits are undefined.
5603  if (OpOpcode == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT &&
5604  isa<ConstantSDNode>(Operand.getOperand(1)) &&
5605  Operand.getConstantOperandVal(1) == 0 &&
5606  Operand.getOperand(0).getValueType() == VT)
5607  return Operand.getOperand(0);
5608  break;
5609  case ISD::FNEG:
5610  // Negation of an unknown bag of bits is still completely undefined.
5611  if (OpOpcode == ISD::UNDEF)
5612  return getUNDEF(VT);
5613 
5614  if (OpOpcode == ISD::FNEG) // --X -> X
5615  return Operand.getOperand(0);
5616  break;
5617  case ISD::FABS:
5618  if (OpOpcode == ISD::FNEG) // abs(-X) -> abs(X)
5619  return getNode(ISD::FABS, DL, VT, Operand.getOperand(0));
5620  break;
5621  case ISD::VSCALE:
5622  assert(VT == Operand.getValueType() && "Unexpected VT!");
5623  break;
5624  case ISD::CTPOP:
5625  if (Operand.getValueType().getScalarType() == MVT::i1)
5626  return Operand;
5627  break;
5628  case ISD::CTLZ:
5629  case ISD::CTTZ:
5630  if (Operand.getValueType().getScalarType() == MVT::i1)
5631  return getNOT(DL, Operand, Operand.getValueType());
5632  break;
5633  case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD:
5634  if (Operand.getValueType().getScalarType() == MVT::i1)
5635  return getNode(ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR, DL, VT, Operand);
5636  break;
5637  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN:
5638  case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX:
5639  if (Operand.getValueType().getScalarType() == MVT::i1)
5640  return getNode(ISD::VECREDUCE_OR, DL, VT, Operand);
5641  break;
5642  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX:
5643  case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN:
5644  if (Operand.getValueType().getScalarType() == MVT::i1)
5645  return getNode(ISD::VECREDUCE_AND, DL, VT, Operand);
5646  break;
5647  }
5648 
5649  SDNode *N;
5650  SDVTList VTs = getVTList(VT);
5651  SDValue Ops[] = {Operand};
5652  if (VT != MVT::Glue) { // Don't CSE flag producing nodes
5653  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5654  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opcode, VTs, Ops);
5655  void *IP = nullptr;
5656  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, DL, IP)) {
5657  E->intersectFlagsWith(Flags);
5658  return SDValue(E, 0);
5659  }
5660 
5661  N = newSDNode<SDNode>(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(), DL.getDebugLoc(), VTs);
5662  N->setFlags(Flags);
5663  createOperands(N, Ops);
5664  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
5665  } else {
5666  N = newSDNode<SDNode>(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(), DL.getDebugLoc(), VTs);
5667  createOperands(N, Ops);
5668  }
5669 
5670  InsertNode(N);
5671  SDValue V = SDValue(N, 0);
5672  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
5673  return V;
5674 }
5675 
5676 static std::optional<APInt> FoldValue(unsigned Opcode, const APInt &C1,
5677  const APInt &C2) {
5678  switch (Opcode) {
5679  case ISD::ADD: return C1 + C2;
5680  case ISD::SUB: return C1 - C2;
5681  case ISD::MUL: return C1 * C2;
5682  case ISD::AND: return C1 & C2;
5683  case ISD::OR: return C1 | C2;
5684  case ISD::XOR: return C1 ^ C2;
5685  case ISD::SHL: return C1 << C2;
5686  case ISD::SRL: return C1.lshr(C2);
5687  case ISD::SRA: return C1.ashr(C2);
5688  case ISD::ROTL: return C1.rotl(C2);
5689  case ISD::ROTR: return C1.rotr(C2);
5690  case ISD::SMIN: return C1.sle(C2) ? C1 : C2;
5691  case ISD::SMAX: return C1.sge(C2) ? C1 : C2;
5692  case ISD::UMIN: return C1.ule(C2) ? C1 : C2;
5693  case ISD::UMAX: return C1.uge(C2) ? C1 : C2;
5694  case ISD::SADDSAT: return C1.sadd_sat(C2);
5695  case ISD::UADDSAT: return C1.uadd_sat(C2);
5696  case ISD::SSUBSAT: return C1.ssub_sat(C2);
5697  case ISD::USUBSAT: return C1.usub_sat(C2);
5698  case ISD::SSHLSAT: return C1.sshl_sat(C2);
5699  case ISD::USHLSAT: return C1.ushl_sat(C2);
5700  case ISD::UDIV:
5701  if (!C2.getBoolValue())
5702  break;
5703  return C1.udiv(C2);
5704  case ISD::UREM:
5705  if (!C2.getBoolValue())
5706  break;
5707  return C1.urem(C2);
5708  case ISD::SDIV:
5709  if (!C2.getBoolValue())
5710  break;
5711  return C1.sdiv(C2);
5712  case ISD::SREM:
5713  if (!C2.getBoolValue())
5714  break;
5715  return C1.srem(C2);
5716  case ISD::MULHS: {
5717  unsigned FullWidth = C1.getBitWidth() * 2;
5718  APInt C1Ext = C1.sext(FullWidth);
5719  APInt C2Ext = C2.sext(FullWidth);
5720  return (C1Ext * C2Ext).extractBits(C1.getBitWidth(), C1.getBitWidth());
5721  }
5722  case ISD::MULHU: {
5723  unsigned FullWidth = C1.getBitWidth() * 2;
5724  APInt C1Ext = C1.zext(FullWidth);
5725  APInt C2Ext = C2.zext(FullWidth);
5726  return (C1Ext * C2Ext).extractBits(C1.getBitWidth(), C1.getBitWidth());
5727  }
5728  case ISD::AVGFLOORS: {
5729  unsigned FullWidth = C1.getBitWidth() + 1;
5730  APInt C1Ext = C1.sext(FullWidth);
5731  APInt C2Ext = C2.sext(FullWidth);
5732  return (C1Ext + C2Ext).extractBits(C1.getBitWidth(), 1);
5733  }
5734  case ISD::AVGFLOORU: {
5735  unsigned FullWidth = C1.getBitWidth() + 1;
5736  APInt C1Ext = C1.zext(FullWidth);
5737  APInt C2Ext = C2.zext(FullWidth);
5738  return (C1Ext + C2Ext).extractBits(C1.getBitWidth(), 1);
5739  }
5740  case ISD::AVGCEILS: {
5741  unsigned FullWidth = C1.getBitWidth() + 1;
5742  APInt C1Ext = C1.sext(FullWidth);
5743  APInt C2Ext = C2.sext(FullWidth);
5744  return (C1Ext + C2Ext + 1).extractBits(C1.getBitWidth(), 1);
5745  }
5746  case ISD::AVGCEILU: {
5747  unsigned FullWidth = C1.getBitWidth() + 1;
5748  APInt C1Ext = C1.zext(FullWidth);
5749  APInt C2Ext = C2.zext(FullWidth);
5750  return (C1Ext + C2Ext + 1).extractBits(C1.getBitWidth(), 1);
5751  }
5752  case ISD::ABDS:
5753  return APIntOps::smax(C1, C2) - APIntOps::smin(C1, C2);
5754  case ISD::ABDU:
5755  return APIntOps::umax(C1, C2) - APIntOps::umin(C1, C2);
5756  }
5757  return std::nullopt;
5758 }
5759 
5760 // Handle constant folding with UNDEF.
5761 // TODO: Handle more cases.
5762 static std::optional<APInt> FoldValueWithUndef(unsigned Opcode, const APInt &C1,
5763  bool IsUndef1, const APInt &C2,
5764  bool IsUndef2) {
5765  if (!(IsUndef1 || IsUndef2))
5766  return FoldValue(Opcode, C1, C2);
5767 
5768  // Fold and(x, undef) -> 0
5769  // Fold mul(x, undef) -> 0
5770  if (Opcode == ISD::AND || Opcode == ISD::MUL)
5771  return APInt::getZero(C1.getBitWidth());
5772 
5773  return std::nullopt;
5774 }
5775 
5776 SDValue SelectionDAG::FoldSymbolOffset(unsigned Opcode, EVT VT,
5777  const GlobalAddressSDNode *GA,
5778  const SDNode *N2) {
5779  if (GA->getOpcode() != ISD::GlobalAddress)
5780  return SDValue();
5781  if (!TLI->isOffsetFoldingLegal(GA))
5782  return SDValue();
5783  auto *C2 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N2);
5784  if (!C2)
5785  return SDValue();
5786  int64_t Offset = C2->getSExtValue();
5787  switch (Opcode) {
5788  case ISD::ADD: break;
5789  case ISD::SUB: Offset = -uint64_t(Offset); break;
5790  default: return SDValue();
5791  }
5792  return getGlobalAddress(GA->getGlobal(), SDLoc(C2), VT,
5793  GA->getOffset() + uint64_t(Offset));
5794 }
5795 
5796 bool SelectionDAG::isUndef(unsigned Opcode, ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops) {
5797  switch (Opcode) {
5798  case ISD::SDIV:
5799  case ISD::UDIV:
5800  case ISD::SREM:
5801  case ISD::UREM: {
5802  // If a divisor is zero/undef or any element of a divisor vector is
5803  // zero/undef, the whole op is undef.
5804  assert(Ops.size() == 2 && "Div/rem should have 2 operands");
5805  SDValue Divisor = Ops[1];
5806  if (Divisor.isUndef() || isNullConstant(Divisor))
5807  return true;
5808 
5809  return ISD::isBuildVectorOfConstantSDNodes(Divisor.getNode()) &&
5810  llvm::any_of(Divisor->op_values(),
5811  [](SDValue V) { return V.isUndef() ||
5812  isNullConstant(V); });
5813  // TODO: Handle signed overflow.
5814  }
5815  // TODO: Handle oversized shifts.
5816  default:
5817  return false;
5818  }
5819 }
5820 
5821 SDValue SelectionDAG::FoldConstantArithmetic(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL,
5822  EVT VT, ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops) {
5823  // If the opcode is a target-specific ISD node, there's nothing we can
5824  // do here and the operand rules may not line up with the below, so
5825  // bail early.
5826  // We can't create a scalar CONCAT_VECTORS so skip it. It will break
5827  // for concats involving SPLAT_VECTOR. Concats of BUILD_VECTORS are handled by
5828  // foldCONCAT_VECTORS in getNode before this is called.
5829  if (Opcode >= ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END || Opcode == ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS)
5830  return SDValue();
5831 
5832  unsigned NumOps = Ops.size();
5833  if (NumOps == 0)
5834  return SDValue();
5835 
5836  if (isUndef(Opcode, Ops))
5837  return getUNDEF(VT);
5838 
5839  // Handle binops special cases.
5840  if (NumOps == 2) {
5841  if (SDValue CFP = foldConstantFPMath(Opcode, DL, VT, Ops[0], Ops[1]))
5842  return CFP;
5843 
5844  if (auto *C1 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Ops[0])) {
5845  if (auto *C2 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Ops[1])) {
5846  if (C1->isOpaque() || C2->isOpaque())
5847  return SDValue();
5848 
5849  std::optional<APInt> FoldAttempt =
5850  FoldValue(Opcode, C1->getAPIntValue(), C2->getAPIntValue());
5851  if (!FoldAttempt)
5852  return SDValue();
5853 
5854  SDValue Folded = getConstant(*FoldAttempt, DL, VT);
5855  assert((!Folded || !VT.isVector()) &&
5856  "Can't fold vectors ops with scalar operands");
5857  return Folded;
5858  }
5859  }
5860 
5861  // fold (add Sym, c) -> Sym+c
5862  if (GlobalAddressSDNode *GA = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Ops[0]))
5863  return FoldSymbolOffset(Opcode, VT, GA, Ops[1].getNode());
5864  if (TLI->isCommutativeBinOp(Opcode))
5865  if (GlobalAddressSDNode *GA = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Ops[1]))
5866  return FoldSymbolOffset(Opcode, VT, GA, Ops[0].getNode());
5867  }
5868 
5869  // This is for vector folding only from here on.
5870  if (!VT.isVector())
5871  return SDValue();
5872 
5873  ElementCount NumElts = VT.getVectorElementCount();
5874 
5875  // See if we can fold through bitcasted integer ops.
5876  if (NumOps == 2 && VT.isFixedLengthVector() && VT.isInteger() &&
5877  Ops[0].getValueType() == VT && Ops[1].getValueType() == VT &&
5878  Ops[0].getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST &&
5879  Ops[1].getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST) {
5880  SDValue N1 = peekThroughBitcasts(Ops[0]);
5881  SDValue N2 = peekThroughBitcasts(Ops[1]);
5882  auto *BV1 = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(N1);
5883  auto *BV2 = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(N2);
5884  EVT BVVT = N1.getValueType();
5885  if (BV1 && BV2 && BVVT.isInteger() && BVVT == N2.getValueType()) {
5886  bool IsLE = getDataLayout().isLittleEndian();
5887  unsigned EltBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
5888  SmallVector<APInt> RawBits1, RawBits2;
5889  BitVector UndefElts1, UndefElts2;
5890  if (BV1->getConstantRawBits(IsLE, EltBits, RawBits1, UndefElts1) &&
5891  BV2->getConstantRawBits(IsLE, EltBits, RawBits2, UndefElts2)) {
5892  SmallVector<APInt> RawBits;
5893  for (unsigned I = 0, E = NumElts.getFixedValue(); I != E; ++I) {
5894  std::optional<APInt> Fold = FoldValueWithUndef(
5895  Opcode, RawBits1[I], UndefElts1[I], RawBits2[I], UndefElts2[I]);
5896  if (!Fold)
5897  break;
5898  RawBits.push_back(*Fold);
5899  }
5900  if (RawBits.size() == NumElts.getFixedValue()) {
5901  // We have constant folded, but we need to cast this again back to
5902  // the original (possibly legalized) type.
5903  SmallVector<APInt> DstBits;
5904  BitVector DstUndefs;
5905  BuildVectorSDNode::recastRawBits(IsLE, BVVT.getScalarSizeInBits(),
5906  DstBits, RawBits, DstUndefs,
5907  BitVector(RawBits.size(), false));
5908  EVT BVEltVT = BV1->getOperand(0).getValueType();
5909  unsigned BVEltBits = BVEltVT.getSizeInBits();
5910  SmallVector<SDValue> Ops(DstBits.size(), getUNDEF(BVEltVT));
5911  for (unsigned I = 0, E = DstBits.size(); I != E; ++I) {
5912  if (DstUndefs[I])
5913  continue;
5914  Ops[I] = getConstant(DstBits[I].sext(BVEltBits), DL, BVEltVT);
5915  }
5916  return getBitcast(VT, getBuildVector(BVVT, DL, Ops));
5917  }
5918  }
5919  }
5920  }
5921 
5922  // Fold (mul step_vector(C0), C1) to (step_vector(C0 * C1)).
5923  // (shl step_vector(C0), C1) -> (step_vector(C0 << C1))
5924  if ((Opcode == ISD::MUL || Opcode == ISD::SHL) &&
5925  Ops[0].getOpcode() == ISD::STEP_VECTOR) {
5926  APInt RHSVal;
5927  if (ISD::isConstantSplatVector(Ops[1].getNode(), RHSVal)) {
5928  APInt NewStep = Opcode == ISD::MUL
5929  ? Ops[0].getConstantOperandAPInt(0) * RHSVal
5930  : Ops[0].getConstantOperandAPInt(0) << RHSVal;
5931  return getStepVector(DL, VT, NewStep);
5932  }
5933  }
5934 
5935  auto IsScalarOrSameVectorSize = [NumElts](const SDValue &Op) {
5936  return !Op.getValueType().isVector() ||
5937  Op.getValueType().getVectorElementCount() == NumElts;
5938  };
5939 
5940  auto IsBuildVectorSplatVectorOrUndef = [](const SDValue &Op) {
5941  return Op.isUndef() || Op.getOpcode() == ISD::CONDCODE ||
5942  Op.getOpcode() == ISD::BUILD_VECTOR ||
5943  Op.getOpcode() == ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR;
5944  };
5945 
5946  // All operands must be vector types with the same number of elements as
5947  // the result type and must be either UNDEF or a build/splat vector
5948  // or UNDEF scalars.
5949  if (!llvm::all_of(Ops, IsBuildVectorSplatVectorOrUndef) ||
5950  !llvm::all_of(Ops, IsScalarOrSameVectorSize))
5951  return SDValue();
5952 
5953  // If we are comparing vectors, then the result needs to be a i1 boolean that
5954  // is then extended back to the legal result type depending on how booleans
5955  // are represented.
5956  EVT SVT = (Opcode == ISD::SETCC ? MVT::i1 : VT.getScalarType());
5957  ISD::NodeType ExtendCode =
5958  (Opcode == ISD::SETCC && SVT != VT.getScalarType())
5959  ? TargetLowering::getExtendForContent(TLI->getBooleanContents(VT))
5960  : ISD::SIGN_EXTEND;
5961 
5962  // Find legal integer scalar type for constant promotion and
5963  // ensure that its scalar size is at least as large as source.
5964  EVT LegalSVT = VT.getScalarType();
5965  if (NewNodesMustHaveLegalTypes && LegalSVT.isInteger()) {
5966  LegalSVT = TLI->getTypeToTransformTo(*getContext(), LegalSVT);
5967  if (LegalSVT.bitsLT(VT.getScalarType()))
5968  return SDValue();
5969  }
5970 
5971  // For scalable vector types we know we're dealing with SPLAT_VECTORs. We
5972  // only have one operand to check. For fixed-length vector types we may have
5973  // a combination of BUILD_VECTOR and SPLAT_VECTOR.
5974  unsigned NumVectorElts = NumElts.isScalable() ? 1 : NumElts.getFixedValue();
5975 
5976  // Constant fold each scalar lane separately.
5977  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> ScalarResults;
5978  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumVectorElts; I++) {
5979  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> ScalarOps;
5980  for (SDValue Op : Ops) {
5981  EVT InSVT = Op.getValueType().getScalarType();
5982  if (Op.getOpcode() != ISD::BUILD_VECTOR &&
5983  Op.getOpcode() != ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR) {
5984  if (Op.isUndef())
5985  ScalarOps.push_back(getUNDEF(InSVT));
5986  else
5987  ScalarOps.push_back(Op);
5988  continue;
5989  }
5990 
5991  SDValue ScalarOp =
5992  Op.getOperand(Op.getOpcode() == ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR ? 0 : I);
5993  EVT ScalarVT = ScalarOp.getValueType();
5994 
5995  // Build vector (integer) scalar operands may need implicit
5996  // truncation - do this before constant folding.
5997  if (ScalarVT.isInteger() && ScalarVT.bitsGT(InSVT)) {
5998  // Don't create illegally-typed nodes unless they're constants or undef
5999  // - if we fail to constant fold we can't guarantee the (dead) nodes
6000  // we're creating will be cleaned up before being visited for
6001  // legalization.
6002  if (NewNodesMustHaveLegalTypes && !ScalarOp.isUndef() &&
6003  !isa<ConstantSDNode>(ScalarOp) &&
6004  TLI->getTypeAction(*getContext(), InSVT) !=
6005  TargetLowering::TypeLegal)
6006  return SDValue();
6007  ScalarOp = getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, InSVT, ScalarOp);
6008  }
6009 
6010  ScalarOps.push_back(ScalarOp);
6011  }
6012 
6013  // Constant fold the scalar operands.
6014  SDValue ScalarResult = getNode(Opcode, DL, SVT, ScalarOps);
6015 
6016  // Legalize the (integer) scalar constant if necessary.
6017  if (LegalSVT != SVT)
6018  ScalarResult = getNode(ExtendCode, DL, LegalSVT, ScalarResult);
6019 
6020  // Scalar folding only succeeded if the result is a constant or UNDEF.
6021  if (!ScalarResult.isUndef() && ScalarResult.getOpcode() != ISD::Constant &&
6022  ScalarResult.getOpcode() != ISD::ConstantFP)
6023  return SDValue();
6024  ScalarResults.push_back(ScalarResult);
6025  }
6026 
6027  SDValue V = NumElts.isScalable() ? getSplatVector(VT, DL, ScalarResults[0])
6028  : getBuildVector(VT, DL, ScalarResults);
6029  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "New node fold constant vector: ", this);
6030  return V;
6031 }
6032 
6033 SDValue SelectionDAG::foldConstantFPMath(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL,
6034  EVT VT, SDValue N1, SDValue N2) {
6035  // TODO: We don't do any constant folding for strict FP opcodes here, but we
6036  // should. That will require dealing with a potentially non-default
6037  // rounding mode, checking the "opStatus" return value from the APFloat
6038  // math calculations, and possibly other variations.
6039  ConstantFPSDNode *N1CFP = isConstOrConstSplatFP(N1, /*AllowUndefs*/ false);
6040  ConstantFPSDNode *N2CFP = isConstOrConstSplatFP(N2, /*AllowUndefs*/ false);
6041  if (N1CFP && N2CFP) {
6042  APFloat C1 = N1CFP->getValueAPF(); // make copy
6043  const APFloat &C2 = N2CFP->getValueAPF();
6044  switch (Opcode) {
6045  case ISD::FADD:
6046  C1.add(C2, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
6047  return getConstantFP(C1, DL, VT);
6048  case ISD::FSUB:
6049  C1.subtract(C2, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
6050  return getConstantFP(C1, DL, VT);
6051  case ISD::FMUL:
6052  C1.multiply(C2, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
6053  return getConstantFP(C1, DL, VT);
6054  case ISD::FDIV:
6055  C1.divide(C2, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
6056  return getConstantFP(C1, DL, VT);
6057  case ISD::FREM:
6058  C1.mod(C2);
6059  return getConstantFP(C1, DL, VT);
6060  case ISD::FCOPYSIGN:
6061  C1.copySign(C2);
6062  return getConstantFP(C1, DL, VT);
6063  case ISD::FMINNUM:
6064  return getConstantFP(minnum(C1, C2), DL, VT);
6065  case ISD::FMAXNUM:
6066  return getConstantFP(maxnum(C1, C2), DL, VT);
6067  case ISD::FMINIMUM:
6068  return getConstantFP(minimum(C1, C2), DL, VT);
6069  case ISD::FMAXIMUM:
6070  return getConstantFP(maximum(C1, C2), DL, VT);
6071  default: break;
6072  }
6073  }
6074  if (N1CFP && Opcode == ISD::FP_ROUND) {
6075  APFloat C1 = N1CFP->getValueAPF(); // make copy
6076  bool Unused;
6077  // This can return overflow, underflow, or inexact; we don't care.
6078  // FIXME need to be more flexible about rounding mode.
6079  (void) C1.convert(EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven,
6080  &Unused);
6081  return getConstantFP(C1, DL, VT);
6082  }
6083 
6084  switch (Opcode) {
6085  case ISD::FSUB:
6086  // -0.0 - undef --> undef (consistent with "fneg undef")
6087  if (ConstantFPSDNode *N1C = isConstOrConstSplatFP(N1, /*AllowUndefs*/ true))
6088  if (N1C && N1C->getValueAPF().isNegZero() && N2.isUndef())
6089  return getUNDEF(VT);
6090  [[fallthrough]];
6091 
6092  case ISD::FADD:
6093  case ISD::FMUL:
6094  case ISD::FDIV:
6095  case ISD::FREM:
6096  // If both operands are undef, the result is undef. If 1 operand is undef,
6097  // the result is NaN. This should match the behavior of the IR optimizer.
6098  if (N1.isUndef() && N2.isUndef())
6099  return getUNDEF(VT);
6100  if (N1.isUndef() || N2.isUndef())
6101  return getConstantFP(APFloat::getNaN(EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT)), DL, VT);
6102  }
6103  return SDValue();
6104 }
6105 
6106 SDValue SelectionDAG::getAssertAlign(const SDLoc &DL, SDValue Val, Align A) {
6107  assert(Val.getValueType().isInteger() && "Invalid AssertAlign!");
6108 
6109  // There's no need to assert on a byte-aligned pointer. All pointers are at
6110  // least byte aligned.
6111  if (A == Align(1))
6112  return Val;
6113 
6114  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
6115  AddNodeIDNode(ID, ISD::AssertAlign, getVTList(Val.getValueType()), {Val});
6116  ID.AddInteger(A.value());
6117 
6118  void *IP = nullptr;
6119  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, DL, IP))
6120  return SDValue(E, 0);
6121 
6122  auto *N = newSDNode<AssertAlignSDNode>(DL.getIROrder(), DL.getDebugLoc(),
6123  Val.getValueType(), A);
6124  createOperands(N, {Val});
6125 
6126  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
6127  InsertNode(N);
6128 
6129  SDValue V(N, 0);
6130  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
6131  return V;
6132 }
6133 
6134 SDValue SelectionDAG::getNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
6135  SDValue N1, SDValue N2) {
6136  SDNodeFlags Flags;
6137  if (Inserter)
6138  Flags = Inserter->getFlags();
6139  return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, N1, N2, Flags);
6140 }
6141 
6142 void SelectionDAG::canonicalizeCommutativeBinop(unsigned Opcode, SDValue &N1,
6143  SDValue &N2) const {
6144  if (!TLI->isCommutativeBinOp(Opcode))
6145  return;
6146 
6147  // Canonicalize:
6148  // binop(const, nonconst) -> binop(nonconst, const)
6149  SDNode *N1C = isConstantIntBuildVectorOrConstantInt(N1);
6150  SDNode *N2C = isConstantIntBuildVectorOrConstantInt(N2);
6151  SDNode *N1CFP = isConstantFPBuildVectorOrConstantFP(N1);
6152  SDNode *N2CFP = isConstantFPBuildVectorOrConstantFP(N2);
6153  if ((N1C && !N2C) || (N1CFP && !N2CFP))
6154  std::swap(N1, N2);
6155 
6156  // Canonicalize:
6157  // binop(splat(x), step_vector) -> binop(step_vector, splat(x))
6158  else if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR &&
6159  N2.getOpcode() == ISD::STEP_VECTOR)
6160  std::swap(N1, N2);
6161 }
6162 
6163 SDValue SelectionDAG::getNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
6164  SDValue N1, SDValue N2, const SDNodeFlags Flags) {
6165  assert(N1.getOpcode() != ISD::DELETED_NODE &&
6166  N2.getOpcode() != ISD::DELETED_NODE &&
6167  "Operand is DELETED_NODE!");
6168 
6169  canonicalizeCommutativeBinop(Opcode, N1, N2);
6170 
6171  auto *N1C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N1);
6172  auto *N2C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N2);
6173 
6174  // Don't allow undefs in vector splats - we might be returning N2 when folding
6175  // to zero etc.
6176  ConstantSDNode *N2CV =
6177  isConstOrConstSplat(N2, /*AllowUndefs*/ false, /*AllowTruncation*/ true);
6178 
6179  switch (Opcode) {
6180  default: break;
6181  case ISD::TokenFactor:
6182  assert(VT == MVT::Other && N1.getValueType() == MVT::Other &&
6183  N2.getValueType() == MVT::Other && "Invalid token factor!");
6184  // Fold trivial token factors.
6185  if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::EntryToken) return N2;
6186  if (N2.getOpcode() == ISD::EntryToken) return N1;
6187  if (N1 == N2) return N1;
6188  break;
6189  case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: {
6190  // Attempt to simplify BUILD_VECTOR.
6191  SDValue Ops[] = {N1, N2};
6192  if (SDValue V = FoldBUILD_VECTOR(DL, VT, Ops, *this))
6193  return V;
6194  break;
6195  }
6196  case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS: {
6197  SDValue Ops[] = {N1, N2};
6198  if (SDValue V = foldCONCAT_VECTORS(DL, VT, Ops, *this))
6199  return V;
6200  break;
6201  }
6202  case ISD::AND:
6203  assert(VT.isInteger() && "This operator does not apply to FP types!");
6204  assert(N1.getValueType() == N2.getValueType() &&
6205  N1.getValueType() == VT && "Binary operator types must match!");
6206  // (X & 0) -> 0. This commonly occurs when legalizing i64 values, so it's
6207  // worth handling here.
6208  if (N2CV && N2CV->isZero())
6209  return N2;
6210  if (N2CV && N2CV->isAllOnes()) // X & -1 -> X
6211  return N1;
6212  break;
6213  case ISD::OR:
6214  case ISD::XOR:
6215  case ISD::ADD:
6216  case ISD::SUB:
6217  assert(VT.isInteger() && "This operator does not apply to FP types!");
6218  assert(N1.getValueType() == N2.getValueType() &&
6219  N1.getValueType() == VT && "Binary operator types must match!");
6220  // (X ^|+- 0) -> X. This commonly occurs when legalizing i64 values, so
6221  // it's worth handling here.
6222  if (N2CV && N2CV->isZero())
6223  return N1;
6224  if ((Opcode == ISD::ADD || Opcode == ISD::SUB) && VT.isVector() &&
6225  VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
6226  return getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, VT, N1, N2);
6227  break;
6228  case ISD::MUL:
6229  assert(VT.isInteger() && "This operator does not apply to FP types!");
6230  assert(N1.getValueType() == N2.getValueType() &&
6231  N1.getValueType() == VT && "Binary operator types must match!");
6232  if (VT.isVector() && VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
6233  return getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, N1, N2);
6234  if (N2C && (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::VSCALE) && Flags.hasNoSignedWrap()) {
6235  const APInt &MulImm = N1->getConstantOperandAPInt(0);
6236  const APInt &N2CImm = N2C->getAPIntValue();
6237  return getVScale(DL, VT, MulImm * N2CImm);
6238  }
6239  break;
6240  case ISD::UDIV:
6241  case ISD::UREM:
6242  case ISD::MULHU:
6243  case ISD::MULHS:
6244  case ISD::SDIV:
6245  case ISD::SREM:
6246  case ISD::SADDSAT:
6247  case ISD::SSUBSAT:
6248  case ISD::UADDSAT:
6249  case ISD::USUBSAT:
6250  assert(VT.isInteger() && "This operator does not apply to FP types!");
6251  assert(N1.getValueType() == N2.getValueType() &&
6252  N1.getValueType() == VT && "Binary operator types must match!");
6253  if (VT.isVector() && VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1) {
6254  // fold (add_sat x, y) -> (or x, y) for bool types.
6255  if (Opcode == ISD::SADDSAT || Opcode == ISD::UADDSAT)
6256  return getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, N1, N2);
6257  // fold (sub_sat x, y) -> (and x, ~y) for bool types.
6258  if (Opcode == ISD::SSUBSAT || Opcode == ISD::USUBSAT)
6259  return getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, N1, getNOT(DL, N2, VT));
6260  }
6261  break;
6262  case ISD::ABDS:
6263  case ISD::ABDU:
6264  assert(VT.isInteger() && "This operator does not apply to FP types!");
6265  assert(N1.getValueType() == N2.getValueType() &&
6266  N1.getValueType() == VT && "Binary operator types must match!");
6267  break;
6268  case ISD::SMIN:
6269  case ISD::UMAX:
6270  assert(VT.isInteger() && "This operator does not apply to FP types!");
6271  assert(N1.getValueType() == N2.getValueType() &&
6272  N1.getValueType() == VT && "Binary operator types must match!");
6273  if (VT.isVector() && VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
6274  return getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, N1, N2);
6275  break;
6276  case ISD::SMAX:
6277  case ISD::UMIN:
6278  assert(VT.isInteger() && "This operator does not apply to FP types!");
6279  assert(N1.getValueType() == N2.getValueType() &&
6280  N1.getValueType() == VT && "Binary operator types must match!");
6281  if (VT.isVector() && VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
6282  return getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, N1, N2);
6283  break;
6284  case ISD::FADD:
6285  case ISD::FSUB:
6286  case ISD::FMUL:
6287  case ISD::FDIV:
6288  case ISD::FREM:
6289  assert(VT.isFloatingPoint() && "This operator only applies to FP types!");
6290  assert(N1.getValueType() == N2.getValueType() &&
6291  N1.getValueType() == VT && "Binary operator types must match!");
6292  if (SDValue V = simplifyFPBinop(Opcode, N1, N2, Flags))
6293  return V;
6294  break;
6295  case ISD::FCOPYSIGN: // N1 and result must match. N1/N2 need not match.
6296  assert(N1.getValueType() == VT &&
6297  N1.getValueType().isFloatingPoint() &&
6298  N2.getValueType().isFloatingPoint() &&
6299  "Invalid FCOPYSIGN!");
6300  break;
6301  case ISD::SHL:
6302  if (N2C && (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::VSCALE) && Flags.hasNoSignedWrap()) {
6303  const APInt &MulImm = N1->getConstantOperandAPInt(0);
6304  const APInt &ShiftImm = N2C->getAPIntValue();
6305  return getVScale(DL, VT, MulImm << ShiftImm);
6306  }
6307  [[fallthrough]];
6308  case ISD::SRA:
6309  case ISD::SRL:
6310  if (SDValue V = simplifyShift(N1, N2))
6311  return V;
6312  [[fallthrough]];
6313  case ISD::ROTL:
6314  case ISD::ROTR:
6315  assert(VT == N1.getValueType() &&
6316  "Shift operators return type must be the same as their first arg");
6317  assert(VT.isInteger() && N2.getValueType().isInteger() &&
6318  "Shifts only work on integers");
6319  assert((!VT.isVector() || VT == N2.getValueType()) &&
6320  "Vector shift amounts must be in the same as their first arg");
6321  // Verify that the shift amount VT is big enough to hold valid shift
6322  // amounts. This catches things like trying to shift an i1024 value by an
6323  // i8, which is easy to fall into in generic code that uses
6324  // TLI.getShiftAmount().
6325  assert(N2.getValueType().getScalarSizeInBits() >=
6326  Log2_32_Ceil(VT.getScalarSizeInBits()) &&
6327  "Invalid use of small shift amount with oversized value!");
6328 
6329  // Always fold shifts of i1 values so the code generator doesn't need to
6330  // handle them. Since we know the size of the shift has to be less than the
6331  // size of the value, the shift/rotate count is guaranteed to be zero.
6332  if (VT == MVT::i1)
6333  return N1;
6334  if (N2CV && N2CV->isZero())
6335  return N1;
6336  break;
6337  case ISD::FP_ROUND:
6338  assert(VT.isFloatingPoint() &&
6339  N1.getValueType().isFloatingPoint() &&
6340  VT.bitsLE(N1.getValueType()) &&
6341  N2C && (N2C->getZExtValue() == 0 || N2C->getZExtValue() == 1) &&
6342  "Invalid FP_ROUND!");
6343  if (N1.getValueType() == VT) return N1; // noop conversion.
6344  break;
6345  case ISD::AssertSext:
6346  case ISD::AssertZext: {
6347  EVT EVT = cast<VTSDNode>(N2)->getVT();
6348  assert(VT == N1.getValueType() && "Not an inreg extend!");
6349  assert(VT.isInteger() && EVT.isInteger() &&
6350  "Cannot *_EXTEND_INREG FP types");
6351  assert(!EVT.isVector() &&
6352  "AssertSExt/AssertZExt type should be the vector element type "
6353  "rather than the vector type!");
6354  assert(EVT.bitsLE(VT.getScalarType()) && "Not extending!");
6355  if (VT.getScalarType() == EVT) return N1; // noop assertion.
6356  break;
6357  }
6358  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: {
6359  EVT EVT = cast<VTSDNode>(N2)->getVT();
6360  assert(VT == N1.getValueType() && "Not an inreg extend!");
6361  assert(VT.isInteger() && EVT.isInteger() &&
6362  "Cannot *_EXTEND_INREG FP types");
6363  assert(EVT.isVector() == VT.isVector() &&
6364  "SIGN_EXTEND_INREG type should be vector iff the operand "
6365  "type is vector!");
6366  assert((!EVT.isVector() ||
6367  EVT.getVectorElementCount() == VT.getVectorElementCount()) &&
6368  "Vector element counts must match in SIGN_EXTEND_INREG");
6369  assert(EVT.bitsLE(VT) && "Not extending!");
6370  if (EVT == VT) return N1; // Not actually extending
6371 
6372  auto SignExtendInReg = [&](APInt Val, llvm::EVT ConstantVT) {
6373  unsigned FromBits = EVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
6374  Val <<= Val.getBitWidth() - FromBits;
6375  Val.ashrInPlace(Val.getBitWidth() - FromBits);
6376  return getConstant(Val, DL, ConstantVT);
6377  };
6378 
6379  if (N1C) {
6380  const APInt &Val = N1C->getAPIntValue();
6381  return SignExtendInReg(Val, VT);
6382  }
6383 
6384  if (ISD::isBuildVectorOfConstantSDNodes(N1.getNode())) {
6385  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
6386  llvm::EVT OpVT = N1.getOperand(0).getValueType();
6387  for (int i = 0, e = VT.getVectorNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
6388  SDValue Op = N1.getOperand(i);
6389  if (Op.isUndef()) {
6390  Ops.push_back(getUNDEF(OpVT));
6391  continue;
6392  }
6393  ConstantSDNode *C = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op);
6394  APInt Val = C->getAPIntValue();
6395  Ops.push_back(SignExtendInReg(Val, OpVT));
6396  }
6397  return getBuildVector(VT, DL, Ops);
6398  }
6399  break;
6400  }
6401  case ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT:
6402  case ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT: {
6403  assert(VT.isInteger() && cast<VTSDNode>(N2)->getVT().isInteger() &&
6404  N1.getValueType().isFloatingPoint() && "Invalid FP_TO_*INT_SAT");
6405  assert(N1.getValueType().isVector() == VT.isVector() &&
6406  "FP_TO_*INT_SAT type should be vector iff the operand type is "
6407  "vector!");
6408  assert((!VT.isVector() || VT.getVectorElementCount() ==
6409  N1.getValueType().getVectorElementCount()) &&
6410  "Vector element counts must match in FP_TO_*INT_SAT");
6411  assert(!cast<VTSDNode>(N2)->getVT().isVector() &&
6412  "Type to saturate to must be a scalar.");
6413  assert(cast<VTSDNode>(N2)->getVT().bitsLE(VT.getScalarType()) &&
6414  "Not extending!");
6415  break;
6416  }
6417  case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT:
6418  assert(VT.getSizeInBits() >= N1.getValueType().getScalarSizeInBits() &&
6419  "The result of EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT must be at least as wide as the \
6420  element type of the vector.");
6421 
6422  // Extract from an undefined value or using an undefined index is undefined.
6423  if (N1.isUndef() || N2.isUndef())
6424  return getUNDEF(VT);
6425 
6426  // EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT of out-of-bounds element is an UNDEF for fixed length
6427  // vectors. For scalable vectors we will provide appropriate support for
6428  // dealing with arbitrary indices.
6429  if (N2C && N1.getValueType().isFixedLengthVector() &&
6430  N2C->getAPIntValue().uge(N1.getValueType().getVectorNumElements()))
6431  return getUNDEF(VT);
6432 
6433  // EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT of CONCAT_VECTORS is often formed while lowering is
6434  // expanding copies of large vectors from registers. This only works for
6435  // fixed length vectors, since we need to know the exact number of
6436  // elements.
6437  if (N2C && N1.getOperand(0).getValueType().isFixedLengthVector() &&
6438  N1.getOpcode() == ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS && N1.getNumOperands() > 0) {
6439  unsigned Factor =
6440  N1.getOperand(0).getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
6441  return getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, VT,
6442  N1.getOperand(N2C->getZExtValue() / Factor),
6443  getVectorIdxConstant(N2C->getZExtValue() % Factor, DL));
6444  }
6445 
6446  // EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT of BUILD_VECTOR or SPLAT_VECTOR is often formed while
6447  // lowering is expanding large vector constants.
6448  if (N2C && (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::BUILD_VECTOR ||
6449  N1.getOpcode() == ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR)) {
6450  assert((N1.getOpcode() != ISD::BUILD_VECTOR ||
6451  N1.getValueType().isFixedLengthVector()) &&
6452  "BUILD_VECTOR used for scalable vectors");
6453  unsigned Index =
6454  N1.getOpcode() == ISD::BUILD_VECTOR ? N2C->getZExtValue() : 0;
6455  SDValue Elt = N1.getOperand(Index);
6456 
6457  if (VT != Elt.getValueType())
6458  // If the vector element type is not legal, the BUILD_VECTOR operands
6459  // are promoted and implicitly truncated, and the result implicitly
6460  // extended. Make that explicit here.
6461  Elt = getAnyExtOrTrunc(Elt, DL, VT);
6462 
6463  return Elt;
6464  }
6465 
6466  // EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT of INSERT_VECTOR_ELT is often formed when vector
6467  // operations are lowered to scalars.
6468  if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT) {
6469  // If the indices are the same, return the inserted element else
6470  // if the indices are known different, extract the element from
6471  // the original vector.
6472  SDValue N1Op2 = N1.getOperand(2);
6473  ConstantSDNode *N1Op2C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N1Op2);
6474 
6475  if (N1Op2C && N2C) {
6476  if (N1Op2C->getZExtValue() == N2C->getZExtValue()) {
6477  if (VT == N1.getOperand(1).getValueType())
6478  return N1.getOperand(1);
6479  if (VT.isFloatingPoint()) {
6480  assert(VT.getSizeInBits() > N1.getOperand(1).getValueType().getSizeInBits());
6481  return getFPExtendOrRound(N1.getOperand(1), DL, VT);
6482  }
6483  return getSExtOrTrunc(N1.getOperand(1), DL, VT);
6484  }
6485  return getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, VT, N1.getOperand(0), N2);
6486  }
6487  }
6488 
6489  // EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT of v1iX EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR could be formed
6490  // when vector types are scalarized and v1iX is legal.
6491  // vextract (v1iX extract_subvector(vNiX, Idx)) -> vextract(vNiX,Idx).
6492  // Here we are completely ignoring the extract element index (N2),
6493  // which is fine for fixed width vectors, since any index other than 0
6494  // is undefined anyway. However, this cannot be ignored for scalable
6495  // vectors - in theory we could support this, but we don't want to do this
6496  // without a profitability check.
6497  if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR &&
6498  N1.getValueType().isFixedLengthVector() &&
6499  N1.getValueType().getVectorNumElements() == 1) {
6500  return getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, VT, N1.getOperand(0),
6501  N1.getOperand(1));
6502  }
6503  break;
6504  case ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT:
6505  assert(N2C && (unsigned)N2C->getZExtValue() < 2 && "Bad EXTRACT_ELEMENT!");
6506  assert(!N1.getValueType().isVector() && !VT.isVector() &&
6507  (N1.getValueType().isInteger() == VT.isInteger()) &&
6508  N1.getValueType() != VT &&
6509  "Wrong types for EXTRACT_ELEMENT!");
6510 
6511  // EXTRACT_ELEMENT of BUILD_PAIR is often formed while legalize is expanding
6512  // 64-bit integers into 32-bit parts. Instead of building the extract of
6513  // the BUILD_PAIR, only to have legalize rip it apart, just do it now.
6514  if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::BUILD_PAIR)
6515  return N1.getOperand(N2C->getZExtValue());
6516 
6517  // EXTRACT_ELEMENT of a constant int is also very common.
6518  if (N1C) {
6519  unsigned ElementSize = VT.getSizeInBits();
6520  unsigned Shift = ElementSize * N2C->getZExtValue();
6521  const APInt &Val = N1C->getAPIntValue();
6522  return getConstant(Val.extractBits(ElementSize, Shift), DL, VT);
6523  }
6524  break;
6525  case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: {
6526  EVT N1VT = N1.getValueType();
6527  assert(VT.isVector() && N1VT.isVector() &&
6528  "Extract subvector VTs must be vectors!");
6529  assert(VT.getVectorElementType() == N1VT.getVectorElementType() &&
6530  "Extract subvector VTs must have the same element type!");
6531  assert((VT.isFixedLengthVector() || N1VT.isScalableVector()) &&
6532  "Cannot extract a scalable vector from a fixed length vector!");
6533  assert((VT.isScalableVector() != N1VT.isScalableVector() ||
6534  VT.getVectorMinNumElements() <= N1VT.getVectorMinNumElements()) &&
6535  "Extract subvector must be from larger vector to smaller vector!");
6536  assert(N2C && "Extract subvector index must be a constant");
6537  assert((VT.isScalableVector() != N1VT.isScalableVector() ||
6538  (VT.getVectorMinNumElements() + N2C->getZExtValue()) <=
6539  N1VT.getVectorMinNumElements()) &&
6540  "Extract subvector overflow!");
6541  assert(N2C->getAPIntValue().getBitWidth() ==
6542  TLI->getVectorIdxTy(getDataLayout()).getFixedSizeInBits() &&
6543  "Constant index for EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR has an invalid size");
6544 
6545  // Trivial extraction.
6546  if (VT == N1VT)
6547  return N1;
6548 
6549  // EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR of an UNDEF is an UNDEF.
6550  if (N1.isUndef())
6551  return getUNDEF(VT);
6552 
6553  // EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR of CONCAT_VECTOR can be simplified if the pieces of
6554  // the concat have the same type as the extract.
6555  if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS && N1.getNumOperands() > 0 &&
6556  VT == N1.getOperand(0).getValueType()) {
6557  unsigned Factor = VT.getVectorMinNumElements();
6558  return N1.getOperand(N2C->getZExtValue() / Factor);
6559  }
6560 
6561  // EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR of INSERT_SUBVECTOR is often created
6562  // during shuffle legalization.
6563  if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR && N2 == N1.getOperand(2) &&
6564  VT == N1.getOperand(1).getValueType())
6565  return N1.getOperand(1);
6566  break;
6567  }
6568  }
6569 
6570  // Perform trivial constant folding.
6571  if (SDValue SV = FoldConstantArithmetic(Opcode, DL, VT, {N1, N2}))
6572  return SV;
6573 
6574  // Canonicalize an UNDEF to the RHS, even over a constant.
6575  if (N1.isUndef()) {
6576  if (TLI->isCommutativeBinOp(Opcode)) {
6577  std::swap(N1, N2);
6578  } else {
6579  switch (Opcode) {
6580  case ISD::SUB:
6581  return getUNDEF(VT); // fold op(undef, arg2) -> undef
6582  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG:
6583  case ISD::UDIV:
6584  case ISD::SDIV:
6585  case ISD::UREM:
6586  case ISD::SREM:
6587  case ISD::SSUBSAT:
6588  case ISD::USUBSAT:
6589  return getConstant(0, DL, VT); // fold op(undef, arg2) -> 0
6590  }
6591  }
6592  }
6593 
6594  // Fold a bunch of operators when the RHS is undef.
6595  if (N2.isUndef()) {
6596  switch (Opcode) {
6597  case ISD::XOR:
6598  if (N1.isUndef())
6599  // Handle undef ^ undef -> 0 special case. This is a common
6600  // idiom (misuse).
6601  return getConstant(0, DL, VT);
6602  [[fallthrough]];
6603  case ISD::ADD:
6604  case ISD::SUB:
6605  case ISD::UDIV:
6606  case ISD::SDIV:
6607  case ISD::UREM:
6608  case ISD::SREM:
6609  return getUNDEF(VT); // fold op(arg1, undef) -> undef
6610  case ISD::MUL:
6611  case ISD::AND:
6612  case ISD::SSUBSAT:
6613  case ISD::USUBSAT:
6614  return getConstant(0, DL, VT); // fold op(arg1, undef) -> 0
6615  case ISD::OR:
6616  case ISD::SADDSAT:
6617  case ISD::UADDSAT:
6618  return getAllOnesConstant(DL, VT);
6619  }
6620  }
6621 
6622  // Memoize this node if possible.
6623  SDNode *N;
6624  SDVTList VTs = getVTList(VT);
6625  SDValue Ops[] = {N1, N2};
6626  if (VT != MVT::Glue) {
6627  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
6628  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opcode, VTs, Ops);
6629  void *IP = nullptr;
6630  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, DL, IP)) {
6631  E->intersectFlagsWith(Flags);
6632  return SDValue(E, 0);
6633  }
6634 
6635  N = newSDNode<SDNode>(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(), DL.getDebugLoc(), VTs);
6636  N->setFlags(Flags);
6637  createOperands(N, Ops);
6638  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
6639  } else {
6640  N = newSDNode<SDNode>(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(), DL.getDebugLoc(), VTs);
6641  createOperands(N, Ops);
6642  }
6643 
6644  InsertNode(N);
6645  SDValue V = SDValue(N, 0);
6646  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
6647  return V;
6648 }
6649 
6650 SDValue SelectionDAG::getNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
6651  SDValue N1, SDValue N2, SDValue N3) {
6652  SDNodeFlags Flags;
6653  if (Inserter)
6654  Flags = Inserter->getFlags();
6655  return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, N1, N2, N3, Flags);
6656 }
6657 
6658 SDValue SelectionDAG::getNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
6659  SDValue N1, SDValue N2, SDValue N3,
6660  const SDNodeFlags Flags) {
6661  assert(N1.getOpcode() != ISD::DELETED_NODE &&
6662  N2.getOpcode() != ISD::DELETED_NODE &&
6663  N3.getOpcode() != ISD::DELETED_NODE &&
6664  "Operand is DELETED_NODE!");
6665  // Perform various simplifications.
6666  switch (Opcode) {
6667  case ISD::FMA: {
6668  assert(VT.isFloatingPoint() && "This operator only applies to FP types!");
6669  assert(N1.getValueType() == VT && N2.getValueType() == VT &&
6670  N3.getValueType() == VT && "FMA types must match!");
6671  ConstantFPSDNode *N1CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N1);
6672  ConstantFPSDNode *N2CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N2);
6673  ConstantFPSDNode *N3CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N3);
6674  if (N1CFP && N2CFP && N3CFP) {
6675  APFloat V1 = N1CFP->getValueAPF();
6676  const APFloat &V2 = N2CFP->getValueAPF();
6677  const APFloat &V3 = N3CFP->getValueAPF();
6678  V1.fusedMultiplyAdd(V2, V3, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
6679  return getConstantFP(V1, DL, VT);
6680  }
6681  break;
6682  }
6683  case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: {
6684  // Attempt to simplify BUILD_VECTOR.
6685  SDValue Ops[] = {N1, N2, N3};
6686  if (SDValue V = FoldBUILD_VECTOR(DL, VT, Ops, *this))
6687  return V;
6688  break;
6689  }
6690  case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS: {
6691  SDValue Ops[] = {N1, N2, N3};
6692  if (SDValue V = foldCONCAT_VECTORS(DL, VT, Ops, *this))
6693  return V;
6694  break;
6695  }
6696  case ISD::SETCC: {
6697  assert(VT.isInteger() && "SETCC result type must be an integer!");
6698  assert(N1.getValueType() == N2.getValueType() &&
6699  "SETCC operands must have the same type!");
6700  assert(VT.isVector() == N1.getValueType().isVector() &&
6701  "SETCC type should be vector iff the operand type is vector!");
6702  assert((!VT.isVector() || VT.getVectorElementCount() ==
6703  N1.getValueType().getVectorElementCount()) &&
6704  "SETCC vector element counts must match!");
6705  // Use FoldSetCC to simplify SETCC's.
6706  if (SDValue V = FoldSetCC(VT, N1, N2, cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N3)->get(), DL))
6707  return V;
6708  // Vector constant folding.
6709  SDValue Ops[] = {N1, N2, N3};
6710  if (SDValue V = FoldConstantArithmetic(Opcode, DL, VT, Ops)) {
6711  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "New node vector constant folding: ", this);
6712  return V;
6713  }
6714  break;
6715  }
6716  case ISD::SELECT:
6717  case ISD::VSELECT:
6718  if (SDValue V = simplifySelect(N1, N2, N3))
6719  return V;
6720  break;
6721  case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE:
6722  llvm_unreachable("should use getVectorShuffle constructor!");
6723  case ISD::VECTOR_SPLICE: {
6724  if (cast<ConstantSDNode>(N3)->isNullValue())
6725  return N1;
6726  break;
6727  }
6728  case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT: {
6729  ConstantSDNode *N3C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N3);
6730  // INSERT_VECTOR_ELT into out-of-bounds element is an UNDEF, except
6731  // for scalable vectors where we will generate appropriate code to
6732  // deal with out-of-bounds cases correctly.
6733  if (N3C && N1.getValueType().isFixedLengthVector() &&
6734  N3C->getZExtValue() >= N1.getValueType().getVectorNumElements())
6735  return getUNDEF(VT);
6736 
6737  // Undefined index can be assumed out-of-bounds, so that's UNDEF too.
6738  if (N3.isUndef())
6739  return getUNDEF(VT);
6740 
6741  // If the inserted element is an UNDEF, just use the input vector.
6742  if (N2.isUndef())
6743  return N1;
6744 
6745  break;
6746  }
6747  case ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR: {
6748  // Inserting undef into undef is still undef.
6749  if (N1.isUndef() && N2.isUndef())
6750  return getUNDEF(VT);
6751 
6752  EVT N2VT = N2.getValueType();
6753  assert(VT == N1.getValueType() &&
6754  "Dest and insert subvector source types must match!");
6755  assert(VT.isVector() && N2VT.isVector() &&
6756  "Insert subvector VTs must be vectors!");
6757  assert(VT.getVectorElementType() == N2VT.getVectorElementType() &&
6758  "Insert subvector VTs must have the same element type!");
6759  assert((VT.isScalableVector() || N2VT.isFixedLengthVector()) &&
6760  "Cannot insert a scalable vector into a fixed length vector!");
6761  assert((VT.isScalableVector() != N2VT.isScalableVector() ||
6762  VT.getVectorMinNumElements() >= N2VT.getVectorMinNumElements()) &&
6763  "Insert subvector must be from smaller vector to larger vector!");
6764  assert(isa<ConstantSDNode>(N3) &&
6765  "Insert subvector index must be constant");
6766  assert((VT.isScalableVector() != N2VT.isScalableVector() ||
6767  (N2VT.getVectorMinNumElements() +
6768  cast<ConstantSDNode>(N3)->getZExtValue()) <=
6769  VT.getVectorMinNumElements()) &&
6770  "Insert subvector overflow!");
6771  assert(cast<ConstantSDNode>(N3)->getAPIntValue().getBitWidth() ==
6772  TLI->getVectorIdxTy(getDataLayout()).getFixedSizeInBits() &&
6773  "Constant index for INSERT_SUBVECTOR has an invalid size");
6774 
6775  // Trivial insertion.
6776  if (VT == N2VT)
6777  return N2;
6778 
6779  // If this is an insert of an extracted vector into an undef vector, we
6780  // can just use the input to the extract.
6781  if (N1.isUndef() && N2.getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR &&
6782  N2.getOperand(1) == N3 && N2.getOperand(0).getValueType() == VT)
6783  return N2.getOperand(0);
6784  break;
6785  }
6786  case ISD::BITCAST:
6787  // Fold bit_convert nodes from a type to themselves.
6788  if (N1.getValueType() == VT)
6789  return N1;
6790  break;
6791  }
6792 
6793  // Memoize node if it doesn't produce a flag.
6794  SDNode *N;
6795  SDVTList VTs = getVTList(VT);
6796  SDValue Ops[] = {N1, N2, N3};
6797  if (VT != MVT::Glue) {
6798  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
6799  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opcode, VTs, Ops);
6800  void *IP = nullptr;
6801  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, DL, IP)) {
6802  E->intersectFlagsWith(Flags);
6803  return SDValue(E, 0);
6804  }
6805 
6806  N = newSDNode<SDNode>(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(), DL.getDebugLoc(), VTs);
6807  N->setFlags(Flags);
6808  createOperands(N, Ops);
6809  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
6810  } else {
6811  N = newSDNode<SDNode>(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(), DL.getDebugLoc(), VTs);
6812  createOperands(N, Ops);
6813  }
6814 
6815  InsertNode(N);
6816  SDValue V = SDValue(N, 0);
6817  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
6818  return V;
6819 }
6820 
6821 SDValue SelectionDAG::getNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
6822  SDValue N1, SDValue N2, SDValue N3, SDValue N4) {
6823  SDValue Ops[] = { N1, N2, N3, N4 };
6824  return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, Ops);
6825 }
6826 
6827 SDValue SelectionDAG::getNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
6828  SDValue N1, SDValue N2, SDValue N3, SDValue N4,
6829  SDValue N5) {
6830  SDValue Ops[] = { N1, N2, N3, N4, N5 };
6831  return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, Ops);
6832 }
6833 
6834 /// getStackArgumentTokenFactor - Compute a TokenFactor to force all
6835 /// the incoming stack arguments to be loaded from the stack.
6836 SDValue SelectionDAG::getStackArgumentTokenFactor(SDValue Chain) {
6837  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> ArgChains;
6838 
6839  // Include the original chain at the beginning of the list. When this is
6840  // used by target LowerCall hooks, this helps legalize find the
6841  // CALLSEQ_BEGIN node.
6842  ArgChains.push_back(Chain);
6843 
6844  // Add a chain value for each stack argument.
6845  for (SDNode *U : getEntryNode().getNode()->uses())
6846  if (LoadSDNode *L = dyn_cast<LoadSDNode>(U))
6847  if (FrameIndexSDNode *FI = dyn_cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(L->getBasePtr()))
6848  if (FI->getIndex() < 0)
6849  ArgChains.push_back(SDValue(L, 1));
6850 
6851  // Build a tokenfactor for all the chains.
6852  return getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, SDLoc(Chain), MVT::Other, ArgChains);
6853 }
6854 
6855 /// getMemsetValue - Vectorized representation of the memset value
6856 /// operand.
6857 static SDValue getMemsetValue(SDValue Value, EVT VT, SelectionDAG &DAG,
6858  const SDLoc &dl) {
6859  assert(!Value.isUndef());
6860 
6861  unsigned NumBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
6862  if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Value)) {
6863  assert(C->getAPIntValue().getBitWidth() == 8);
6864  APInt Val = APInt::getSplat(NumBits, C->getAPIntValue());
6865  if (VT.isInteger()) {
6866  bool IsOpaque = VT.getSizeInBits() > 64 ||
6867  !DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo().isLegalStoreImmediate(C->getSExtValue());
6868  return DAG.getConstant(Val, dl, VT, false, IsOpaque);
6869  }
6870  return DAG.getConstantFP(APFloat(DAG.EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT), Val), dl,
6871  VT);
6872  }
6873 
6874  assert(Value.getValueType() == MVT::i8 && "memset with non-byte fill value?");
6875  EVT IntVT = VT.getScalarType();
6876  if (!IntVT.isInteger())
6877  IntVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), IntVT.getSizeInBits());
6878 
6879  Value = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, IntVT, Value);
6880  if (NumBits > 8) {
6881  // Use a multiplication with 0x010101... to extend the input to the
6882  // required length.
6883  APInt Magic = APInt::getSplat(NumBits, APInt(8, 0x01));
6884  Value = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, IntVT, Value,
6885  DAG.getConstant(Magic, dl, IntVT));
6886  }
6887 
6888  if (VT != Value.getValueType() && !VT.isInteger())
6889  Value = DAG.getBitcast(VT.getScalarType(), Value);
6890  if (VT != Value.getValueType())
6891  Value = DAG.getSplatBuildVector(VT, dl, Value);
6892 
6893  return Value;
6894 }
6895 
6896 /// getMemsetStringVal - Similar to getMemsetValue. Except this is only
6897 /// used when a memcpy is turned into a memset when the source is a constant
6898 /// string ptr.
6899 static SDValue getMemsetStringVal(EVT VT, const SDLoc &dl, SelectionDAG &DAG,
6900  const TargetLowering &TLI,
6901  const ConstantDataArraySlice &Slice) {
6902  // Handle vector with all elements zero.
6903  if (Slice.Array == nullptr) {
6904  if (VT.isInteger())
6905  return DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
6906  if (VT == MVT::f32 || VT == MVT::f64 || VT == MVT::f128)
6907  return DAG.getConstantFP(0.0, dl, VT);
6908  if (VT.isVector()) {
6909  unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
6910  MVT EltVT = (VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::f32) ? MVT::i32 : MVT::i64;
6911  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, VT,
6912  DAG.getConstant(0, dl,
6913  EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6914  EltVT, NumElts)));
6915  }
6916  llvm_unreachable("Expected type!");
6917  }
6918 
6919  assert(!VT.isVector() && "Can't handle vector type here!");
6920  unsigned NumVTBits = VT.getSizeInBits();
6921  unsigned NumVTBytes = NumVTBits / 8;
6922  unsigned NumBytes = std::min(NumVTBytes, unsigned(Slice.Length));
6923 
6924  APInt Val(NumVTBits, 0);
6925  if (DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian()) {
6926  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumBytes; ++i)
6927  Val |= (uint64_t)(unsigned char)Slice[i] << i*8;
6928  } else {
6929  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumBytes; ++i)
6930  Val |= (uint64_t)(unsigned char)Slice[i] << (NumVTBytes-i-1)*8;
6931  }
6932 
6933  // If the "cost" of materializing the integer immediate is less than the cost
6934  // of a load, then it is cost effective to turn the load into the immediate.
6935  Type *Ty = VT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
6936  if (TLI.shouldConvertConstantLoadToIntImm(Val, Ty))
6937  return DAG.getConstant(Val, dl, VT);
6938  return SDValue();
6939 }
6940 
6941 SDValue SelectionDAG::getMemBasePlusOffset(SDValue Base, TypeSize Offset,
6942  const SDLoc &DL,
6943  const SDNodeFlags Flags) {
6944  EVT VT = Base.getValueType();
6945  SDValue Index;
6946 
6947  if (Offset.isScalable())
6948  Index = getVScale(DL, Base.getValueType(),
6949  APInt(Base.getValueSizeInBits().getFixedValue(),
6950  Offset.getKnownMinValue()));
6951  else
6952  Index = getConstant(Offset.getFixedValue(), DL, VT);
6953 
6954  return getMemBasePlusOffset(Base, Index, DL, Flags);
6955 }
6956 
6957 SDValue SelectionDAG::getMemBasePlusOffset(SDValue Ptr, SDValue Offset,
6958  const SDLoc &DL,
6959  const SDNodeFlags Flags) {
6960  assert(Offset.getValueType().isInteger());
6961  EVT BasePtrVT = Ptr.getValueType();
6962  return getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, BasePtrVT, Ptr, Offset, Flags);
6963 }
6964 
6965 /// Returns true if memcpy source is constant data.
6966 static bool isMemSrcFromConstant(SDValue Src, ConstantDataArraySlice &Slice) {
6967  uint64_t SrcDelta = 0;
6968  GlobalAddressSDNode *G = nullptr;
6969  if (Src.getOpcode() == ISD::GlobalAddress)
6970  G = cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Src);
6971  else if (Src.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD &&
6972  Src.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::GlobalAddress &&
6973  Src.getOperand(1).getOpcode() == ISD::Constant) {
6974  G = cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Src.getOperand(0));
6975  SrcDelta = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Src.getOperand(1))->getZExtValue();
6976  }
6977  if (!G)
6978  return false;
6979 
6980  return getConstantDataArrayInfo(G->getGlobal(), Slice, 8,
6981  SrcDelta + G->getOffset());
6982 }
6983 
6984 static bool shouldLowerMemFuncForSize(const MachineFunction &MF,
6985  SelectionDAG &DAG) {
