6986  // On Darwin, -Os means optimize for size without hurting performance, so
6987  // only really optimize for size when -Oz (MinSize) is used.
6988  if (MF.getTarget().getTargetTriple().isOSDarwin())
6989  return MF.getFunction().hasMinSize();
6990  return DAG.shouldOptForSize();
6991 }
6992 
6993 static void chainLoadsAndStoresForMemcpy(SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &dl,
6994  SmallVector<SDValue, 32> &OutChains, unsigned From,
6995  unsigned To, SmallVector<SDValue, 16> &OutLoadChains,
6996  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> &OutStoreChains) {
6997  assert(OutLoadChains.size() && "Missing loads in memcpy inlining");
6998  assert(OutStoreChains.size() && "Missing stores in memcpy inlining");
6999  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> GluedLoadChains;
7000  for (unsigned i = From; i < To; ++i) {
7001  OutChains.push_back(OutLoadChains[i]);
7002  GluedLoadChains.push_back(OutLoadChains[i]);
7003  }
7004 
7005  // Chain for all loads.
7006  SDValue LoadToken = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other,
7007  GluedLoadChains);
7008 
7009  for (unsigned i = From; i < To; ++i) {
7010  StoreSDNode *ST = dyn_cast<StoreSDNode>(OutStoreChains[i]);
7011  SDValue NewStore = DAG.getTruncStore(LoadToken, dl, ST->getValue(),
7012  ST->getBasePtr(), ST->getMemoryVT(),
7013  ST->getMemOperand());
7014  OutChains.push_back(NewStore);
7015  }
7016 }
7017 
7018 static SDValue getMemcpyLoadsAndStores(SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &dl,
7019  SDValue Chain, SDValue Dst, SDValue Src,
7020  uint64_t Size, Align Alignment,
7021  bool isVol, bool AlwaysInline,
7022  MachinePointerInfo DstPtrInfo,
7023  MachinePointerInfo SrcPtrInfo,
7024  const AAMDNodes &AAInfo, AAResults *AA) {
7025  // Turn a memcpy of undef to nop.
7026  // FIXME: We need to honor volatile even is Src is undef.
7027  if (Src.isUndef())
7028  return Chain;
7029 
7030  // Expand memcpy to a series of load and store ops if the size operand falls
7031  // below a certain threshold.
7032  // TODO: In the AlwaysInline case, if the size is big then generate a loop
7033  // rather than maybe a humongous number of loads and stores.
7034  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
7035  const DataLayout &DL = DAG.getDataLayout();
7036  LLVMContext &C = *DAG.getContext();
7037  std::vector<EVT> MemOps;
7038  bool DstAlignCanChange = false;
7039  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
7040  MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
7041  bool OptSize = shouldLowerMemFuncForSize(MF, DAG);
7042  FrameIndexSDNode *FI = dyn_cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(Dst);
7043  if (FI && !MFI.isFixedObjectIndex(FI->getIndex()))
7044  DstAlignCanChange = true;
7045  MaybeAlign SrcAlign = DAG.InferPtrAlign(Src);
7046  if (!SrcAlign || Alignment > *SrcAlign)
7047  SrcAlign = Alignment;
7048  assert(SrcAlign && "SrcAlign must be set");
7049  ConstantDataArraySlice Slice;
7050  // If marked as volatile, perform a copy even when marked as constant.
7051  bool CopyFromConstant = !isVol && isMemSrcFromConstant(Src, Slice);
7052  bool isZeroConstant = CopyFromConstant && Slice.Array == nullptr;
7053  unsigned Limit = AlwaysInline ? ~0U : TLI.getMaxStoresPerMemcpy(OptSize);
7054  const MemOp Op = isZeroConstant
7055  ? MemOp::Set(Size, DstAlignCanChange, Alignment,
7056  /*IsZeroMemset*/ true, isVol)
7057  : MemOp::Copy(Size, DstAlignCanChange, Alignment,
7058  *SrcAlign, isVol, CopyFromConstant);
7059  if (!TLI.findOptimalMemOpLowering(
7060  MemOps, Limit, Op, DstPtrInfo.getAddrSpace(),
7061  SrcPtrInfo.getAddrSpace(), MF.getFunction().getAttributes()))
7062  return SDValue();
7063 
7064  if (DstAlignCanChange) {
7065  Type *Ty = MemOps[0].getTypeForEVT(C);
7066  Align NewAlign = DL.getABITypeAlign(Ty);
7067 
7068  // Don't promote to an alignment that would require dynamic stack
7069  // realignment which may conflict with optimizations such as tail call
7070  // optimization.
7071  const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo();
7072  if (!TRI->hasStackRealignment(MF))
7073  while (NewAlign > Alignment && DL.exceedsNaturalStackAlignment(NewAlign))
7074  NewAlign = NewAlign.previous();
7075 
7076  if (NewAlign > Alignment) {
7077  // Give the stack frame object a larger alignment if needed.
7078  if (MFI.getObjectAlign(FI->getIndex()) < NewAlign)
7079  MFI.setObjectAlignment(FI->getIndex(), NewAlign);
7080  Alignment = NewAlign;
7081  }
7082  }
7083 
7084  // Prepare AAInfo for loads/stores after lowering this memcpy.
7085  AAMDNodes NewAAInfo = AAInfo;
7086  NewAAInfo.TBAA = NewAAInfo.TBAAStruct = nullptr;
7087 
7088  const Value *SrcVal = SrcPtrInfo.V.dyn_cast<const Value *>();
7089  bool isConstant =
7090  AA && SrcVal &&
7091  AA->pointsToConstantMemory(MemoryLocation(SrcVal, Size, AAInfo));
7092 
7093  MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags =
7094  isVol ? MachineMemOperand::MOVolatile : MachineMemOperand::MONone;
7095  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> OutLoadChains;
7096  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> OutStoreChains;
7097  SmallVector<SDValue, 32> OutChains;
7098  unsigned NumMemOps = MemOps.size();
7099  uint64_t SrcOff = 0, DstOff = 0;
7100  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumMemOps; ++i) {
7101  EVT VT = MemOps[i];
7102  unsigned VTSize = VT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
7103  SDValue Value, Store;
7104 
7105  if (VTSize > Size) {
7106  // Issuing an unaligned load / store pair that overlaps with the previous
7107  // pair. Adjust the offset accordingly.
7108  assert(i == NumMemOps-1 && i != 0);
7109  SrcOff -= VTSize - Size;
7110  DstOff -= VTSize - Size;
7111  }
7112 
7113  if (CopyFromConstant &&
7114  (isZeroConstant || (VT.isInteger() && !VT.isVector()))) {
7115  // It's unlikely a store of a vector immediate can be done in a single
7116  // instruction. It would require a load from a constantpool first.
7117  // We only handle zero vectors here.
7118  // FIXME: Handle other cases where store of vector immediate is done in
7119  // a single instruction.
7120  ConstantDataArraySlice SubSlice;
7121  if (SrcOff < Slice.Length) {
7122  SubSlice = Slice;
7123  SubSlice.move(SrcOff);
7124  } else {
7125  // This is an out-of-bounds access and hence UB. Pretend we read zero.
7126  SubSlice.Array = nullptr;
7127  SubSlice.Offset = 0;
7128  SubSlice.Length = VTSize;
7129  }
7130  Value = getMemsetStringVal(VT, dl, DAG, TLI, SubSlice);
7131  if (Value.getNode()) {
7132  Store = DAG.getStore(
7133  Chain, dl, Value,
7134  DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(Dst, TypeSize::Fixed(DstOff), dl),
7135  DstPtrInfo.getWithOffset(DstOff), Alignment, MMOFlags, NewAAInfo);
7136  OutChains.push_back(Store);
7137  }
7138  }
7139 
7140  if (!Store.getNode()) {
7141  // The type might not be legal for the target. This should only happen
7142  // if the type is smaller than a legal type, as on PPC, so the right
7143  // thing to do is generate a LoadExt/StoreTrunc pair. These simplify
7144  // to Load/Store if NVT==VT.
7145  // FIXME does the case above also need this?
7146  EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(C, VT);
7147  assert(NVT.bitsGE(VT));
7148 
7149  bool isDereferenceable =
7150  SrcPtrInfo.getWithOffset(SrcOff).isDereferenceable(VTSize, C, DL);
7151  MachineMemOperand::Flags SrcMMOFlags = MMOFlags;
7152  if (isDereferenceable)
7153  SrcMMOFlags |= MachineMemOperand::MODereferenceable;
7154  if (isConstant)
7155  SrcMMOFlags |= MachineMemOperand::MOInvariant;
7156 
7157  Value = DAG.getExtLoad(
7158  ISD::EXTLOAD, dl, NVT, Chain,
7159  DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(Src, TypeSize::Fixed(SrcOff), dl),
7160  SrcPtrInfo.getWithOffset(SrcOff), VT,
7161  commonAlignment(*SrcAlign, SrcOff), SrcMMOFlags, NewAAInfo);
7162  OutLoadChains.push_back(Value.getValue(1));
7163 
7164  Store = DAG.getTruncStore(
7165  Chain, dl, Value,
7166  DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(Dst, TypeSize::Fixed(DstOff), dl),
7167  DstPtrInfo.getWithOffset(DstOff), VT, Alignment, MMOFlags, NewAAInfo);
7168  OutStoreChains.push_back(Store);
7169  }
7170  SrcOff += VTSize;
7171  DstOff += VTSize;
7172  Size -= VTSize;
7173  }
7174 
7175  unsigned GluedLdStLimit = MaxLdStGlue == 0 ?
7176  TLI.getMaxGluedStoresPerMemcpy() : MaxLdStGlue;
7177  unsigned NumLdStInMemcpy = OutStoreChains.size();
7178 
7179  if (NumLdStInMemcpy) {
7180  // It may be that memcpy might be converted to memset if it's memcpy
7181  // of constants. In such a case, we won't have loads and stores, but
7182  // just stores. In the absence of loads, there is nothing to gang up.
7183  if ((GluedLdStLimit <= 1) || !EnableMemCpyDAGOpt) {
7184  // If target does not care, just leave as it.
7185  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumLdStInMemcpy; ++i) {
7186  OutChains.push_back(OutLoadChains[i]);
7187  OutChains.push_back(OutStoreChains[i]);
7188  }
7189  } else {
7190  // Ld/St less than/equal limit set by target.
7191  if (NumLdStInMemcpy <= GluedLdStLimit) {
7192  chainLoadsAndStoresForMemcpy(DAG, dl, OutChains, 0,
7193  NumLdStInMemcpy, OutLoadChains,
7194  OutStoreChains);
7195  } else {
7196  unsigned NumberLdChain = NumLdStInMemcpy / GluedLdStLimit;
7197  unsigned RemainingLdStInMemcpy = NumLdStInMemcpy % GluedLdStLimit;
7198  unsigned GlueIter = 0;
7199 
7200  for (unsigned cnt = 0; cnt < NumberLdChain; ++cnt) {
7201  unsigned IndexFrom = NumLdStInMemcpy - GlueIter - GluedLdStLimit;
7202  unsigned IndexTo = NumLdStInMemcpy - GlueIter;
7203 
7204  chainLoadsAndStoresForMemcpy(DAG, dl, OutChains, IndexFrom, IndexTo,
7205  OutLoadChains, OutStoreChains);
7206  GlueIter += GluedLdStLimit;
7207  }
7208 
7209  // Residual ld/st.
7210  if (RemainingLdStInMemcpy) {
7211  chainLoadsAndStoresForMemcpy(DAG, dl, OutChains, 0,
7212  RemainingLdStInMemcpy, OutLoadChains,
7213  OutStoreChains);
7214  }
7215  }
7216  }
7217  }
7218  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, OutChains);
7219 }
7220 
7221 static SDValue getMemmoveLoadsAndStores(SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &dl,
7222  SDValue Chain, SDValue Dst, SDValue Src,
7223  uint64_t Size, Align Alignment,
7224  bool isVol, bool AlwaysInline,
7225  MachinePointerInfo DstPtrInfo,
7226  MachinePointerInfo SrcPtrInfo,
7227  const AAMDNodes &AAInfo) {
7228  // Turn a memmove of undef to nop.
7229  // FIXME: We need to honor volatile even is Src is undef.
7230  if (Src.isUndef())
7231  return Chain;
7232 
7233  // Expand memmove to a series of load and store ops if the size operand falls
7234  // below a certain threshold.
7235  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
7236  const DataLayout &DL = DAG.getDataLayout();
7237  LLVMContext &C = *DAG.getContext();
7238  std::vector<EVT> MemOps;
7239  bool DstAlignCanChange = false;
7240  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
7241  MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
7242  bool OptSize = shouldLowerMemFuncForSize(MF, DAG);
7243  FrameIndexSDNode *FI = dyn_cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(Dst);
7244  if (FI && !MFI.isFixedObjectIndex(FI->getIndex()))
7245  DstAlignCanChange = true;
7246  MaybeAlign SrcAlign = DAG.InferPtrAlign(Src);
7247  if (!SrcAlign || Alignment > *SrcAlign)
7248  SrcAlign = Alignment;
7249  assert(SrcAlign && "SrcAlign must be set");
7250  unsigned Limit = AlwaysInline ? ~0U : TLI.getMaxStoresPerMemmove(OptSize);
7251  if (!TLI.findOptimalMemOpLowering(
7252  MemOps, Limit,
7253  MemOp::Copy(Size, DstAlignCanChange, Alignment, *SrcAlign,
7254  /*IsVolatile*/ true),
7255  DstPtrInfo.getAddrSpace(), SrcPtrInfo.getAddrSpace(),
7256  MF.getFunction().getAttributes()))
7257  return SDValue();
7258 
7259  if (DstAlignCanChange) {
7260  Type *Ty = MemOps[0].getTypeForEVT(C);
7261  Align NewAlign = DL.getABITypeAlign(Ty);
7262 
7263  // Don't promote to an alignment that would require dynamic stack
7264  // realignment which may conflict with optimizations such as tail call
7265  // optimization.
7266  const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo();
7267  if (!TRI->hasStackRealignment(MF))
7268  while (NewAlign > Alignment && DL.exceedsNaturalStackAlignment(NewAlign))
7269  NewAlign = NewAlign.previous();
7270 
7271  if (NewAlign > Alignment) {
7272  // Give the stack frame object a larger alignment if needed.
7273  if (MFI.getObjectAlign(FI->getIndex()) < NewAlign)
7274  MFI.setObjectAlignment(FI->getIndex(), NewAlign);
7275  Alignment = NewAlign;
7276  }
7277  }
7278 
7279  // Prepare AAInfo for loads/stores after lowering this memmove.
7280  AAMDNodes NewAAInfo = AAInfo;
7281  NewAAInfo.TBAA = NewAAInfo.TBAAStruct = nullptr;
7282 
7283  MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags =
7284  isVol ? MachineMemOperand::MOVolatile : MachineMemOperand::MONone;
7285  uint64_t SrcOff = 0, DstOff = 0;
7286  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> LoadValues;
7287  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> LoadChains;
7288  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> OutChains;
7289  unsigned NumMemOps = MemOps.size();
7290  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumMemOps; i++) {
7291  EVT VT = MemOps[i];
7292  unsigned VTSize = VT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
7293  SDValue Value;
7294 
7295  bool isDereferenceable =
7296  SrcPtrInfo.getWithOffset(SrcOff).isDereferenceable(VTSize, C, DL);
7297  MachineMemOperand::Flags SrcMMOFlags = MMOFlags;
7298  if (isDereferenceable)
7299  SrcMMOFlags |= MachineMemOperand::MODereferenceable;
7300 
7301  Value = DAG.getLoad(
7302  VT, dl, Chain,
7303  DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(Src, TypeSize::Fixed(SrcOff), dl),
7304  SrcPtrInfo.getWithOffset(SrcOff), *SrcAlign, SrcMMOFlags, NewAAInfo);
7305  LoadValues.push_back(Value);
7306  LoadChains.push_back(Value.getValue(1));
7307  SrcOff += VTSize;
7308  }
7309  Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, LoadChains);
7310  OutChains.clear();
7311  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumMemOps; i++) {
7312  EVT VT = MemOps[i];
7313  unsigned VTSize = VT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
7314  SDValue Store;
7315 
7316  Store = DAG.getStore(
7317  Chain, dl, LoadValues[i],
7318  DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(Dst, TypeSize::Fixed(DstOff), dl),
7319  DstPtrInfo.getWithOffset(DstOff), Alignment, MMOFlags, NewAAInfo);
7320  OutChains.push_back(Store);
7321  DstOff += VTSize;
7322  }
7323 
7324  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, OutChains);
7325 }
7326 
7327 /// Lower the call to 'memset' intrinsic function into a series of store
7328 /// operations.
7329 ///
7330 /// \param DAG Selection DAG where lowered code is placed.
7331 /// \param dl Link to corresponding IR location.
7332 /// \param Chain Control flow dependency.
7333 /// \param Dst Pointer to destination memory location.
7334 /// \param Src Value of byte to write into the memory.
7335 /// \param Size Number of bytes to write.
7336 /// \param Alignment Alignment of the destination in bytes.
7337 /// \param isVol True if destination is volatile.
7338 /// \param AlwaysInline Makes sure no function call is generated.
7339 /// \param DstPtrInfo IR information on the memory pointer.
7340 /// \returns New head in the control flow, if lowering was successful, empty
7341 /// SDValue otherwise.
7342 ///
7343 /// The function tries to replace 'llvm.memset' intrinsic with several store
7344 /// operations and value calculation code. This is usually profitable for small
7345 /// memory size or when the semantic requires inlining.
7346 static SDValue getMemsetStores(SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &dl,
7347  SDValue Chain, SDValue Dst, SDValue Src,
7348  uint64_t Size, Align Alignment, bool isVol,
7349  bool AlwaysInline, MachinePointerInfo DstPtrInfo,
7350  const AAMDNodes &AAInfo) {
7351  // Turn a memset of undef to nop.
7352  // FIXME: We need to honor volatile even is Src is undef.
7353  if (Src.isUndef())
7354  return Chain;
7355 
7356  // Expand memset to a series of load/store ops if the size operand
7357  // falls below a certain threshold.
7358  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
7359  std::vector<EVT> MemOps;
7360  bool DstAlignCanChange = false;
7361  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
7362  MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
7363  bool OptSize = shouldLowerMemFuncForSize(MF, DAG);
7364  FrameIndexSDNode *FI = dyn_cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(Dst);
7365  if (FI && !MFI.isFixedObjectIndex(FI->getIndex()))
7366  DstAlignCanChange = true;
7367  bool IsZeroVal =
7368  isa<ConstantSDNode>(Src) && cast<ConstantSDNode>(Src)->isZero();
7369  unsigned Limit = AlwaysInline ? ~0 : TLI.getMaxStoresPerMemset(OptSize);
7370 
7371  if (!TLI.findOptimalMemOpLowering(
7372  MemOps, Limit,
7373  MemOp::Set(Size, DstAlignCanChange, Alignment, IsZeroVal, isVol),
7374  DstPtrInfo.getAddrSpace(), ~0u, MF.getFunction().getAttributes()))
7375  return SDValue();
7376 
7377  if (DstAlignCanChange) {
7378  Type *Ty = MemOps[0].getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
7379  const DataLayout &DL = DAG.getDataLayout();
7380  Align NewAlign = DL.getABITypeAlign(Ty);
7381 
7382  // Don't promote to an alignment that would require dynamic stack
7383  // realignment which may conflict with optimizations such as tail call
7384  // optimization.
7385  const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo();
7386  if (!TRI->hasStackRealignment(MF))
7387  while (NewAlign > Alignment && DL.exceedsNaturalStackAlignment(NewAlign))
7388  NewAlign = NewAlign.previous();
7389 
7390  if (NewAlign > Alignment) {
7391  // Give the stack frame object a larger alignment if needed.
7392  if (MFI.getObjectAlign(FI->getIndex()) < NewAlign)
7393  MFI.setObjectAlignment(FI->getIndex(), NewAlign);
7394  Alignment = NewAlign;
7395  }
7396  }
7397 
7398  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> OutChains;
7399  uint64_t DstOff = 0;
7400  unsigned NumMemOps = MemOps.size();
7401 
7402  // Find the largest store and generate the bit pattern for it.
7403  EVT LargestVT = MemOps[0];
7404  for (unsigned i = 1; i < NumMemOps; i++)
7405  if (MemOps[i].bitsGT(LargestVT))
7406  LargestVT = MemOps[i];
7407  SDValue MemSetValue = getMemsetValue(Src, LargestVT, DAG, dl);
7408 
7409  // Prepare AAInfo for loads/stores after lowering this memset.
7410  AAMDNodes NewAAInfo = AAInfo;
7411  NewAAInfo.TBAA = NewAAInfo.TBAAStruct = nullptr;
7412 
7413  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumMemOps; i++) {
7414  EVT VT = MemOps[i];
7415  unsigned VTSize = VT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
7416  if (VTSize > Size) {
7417  // Issuing an unaligned load / store pair that overlaps with the previous
7418  // pair. Adjust the offset accordingly.
7419  assert(i == NumMemOps-1 && i != 0);
7420  DstOff -= VTSize - Size;
7421  }
7422 
7423  // If this store is smaller than the largest store see whether we can get
7424  // the smaller value for free with a truncate.
7425  SDValue Value = MemSetValue;
7426  if (VT.bitsLT(LargestVT)) {
7427  if (!LargestVT.isVector() && !VT.isVector() &&
7428  TLI.isTruncateFree(LargestVT, VT))
7429  Value = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, VT, MemSetValue);
7430  else
7431  Value = getMemsetValue(Src, VT, DAG, dl);
7432  }
7433  assert(Value.getValueType() == VT && "Value with wrong type.");
7434  SDValue Store = DAG.getStore(
7435  Chain, dl, Value,
7436  DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(Dst, TypeSize::Fixed(DstOff), dl),
7437  DstPtrInfo.getWithOffset(DstOff), Alignment,
7438  isVol ? MachineMemOperand::MOVolatile : MachineMemOperand::MONone,
7439  NewAAInfo);
7440  OutChains.push_back(Store);
7441  DstOff += VT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
7442  Size -= VTSize;
7443  }
7444 
7445  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, OutChains);
7446 }
7447 
7448 static void checkAddrSpaceIsValidForLibcall(const TargetLowering *TLI,
7449  unsigned AS) {
7450  // Lowering memcpy / memset / memmove intrinsics to calls is only valid if all
7451  // pointer operands can be losslessly bitcasted to pointers of address space 0
7452  if (AS != 0 && !TLI->getTargetMachine().isNoopAddrSpaceCast(AS, 0)) {
7453  report_fatal_error("cannot lower memory intrinsic in address space " +
7454  Twine(AS));
7455  }
7456 }
7457 
7458 SDValue SelectionDAG::getMemcpy(SDValue Chain, const SDLoc &dl, SDValue Dst,
7459  SDValue Src, SDValue Size, Align Alignment,
7460  bool isVol, bool AlwaysInline, bool isTailCall,
7461  MachinePointerInfo DstPtrInfo,
7462  MachinePointerInfo SrcPtrInfo,
7463  const AAMDNodes &AAInfo, AAResults *AA) {
7464  // Check to see if we should lower the memcpy to loads and stores first.
7465  // For cases within the target-specified limits, this is the best choice.
7466  ConstantSDNode *ConstantSize = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Size);
7467  if (ConstantSize) {
7468  // Memcpy with size zero? Just return the original chain.
7469  if (ConstantSize->isZero())
7470  return Chain;
7471 
7472  SDValue Result = getMemcpyLoadsAndStores(
7473  *this, dl, Chain, Dst, Src, ConstantSize->getZExtValue(), Alignment,
7474  isVol, false, DstPtrInfo, SrcPtrInfo, AAInfo, AA);
7475  if (Result.getNode())
7476  return Result;
7477  }
7478 
7479  // Then check to see if we should lower the memcpy with target-specific
7480  // code. If the target chooses to do this, this is the next best.
7481  if (TSI) {
7482  SDValue Result = TSI->EmitTargetCodeForMemcpy(
7483  *this, dl, Chain, Dst, Src, Size, Alignment, isVol, AlwaysInline,
7484  DstPtrInfo, SrcPtrInfo);
7485  if (Result.getNode())
7486  return Result;
7487  }
7488 
7489  // If we really need inline code and the target declined to provide it,
7490  // use a (potentially long) sequence of loads and stores.
7491  if (AlwaysInline) {
7492  assert(ConstantSize && "AlwaysInline requires a constant size!");
7493  return getMemcpyLoadsAndStores(
7494  *this, dl, Chain, Dst, Src, ConstantSize->getZExtValue(), Alignment,
7495  isVol, true, DstPtrInfo, SrcPtrInfo, AAInfo, AA);
7496  }
7497 
7498  checkAddrSpaceIsValidForLibcall(TLI, DstPtrInfo.getAddrSpace());
7499  checkAddrSpaceIsValidForLibcall(TLI, SrcPtrInfo.getAddrSpace());
7500 
7501  // FIXME: If the memcpy is volatile (isVol), lowering it to a plain libc
7502  // memcpy is not guaranteed to be safe. libc memcpys aren't required to
7503  // respect volatile, so they may do things like read or write memory
7504  // beyond the given memory regions. But fixing this isn't easy, and most
7505  // people don't care.
7506 
7507  // Emit a library call.
7508  TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args;
7509  TargetLowering::ArgListEntry Entry;
7510  Entry.Ty = Type::getInt8PtrTy(*getContext());
7511  Entry.Node = Dst; Args.push_back(Entry);
7512  Entry.Node = Src; Args.push_back(Entry);
7513 
7514  Entry.Ty = getDataLayout().getIntPtrType(*getContext());
7515  Entry.Node = Size; Args.push_back(Entry);
7516  // FIXME: pass in SDLoc
7517  TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(*this);
7518  CLI.setDebugLoc(dl)
7519  .setChain(Chain)
7520  .setLibCallee(TLI->getLibcallCallingConv(RTLIB::MEMCPY),
7521  Dst.getValueType().getTypeForEVT(*getContext()),
7522  getExternalSymbol(TLI->getLibcallName(RTLIB::MEMCPY),
7523  TLI->getPointerTy(getDataLayout())),
7524  std::move(Args))
7525  .setDiscardResult()
7526  .setTailCall(isTailCall);
7527 
7528  std::pair<SDValue,SDValue> CallResult = TLI->LowerCallTo(CLI);
7529  return CallResult.second;
7530 }
7531 
7532 SDValue SelectionDAG::getAtomicMemcpy(SDValue Chain, const SDLoc &dl,
7533  SDValue Dst, SDValue Src, SDValue Size,
7534  Type *SizeTy, unsigned ElemSz,
7535  bool isTailCall,
7536  MachinePointerInfo DstPtrInfo,
7537  MachinePointerInfo SrcPtrInfo) {
7538  // Emit a library call.
7539  TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args;
7540  TargetLowering::ArgListEntry Entry;
7541  Entry.Ty = getDataLayout().getIntPtrType(*getContext());
7542  Entry.Node = Dst;
7543  Args.push_back(Entry);
7544 
7545  Entry.Node = Src;
7546  Args.push_back(Entry);
7547 
7548  Entry.Ty = SizeTy;
7549  Entry.Node = Size;
7550  Args.push_back(Entry);
7551 
7552  RTLIB::Libcall LibraryCall =
7553  RTLIB::getMEMCPY_ELEMENT_UNORDERED_ATOMIC(ElemSz);
7554  if (LibraryCall == RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL)
7555  report_fatal_error("Unsupported element size");
7556 
7557  TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(*this);
7558  CLI.setDebugLoc(dl)
7559  .setChain(Chain)
7560  .setLibCallee(TLI->getLibcallCallingConv(LibraryCall),
7561  Type::getVoidTy(*getContext()),
7562  getExternalSymbol(TLI->getLibcallName(LibraryCall),
7563  TLI->getPointerTy(getDataLayout())),
7564  std::move(Args))
7565  .setDiscardResult()
7566  .setTailCall(isTailCall);
7567 
7568  std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> CallResult = TLI->LowerCallTo(CLI);
7569  return CallResult.second;
7570 }

7674 SDValue SelectionDAG::getMemset(SDValue Chain, const SDLoc &dl, SDValue Dst,
7675  SDValue Src, SDValue Size, Align Alignment,
7676  bool isVol, bool AlwaysInline, bool isTailCall,
7677  MachinePointerInfo DstPtrInfo,
7678  const AAMDNodes &AAInfo) {
7679  // Check to see if we should lower the memset to stores first.
7680  // For cases within the target-specified limits, this is the best choice.
7681  ConstantSDNode *ConstantSize = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Size);
7682  if (ConstantSize) {
7683  // Memset with size zero? Just return the original chain.
7684  if (ConstantSize->isZero())
7685  return Chain;
7686 
7687  SDValue Result = getMemsetStores(*this, dl, Chain, Dst, Src,
7688  ConstantSize->getZExtValue(), Alignment,
7689  isVol, false, DstPtrInfo, AAInfo);
7690 
7691  if (Result.getNode())
7692  return Result;
7693  }
7694 
7695  // Then check to see if we should lower the memset with target-specific
7696  // code. If the target chooses to do this, this is the next best.
7697  if (TSI) {
7698  SDValue Result = TSI->EmitTargetCodeForMemset(
7699  *this, dl, Chain, Dst, Src, Size, Alignment, isVol, AlwaysInline, DstPtrInfo);
7700  if (Result.getNode())
7701  return Result;
7702  }
7703 
7704  // If we really need inline code and the target declined to provide it,
7705  // use a (potentially long) sequence of loads and stores.
7706  if (AlwaysInline) {
7707  assert(ConstantSize && "AlwaysInline requires a constant size!");
7708  SDValue Result = getMemsetStores(*this, dl, Chain, Dst, Src,
7709  ConstantSize->getZExtValue(), Alignment,
7710  isVol, true, DstPtrInfo, AAInfo);
7711  assert(Result &&
7712  "getMemsetStores must return a valid sequence when AlwaysInline");
7713  return Result;
7714  }
7715 
7716  checkAddrSpaceIsValidForLibcall(TLI, DstPtrInfo.getAddrSpace());
7717 
7718  // Emit a library call.
7719  auto &Ctx = *getContext();
7720  const auto& DL = getDataLayout();
7721 
7722  TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(*this);
7723  // FIXME: pass in SDLoc
7724  CLI.setDebugLoc(dl).setChain(Chain);
7725 
7726  ConstantSDNode *ConstantSrc = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Src);
7727  const bool SrcIsZero = ConstantSrc && ConstantSrc->isZero();
7728  const char *BzeroName = getTargetLoweringInfo().getLibcallName(RTLIB::BZERO);
7729 
7730  // Helper function to create an Entry from Node and Type.
7731  const auto CreateEntry = [](SDValue Node, Type *Ty) {
7732  TargetLowering::ArgListEntry Entry;
7733  Entry.Node = Node;
7734  Entry.Ty = Ty;
7735  return Entry;
7736  };
7737 
7738  // If zeroing out and bzero is present, use it.
7739  if (SrcIsZero && BzeroName) {
7740  TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args;
7741  Args.push_back(CreateEntry(Dst, Type::getInt8PtrTy(Ctx)));
7742  Args.push_back(CreateEntry(Size, DL.getIntPtrType(Ctx)));
7743  CLI.setLibCallee(
7744  TLI->getLibcallCallingConv(RTLIB::BZERO), Type::getVoidTy(Ctx),
7745  getExternalSymbol(BzeroName, TLI->getPointerTy(DL)), std::move(Args));
7746  } else {
7747  TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args;
7748  Args.push_back(CreateEntry(Dst, Type::getInt8PtrTy(Ctx)));
7749  Args.push_back(CreateEntry(Src, Src.getValueType().getTypeForEVT(Ctx)));
7750  Args.push_back(CreateEntry(Size, DL.getIntPtrType(Ctx)));
7751  CLI.setLibCallee(TLI->getLibcallCallingConv(RTLIB::MEMSET),
7752  Dst.getValueType().getTypeForEVT(Ctx),
7753  getExternalSymbol(TLI->getLibcallName(RTLIB::MEMSET),
7754  TLI->getPointerTy(DL)),
7755  std::move(Args));
7756  }
7757 
7758  CLI.setDiscardResult().setTailCall(isTailCall);
7759 
7760  std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> CallResult = TLI->LowerCallTo(CLI);
7761  return CallResult.second;
7762 }

7766  Type *SizeTy, unsigned ElemSz,

7804 SDValue SelectionDAG::getAtomic(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &dl, EVT MemVT,
7805  SDVTList VTList, ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops,
7806  MachineMemOperand *MMO) {
7807  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
7808  ID.AddInteger(MemVT.getRawBits());
7809  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opcode, VTList, Ops);
7810  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
7811  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getFlags());
7812  void* IP = nullptr;
7813  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, dl, IP)) {
7814  cast<AtomicSDNode>(E)->refineAlignment(MMO);
7815  return SDValue(E, 0);
7816  }
7817 
7818  auto *N = newSDNode<AtomicSDNode>(Opcode, dl.getIROrder(), dl.getDebugLoc(),
7819  VTList, MemVT, MMO);
7820  createOperands(N, Ops);
7821 
7822  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
7823  InsertNode(N);
7824  return SDValue(N, 0);
7825 }

7827 SDValue SelectionDAG::getAtomicCmpSwap(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &dl,
7828  EVT MemVT, SDVTList VTs, SDValue Chain,
7829  SDValue Ptr, SDValue Cmp, SDValue Swp,
7830  MachineMemOperand *MMO) {
7831  assert(Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP ||
7832  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_WITH_SUCCESS);
7833  assert(Cmp.getValueType() == Swp.getValueType() && "Invalid Atomic Op Types");
7834 
7835  SDValue Ops[] = {Chain, Ptr, Cmp, Swp};
7836  return getAtomic(Opcode, dl, MemVT, VTs, Ops, MMO);
7837 }

7839 SDValue SelectionDAG::getAtomic(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &dl, EVT MemVT,
7840  SDValue Chain, SDValue Ptr, SDValue Val,
7841  MachineMemOperand *MMO) {
7842  assert((Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD ||
7843  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB ||
7844  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND ||
7845  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_CLR ||
7846  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR ||
7847  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR ||
7848  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND ||
7849  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN ||
7850  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX ||
7851  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN ||
7852  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX ||
7853  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_FADD ||
7854  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_FSUB ||
7855  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_FMAX ||
7856  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_FMIN ||
7857  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UINC_WRAP ||
7858  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UDEC_WRAP ||
7859  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP ||
7860  Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_STORE) &&
7861  "Invalid Atomic Op");
7862 
7863  EVT VT = Val.getValueType();
7864 
7865  SDVTList VTs = Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_STORE ? getVTList(MVT::Other) :
7866  getVTList(VT, MVT::Other);
7867  SDValue Ops[] = {Chain, Ptr, Val};
7868  return getAtomic(Opcode, dl, MemVT, VTs, Ops, MMO);
7869 }

7871 SDValue SelectionDAG::getAtomic(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &dl, EVT MemVT,
7872  EVT VT, SDValue Chain, SDValue Ptr,
7873  MachineMemOperand *MMO) {
7874  assert(Opcode == ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD && "Invalid Atomic Op");
7875 
7876  SDVTList VTs = getVTList(VT, MVT::Other);
7877  SDValue Ops[] = {Chain, Ptr};
7878  return getAtomic(Opcode, dl, MemVT, VTs, Ops, MMO);
7879 }

7881 /// getMergeValues - Create a MERGE_VALUES node from the given operands.
7882 SDValue SelectionDAG::getMergeValues(ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops, const SDLoc &dl) {
7883  if (Ops.size() == 1)
7884  return Ops[0];
7885 
7886  SmallVector<EVT, 4> VTs;
7887  VTs.reserve(Ops.size());
7888  for (const SDValue &Op : Ops)
7889  VTs.push_back(Op.getValueType());
7890  return getNode(ISD::MERGE_VALUES, dl, getVTList(VTs), Ops);
7891 }

7893 SDValue SelectionDAG::getMemIntrinsicNode(
7894  unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &dl, SDVTList VTList, ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops,
7895  EVT MemVT, MachinePointerInfo PtrInfo, Align Alignment,
7896  MachineMemOperand::Flags Flags, uint64_t Size, const AAMDNodes &AAInfo) {
7897  if (!Size && MemVT.isScalableVector())
7898  Size = MemoryLocation::UnknownSize;
7899  else if (!Size)
7900  Size = MemVT.getStoreSize();
7901 
7902  MachineFunction &MF = getMachineFunction();
7903  MachineMemOperand *MMO =
7904  MF.getMachineMemOperand(PtrInfo, Flags, Size, Alignment, AAInfo);
7905 
7906  return getMemIntrinsicNode(Opcode, dl, VTList, Ops, MemVT, MMO);
7907 }
7908 
7909 SDValue SelectionDAG::getMemIntrinsicNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &dl,
7910  SDVTList VTList,
7911  ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops, EVT MemVT,
7912  MachineMemOperand *MMO) {
7913  assert((Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID ||
7914  Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN ||
7915  Opcode == ISD::PREFETCH ||
7916  ((int)Opcode <= std::numeric_limits<int>::max() &&
7917  (int)Opcode >= ISD::FIRST_TARGET_MEMORY_OPCODE)) &&
7918  "Opcode is not a memory-accessing opcode!");
7919 
7920  // Memoize the node unless it returns a flag.
7921  MemIntrinsicSDNode *N;
7922  if (VTList.VTs[VTList.NumVTs-1] != MVT::Glue) {
7923  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
7924  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opcode, VTList, Ops);
7925  ID.AddInteger(getSyntheticNodeSubclassData<MemIntrinsicSDNode>(
7926  Opcode, dl.getIROrder(), VTList, MemVT, MMO));
7927  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
7928  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getFlags());
7929  void *IP = nullptr;
7930  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, dl, IP)) {
7931  cast<MemIntrinsicSDNode>(E)->refineAlignment(MMO);
7932  return SDValue(E, 0);
7933  }
7934 
7935  N = newSDNode<MemIntrinsicSDNode>(Opcode, dl.getIROrder(), dl.getDebugLoc(),
7936  VTList, MemVT, MMO);
7937  createOperands(N, Ops);
7938 
7939  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
7940  } else {
7941  N = newSDNode<MemIntrinsicSDNode>(Opcode, dl.getIROrder(), dl.getDebugLoc(),
7942  VTList, MemVT, MMO);
7943  createOperands(N, Ops);
7944  }
7945  InsertNode(N);
7946  SDValue V(N, 0);
7947  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
7948  return V;
7949 }
7950 
7951 SDValue SelectionDAG::getLifetimeNode(bool IsStart, const SDLoc &dl,
7952  SDValue Chain, int FrameIndex,
7953  int64_t Size, int64_t Offset) {
7954  const unsigned Opcode = IsStart ? ISD::LIFETIME_START : ISD::LIFETIME_END;
7955  const auto VTs = getVTList(MVT::Other);
7956  SDValue Ops[2] = {
7957  Chain,
7958  getFrameIndex(FrameIndex,
7959  getTargetLoweringInfo().getFrameIndexTy(getDataLayout()),
7960  true)};
7961 
7962  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
7963  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opcode, VTs, Ops);
7964  ID.AddInteger(FrameIndex);
7965  ID.AddInteger(Size);
7966  ID.AddInteger(Offset);
7967  void *IP = nullptr;
7968  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, dl, IP))
7969  return SDValue(E, 0);
7970 
7971  LifetimeSDNode *N = newSDNode<LifetimeSDNode>(
7972  Opcode, dl.getIROrder(), dl.getDebugLoc(), VTs, Size, Offset);
7973  createOperands(N, Ops);
7974  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
7975  InsertNode(N);
7976  SDValue V(N, 0);
7977  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
7978  return V;
7979 }

7981 SDValue SelectionDAG::getPseudoProbeNode(const SDLoc &Dl, SDValue Chain,
7982  uint64_t Guid, uint64_t Index,
7983  uint32_t Attr) {
7984  const unsigned Opcode = ISD::PSEUDO_PROBE;
7985  const auto VTs = getVTList(MVT::Other);
7986  SDValue Ops[] = {Chain};
7987  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
7988  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opcode, VTs, Ops);
7989  ID.AddInteger(Guid);
7990  ID.AddInteger(Index);
7991  void *IP = nullptr;
7992  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, Dl, IP))
7993  return SDValue(E, 0);
7994 
7995  auto *N = newSDNode<PseudoProbeSDNode>(
7996  Opcode, Dl.getIROrder(), Dl.getDebugLoc(), VTs, Guid, Index, Attr);
7997  createOperands(N, Ops);
7998  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
7999  InsertNode(N);
8000  SDValue V(N, 0);
8001  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
8002  return V;
8003 }
8004 
8005 /// InferPointerInfo - If the specified ptr/offset is a frame index, infer a
8006 /// MachinePointerInfo record from it. This is particularly useful because the
8007 /// code generator has many cases where it doesn't bother passing in a
8008 /// MachinePointerInfo to getLoad or getStore when it has "FI+Cst".
8009 static MachinePointerInfo InferPointerInfo(const MachinePointerInfo &Info,
8010  SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Ptr,
8011  int64_t Offset = 0) {
8012  // If this is FI+Offset, we can model it.
8013  if (const FrameIndexSDNode *FI = dyn_cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(Ptr))
8014  return MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(),
8015  FI->getIndex(), Offset);
8016 
8017  // If this is (FI+Offset1)+Offset2, we can model it.
8018  if (Ptr.getOpcode() != ISD::ADD ||
8019  !isa<ConstantSDNode>(Ptr.getOperand(1)) ||
8020  !isa<FrameIndexSDNode>(Ptr.getOperand(0)))
8021  return Info;
8022 
8023  int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(Ptr.getOperand(0))->getIndex();
8024  return MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(
8025  DAG.getMachineFunction(), FI,
8026  Offset + cast<ConstantSDNode>(Ptr.getOperand(1))->getSExtValue());
8027 }
8028 
8029 /// InferPointerInfo - If the specified ptr/offset is a frame index, infer a
8030 /// MachinePointerInfo record from it. This is particularly useful because the
8031 /// code generator has many cases where it doesn't bother passing in a
8032 /// MachinePointerInfo to getLoad or getStore when it has "FI+Cst".
8033 static MachinePointerInfo InferPointerInfo(const MachinePointerInfo &Info,
8034  SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Ptr,
8035  SDValue OffsetOp) {
8036  // If the 'Offset' value isn't a constant, we can't handle this.
8037  if (ConstantSDNode *OffsetNode = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(OffsetOp))
8038  return InferPointerInfo(Info, DAG, Ptr, OffsetNode->getSExtValue());
8039  if (OffsetOp.isUndef())
8040  return InferPointerInfo(Info, DAG, Ptr);
8041  return Info;
8042 }
8043 
8044 SDValue SelectionDAG::getLoad(ISD::MemIndexedMode AM, ISD::LoadExtType ExtType,
8045  EVT VT, const SDLoc &dl, SDValue Chain,
8046  SDValue Ptr, SDValue Offset,
8047  MachinePointerInfo PtrInfo, EVT MemVT,
8048  Align Alignment,
8049  MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags,
8050  const AAMDNodes &AAInfo, const MDNode *Ranges) {
8051  assert(Chain.getValueType() == MVT::Other &&
8052  "Invalid chain type");
8053 
8054  MMOFlags |= MachineMemOperand::MOLoad;
8055  assert((MMOFlags & MachineMemOperand::MOStore) == 0);
8056  // If we don't have a PtrInfo, infer the trivial frame index case to simplify
8057  // clients.
8058  if (PtrInfo.V.isNull())
8059  PtrInfo = InferPointerInfo(PtrInfo, *this, Ptr, Offset);
8060 
8061  uint64_t Size = MemoryLocation::getSizeOrUnknown(MemVT.getStoreSize());
8062  MachineFunction &MF = getMachineFunction();
8063  MachineMemOperand *MMO = MF.getMachineMemOperand(PtrInfo, MMOFlags, Size,
8064  Alignment, AAInfo, Ranges);
8065  return getLoad(AM, ExtType, VT, dl, Chain, Ptr, Offset, MemVT, MMO);
8066 }
8067 
8068 SDValue SelectionDAG::getLoad(ISD::MemIndexedMode AM, ISD::LoadExtType ExtType,
8069  EVT VT, const SDLoc &dl, SDValue Chain,
8070  SDValue Ptr, SDValue Offset, EVT MemVT,
8071  MachineMemOperand *MMO) {
8072  if (VT == MemVT) {
8073  ExtType = ISD::NON_EXTLOAD;
8074  } else if (ExtType == ISD::NON_EXTLOAD) {
8075  assert(VT == MemVT && "Non-extending load from different memory type!");
8076  } else {
8077  // Extending load.
8078  assert(MemVT.getScalarType().bitsLT(VT.getScalarType()) &&
8079  "Should only be an extending load, not truncating!");
8080  assert(VT.isInteger() == MemVT.isInteger() &&
8081  "Cannot convert from FP to Int or Int -> FP!");
8082  assert(VT.isVector() == MemVT.isVector() &&
8083  "Cannot use an ext load to convert to or from a vector!");
8084  assert((!VT.isVector() ||
8085  VT.getVectorElementCount() == MemVT.getVectorElementCount()) &&
8086  "Cannot use an ext load to change the number of vector elements!");
8087  }
8088 
8089  bool Indexed = AM != ISD::UNINDEXED;
8090  assert((Indexed || Offset.isUndef()) && "Unindexed load with an offset!");
8091 
8092  SDVTList VTs = Indexed ?
8093  getVTList(VT, Ptr.getValueType(), MVT::Other) : getVTList(VT, MVT::Other);
8094  SDValue Ops[] = { Chain, Ptr, Offset };
8095  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
8096  AddNodeIDNode(ID, ISD::LOAD, VTs, Ops);
8097  ID.AddInteger(MemVT.getRawBits());
8098  ID.AddInteger(getSyntheticNodeSubclassData<LoadSDNode>(
8099  dl.getIROrder(), VTs, AM, ExtType, MemVT, MMO));
8100  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
8101  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getFlags());
8102  void *IP = nullptr;
8103  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, dl, IP)) {
8104  cast<LoadSDNode>(E)->refineAlignment(MMO);
8105  return SDValue(E, 0);
8106  }
8107  auto *N = newSDNode<LoadSDNode>(dl.getIROrder(), dl.getDebugLoc(), VTs, AM,
8108  ExtType, MemVT, MMO);
8109  createOperands(N, Ops);
8110 
8111  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
8112  InsertNode(N);
8113  SDValue V(N, 0);
8114  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
8115  return V;
8116 }
8117 
8118 SDValue SelectionDAG::getLoad(EVT VT, const SDLoc &dl, SDValue Chain,
8119  SDValue Ptr, MachinePointerInfo PtrInfo,
8120  MaybeAlign Alignment,
8121  MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags,
8122  const AAMDNodes &AAInfo, const MDNode *Ranges) {
8123  SDValue Undef = getUNDEF(Ptr.getValueType());
8124  return getLoad(ISD::UNINDEXED, ISD::NON_EXTLOAD, VT, dl, Chain, Ptr, Undef,
8125  PtrInfo, VT, Alignment, MMOFlags, AAInfo, Ranges);
8126 }

8129  SDValue Ptr, MachineMemOperand *MMO) {
8130  SDValue Undef = getUNDEF(Ptr.getValueType());
8131  return getLoad(ISD::UNINDEXED, ISD::NON_EXTLOAD, VT, dl, Chain, Ptr, Undef,
8132  VT, MMO);
8133 }

8154 SDValue SelectionDAG::getIndexedLoad(SDValue OrigLoad, const SDLoc &dl,
8155  SDValue Base, SDValue Offset,
8156  ISD::MemIndexedMode AM) {
8157  LoadSDNode *LD = cast<LoadSDNode>(OrigLoad);
8158  assert(LD->getOffset().isUndef() && "Load is already a indexed load!");
8159  // Don't propagate the invariant or dereferenceable flags.
8160  auto MMOFlags =
8161  LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags() &
8162  ~(MachineMemOperand::MOInvariant | MachineMemOperand::MODereferenceable);
8163  return getLoad(AM, LD->getExtensionType(), OrigLoad.getValueType(), dl,
8164  LD->getChain(), Base, Offset, LD->getPointerInfo(),
8165  LD->getMemoryVT(), LD->getAlign(), MMOFlags, LD->getAAInfo());
8166 }

8168 SDValue SelectionDAG::getStore(SDValue Chain, const SDLoc &dl, SDValue Val,
8169  SDValue Ptr, MachinePointerInfo PtrInfo,
8170  Align Alignment,
8171  MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags,
8172  const AAMDNodes &AAInfo) {
8173  assert(Chain.getValueType() == MVT::Other && "Invalid chain type");
8174 
8175  MMOFlags |= MachineMemOperand::MOStore;
8176  assert((MMOFlags & MachineMemOperand::MOLoad) == 0);
8177 
8178  if (PtrInfo.V.isNull())
8179  PtrInfo = InferPointerInfo(PtrInfo, *this, Ptr);
8180 
8181  MachineFunction &MF = getMachineFunction();
8182  uint64_t Size =
8183  MemoryLocation::getSizeOrUnknown(Val.getValueType().getStoreSize());
8184  MachineMemOperand *MMO =
8185  MF.getMachineMemOperand(PtrInfo, MMOFlags, Size, Alignment, AAInfo);
8186  return getStore(Chain, dl, Val, Ptr, MMO);
8187 }

8189 SDValue SelectionDAG::getStore(SDValue Chain, const SDLoc &dl, SDValue Val,
8190  SDValue Ptr, MachineMemOperand *MMO) {

8192  "Invalid chain type");

8195  SDValue Undef = getUNDEF(Ptr.getValueType());
8196  SDValue Ops[] = { Chain, Val, Ptr, Undef };
8197  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
8198  AddNodeIDNode(ID, ISD::STORE, VTs, Ops);
8199  ID.AddInteger(VT.getRawBits());
8200  ID.AddInteger(getSyntheticNodeSubclassData<StoreSDNode>(
8201  dl.getIROrder(), VTs, ISD::UNINDEXED, false, VT, MMO));
8202  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
8203  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getFlags());
8204  void *IP = nullptr;
8205  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, dl, IP)) {
8206  cast<StoreSDNode>(E)->refineAlignment(MMO);
8207  return SDValue(E, 0);
8208  }
8209  auto *N = newSDNode<StoreSDNode>(dl.getIROrder(), dl.getDebugLoc(), VTs,
8210  ISD::UNINDEXED, false, VT, MMO);
8211  createOperands(N, Ops);
8212 
8213  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
8214  InsertNode(N);
8215  SDValue V(N, 0);
8216  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
8217  return V;
8218 }

8226  "Invalid chain type");

8229  assert((MMOFlags & MachineMemOperand::MOLoad) == 0);

8241 SDValue SelectionDAG::getTruncStore(SDValue Chain, const SDLoc &dl, SDValue Val,
8242  SDValue Ptr, EVT SVT,
8243  MachineMemOperand *MMO) {
8244  EVT VT = Val.getValueType();
8245 
8246  assert(Chain.getValueType() == MVT::Other &&
8247  "Invalid chain type");
8248  if (VT == SVT)
8249  return getStore(Chain, dl, Val, Ptr, MMO);
8250 
8251  assert(SVT.getScalarType().bitsLT(VT.getScalarType()) &&
8252  "Should only be a truncating store, not extending!");
8253  assert(VT.isInteger() == SVT.isInteger() &&
8254  "Can't do FP-INT conversion!");
8255  assert(VT.isVector() == SVT.isVector() &&
8256  "Cannot use trunc store to convert to or from a vector!");
8257  assert((!VT.isVector() ||
8258  VT.getVectorElementCount() == SVT.getVectorElementCount()) &&
8259  "Cannot use trunc store to change the number of vector elements!");
8260 
8261  SDVTList VTs = getVTList(MVT::Other);
8262  SDValue Undef = getUNDEF(Ptr.getValueType());
8263  SDValue Ops[] = { Chain, Val, Ptr, Undef };
8264  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
8265  AddNodeIDNode(ID, ISD::STORE, VTs, Ops);
8266  ID.AddInteger(SVT.getRawBits());
8267  ID.AddInteger(getSyntheticNodeSubclassData<StoreSDNode>(
8268  dl.getIROrder(), VTs, ISD::UNINDEXED, true, SVT, MMO));
8269  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
8270  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getFlags());
8271  void *IP = nullptr;
8272  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, dl, IP)) {
8273  cast<StoreSDNode>(E)->refineAlignment(MMO);
8274  return SDValue(E, 0);
8275  }
8276  auto *N = newSDNode<StoreSDNode>(dl.getIROrder(), dl.getDebugLoc(), VTs,
8277  ISD::UNINDEXED, true, SVT, MMO);
8278  createOperands(N, Ops);
8279 
8280  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
8281  InsertNode(N);
8282  SDValue V(N, 0);
8283  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
8284  return V;
8285 }

8429  LD->getMemoryVT(), LD->getAlign(), MMOFlags, LD->getAAInfo(),
8430  nullptr, LD->isExpandingLoad());

8433 SDValue SelectionDAG::getStoreVP(SDValue Chain, const SDLoc &dl, SDValue Val,
8434  SDValue Ptr, SDValue Offset, SDValue Mask,
8435  SDValue EVL, EVT MemVT, MachineMemOperand *MMO,
8436  ISD::MemIndexedMode AM, bool IsTruncating,
8437  bool IsCompressing) {
8438  assert(Chain.getValueType() == MVT::Other && "Invalid chain type");
8439  bool Indexed = AM != ISD::UNINDEXED;
8440  assert((Indexed || Offset.isUndef()) && "Unindexed vp_store with an offset!");
8441  SDVTList VTs = Indexed ? getVTList(Ptr.getValueType(), MVT::Other)
8442  : getVTList(MVT::Other);
8443  SDValue Ops[] = {Chain, Val, Ptr, Offset, Mask, EVL};
8444  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
8445  AddNodeIDNode(ID, ISD::VP_STORE, VTs, Ops);
8446  ID.AddInteger(MemVT.getRawBits());
8447  ID.AddInteger(getSyntheticNodeSubclassData<VPStoreSDNode>(
8448  dl.getIROrder(), VTs, AM, IsTruncating, IsCompressing, MemVT, MMO));
8449  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
8450  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getFlags());
8451  void *IP = nullptr;
8452  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, dl, IP)) {
8453  cast<VPStoreSDNode>(E)->refineAlignment(MMO);
8454  return SDValue(E, 0);
8455  }
8456  auto *N = newSDNode<VPStoreSDNode>(dl.getIROrder(), dl.getDebugLoc(), VTs, AM,
8457  IsTruncating, IsCompressing, MemVT, MMO);
8458  createOperands(N, Ops);
8459 
8460  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
8461  InsertNode(N);
8462  SDValue V(N, 0);
8463  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
8464  return V;
8465 }

8467 SDValue SelectionDAG::getTruncStoreVP(SDValue Chain, const SDLoc &dl,
8468  SDValue Val, SDValue Ptr, SDValue Mask,
8469  SDValue EVL, MachinePointerInfo PtrInfo,
8470  EVT SVT, Align Alignment,
8471  MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags,
8472  const AAMDNodes &AAInfo,
8473  bool IsCompressing) {
8474  assert(Chain.getValueType() == MVT::Other && "Invalid chain type");
8475 
8476  MMOFlags |= MachineMemOperand::MOStore;
8477  assert((MMOFlags & MachineMemOperand::MOLoad) == 0);
8478

8480  PtrInfo = InferPointerInfo(PtrInfo, *this, Ptr);
8481

8489 
8490 SDValue SelectionDAG::getTruncStoreVP(SDValue Chain, const SDLoc &dl,
8491  SDValue Val, SDValue Ptr, SDValue Mask,
8492  SDValue EVL, EVT SVT,
8493  MachineMemOperand *MMO,
8494  bool IsCompressing) {
8495  EVT VT = Val.getValueType();
8496 
8497  assert(Chain.getValueType() == MVT::Other && "Invalid chain type");
8498  if (VT == SVT)
8499  return getStoreVP(Chain, dl, Val, Ptr, getUNDEF(Ptr.getValueType()), Mask,
8500  EVL, VT, MMO, ISD::UNINDEXED,
8501  /*IsTruncating*/ false, IsCompressing);
8502 
8503  assert(SVT.getScalarType().bitsLT(VT.getScalarType()) &&
8504  "Should only be a truncating store, not extending!");
8505  assert(VT.isInteger() == SVT.isInteger() && "Can't do FP-INT conversion!");
8506  assert(VT.isVector() == SVT.isVector() &&
8507  "Cannot use trunc store to convert to or from a vector!");
8508  assert((!VT.isVector() ||
8509  VT.getVectorElementCount() == SVT.getVectorElementCount()) &&
8510  "Cannot use trunc store to change the number of vector elements!");
8511 
8512  SDVTList VTs = getVTList(MVT::Other);
8513  SDValue Undef = getUNDEF(Ptr.getValueType());
8514  SDValue Ops[] = {Chain, Val, Ptr, Undef, Mask, EVL};
8515  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
8516  AddNodeIDNode(ID, ISD::VP_STORE, VTs, Ops);
8517  ID.AddInteger(SVT.getRawBits());
8518  ID.AddInteger(getSyntheticNodeSubclassData<VPStoreSDNode>(
8519  dl.getIROrder(), VTs, ISD::UNINDEXED, true, IsCompressing, SVT, MMO));
8520  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
8521  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getFlags());
8522  void *IP = nullptr;
8523  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, dl, IP)) {
8524  cast<VPStoreSDNode>(E)->refineAlignment(MMO);
8525  return SDValue(E, 0);
8526  }
8527  auto *N =
8528  newSDNode<VPStoreSDNode>(dl.getIROrder(), dl.getDebugLoc(), VTs,
8529  ISD::UNINDEXED, true, IsCompressing, SVT, MMO);
8530  createOperands(N, Ops);
8531 
8532  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
8533  InsertNode(N);
8534  SDValue V(N, 0);
8535  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
8536  return V;
8537 }

8539 SDValue SelectionDAG::getIndexedStoreVP(SDValue OrigStore, const SDLoc &dl,
8540  SDValue Base, SDValue Offset,
8541  ISD::MemIndexedMode AM) {
8542  auto *ST = cast<VPStoreSDNode>(OrigStore);
8543  assert(ST->getOffset().isUndef() && "Store is already an indexed store!");
8544  SDVTList VTs = getVTList(Base.getValueType(), MVT::Other);
8545  SDValue Ops[] = {ST->getChain(), ST->getValue(), Base,
8546  Offset, ST->getMask(), ST->getVectorLength()};

8548  AddNodeIDNode(ID, ISD::VP_STORE, VTs, Ops);
8549  ID.AddInteger(ST->getMemoryVT().getRawBits());

8551  ID.AddInteger(ST->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
8552  ID.AddInteger(ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags());

8555  return SDValue(E, 0);
8556

8558  dl.getIROrder(), dl.getDebugLoc(), VTs, AM, ST->isTruncatingStore(),
8559  ST->isCompressingStore(), ST->getMemoryVT(), ST->getMemOperand());
8560  createOperands(N, Ops);
8561 
8562  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
8563  InsertNode(N);
8564  SDValue V(N, 0);
8565  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
8566  return V;
8567 }

8569 SDValue SelectionDAG::getStridedLoadVP(
8570  ISD::MemIndexedMode AM, ISD::LoadExtType ExtType, EVT VT, const SDLoc &DL,
8571  SDValue Chain, SDValue Ptr, SDValue Offset, SDValue Stride, SDValue Mask,
8572  SDValue EVL, MachinePointerInfo PtrInfo, EVT MemVT, Align Alignment,
8573  MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags, const AAMDNodes &AAInfo,
8574  const MDNode *Ranges, bool IsExpanding) {
8575  assert(Chain.getValueType() == MVT::Other && "Invalid chain type");
8576 
8577  MMOFlags |= MachineMemOperand::MOLoad;
8578  assert((MMOFlags & MachineMemOperand::MOStore) == 0);
8579  // If we don't have a PtrInfo, infer the trivial frame index case to simplify
8580  // clients.
8581  if (PtrInfo.V.isNull())
8582  PtrInfo = InferPointerInfo(PtrInfo, *this, Ptr, Offset);
8583 
8584  uint64_t Size = MemoryLocation::UnknownSize;
8585  MachineFunction &MF = getMachineFunction();
8586  MachineMemOperand *MMO = MF.getMachineMemOperand(PtrInfo, MMOFlags, Size,
8587  Alignment, AAInfo, Ranges);
8588  return getStridedLoadVP(AM, ExtType, VT, DL, Chain, Ptr, Offset, Stride, Mask,
8589  EVL, MemVT, MMO, IsExpanding);
8590 }

8673  "Strided load is already a indexed load!");

8683 }

8822 SDValue SelectionDAG::getGatherVP(SDVTList VTs, EVT VT, const SDLoc &dl,
8823  ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops, MachineMemOperand *MMO,
8824  ISD::MemIndexType IndexType) {
8825  assert(Ops.size() == 6 && "Incompatible number of operands");
8826 
8827  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
8828  AddNodeIDNode(ID, ISD::VP_GATHER, VTs, Ops);
8829  ID.AddInteger(VT.getRawBits());
8830  ID.AddInteger(getSyntheticNodeSubclassData<VPGatherSDNode>(
8831  dl.getIROrder(), VTs, VT, MMO, IndexType));
8832  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
8833  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getFlags());
8834  void *IP = nullptr;
8835  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, dl, IP)) {
8836  cast<VPGatherSDNode>(E)->refineAlignment(MMO);
8837  return SDValue(E, 0);
8838  }
8839 
8840  auto *N = newSDNode<VPGatherSDNode>(dl.getIROrder(), dl.getDebugLoc(), VTs,
8841  VT, MMO, IndexType);
8842  createOperands(N, Ops);
8843 
8844  assert(N->getMask().getValueType().getVectorElementCount() ==
8845  N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementCount() &&
8846  "Vector width mismatch between mask and data");
8847  assert(N->getIndex().getValueType().getVectorElementCount().isScalable() ==
8848  N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementCount().isScalable() &&
8849  "Scalable flags of index and data do not match");
8850  assert(ElementCount::isKnownGE(
8851  N->getIndex().getValueType().getVectorElementCount(),
8852  N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementCount()) &&
8853  "Vector width mismatch between index and data");
8854  assert(isa<ConstantSDNode>(N->getScale()) &&
8855  cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getScale())->getAPIntValue().isPowerOf2() &&
8856  "Scale should be a constant power of 2");
8857 
8858  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
8859  InsertNode(N);
8860  SDValue V(N, 0);
8861  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
8862  return V;
8863 }

8865 SDValue SelectionDAG::getScatterVP(SDVTList VTs, EVT VT, const SDLoc &dl,
8866  ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops,
8867  MachineMemOperand *MMO,
8868  ISD::MemIndexType IndexType) {
8869  assert(Ops.size() == 7 && "Incompatible number of operands");
8870 
8871  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
8872  AddNodeIDNode(ID, ISD::VP_SCATTER, VTs, Ops);
8873  ID.AddInteger(VT.getRawBits());
8874  ID.AddInteger(getSyntheticNodeSubclassData<VPScatterSDNode>(
8875  dl.getIROrder(), VTs, VT, MMO, IndexType));
8876  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
8877  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getFlags());
8878  void *IP = nullptr;
8879  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, dl, IP)) {
8880  cast<VPScatterSDNode>(E)->refineAlignment(MMO);
8881  return SDValue(E, 0);
8882  }
8883  auto *N = newSDNode<VPScatterSDNode>(dl.getIROrder(), dl.getDebugLoc(), VTs,
8884  VT, MMO, IndexType);
8885  createOperands(N, Ops);
8886 
8887  assert(N->getMask().getValueType().getVectorElementCount() ==
8888  N->getValue().getValueType().getVectorElementCount() &&
8889  "Vector width mismatch between mask and data");
8890  assert(
8891  N->getIndex().getValueType().getVectorElementCount().isScalable() ==
8892  N->getValue().getValueType().getVectorElementCount().isScalable() &&
8893  "Scalable flags of index and data do not match");
8894  assert(ElementCount::isKnownGE(
8895  N->getIndex().getValueType().getVectorElementCount(),
8896  N->getValue().getValueType().getVectorElementCount()) &&
8897  "Vector width mismatch between index and data");
8898  assert(isa<ConstantSDNode>(N->getScale()) &&
8899  cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getScale())->getAPIntValue().isPowerOf2() &&
8900  "Scale should be a constant power of 2");
8901 
8902  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
8903  InsertNode(N);
8904  SDValue V(N, 0);
8905  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
8906  return V;
8907 }

8909 SDValue SelectionDAG::getMaskedLoad(EVT VT, const SDLoc &dl, SDValue Chain,
8910  SDValue Base, SDValue Offset, SDValue Mask,
8911  SDValue PassThru, EVT MemVT,
8912  MachineMemOperand *MMO,
8913  ISD::MemIndexedMode AM,
8914  ISD::LoadExtType ExtTy, bool isExpanding) {
8915  bool Indexed = AM != ISD::UNINDEXED;

8917  "Unindexed masked load with an offset!");

8919  : getVTList(VT, MVT::Other);

8927  ID.AddInteger(MMO->getFlags());

8930  cast<MaskedLoadSDNode>(E)->refineAlignment(MMO);
8931  return SDValue(E, 0);
8932  }

8934  AM, ExtTy, isExpanding, MemVT, MMO);
8935  createOperands(N, Ops);
8936 
8937  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
8938  InsertNode(N);
8939  SDValue V(N, 0);
8940  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
8941  return V;
8942 }

9096 
9097 SDValue SelectionDAG::simplifySelect(SDValue Cond, SDValue T, SDValue F) {
9098  // select undef, T, F --> T (if T is a constant), otherwise F
9099  // select, ?, undef, F --> F
9100  // select, ?, T, undef --> T
9101  if (Cond.isUndef())
9102  return isConstantValueOfAnyType(T) ? T : F;
9103  if (T.isUndef())
9104  return F;
9105  if (F.isUndef())
9106  return T;
9107 
9108  // select true, T, F --> T
9109  // select false, T, F --> F
9110  if (auto *CondC = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Cond))
9111  return CondC->isZero() ? F : T;
9112 
9113  // TODO: This should simplify VSELECT with non-zero constant condition using
9114  // something like this (but check boolean contents to be complete?):
9115  if (ConstantSDNode *CondC = isConstOrConstSplat(Cond, /*AllowUndefs*/ false,
9116  /*AllowTruncation*/ true))
9117  if (CondC->isZero())
9118  return F;
9119 
9120  // select ?, T, T --> T
9121  if (T == F)
9122  return T;
9123 
9124  return SDValue();
9125 }
9126 
9127 SDValue SelectionDAG::simplifyShift(SDValue X, SDValue Y) {
9128  // shift undef, Y --> 0 (can always assume that the undef value is 0)
9129  if (X.isUndef())
9130  return getConstant(0, SDLoc(X.getNode()), X.getValueType());
9131  // shift X, undef --> undef (because it may shift by the bitwidth)
9132  if (Y.isUndef())
9133  return getUNDEF(X.getValueType());
9134 
9135  // shift 0, Y --> 0
9136  // shift X, 0 --> X
9137  if (isNullOrNullSplat(X) || isNullOrNullSplat(Y))
9138  return X;
9139 
9140  // shift X, C >= bitwidth(X) --> undef
9141  // All vector elements must be too big (or undef) to avoid partial undefs.
9142  auto isShiftTooBig = [X](ConstantSDNode *Val) {
9143  return !Val || Val->getAPIntValue().uge(X.getScalarValueSizeInBits());
9144  };
9145  if (ISD::matchUnaryPredicate(Y, isShiftTooBig, true))
9146  return getUNDEF(X.getValueType());
9147 
9148  return SDValue();
9149 }
9150 
9151 SDValue SelectionDAG::simplifyFPBinop(unsigned Opcode, SDValue X, SDValue Y,
9152  SDNodeFlags Flags) {
9153  // If this operation has 'nnan' or 'ninf' and at least 1 disallowed operand
9154  // (an undef operand can be chosen to be Nan/Inf), then the result of this
9155  // operation is poison. That result can be relaxed to undef.
9156  ConstantFPSDNode *XC = isConstOrConstSplatFP(X, /* AllowUndefs */ true);
9157  ConstantFPSDNode *YC = isConstOrConstSplatFP(Y, /* AllowUndefs */ true);
9158  bool HasNan = (XC && XC->getValueAPF().isNaN()) ||
9159  (YC && YC->getValueAPF().isNaN());
9160  bool HasInf = (XC && XC->getValueAPF().isInfinity()) ||
9161  (YC && YC->getValueAPF().isInfinity());
9162 
9163  if (Flags.hasNoNaNs() && (HasNan || X.isUndef() || Y.isUndef()))
9164  return getUNDEF(X.getValueType());
9165 
9166  if (Flags.hasNoInfs() && (HasInf || X.isUndef() || Y.isUndef()))
9167  return getUNDEF(X.getValueType());
9168 
9169  if (!YC)
9170  return SDValue();
9171 
9172  // X + -0.0 --> X
9173  if (Opcode == ISD::FADD)
9174  if (YC->getValueAPF().isNegZero())
9175  return X;
9176 
9177  // X - +0.0 --> X
9178  if (Opcode == ISD::FSUB)
9179  if (YC->getValueAPF().isPosZero())
9180  return X;
9181 
9182  // X * 1.0 --> X
9183  // X / 1.0 --> X
9184  if (Opcode == ISD::FMUL || Opcode == ISD::FDIV)
9185  if (YC->getValueAPF().isExactlyValue(1.0))
9186  return X;
9187 
9188  // X * 0.0 --> 0.0
9189  if (Opcode == ISD::FMUL && Flags.hasNoNaNs() && Flags.hasNoSignedZeros())
9190  if (YC->getValueAPF().isZero())
9191  return getConstantFP(0.0, SDLoc(Y), Y.getValueType());
9192 
9193  return SDValue();
9194 }
9195 
9196 SDValue SelectionDAG::getVAArg(EVT VT, const SDLoc &dl, SDValue Chain,
9197  SDValue Ptr, SDValue SV, unsigned Align) {
9198  SDValue Ops[] = { Chain, Ptr, SV, getTargetConstant(Align, dl, MVT::i32) };
9199  return getNode(ISD::VAARG, dl, getVTList(VT, MVT::Other), Ops);
9200 }
9201 
9202 SDValue SelectionDAG::getNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
9203  ArrayRef<SDUse> Ops) {
9204  switch (Ops.size()) {
9205  case 0: return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT);
9206  case 1: return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, static_cast<const SDValue>(Ops[0]));
9207  case 2: return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, Ops[0], Ops[1]);
9208  case 3: return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, Ops[0], Ops[1], Ops[2]);
9209  default: break;
9210  }
9211 
9212  // Copy from an SDUse array into an SDValue array for use with
9213  // the regular getNode logic.
9214  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> NewOps(Ops.begin(), Ops.end());
9215  return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, NewOps);
9216 }
9217 
9218 SDValue SelectionDAG::getNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
9219  ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops) {
9220  SDNodeFlags Flags;
9221  if (Inserter)
9222  Flags = Inserter->getFlags();
9223  return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, Ops, Flags);
9224 }
9225 
9226 SDValue SelectionDAG::getNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
9227  ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops, const SDNodeFlags Flags) {
9228  unsigned NumOps = Ops.size();
9229  switch (NumOps) {
9230  case 0: return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT);
9231  case 1: return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, Ops[0], Flags);
9232  case 2: return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, Ops[0], Ops[1], Flags);
9233  case 3: return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, Ops[0], Ops[1], Ops[2], Flags);
9234  default: break;
9235  }
9236 
9237 #ifndef NDEBUG
9238  for (const auto &Op : Ops)
9239  assert(Op.getOpcode() != ISD::DELETED_NODE &&
9240  "Operand is DELETED_NODE!");
9241 #endif
9242 
9243  switch (Opcode) {
9244  default: break;
9245  case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR:
9246  // Attempt to simplify BUILD_VECTOR.
9247  if (SDValue V = FoldBUILD_VECTOR(DL, VT, Ops, *this))
9248  return V;
9249  break;
9250  case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS:
9251  if (SDValue V = foldCONCAT_VECTORS(DL, VT, Ops, *this))
9252  return V;
9253  break;
9254  case ISD::SELECT_CC:
9255  assert(NumOps == 5 && "SELECT_CC takes 5 operands!");
9256  assert(Ops[0].getValueType() == Ops[1].getValueType() &&
9257  "LHS and RHS of condition must have same type!");
9258  assert(Ops[2].getValueType() == Ops[3].getValueType() &&
9259  "True and False arms of SelectCC must have same type!");
9260  assert(Ops[2].getValueType() == VT &&
9261  "select_cc node must be of same type as true and false value!");
9262  assert((!Ops[0].getValueType().isVector() ||
9263  Ops[0].getValueType().getVectorElementCount() ==
9264  VT.getVectorElementCount()) &&
9265  "Expected select_cc with vector result to have the same sized "
9266  "comparison type!");
9267  break;
9268  case ISD::BR_CC:
9269  assert(NumOps == 5 && "BR_CC takes 5 operands!");
9270  assert(Ops[2].getValueType() == Ops[3].getValueType() &&
9271  "LHS/RHS of comparison should match types!");
9272  break;
9273  case ISD::VP_ADD:
9274  case ISD::VP_SUB:
9275  // If it is VP_ADD/VP_SUB mask operation then turn it to VP_XOR
9276  if (VT.isVector() && VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
9277  Opcode = ISD::VP_XOR;
9278  break;
9279  case ISD::VP_MUL:
9280  // If it is VP_MUL mask operation then turn it to VP_AND
9281  if (VT.isVector() && VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
9282  Opcode = ISD::VP_AND;
9283  break;
9284  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_MUL:
9285  // If it is VP_REDUCE_MUL mask operation then turn it to VP_REDUCE_AND
9286  if (VT == MVT::i1)
9287  Opcode = ISD::VP_REDUCE_AND;
9288  break;
9289  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_ADD:
9290  // If it is VP_REDUCE_ADD mask operation then turn it to VP_REDUCE_XOR
9291  if (VT == MVT::i1)
9292  Opcode = ISD::VP_REDUCE_XOR;
9293  break;
9294  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SMAX:
9295  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_UMIN:
9296  // If it is VP_REDUCE_SMAX/VP_REDUCE_UMIN mask operation then turn it to
9297  // VP_REDUCE_AND.
9298  if (VT == MVT::i1)
9299  Opcode = ISD::VP_REDUCE_AND;
9300  break;
9301  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SMIN:
9302  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_UMAX:
9303  // If it is VP_REDUCE_SMIN/VP_REDUCE_UMAX mask operation then turn it to
9304  // VP_REDUCE_OR.
9305  if (VT == MVT::i1)
9306  Opcode = ISD::VP_REDUCE_OR;
9307  break;
9308  }
9309 
9310  // Memoize nodes.
9311  SDNode *N;
9312  SDVTList VTs = getVTList(VT);
9313 
9314  if (VT != MVT::Glue) {
9315  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
9316  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opcode, VTs, Ops);
9317  void *IP = nullptr;
9318 
9319  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, DL, IP))
9320  return SDValue(E, 0);
9321 
9322  N = newSDNode<SDNode>(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(), DL.getDebugLoc(), VTs);
9323  createOperands(N, Ops);
9324 
9325  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
9326  } else {
9327  N = newSDNode<SDNode>(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(), DL.getDebugLoc(), VTs);
9328  createOperands(N, Ops);
9329  }
9330 
9331  N->setFlags(Flags);
9332  InsertNode(N);
9333  SDValue V(N, 0);
9334  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
9335  return V;
9336 }
9337 
9338 SDValue SelectionDAG::getNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL,
9339  ArrayRef<EVT> ResultTys, ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops) {
9340  return getNode(Opcode, DL, getVTList(ResultTys), Ops);
9341 }
9342 
9343 SDValue SelectionDAG::getNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL, SDVTList VTList,
9344  ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops) {
9345  SDNodeFlags Flags;
9346  if (Inserter)
9347  Flags = Inserter->getFlags();
9348  return getNode(Opcode, DL, VTList, Ops, Flags);
9349 }
9350 
9351 SDValue SelectionDAG::getNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL, SDVTList VTList,
9352  ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops, const SDNodeFlags Flags) {
9353  if (VTList.NumVTs == 1)
9354  return getNode(Opcode, DL, VTList.VTs[0], Ops, Flags);
9355 
9356 #ifndef NDEBUG
9357  for (const auto &Op : Ops)
9358  assert(Op.getOpcode() != ISD::DELETED_NODE &&
9359  "Operand is DELETED_NODE!");
9360 #endif
9361 
9362  switch (Opcode) {
9363  case ISD::SADDO:
9364  case ISD::UADDO:
9365  case ISD::SSUBO:
9366  case ISD::USUBO: {
9367  assert(VTList.NumVTs == 2 && Ops.size() == 2 &&
9368  "Invalid add/sub overflow op!");
9369  assert(VTList.VTs[0].isInteger() && VTList.VTs[1].isInteger() &&
9370  Ops[0].getValueType() == Ops[1].getValueType() &&
9371  Ops[0].getValueType() == VTList.VTs[0] &&
9372  "Binary operator types must match!");
9373  SDValue N1 = Ops[0], N2 = Ops[1];
9374  canonicalizeCommutativeBinop(Opcode, N1, N2);
9375 
9376  // (X +- 0) -> X with zero-overflow.
9377  ConstantSDNode *N2CV = isConstOrConstSplat(N2, /*AllowUndefs*/ false,
9378  /*AllowTruncation*/ true);
9379  if (N2CV && N2CV->isZero()) {
9380  SDValue ZeroOverFlow = getConstant(0, DL, VTList.VTs[1]);
9381  return getNode(ISD::MERGE_VALUES, DL, VTList, {N1, ZeroOverFlow}, Flags);
9382  }
9383  break;
9384  }
9385  case ISD::SMUL_LOHI:
9386  case ISD::UMUL_LOHI: {
9387  assert(VTList.NumVTs == 2 && Ops.size() == 2 && "Invalid mul lo/hi op!");
9388  assert(VTList.VTs[0].isInteger() && VTList.VTs[0] == VTList.VTs[1] &&
9389  VTList.VTs[0] == Ops[0].getValueType() &&
9390  VTList.VTs[0] == Ops[1].getValueType() &&
9391  "Binary operator types must match!");
9392  break;
9393  }
9394  case ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND:
9395  assert(VTList.NumVTs == 2 && Ops.size() == 2 &&
9396  "Invalid STRICT_FP_EXTEND!");
9397  assert(VTList.VTs[0].isFloatingPoint() &&
9398  Ops[1].getValueType().isFloatingPoint() && "Invalid FP cast!");
9399  assert(VTList.VTs[0].isVector() == Ops[1].getValueType().isVector() &&
9400  "STRICT_FP_EXTEND result type should be vector iff the operand "
9401  "type is vector!");
9402  assert((!VTList.VTs[0].isVector() ||
9403  VTList.VTs[0].getVectorNumElements() ==
9404  Ops[1].getValueType().getVectorNumElements()) &&
9405  "Vector element count mismatch!");
9406  assert(Ops[1].getValueType().bitsLT(VTList.VTs[0]) &&
9407  "Invalid fpext node, dst <= src!");
9408  break;
9409  case ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND:
9410  assert(VTList.NumVTs == 2 && Ops.size() == 3 && "Invalid STRICT_FP_ROUND!");
9411  assert(VTList.VTs[0].isVector() == Ops[1].getValueType().isVector() &&
9412  "STRICT_FP_ROUND result type should be vector iff the operand "
9413  "type is vector!");
9414  assert((!VTList.VTs[0].isVector() ||
9415  VTList.VTs[0].getVectorNumElements() ==
9416  Ops[1].getValueType().getVectorNumElements()) &&
9417  "Vector element count mismatch!");
9418  assert(VTList.VTs[0].isFloatingPoint() &&
9419  Ops[1].getValueType().isFloatingPoint() &&
9420  VTList.VTs[0].bitsLT(Ops[1].getValueType()) &&
9421  isa<ConstantSDNode>(Ops[2]) &&
9422  (cast<ConstantSDNode>(Ops[2])->getZExtValue() == 0 ||
9423  cast<ConstantSDNode>(Ops[2])->getZExtValue() == 1) &&
9424  "Invalid STRICT_FP_ROUND!");
9425  break;
9426 #if 0
9427  // FIXME: figure out how to safely handle things like
9428  // int foo(int x) { return 1 << (x & 255); }
9429  // int bar() { return foo(256); }
9430  case ISD::SRA_PARTS:
9431  case ISD::SRL_PARTS:
9432  case ISD::SHL_PARTS:
9433  if (N3.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG &&
9434  cast<VTSDNode>(N3.getOperand(1))->getVT() != MVT::i1)
9435  return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, N1, N2, N3.getOperand(0));
9436  else if (N3.getOpcode() == ISD::AND)
9437  if (ConstantSDNode *AndRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N3.getOperand(1))) {
9438  // If the and is only masking out bits that cannot effect the shift,
9439  // eliminate the and.
9440  unsigned NumBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits()*2;
9441  if ((AndRHS->getValue() & (NumBits-1)) == NumBits-1)
9442  return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, N1, N2, N3.getOperand(0));
9443  }
9444  break;
9445 #endif
9446  }
9447 
9448  // Memoize the node unless it returns a flag.
9449  SDNode *N;
9450  if (VTList.VTs[VTList.NumVTs-1] != MVT::Glue) {
9451  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
9452  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opcode, VTList, Ops);
9453  void *IP = nullptr;
9454  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, DL, IP))
9455  return SDValue(E, 0);
9456 
9457  N = newSDNode<SDNode>(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(), DL.getDebugLoc(), VTList);
9458  createOperands(N, Ops);
9459  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
9460  } else {
9461  N = newSDNode<SDNode>(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(), DL.getDebugLoc(), VTList);
9462  createOperands(N, Ops);
9463  }
9464 
9465  N->setFlags(Flags);
9466  InsertNode(N);
9467  SDValue V(N, 0);
9468  NewSDValueDbgMsg(V, "Creating new node: ", this);
9469  return V;
9470 }

9512 SDVTList SelectionDAG::getVTList(EVT VT1, EVT VT2) {
9513  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
9514  ID.AddInteger(2U);
9515  ID.AddInteger(VT1.getRawBits());
9516  ID.AddInteger(VT2.getRawBits());
9517 
9518  void *IP = nullptr;
9519  SDVTListNode *Result = VTListMap.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, IP);
9520  if (!Result) {
9521  EVT *Array = Allocator.Allocate<EVT>(2);
9522  Array[0] = VT1;
9523  Array[1] = VT2;
9524  Result = new (Allocator) SDVTListNode(ID.Intern(Allocator), Array, 2);
9525  VTListMap.InsertNode(Result, IP);
9526  }
9527  return Result->getSDVTList();
9528 }

9592 /// UpdateNodeOperands - *Mutate* the specified node in-place to have the
9593 /// specified operands. If the resultant node already exists in the DAG,
9594 /// this does not modify the specified node, instead it returns the node that
9595 /// already exists. If the resultant node does not exist in the DAG, the
9596 /// input node is returned. As a degenerate case, if you specify the same
9597 /// input operands as the node already has, the input node is returned.
9598 SDNode *SelectionDAG::UpdateNodeOperands(SDNode *N, SDValue Op) {
9599  assert(N->getNumOperands() == 1 && "Update with wrong number of operands");
9600 
9601  // Check to see if there is no change.
9602  if (Op == N->getOperand(0)) return N;
9603 
9604  // See if the modified node already exists.
9605  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
9606  if (SDNode *Existing = FindModifiedNodeSlot(N, Op, InsertPos))
9607  return Existing;
9608 
9609  // Nope it doesn't. Remove the node from its current place in the maps.
9610  if (InsertPos)
9611  if (!RemoveNodeFromCSEMaps(N))
9612  InsertPos = nullptr;
9613 
9614  // Now we update the operands.
9615  N->OperandList[0].set(Op);
9616 
9617  updateDivergence(N);
9618  // If this gets put into a CSE map, add it.
9619  if (InsertPos) CSEMap.InsertNode(N, InsertPos);
9620  return N;
9621 }
9622 
9623 SDNode *SelectionDAG::UpdateNodeOperands(SDNode *N, SDValue Op1, SDValue Op2) {
9624  assert(N->getNumOperands() == 2 && "Update with wrong number of operands");
9625 
9626  // Check to see if there is no change.
9627  if (Op1 == N->getOperand(0) && Op2 == N->getOperand(1))
9628  return N; // No operands changed, just return the input node.
9629 
9630  // See if the modified node already exists.
9631  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
9632  if (SDNode *Existing = FindModifiedNodeSlot(N, Op1, Op2, InsertPos))
9633  return Existing;
9634 
9635  // Nope it doesn't. Remove the node from its current place in the maps.
9636  if (InsertPos)
9637  if (!RemoveNodeFromCSEMaps(N))
9638  InsertPos = nullptr;
9639 
9640  // Now we update the operands.
9641  if (N->OperandList[0] != Op1)
9642  N->OperandList[0].set(Op1);
9643  if (N->OperandList[1] != Op2)
9644  N->OperandList[1].set(Op2);
9645 
9646  updateDivergence(N);
9647  // If this gets put into a CSE map, add it.
9648  if (InsertPos) CSEMap.InsertNode(N, InsertPos);
9649  return N;
9650 }

9653 UpdateNodeOperands(SDNode *N, SDValue Op1, SDValue Op2, SDValue Op3) {
9654  SDValue Ops[] = { Op1, Op2, Op3 };
9655  return UpdateNodeOperands(N, Ops);
9656 }

9660  SDValue Op3, SDValue Op4) {
9661  SDValue Ops[] = { Op1, Op2, Op3, Op4 };

9665 SDNode *SelectionDAG::
9666 UpdateNodeOperands(SDNode *N, SDValue Op1, SDValue Op2,
9667  SDValue Op3, SDValue Op4, SDValue Op5) {
9668  SDValue Ops[] = { Op1, Op2, Op3, Op4, Op5 };

9670 }
9671 
9672 SDNode *SelectionDAG::
9673 UpdateNodeOperands(SDNode *N, ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops) {
9674  unsigned NumOps = Ops.size();
9675  assert(N->getNumOperands() == NumOps &&
9676  "Update with wrong number of operands");
9677 
9678  // If no operands changed just return the input node.
9679  if (std::equal(Ops.begin(), Ops.end(), N->op_begin()))
9680  return N;
9681 
9682  // See if the modified node already exists.
9683  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
9684  if (SDNode *Existing = FindModifiedNodeSlot(N, Ops, InsertPos))
9685  return Existing;
9686 
9687  // Nope it doesn't. Remove the node from its current place in the maps.
9688  if (InsertPos)
9689  if (!RemoveNodeFromCSEMaps(N))
9690  InsertPos = nullptr;
9691 
9692  // Now we update the operands.
9693  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumOps; ++i)
9694  if (N->OperandList[i] != Ops[i])
9695  N->OperandList[i].set(Ops[i]);
9696 
9697  updateDivergence(N);
9698  // If this gets put into a CSE map, add it.
9699  if (InsertPos) CSEMap.InsertNode(N, InsertPos);
9700  return N;
9701 }

9703 /// DropOperands - Release the operands and set this node to have
9704 /// zero operands.
9705 void SDNode::DropOperands() {
9706  // Unlike the code in MorphNodeTo that does this, we don't need to
9707  // watch for dead nodes here.
9708  for (op_iterator I = op_begin(), E = op_end(); I != E; ) {
9709  SDUse &Use = *I++;
9710  Use.set(SDValue());
9711  }
9712 }

9714 void SelectionDAG::setNodeMemRefs(MachineSDNode *N,
9715  ArrayRef<MachineMemOperand *> NewMemRefs) {
9716  if (NewMemRefs.empty()) {
9717  N->clearMemRefs();
9718  return;
9719  }
9720 
9721  // Check if we can avoid allocating by storing a single reference directly.
9722  if (NewMemRefs.size() == 1) {
9723  N->MemRefs = NewMemRefs[0];
9724  N->NumMemRefs = 1;
9725  return;
9726  }
9727 
9728  MachineMemOperand **MemRefsBuffer =
9729  Allocator.template Allocate<MachineMemOperand *>(NewMemRefs.size());
9730  llvm::copy(NewMemRefs, MemRefsBuffer);
9731  N->MemRefs = MemRefsBuffer;
9732  N->NumMemRefs = static_cast<int>(NewMemRefs.size());
9733 }

9800 SDNode *SelectionDAG::SelectNodeTo(SDNode *N, unsigned MachineOpc,
9801  SDVTList VTs,ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops) {
9802  SDNode *New = MorphNodeTo(N, ~MachineOpc, VTs, Ops);
9803  // Reset the NodeID to -1.
9804  New->setNodeId(-1);
9805  if (New != N) {
9806  ReplaceAllUsesWith(N, New);
9807  RemoveDeadNode(N);
9808  }
9809  return New;
9810 }
