9812 /// UpdateSDLocOnMergeSDNode - If the opt level is -O0 then it throws away
9813 /// the line number information on the merged node since it is not possible to
9814 /// preserve the information that operation is associated with multiple lines.
9815 /// This will make the debugger working better at -O0, were there is a higher
9816 /// probability having other instructions associated with that line.
9817 ///
9818 /// For IROrder, we keep the smaller of the two
9819 SDNode *SelectionDAG::UpdateSDLocOnMergeSDNode(SDNode *N, const SDLoc &OLoc) {
9820  DebugLoc NLoc = N->getDebugLoc();
9821  if (NLoc && OptLevel == CodeGenOpt::None && OLoc.getDebugLoc() != NLoc) {
9822  N->setDebugLoc(DebugLoc());
9823  }
9824  unsigned Order = std::min(N->getIROrder(), OLoc.getIROrder());
9825  N->setIROrder(Order);
9826  return N;
9827 }
9828 
9829 /// MorphNodeTo - This *mutates* the specified node to have the specified
9830 /// return type, opcode, and operands.
9831 ///
9832 /// Note that MorphNodeTo returns the resultant node. If there is already a
9833 /// node of the specified opcode and operands, it returns that node instead of
9834 /// the current one. Note that the SDLoc need not be the same.
9835 ///
9836 /// Using MorphNodeTo is faster than creating a new node and swapping it in
9837 /// with ReplaceAllUsesWith both because it often avoids allocating a new
9838 /// node, and because it doesn't require CSE recalculation for any of
9839 /// the node's users.
9840 ///
9841 /// However, note that MorphNodeTo recursively deletes dead nodes from the DAG.
9842 /// As a consequence it isn't appropriate to use from within the DAG combiner or
9843 /// the legalizer which maintain worklists that would need to be updated when
9844 /// deleting things.
9845 SDNode *SelectionDAG::MorphNodeTo(SDNode *N, unsigned Opc,
9846  SDVTList VTs, ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops) {
9847  // If an identical node already exists, use it.
9848  void *IP = nullptr;
9849  if (VTs.VTs[VTs.NumVTs-1] != MVT::Glue) {
9850  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
9851  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opc, VTs, Ops);
9852  if (SDNode *ON = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, SDLoc(N), IP))
9853  return UpdateSDLocOnMergeSDNode(ON, SDLoc(N));
9854  }
9855 
9856  if (!RemoveNodeFromCSEMaps(N))
9857  IP = nullptr;
9858 
9859  // Start the morphing.
9860  N->NodeType = Opc;
9861  N->ValueList = VTs.VTs;
9862  N->NumValues = VTs.NumVTs;
9863 
9864  // Clear the operands list, updating used nodes to remove this from their
9865  // use list. Keep track of any operands that become dead as a result.
9866  SmallPtrSet<SDNode*, 16> DeadNodeSet;
9867  for (SDNode::op_iterator I = N->op_begin(), E = N->op_end(); I != E; ) {
9868  SDUse &Use = *I++;
9869  SDNode *Used = Use.getNode();
9870  Use.set(SDValue());
9871  if (Used->use_empty())
9872  DeadNodeSet.insert(Used);
9873  }
9874 
9875  // For MachineNode, initialize the memory references information.
9876  if (MachineSDNode *MN = dyn_cast<MachineSDNode>(N))
9877  MN->clearMemRefs();
9878 
9879  // Swap for an appropriately sized array from the recycler.
9880  removeOperands(N);
9881  createOperands(N, Ops);
9882 
9883  // Delete any nodes that are still dead after adding the uses for the
9884  // new operands.
9885  if (!DeadNodeSet.empty()) {
9886  SmallVector<SDNode *, 16> DeadNodes;
9887  for (SDNode *N : DeadNodeSet)
9888  if (N->use_empty())
9889  DeadNodes.push_back(N);
9890  RemoveDeadNodes(DeadNodes);
9891  }
9892 
9893  if (IP)
9894  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP); // Memoize the new node.
9895  return N;
9896 }
9897 
9898 SDNode* SelectionDAG::mutateStrictFPToFP(SDNode *Node) {
9899  unsigned OrigOpc = Node->getOpcode();
9900  unsigned NewOpc;
9901  switch (OrigOpc) {
9902  default:
9903  llvm_unreachable("mutateStrictFPToFP called with unexpected opcode!");
9904 #define DAG_INSTRUCTION(NAME, NARG, ROUND_MODE, INTRINSIC, DAGN) \
9905  case ISD::STRICT_##DAGN: NewOpc = ISD::DAGN; break;
9906 #define CMP_INSTRUCTION(NAME, NARG, ROUND_MODE, INTRINSIC, DAGN) \
9907  case ISD::STRICT_##DAGN: NewOpc = ISD::SETCC; break;
9908 #include "llvm/IR/ConstrainedOps.def"
9909  }
9910 
9911  assert(Node->getNumValues() == 2 && "Unexpected number of results!");
9912 
9913  // We're taking this node out of the chain, so we need to re-link things.
9914  SDValue InputChain = Node->getOperand(0);
9915  SDValue OutputChain = SDValue(Node, 1);
9916  ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(OutputChain, InputChain);
9917 
9918  SmallVector<SDValue, 3> Ops;
9919  for (unsigned i = 1, e = Node->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i)
9920  Ops.push_back(Node->getOperand(i));
9921 
9922  SDVTList VTs = getVTList(Node->getValueType(0));
9923  SDNode *Res = MorphNodeTo(Node, NewOpc, VTs, Ops);
9924 
9925  // MorphNodeTo can operate in two ways: if an existing node with the
9926  // specified operands exists, it can just return it. Otherwise, it
9927  // updates the node in place to have the requested operands.
9928  if (Res == Node) {
9929  // If we updated the node in place, reset the node ID. To the isel,
9930  // this should be just like a newly allocated machine node.
9931  Res->setNodeId(-1);
9932  } else {
9933  ReplaceAllUsesWith(Node, Res);
9934  RemoveDeadNode(Node);
9935  }
9936 
9937  return Res;
9938 }
9939 
9940 /// getMachineNode - These are used for target selectors to create a new node

10033 
10034 MachineSDNode *SelectionDAG::getMachineNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL,
10035  SDVTList VTs,
10036  ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops) {
10037  bool DoCSE = VTs.VTs[VTs.NumVTs-1] != MVT::Glue;
10038  MachineSDNode *N;
10039  void *IP = nullptr;
10040 
10041  if (DoCSE) {
10042  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
10043  AddNodeIDNode(ID, ~Opcode, VTs, Ops);
10044  IP = nullptr;
10045  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, DL, IP)) {
10046  return cast<MachineSDNode>(UpdateSDLocOnMergeSDNode(E, DL));
10047  }
10048  }
10049 
10050  // Allocate a new MachineSDNode.
10051  N = newSDNode<MachineSDNode>(~Opcode, DL.getIROrder(), DL.getDebugLoc(), VTs);
10052  createOperands(N, Ops);
10053 
10054  if (DoCSE)
10055  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
10056 
10057  InsertNode(N);
10058  NewSDValueDbgMsg(SDValue(N, 0), "Creating new machine node: ", this);
10059  return N;
10060 }

10092 SDNode *SelectionDAG::getNodeIfExists(unsigned Opcode, SDVTList VTList,
10093  ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops,
10094  const SDNodeFlags Flags) {
10095  if (VTList.VTs[VTList.NumVTs - 1] != MVT::Glue) {
10096  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
10097  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opcode, VTList, Ops);
10098  void *IP = nullptr;
10099  if (SDNode *E = FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, SDLoc(), IP)) {
10100  E->intersectFlagsWith(Flags);
10101  return E;
10102  }
10103  }
10104  return nullptr;
10105 }

10107 /// doesNodeExist - Check if a node exists without modifying its flags.
10108 bool SelectionDAG::doesNodeExist(unsigned Opcode, SDVTList VTList,
10109  ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops) {

10111  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
10112  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opcode, VTList, Ops);
10113  void *IP = nullptr;
10114  if (FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, SDLoc(), IP))
10115  return true;
10116  }
10117  return false;
10118 }

10196 
10197 void SelectionDAG::transferDbgValues(SDValue From, SDValue To,
10198  unsigned OffsetInBits, unsigned SizeInBits,
10199  bool InvalidateDbg) {
10200  SDNode *FromNode = From.getNode();
10201  SDNode *ToNode = To.getNode();
10202  assert(FromNode && ToNode && "Can't modify dbg values");
10203 
10204  // PR35338
10205  // TODO: assert(From != To && "Redundant dbg value transfer");
10206  // TODO: assert(FromNode != ToNode && "Intranode dbg value transfer");
10207  if (From == To || FromNode == ToNode)
10208  return;
10209 
10210  if (!FromNode->getHasDebugValue())
10211  return;
10212 
10213  SDDbgOperand FromLocOp =
10214  SDDbgOperand::fromNode(From.getNode(), From.getResNo());
10215  SDDbgOperand ToLocOp = SDDbgOperand::fromNode(To.getNode(), To.getResNo());
10216 
10217  SmallVector<SDDbgValue *, 2> ClonedDVs;
10218  for (SDDbgValue *Dbg : GetDbgValues(FromNode)) {
10219  if (Dbg->isInvalidated())
10220  continue;
10221 
10222  // TODO: assert(!Dbg->isInvalidated() && "Transfer of invalid dbg value");
10223 
10224  // Create a new location ops vector that is equal to the old vector, but
10225  // with each instance of FromLocOp replaced with ToLocOp.
10226  bool Changed = false;
10227  auto NewLocOps = Dbg->copyLocationOps();
10228  std::replace_if(
10229  NewLocOps.begin(), NewLocOps.end(),
10230  [&Changed, FromLocOp](const SDDbgOperand &Op) {
10231  bool Match = Op == FromLocOp;
10232  Changed |= Match;
10233  return Match;
10234  },
10235  ToLocOp);
10236  // Ignore this SDDbgValue if we didn't find a matching location.
10237  if (!Changed)
10238  continue;
10239 
10240  DIVariable *Var = Dbg->getVariable();
10241  auto *Expr = Dbg->getExpression();
10242  // If a fragment is requested, update the expression.
10243  if (SizeInBits) {
10244  // When splitting a larger (e.g., sign-extended) value whose
10245  // lower bits are described with an SDDbgValue, do not attempt
10246  // to transfer the SDDbgValue to the upper bits.
10247  if (auto FI = Expr->getFragmentInfo())
10248  if (OffsetInBits + SizeInBits > FI->SizeInBits)
10249  continue;
10250  auto Fragment = DIExpression::createFragmentExpression(Expr, OffsetInBits,
10251  SizeInBits);
10252  if (!Fragment)
10253  continue;
10254  Expr = *Fragment;
10255  }
10256 
10257  auto AdditionalDependencies = Dbg->getAdditionalDependencies();
10258  // Clone the SDDbgValue and move it to To.
10259  SDDbgValue *Clone = getDbgValueList(
10260  Var, Expr, NewLocOps, AdditionalDependencies, Dbg->isIndirect(),
10261  Dbg->getDebugLoc(), std::max(ToNode->getIROrder(), Dbg->getOrder()),
10262  Dbg->isVariadic());
10263  ClonedDVs.push_back(Clone);
10264 
10265  if (InvalidateDbg) {
10266  // Invalidate value and indicate the SDDbgValue should not be emitted.
10267  Dbg->setIsInvalidated();
10268  Dbg->setIsEmitted();
10269  }
10270  }
10271 
10272  for (SDDbgValue *Dbg : ClonedDVs) {
10273  assert(is_contained(Dbg->getSDNodes(), ToNode) &&
10274  "Transferred DbgValues should depend on the new SDNode");
10275  AddDbgValue(Dbg, false);
10276  }
10277 }
10278 
10279 void SelectionDAG::salvageDebugInfo(SDNode &N) {
10280  if (!N.getHasDebugValue())
10281  return;
10282 
10283  SmallVector<SDDbgValue *, 2> ClonedDVs;
10284  for (auto *DV : GetDbgValues(&N)) {
10285  if (DV->isInvalidated())
10286  continue;
10287  switch (N.getOpcode()) {
10288  default:
10289  break;
10290  case ISD::ADD:
10291  SDValue N0 = N.getOperand(0);
10292  SDValue N1 = N.getOperand(1);
10293  if (!isConstantIntBuildVectorOrConstantInt(N0) &&
10294  isConstantIntBuildVectorOrConstantInt(N1)) {
10295  uint64_t Offset = N.getConstantOperandVal(1);
10296 
10297  // Rewrite an ADD constant node into a DIExpression. Since we are
10298  // performing arithmetic to compute the variable's *value* in the
10299  // DIExpression, we need to mark the expression with a
10300  // DW_OP_stack_value.
10301  auto *DIExpr = DV->getExpression();
10302  auto NewLocOps = DV->copyLocationOps();
10303  bool Changed = false;
10304  for (size_t i = 0; i < NewLocOps.size(); ++i) {
10305  // We're not given a ResNo to compare against because the whole
10306  // node is going away. We know that any ISD::ADD only has one
10307  // result, so we can assume any node match is using the result.
10308  if (NewLocOps[i].getKind() != SDDbgOperand::SDNODE ||
10309  NewLocOps[i].getSDNode() != &N)
10310  continue;
10311  NewLocOps[i] = SDDbgOperand::fromNode(N0.getNode(), N0.getResNo());
10312  SmallVector<uint64_t, 3> ExprOps;
10313  DIExpression::appendOffset(ExprOps, Offset);
10314  DIExpr = DIExpression::appendOpsToArg(DIExpr, ExprOps, i, true);
10315  Changed = true;
10316  }
10317  (void)Changed;
10318  assert(Changed && "Salvage target doesn't use N");
10319 
10320  auto AdditionalDependencies = DV->getAdditionalDependencies();
10321  SDDbgValue *Clone = getDbgValueList(DV->getVariable(), DIExpr,
10322  NewLocOps, AdditionalDependencies,
10323  DV->isIndirect(), DV->getDebugLoc(),
10324  DV->getOrder(), DV->isVariadic());
10325  ClonedDVs.push_back(Clone);
10326  DV->setIsInvalidated();
10327  DV->setIsEmitted();
10328  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SALVAGE: Rewriting";
10329  N0.getNode()->dumprFull(this);
10330  dbgs() << " into " << *DIExpr << '\n');
10331  }
10332  }
10333  }
10334 
10335  for (SDDbgValue *Dbg : ClonedDVs) {
10336  assert(!Dbg->getSDNodes().empty() &&
10337  "Salvaged DbgValue should depend on a new SDNode");
10338  AddDbgValue(Dbg, false);
10339  }
10340 }

10350 namespace {
10351 
10352 /// RAUWUpdateListener - Helper for ReplaceAllUsesWith - When the node
10353 /// pointed to by a use iterator is deleted, increment the use iterator
10354 /// so that it doesn't dangle.
10355 ///
10356 class RAUWUpdateListener : public SelectionDAG::DAGUpdateListener {
10357  SDNode::use_iterator &UI;
10358  SDNode::use_iterator &UE;
10359 
10360  void NodeDeleted(SDNode *N, SDNode *E) override {
10361  // Increment the iterator as needed.
10362  while (UI != UE && N == *UI)
10363  ++UI;
10364  }
10365 
10366 public:
10367  RAUWUpdateListener(SelectionDAG &d,
10368  SDNode::use_iterator &ui,
10369  SDNode::use_iterator &ue)
10370  : SelectionDAG::DAGUpdateListener(d), UI(ui), UE(ue) {}
10371 };
10372 
10373 } // end anonymous namespace
10374 
10375 /// ReplaceAllUsesWith - Modify anything using 'From' to use 'To' instead.
10376 /// This can cause recursive merging of nodes in the DAG.
10377 ///
10378 /// This version assumes From has a single result value.
10379 ///
10380 void SelectionDAG::ReplaceAllUsesWith(SDValue FromN, SDValue To) {
10381  SDNode *From = FromN.getNode();
10382  assert(From->getNumValues() == 1 && FromN.getResNo() == 0 &&
10383  "Cannot replace with this method!");
10384  assert(From != To.getNode() && "Cannot replace uses of with self");
10385 
10386  // Preserve Debug Values
10387  transferDbgValues(FromN, To);
10388  // Preserve extra info.
10389  copyExtraInfo(From, To.getNode());
10390 
10391  // Iterate over all the existing uses of From. New uses will be added
10392  // to the beginning of the use list, which we avoid visiting.
10393  // This specifically avoids visiting uses of From that arise while the
10394  // replacement is happening, because any such uses would be the result
10395  // of CSE: If an existing node looks like From after one of its operands
10396  // is replaced by To, we don't want to replace of all its users with To
10397  // too. See PR3018 for more info.
10398  SDNode::use_iterator UI = From->use_begin(), UE = From->use_end();
10399  RAUWUpdateListener Listener(*this, UI, UE);
10400  while (UI != UE) {
10401  SDNode *User = *UI;
10402 
10403  // This node is about to morph, remove its old self from the CSE maps.
10404  RemoveNodeFromCSEMaps(User);
10405 
10406  // A user can appear in a use list multiple times, and when this
10407  // happens the uses are usually next to each other in the list.
10408  // To help reduce the number of CSE recomputations, process all
10409  // the uses of this user that we can find this way.
10410  do {
10411  SDUse &Use = UI.getUse();
10412  ++UI;
10413  Use.set(To);
10414  if (To->isDivergent() != From->isDivergent())
10415  updateDivergence(User);
10416  } while (UI != UE && *UI == User);
10417  // Now that we have modified User, add it back to the CSE maps. If it
10418  // already exists there, recursively merge the results together.
10419  AddModifiedNodeToCSEMaps(User);
10420  }
10421 
10422  // If we just RAUW'd the root, take note.
10423  if (FromN == getRoot())
10424  setRoot(To);
10425 }
10426 
10427 /// ReplaceAllUsesWith - Modify anything using 'From' to use 'To' instead.
10428 /// This can cause recursive merging of nodes in the DAG.
10429 ///
10430 /// This version assumes that for each value of From, there is a
10431 /// corresponding value in To in the same position with the same type.
10432 ///
10433 void SelectionDAG::ReplaceAllUsesWith(SDNode *From, SDNode *To) {
10434 #ifndef NDEBUG
10435  for (unsigned i = 0, e = From->getNumValues(); i != e; ++i)
10436  assert((!From->hasAnyUseOfValue(i) ||
10437  From->getValueType(i) == To->getValueType(i)) &&
10438  "Cannot use this version of ReplaceAllUsesWith!");
10439 #endif
10440 
10441  // Handle the trivial case.
10442  if (From == To)
10443  return;
10444 
10445  // Preserve Debug Info. Only do this if there's a use.
10446  for (unsigned i = 0, e = From->getNumValues(); i != e; ++i)
10447  if (From->hasAnyUseOfValue(i)) {
10448  assert((i < To->getNumValues()) && "Invalid To location");
10449  transferDbgValues(SDValue(From, i), SDValue(To, i));
10450  }
10451  // Preserve extra info.
10452  copyExtraInfo(From, To);
10453 
10454  // Iterate over just the existing users of From. See the comments in
10455  // the ReplaceAllUsesWith above.
10456  SDNode::use_iterator UI = From->use_begin(), UE = From->use_end();
10457  RAUWUpdateListener Listener(*this, UI, UE);
10458  while (UI != UE) {
10459  SDNode *User = *UI;
10460 
10461  // This node is about to morph, remove its old self from the CSE maps.
10462  RemoveNodeFromCSEMaps(User);
10463 
10464  // A user can appear in a use list multiple times, and when this
10465  // happens the uses are usually next to each other in the list.
10466  // To help reduce the number of CSE recomputations, process all
10467  // the uses of this user that we can find this way.
10468  do {
10469  SDUse &Use = UI.getUse();
10470  ++UI;
10471  Use.setNode(To);
10472  if (To->isDivergent() != From->isDivergent())
10473  updateDivergence(User);
10474  } while (UI != UE && *UI == User);
10475 
10476  // Now that we have modified User, add it back to the CSE maps. If it
10477  // already exists there, recursively merge the results together.
10478  AddModifiedNodeToCSEMaps(User);
10479  }
10480 
10481  // If we just RAUW'd the root, take note.
10482  if (From == getRoot().getNode())
10483  setRoot(SDValue(To, getRoot().getResNo()));
10484 }
10485 
10486 /// ReplaceAllUsesWith - Modify anything using 'From' to use 'To' instead.
10487 /// This can cause recursive merging of nodes in the DAG.
10488 ///
10489 /// This version can replace From with any result values. To must match the
10490 /// number and types of values returned by From.
10491 void SelectionDAG::ReplaceAllUsesWith(SDNode *From, const SDValue *To) {
10492  if (From->getNumValues() == 1) // Handle the simple case efficiently.
10493  return ReplaceAllUsesWith(SDValue(From, 0), To[0]);
10494 
10495  for (unsigned i = 0, e = From->getNumValues(); i != e; ++i) {
10496  // Preserve Debug Info.
10497  transferDbgValues(SDValue(From, i), To[i]);
10498  // Preserve extra info.
10499  copyExtraInfo(From, To[i].getNode());
10500  }
10501 
10502  // Iterate over just the existing users of From. See the comments in
10503  // the ReplaceAllUsesWith above.
10504  SDNode::use_iterator UI = From->use_begin(), UE = From->use_end();
10505  RAUWUpdateListener Listener(*this, UI, UE);
10506  while (UI != UE) {
10507  SDNode *User = *UI;
10508 
10509  // This node is about to morph, remove its old self from the CSE maps.
10510  RemoveNodeFromCSEMaps(User);
10511 
10512  // A user can appear in a use list multiple times, and when this happens the
10513  // uses are usually next to each other in the list. To help reduce the
10514  // number of CSE and divergence recomputations, process all the uses of this
10515  // user that we can find this way.
10516  bool To_IsDivergent = false;
10517  do {
10518  SDUse &Use = UI.getUse();
10519  const SDValue &ToOp = To[Use.getResNo()];
10520  ++UI;
10521  Use.set(ToOp);
10522  To_IsDivergent |= ToOp->isDivergent();
10523  } while (UI != UE && *UI == User);
10524 
10525  if (To_IsDivergent != From->isDivergent())
10526  updateDivergence(User);
10527 
10528  // Now that we have modified User, add it back to the CSE maps. If it
10529  // already exists there, recursively merge the results together.
10530  AddModifiedNodeToCSEMaps(User);
10531  }
10532 
10533  // If we just RAUW'd the root, take note.
10534  if (From == getRoot().getNode())
10535  setRoot(SDValue(To[getRoot().getResNo()]));
10536 }
10537 
10538 /// ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith - Replace any uses of From with To, leaving
10539 /// uses of other values produced by From.getNode() alone. The Deleted
10540 /// vector is handled the same way as for ReplaceAllUsesWith.
10541 void SelectionDAG::ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue From, SDValue To){
10542  // Handle the really simple, really trivial case efficiently.
10543  if (From == To) return;
10544 
10545  // Handle the simple, trivial, case efficiently.
10546  if (From.getNode()->getNumValues() == 1) {
10547  ReplaceAllUsesWith(From, To);
10548  return;
10549  }
10550 
10551  // Preserve Debug Info.
10552  transferDbgValues(From, To);
10553  copyExtraInfo(From.getNode(), To.getNode());
10554 
10555  // Iterate over just the existing users of From. See the comments in
10556  // the ReplaceAllUsesWith above.
10557  SDNode::use_iterator UI = From.getNode()->use_begin(),
10558  UE = From.getNode()->use_end();
10559  RAUWUpdateListener Listener(*this, UI, UE);
10560  while (UI != UE) {
10561  SDNode *User = *UI;
10562  bool UserRemovedFromCSEMaps = false;
10563 
10564  // A user can appear in a use list multiple times, and when this
10565  // happens the uses are usually next to each other in the list.
10566  // To help reduce the number of CSE recomputations, process all
10567  // the uses of this user that we can find this way.
10568  do {
10569  SDUse &Use = UI.getUse();
10570 
10571  // Skip uses of different values from the same node.
10572  if (Use.getResNo() != From.getResNo()) {
10573  ++UI;
10574  continue;
10575  }
10576 
10577  // If this node hasn't been modified yet, it's still in the CSE maps,
10578  // so remove its old self from the CSE maps.
10579  if (!UserRemovedFromCSEMaps) {
10580  RemoveNodeFromCSEMaps(User);
10581  UserRemovedFromCSEMaps = true;
10582  }
10583 
10584  ++UI;
10585  Use.set(To);
10586  if (To->isDivergent() != From->isDivergent())
10587  updateDivergence(User);
10588  } while (UI != UE && *UI == User);
10589  // We are iterating over all uses of the From node, so if a use
10590  // doesn't use the specific value, no changes are made.
10591  if (!UserRemovedFromCSEMaps)
10592  continue;
10593 
10594  // Now that we have modified User, add it back to the CSE maps. If it
10595  // already exists there, recursively merge the results together.
10596  AddModifiedNodeToCSEMaps(User);
10597  }
10598 
10599  // If we just RAUW'd the root, take note.
10600  if (From == getRoot())
10601  setRoot(To);
10602 }
10603 
10604 namespace {
10605 
10606 /// UseMemo - This class is used by SelectionDAG::ReplaceAllUsesOfValuesWith
10607 /// to record information about a use.
10608 struct UseMemo {
10609  SDNode *User;
10610  unsigned Index;
10611  SDUse *Use;
10612 };
10613 
10614 /// operator< - Sort Memos by User.
10615 bool operator<(const UseMemo &L, const UseMemo &R) {
10616  return (intptr_t)L.User < (intptr_t)R.User;
10617 }
10618 
10619 /// RAUOVWUpdateListener - Helper for ReplaceAllUsesOfValuesWith - When the node
10620 /// pointed to by a UseMemo is deleted, set the User to nullptr to indicate that
10621 /// the node already has been taken care of recursively.
10622 class RAUOVWUpdateListener : public SelectionDAG::DAGUpdateListener {
10623  SmallVector<UseMemo, 4> &Uses;
10624 
10625  void NodeDeleted(SDNode *N, SDNode *E) override {
10626  for (UseMemo &Memo : Uses)
10627  if (Memo.User == N)
10628  Memo.User = nullptr;
10629  }
10630 
10631 public:
10632  RAUOVWUpdateListener(SelectionDAG &d, SmallVector<UseMemo, 4> &uses)
10633  : SelectionDAG::DAGUpdateListener(d), Uses(uses) {}
10634 };
10635 
10636 } // end anonymous namespace
10637 
10638 bool SelectionDAG::calculateDivergence(SDNode *N) {
10639  if (TLI->isSDNodeAlwaysUniform(N)) {
10640  assert(!TLI->isSDNodeSourceOfDivergence(N, FLI, DA) &&
10641  "Conflicting divergence information!");
10642  return false;
10643  }
10644  if (TLI->isSDNodeSourceOfDivergence(N, FLI, DA))
10645  return true;
10646  for (const auto &Op : N->ops()) {
10647  if (Op.Val.getValueType() != MVT::Other && Op.getNode()->isDivergent())
10648  return true;
10649  }
10650  return false;
10651 }
10652 
10653 void SelectionDAG::updateDivergence(SDNode *N) {
10654  SmallVector<SDNode *, 16> Worklist(1, N);
10655  do {
10656  N = Worklist.pop_back_val();
10657  bool IsDivergent = calculateDivergence(N);
10658  if (N->SDNodeBits.IsDivergent != IsDivergent) {
10659  N->SDNodeBits.IsDivergent = IsDivergent;
10660  llvm::append_range(Worklist, N->uses());
10661  }
10662  } while (!Worklist.empty());
10663 }
10664 
10665 void SelectionDAG::CreateTopologicalOrder(std::vector<SDNode *> &Order) {
10666  DenseMap<SDNode *, unsigned> Degree;
10667  Order.reserve(AllNodes.size());
10668  for (auto &N : allnodes()) {
10669  unsigned NOps = N.getNumOperands();
10670  Degree[&N] = NOps;
10671  if (0 == NOps)
10672  Order.push_back(&N);
10673  }
10674  for (size_t I = 0; I != Order.size(); ++I) {
10675  SDNode *N = Order[I];
10676  for (auto *U : N->uses()) {
10677  unsigned &UnsortedOps = Degree[U];
10678  if (0 == --UnsortedOps)
10679  Order.push_back(U);
10680  }
10681  }
10682 }
10683 
10684 #ifndef NDEBUG
10685 void SelectionDAG::VerifyDAGDivergence() {
10686  std::vector<SDNode *> TopoOrder;
10687  CreateTopologicalOrder(TopoOrder);
10688  for (auto *N : TopoOrder) {
10689  assert(calculateDivergence(N) == N->isDivergent() &&
10690  "Divergence bit inconsistency detected");
10691  }
10692 }
10693 #endif
10694 
10695 /// ReplaceAllUsesOfValuesWith - Replace any uses of From with To, leaving
10696 /// uses of other values produced by From.getNode() alone. The same value
10697 /// may appear in both the From and To list. The Deleted vector is
10698 /// handled the same way as for ReplaceAllUsesWith.
10699 void SelectionDAG::ReplaceAllUsesOfValuesWith(const SDValue *From,
10700  const SDValue *To,
10701  unsigned Num){
10702  // Handle the simple, trivial case efficiently.
10703  if (Num == 1)
10704  return ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(*From, *To);
10705 
10706  transferDbgValues(*From, *To);
10707  copyExtraInfo(From->getNode(), To->getNode());
10708 
10709  // Read up all the uses and make records of them. This helps
10710  // processing new uses that are introduced during the
10711  // replacement process.
10712  SmallVector<UseMemo, 4> Uses;
10713  for (unsigned i = 0; i != Num; ++i) {
10714  unsigned FromResNo = From[i].getResNo();
10715  SDNode *FromNode = From[i].getNode();
10716  for (SDNode::use_iterator UI = FromNode->use_begin(),
10717  E = FromNode->use_end(); UI != E; ++UI) {
10718  SDUse &Use = UI.getUse();
10719  if (Use.getResNo() == FromResNo) {
10720  UseMemo Memo = { *UI, i, &Use };
10721  Uses.push_back(Memo);
10722  }
10723  }
10724  }
10725 
10726  // Sort the uses, so that all the uses from a given User are together.
10727  llvm::sort(Uses);
10728  RAUOVWUpdateListener Listener(*this, Uses);
10729 
10730  for (unsigned UseIndex = 0, UseIndexEnd = Uses.size();
10731  UseIndex != UseIndexEnd; ) {
10732  // We know that this user uses some value of From. If it is the right
10733  // value, update it.
10734  SDNode *User = Uses[UseIndex].User;
10735  // If the node has been deleted by recursive CSE updates when updating
10736  // another node, then just skip this entry.
10737  if (User == nullptr) {
10738  ++UseIndex;
10739  continue;
10740  }
10741 
10742  // This node is about to morph, remove its old self from the CSE maps.
10743  RemoveNodeFromCSEMaps(User);
10744 
10745  // The Uses array is sorted, so all the uses for a given User
10746  // are next to each other in the list.
10747  // To help reduce the number of CSE recomputations, process all
10748  // the uses of this user that we can find this way.
10749  do {
10750  unsigned i = Uses[UseIndex].Index;
10751  SDUse &Use = *Uses[UseIndex].Use;
10752  ++UseIndex;
10753 
10754  Use.set(To[i]);
10755  } while (UseIndex != UseIndexEnd && Uses[UseIndex].User == User);
10756 
10757  // Now that we have modified User, add it back to the CSE maps. If it
10758  // already exists there, recursively merge the results together.
10759  AddModifiedNodeToCSEMaps(User);
10760  }
10761 }
10762 
10763 /// AssignTopologicalOrder - Assign a unique node id for each node in the DAG
10764 /// based on their topological order. It returns the maximum id and a vector
10765 /// of the SDNodes* in assigned order by reference.
10766 unsigned SelectionDAG::AssignTopologicalOrder() {
10767  unsigned DAGSize = 0;
10768 
10769  // SortedPos tracks the progress of the algorithm. Nodes before it are
10770  // sorted, nodes after it are unsorted. When the algorithm completes
10771  // it is at the end of the list.
10772  allnodes_iterator SortedPos = allnodes_begin();
10773 
10774  // Visit all the nodes. Move nodes with no operands to the front of
10775  // the list immediately. Annotate nodes that do have operands with their
10776  // operand count. Before we do this, the Node Id fields of the nodes
10777  // may contain arbitrary values. After, the Node Id fields for nodes
10778  // before SortedPos will contain the topological sort index, and the
10779  // Node Id fields for nodes At SortedPos and after will contain the
10780  // count of outstanding operands.
10781  for (SDNode &N : llvm::make_early_inc_range(allnodes())) {
10782  checkForCycles(&N, this);
10783  unsigned Degree = N.getNumOperands();
10784  if (Degree == 0) {
10785  // A node with no uses, add it to the result array immediately.
10786  N.setNodeId(DAGSize++);
10787  allnodes_iterator Q(&N);
10788  if (Q != SortedPos)
10789  SortedPos = AllNodes.insert(SortedPos, AllNodes.remove(Q));
10790  assert(SortedPos != AllNodes.end() && "Overran node list");
10791  ++SortedPos;
10792  } else {
10793  // Temporarily use the Node Id as scratch space for the degree count.
10794  N.setNodeId(Degree);
10795  }
10796  }
10797 
10798  // Visit all the nodes. As we iterate, move nodes into sorted order,
10799  // such that by the time the end is reached all nodes will be sorted.
10800  for (SDNode &Node : allnodes()) {
10801  SDNode *N = &Node;
10802  checkForCycles(N, this);
10803  // N is in sorted position, so all its uses have one less operand
10804  // that needs to be sorted.
10805  for (SDNode *P : N->uses()) {
10806  unsigned Degree = P->getNodeId();
10807  assert(Degree != 0 && "Invalid node degree");
10808  --Degree;
10809  if (Degree == 0) {
10810  // All of P's operands are sorted, so P may sorted now.
10811  P->setNodeId(DAGSize++);
10812  if (P->getIterator() != SortedPos)
10813  SortedPos = AllNodes.insert(SortedPos, AllNodes.remove(P));
10814  assert(SortedPos != AllNodes.end() && "Overran node list");
10815  ++SortedPos;
10816  } else {
10817  // Update P's outstanding operand count.
10818  P->setNodeId(Degree);
10819  }
10820  }
10821  if (Node.getIterator() == SortedPos) {
10822 #ifndef NDEBUG
10823  allnodes_iterator I(N);
10824  SDNode *S = &*++I;
10825  dbgs() << "Overran sorted position:\n";
10826  S->dumprFull(this); dbgs() << "\n";
10827  dbgs() << "Checking if this is due to cycles\n";
10828  checkForCycles(this, true);
10829 #endif
10830  llvm_unreachable(nullptr);
10831  }
10832  }
10833 
10834  assert(SortedPos == AllNodes.end() &&
10835  "Topological sort incomplete!");
10836  assert(AllNodes.front().getOpcode() == ISD::EntryToken &&
10837  "First node in topological sort is not the entry token!");
10838  assert(AllNodes.front().getNodeId() == 0 &&
10839  "First node in topological sort has non-zero id!");
10840  assert(AllNodes.front().getNumOperands() == 0 &&
10841  "First node in topological sort has operands!");
10842  assert(AllNodes.back().getNodeId() == (int)DAGSize-1 &&
10843  "Last node in topologic sort has unexpected id!");
10844  assert(AllNodes.back().use_empty() &&
10845  "Last node in topologic sort has users!");
10846  assert(DAGSize == allnodes_size() && "Node count mismatch!");
10847  return DAGSize;
10848 }

10850 /// AddDbgValue - Add a dbg_value SDNode. If SD is non-null that means the
10851 /// value is produced by SD.
10852 void SelectionDAG::AddDbgValue(SDDbgValue *DB, bool isParameter) {
10853  for (SDNode *SD : DB->getSDNodes()) {
10854  if (!SD)
10855  continue;
10856  assert(DbgInfo->getSDDbgValues(SD).empty() || SD->getHasDebugValue());
10857  SD->setHasDebugValue(true);
10858  }
10859  DbgInfo->add(DB, isParameter);
10860 }

10863 
10864 SDValue SelectionDAG::makeEquivalentMemoryOrdering(SDValue OldChain,
10865  SDValue NewMemOpChain) {
10866  assert(isa<MemSDNode>(NewMemOpChain) && "Expected a memop node");
10867  assert(NewMemOpChain.getValueType() == MVT::Other && "Expected a token VT");
10868  // The new memory operation must have the same position as the old load in
10869  // terms of memory dependency. Create a TokenFactor for the old load and new
10870  // memory operation and update uses of the old load's output chain to use that
10871  // TokenFactor.
10872  if (OldChain == NewMemOpChain || OldChain.use_empty())
10873  return NewMemOpChain;
10874 
10875  SDValue TokenFactor = getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, SDLoc(OldChain), MVT::Other,
10876  OldChain, NewMemOpChain);
10877  ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(OldChain, TokenFactor);
10878  UpdateNodeOperands(TokenFactor.getNode(), OldChain, NewMemOpChain);
10879  return TokenFactor;
10880 }
10881 
10882 SDValue SelectionDAG::makeEquivalentMemoryOrdering(LoadSDNode *OldLoad,
10883  SDValue NewMemOp) {
10884  assert(isa<MemSDNode>(NewMemOp.getNode()) && "Expected a memop node");
10885  SDValue OldChain = SDValue(OldLoad, 1);
10886  SDValue NewMemOpChain = NewMemOp.getValue(1);
10887  return makeEquivalentMemoryOrdering(OldChain, NewMemOpChain);
10888 }

10890 SDValue SelectionDAG::getSymbolFunctionGlobalAddress(SDValue Op,
10891  Function **OutFunction) {
10892  assert(isa<ExternalSymbolSDNode>(Op) && "Node should be an ExternalSymbol");
10893 
10894  auto *Symbol = cast<ExternalSymbolSDNode>(Op)->getSymbol();
10895  auto *Module = MF->getFunction().getParent();
10896  auto *Function = Module->getFunction(Symbol);
10897 
10898  if (OutFunction != nullptr)
10899  *OutFunction = Function;
10900 
10901  if (Function != nullptr) {
10902  auto PtrTy = TLI->getPointerTy(getDataLayout(), Function->getAddressSpace());
10903  return getGlobalAddress(Function, SDLoc(Op), PtrTy);
10904  }
10905 
10906  std::string ErrorStr;
10907  raw_string_ostream ErrorFormatter(ErrorStr);
10908  ErrorFormatter << "Undefined external symbol ";
10909  ErrorFormatter << '"' << Symbol << '"';
10910  report_fatal_error(Twine(ErrorFormatter.str()));
10911 }

10941 
10942 bool llvm::isNeutralConstant(unsigned Opcode, SDNodeFlags Flags, SDValue V,
10943  unsigned OperandNo) {
10944  // NOTE: The cases should match with IR's ConstantExpr::getBinOpIdentity().
10945  // TODO: Target-specific opcodes could be added.
10946  if (auto *Const = isConstOrConstSplat(V)) {
10947  switch (Opcode) {
10948  case ISD::ADD:
10949  case ISD::OR:
10950  case ISD::XOR:
10951  case ISD::UMAX:
10952  return Const->isZero();
10953  case ISD::MUL:
10954  return Const->isOne();
10955  case ISD::AND:
10956  case ISD::UMIN:
10957  return Const->isAllOnes();
10958  case ISD::SMAX:
10959  return Const->isMinSignedValue();
10960  case ISD::SMIN:
10961  return Const->isMaxSignedValue();
10962  case ISD::SUB:
10963  case ISD::SHL:
10964  case ISD::SRA:
10965  case ISD::SRL:
10966  return OperandNo == 1 && Const->isZero();
10967  case ISD::UDIV:
10968  case ISD::SDIV:
10969  return OperandNo == 1 && Const->isOne();
10970  }
10971  } else if (auto *ConstFP = isConstOrConstSplatFP(V)) {
10972  switch (Opcode) {
10973  case ISD::FADD:
10974  return ConstFP->isZero() &&
10975  (Flags.hasNoSignedZeros() || ConstFP->isNegative());
10976  case ISD::FSUB:
10977  return OperandNo == 1 && ConstFP->isZero() &&
10978  (Flags.hasNoSignedZeros() || !ConstFP->isNegative());
10979  case ISD::FMUL:
10980  return ConstFP->isExactlyValue(1.0);
10981  case ISD::FDIV:
10982  return OperandNo == 1 && ConstFP->isExactlyValue(1.0);
10983  case ISD::FMINNUM:
10984  case ISD::FMAXNUM: {
10985  // Neutral element for fminnum is NaN, Inf or FLT_MAX, depending on FMF.
10986  EVT VT = V.getValueType();
10987  const fltSemantics &Semantics = SelectionDAG::EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT);
10988  APFloat NeutralAF = !Flags.hasNoNaNs()
10989  ? APFloat::getQNaN(Semantics)
10990  : !Flags.hasNoInfs()
10991  ? APFloat::getInf(Semantics)
10992  : APFloat::getLargest(Semantics);
10993  if (Opcode == ISD::FMAXNUM)
10994  NeutralAF.changeSign();
10995 
10996  return ConstFP->isExactlyValue(NeutralAF);
10997  }
10998  }
10999  }
11000  return false;
11001 }

11003 SDValue llvm::peekThroughBitcasts(SDValue V) {
11004  while (V.getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST)
11005  V = V.getOperand(0);
11006  return V;
11007 }

11011  V = V.getOperand(0);
11012  return V;
11013 }

11015 SDValue llvm::peekThroughExtractSubvectors(SDValue V) {

11017  V = V.getOperand(0);
11018  return V;

11021 bool llvm::isBitwiseNot(SDValue V, bool AllowUndefs) {
11022  if (V.getOpcode() != ISD::XOR)
11023  return false;
11024  V = peekThroughBitcasts(V.getOperand(1));
11025  unsigned NumBits = V.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
11026  ConstantSDNode *C =
11027  isConstOrConstSplat(V, AllowUndefs, /*AllowTruncation*/ true);
11028  return C && (C->getAPIntValue().countTrailingOnes() >= NumBits);
11029 }
11030 
11031 ConstantSDNode *llvm::isConstOrConstSplat(SDValue N, bool AllowUndefs,
11032  bool AllowTruncation) {
11033  EVT VT = N.getValueType();
11034  APInt DemandedElts = VT.isFixedLengthVector()
11035  ? APInt::getAllOnes(VT.getVectorMinNumElements())
11036  : APInt(1, 1);
11037  return isConstOrConstSplat(N, DemandedElts, AllowUndefs, AllowTruncation);
11038 }
11039 
11040 ConstantSDNode *llvm::isConstOrConstSplat(SDValue N, const APInt &DemandedElts,
11041  bool AllowUndefs,
11042  bool AllowTruncation) {
11043  if (ConstantSDNode *CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N))
11044  return CN;
11045 
11046  // SplatVectors can truncate their operands. Ignore that case here unless
11047  // AllowTruncation is set.
11048  if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR) {
11049  EVT VecEltVT = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
11050  if (auto *CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(0))) {
11051  EVT CVT = CN->getValueType(0);
11052  assert(CVT.bitsGE(VecEltVT) && "Illegal splat_vector element extension");
11053  if (AllowTruncation || CVT == VecEltVT)
11054  return CN;
11055  }
11056  }
11057 
11058  if (BuildVectorSDNode *BV = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(N)) {
11059  BitVector UndefElements;
11060  ConstantSDNode *CN = BV->getConstantSplatNode(DemandedElts, &UndefElements);
11061 
11062  // BuildVectors can truncate their operands. Ignore that case here unless
11063  // AllowTruncation is set.
11064  // TODO: Look into whether we should allow UndefElements in non-DemandedElts
11065  if (CN && (UndefElements.none() || AllowUndefs)) {
11066  EVT CVT = CN->getValueType(0);
11067  EVT NSVT = N.getValueType().getScalarType();
11068  assert(CVT.bitsGE(NSVT) && "Illegal build vector element extension");
11069  if (AllowTruncation || (CVT == NSVT))
11070  return CN;
11071  }
11072  }
11073 
11074  return nullptr;
11075 }
11076 
11077 ConstantFPSDNode *llvm::isConstOrConstSplatFP(SDValue N, bool AllowUndefs) {
11078  EVT VT = N.getValueType();
11079  APInt DemandedElts = VT.isFixedLengthVector()
11080  ? APInt::getAllOnes(VT.getVectorMinNumElements())
11081  : APInt(1, 1);
11082  return isConstOrConstSplatFP(N, DemandedElts, AllowUndefs);
11083 }
11084 
11085 ConstantFPSDNode *llvm::isConstOrConstSplatFP(SDValue N,
11086  const APInt &DemandedElts,
11087  bool AllowUndefs) {
11088  if (ConstantFPSDNode *CN = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N))
11089  return CN;
11090 
11091  if (BuildVectorSDNode *BV = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(N)) {
11092  BitVector UndefElements;
11093  ConstantFPSDNode *CN =
11094  BV->getConstantFPSplatNode(DemandedElts, &UndefElements);
11095  // TODO: Look into whether we should allow UndefElements in non-DemandedElts
11096  if (CN && (UndefElements.none() || AllowUndefs))
11097  return CN;
11098  }
11099 
11100  if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR)
11101  if (ConstantFPSDNode *CN = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N.getOperand(0)))
11102  return CN;
11103 
11104  return nullptr;
11105 }

11196 /// hasNUsesOfValue - Return true if there are exactly NUSES uses of the
11197 /// indicated value. This method ignores uses of other values defined by this
11198 /// operation.
11199 bool SDNode::hasNUsesOfValue(unsigned NUses, unsigned Value) const {
11200  assert(Value < getNumValues() && "Bad value!");
11201 
11202  // TODO: Only iterate over uses of a given value of the node
11203  for (SDNode::use_iterator UI = use_begin(), E = use_end(); UI != E; ++UI) {
11204  if (UI.getUse().getResNo() == Value) {
11205  if (NUses == 0)
11206  return false;
11207  --NUses;
11208  }
11209  }
11210 
11211  // Found exactly the right number of uses?
11212  return NUses == 0;
11213 }

11262 
11263 /// reachesChainWithoutSideEffects - Return true if this operand (which must
11264 /// be a chain) reaches the specified operand without crossing any
11265 /// side-effecting instructions on any chain path. In practice, this looks
11266 /// through token factors and non-volatile loads. In order to remain efficient,
11267 /// this only looks a couple of nodes in, it does not do an exhaustive search.
11268 ///
11269 /// Note that we only need to examine chains when we're searching for
11270 /// side-effects; SelectionDAG requires that all side-effects are represented
11271 /// by chains, even if another operand would force a specific ordering. This
11272 /// constraint is necessary to allow transformations like splitting loads.
11273 bool SDValue::reachesChainWithoutSideEffects(SDValue Dest,
11274  unsigned Depth) const {
11275  if (*this == Dest) return true;
11276 
11277  // Don't search too deeply, we just want to be able to see through
11278  // TokenFactor's etc.
11279  if (Depth == 0) return false;
11280 
11281  // If this is a token factor, all inputs to the TF happen in parallel.
11282  if (getOpcode() == ISD::TokenFactor) {
11283  // First, try a shallow search.
11284  if (is_contained((*this)->ops(), Dest)) {
11285  // We found the chain we want as an operand of this TokenFactor.
11286  // Essentially, we reach the chain without side-effects if we could
11287  // serialize the TokenFactor into a simple chain of operations with
11288  // Dest as the last operation. This is automatically true if the
11289  // chain has one use: there are no other ordering constraints.
11290  // If the chain has more than one use, we give up: some other
11291  // use of Dest might force a side-effect between Dest and the current
11292  // node.
11293  if (Dest.hasOneUse())
11294  return true;
11295  }
11296  // Next, try a deep search: check whether every operand of the TokenFactor
11297  // reaches Dest.
11298  return llvm::all_of((*this)->ops(), [=](SDValue Op) {
11299  return Op.reachesChainWithoutSideEffects(Dest, Depth - 1);
11300  });
11301  }
11302 
11303  // Loads don't have side effects, look through them.
11304  if (LoadSDNode *Ld = dyn_cast<LoadSDNode>(*this)) {
11305  if (Ld->isUnordered())
11306  return Ld->getChain().reachesChainWithoutSideEffects(Dest, Depth-1);
11307  }
11308  return false;
11309 }

11314  Worklist.push_back(this);
11315  return hasPredecessorHelper(N, Visited, Worklist);
11316 }

11321 
11322 SDValue
11323 SelectionDAG::matchBinOpReduction(SDNode *Extract, ISD::NodeType &BinOp,
11324  ArrayRef<ISD::NodeType> CandidateBinOps,
11325  bool AllowPartials) {
11326  // The pattern must end in an extract from index 0.
11327  if (Extract->getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT ||
11328  !isNullConstant(Extract->getOperand(1)))
11329  return SDValue();
11330 
11331  // Match against one of the candidate binary ops.
11332  SDValue Op = Extract->getOperand(0);
11333  if (llvm::none_of(CandidateBinOps, [Op](ISD::NodeType BinOp) {
11334  return Op.getOpcode() == unsigned(BinOp);
11335  }))
11336  return SDValue();
11337 
11338  // Floating-point reductions may require relaxed constraints on the final step
11339  // of the reduction because they may reorder intermediate operations.
11340  unsigned CandidateBinOp = Op.getOpcode();
11341  if (Op.getValueType().isFloatingPoint()) {
11342  SDNodeFlags Flags = Op->getFlags();
11343  switch (CandidateBinOp) {
11344  case ISD::FADD:
11345  if (!Flags.hasNoSignedZeros() || !Flags.hasAllowReassociation())
11346  return SDValue();
11347  break;
11348  default:
11349  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled FP opcode for binop reduction");
11350  }
11351  }
11352 
11353  // Matching failed - attempt to see if we did enough stages that a partial
11354  // reduction from a subvector is possible.
11355  auto PartialReduction = [&](SDValue Op, unsigned NumSubElts) {
11356  if (!AllowPartials || !Op)
11357  return SDValue();
11358  EVT OpVT = Op.getValueType();
11359  EVT OpSVT = OpVT.getScalarType();
11360  EVT SubVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*getContext(), OpSVT, NumSubElts);
11361  if (!TLI->isExtractSubvectorCheap(SubVT, OpVT, 0))
11362  return SDValue();
11363  BinOp = (ISD::NodeType)CandidateBinOp;
11364  return getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, SDLoc(Op), SubVT, Op,
11365  getVectorIdxConstant(0, SDLoc(Op)));
11366  };
11367 
11368  // At each stage, we're looking for something that looks like:
11369  // %s = shufflevector <8 x i32> %op, <8 x i32> undef,
11370  // <8 x i32> <i32 2, i32 3, i32 undef, i32 undef,
11371  // i32 undef, i32 undef, i32 undef, i32 undef>
11372  // %a = binop <8 x i32> %op, %s
11373  // Where the mask changes according to the stage. E.g. for a 3-stage pyramid,
11374  // we expect something like:
11375  // <4,5,6,7,u,u,u,u>
11376  // <2,3,u,u,u,u,u,u>
11377  // <1,u,u,u,u,u,u,u>
11378  // While a partial reduction match would be:
11379  // <2,3,u,u,u,u,u,u>
11380  // <1,u,u,u,u,u,u,u>
11381  unsigned Stages = Log2_32(Op.getValueType().getVectorNumElements());
11382  SDValue PrevOp;
11383  for (unsigned i = 0; i < Stages; ++i) {
11384  unsigned MaskEnd = (1 << i);
11385 
11386  if (Op.getOpcode() != CandidateBinOp)
11387  return PartialReduction(PrevOp, MaskEnd);
11388 
11389  SDValue Op0 = Op.getOperand(0);
11390  SDValue Op1 = Op.getOperand(1);
11391 
11392  ShuffleVectorSDNode *Shuffle = dyn_cast<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(Op0);
11393  if (Shuffle) {
11394  Op = Op1;
11395  } else {
11396  Shuffle = dyn_cast<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(Op1);
11397  Op = Op0;
11398  }
11399 
11400  // The first operand of the shuffle should be the same as the other operand
11401  // of the binop.
11402  if (!Shuffle || Shuffle->getOperand(0) != Op)
11403  return PartialReduction(PrevOp, MaskEnd);
11404 
11405  // Verify the shuffle has the expected (at this stage of the pyramid) mask.
11406  for (int Index = 0; Index < (int)MaskEnd; ++Index)
11407  if (Shuffle->getMaskElt(Index) != (int)(MaskEnd + Index))
11408  return PartialReduction(PrevOp, MaskEnd);
11409 
11410  PrevOp = Op;
11411  }
11412 
11413  // Handle subvector reductions, which tend to appear after the shuffle
11414  // reduction stages.
11415  while (Op.getOpcode() == CandidateBinOp) {
11416  unsigned NumElts = Op.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
11417  SDValue Op0 = Op.getOperand(0);
11418  SDValue Op1 = Op.getOperand(1);
11419  if (Op0.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR ||
11420  Op1.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR ||
11421  Op0.getOperand(0) != Op1.getOperand(0))
11422  break;
11423  SDValue Src = Op0.getOperand(0);
11424  unsigned NumSrcElts = Src.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
11425  if (NumSrcElts != (2 * NumElts))
11426  break;
11427  if (!(Op0.getConstantOperandAPInt(1) == 0 &&
11428  Op1.getConstantOperandAPInt(1) == NumElts) &&
11429  !(Op1.getConstantOperandAPInt(1) == 0 &&
11430  Op0.getConstantOperandAPInt(1) == NumElts))
11431  break;
11432  Op = Src;
11433  }
11434 
11435  BinOp = (ISD::NodeType)CandidateBinOp;
11436  return Op;
11437 }
11438 
11439 SDValue SelectionDAG::UnrollVectorOp(SDNode *N, unsigned ResNE) {
11440  assert(N->getNumValues() == 1 &&
11441  "Can't unroll a vector with multiple results!");
11442 
11443  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
11444  unsigned NE = VT.getVectorNumElements();
11445  EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
11446  SDLoc dl(N);
11447 
11448  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Scalars;
11449  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Operands(N->getNumOperands());
11450 
11451  // If ResNE is 0, fully unroll the vector op.
11452  if (ResNE == 0)
11453  ResNE = NE;
11454  else if (NE > ResNE)
11455  NE = ResNE;
11456 
11457  unsigned i;
11458  for (i= 0; i != NE; ++i) {
11459  for (unsigned j = 0, e = N->getNumOperands(); j != e; ++j) {
11460  SDValue Operand = N->getOperand(j);
11461  EVT OperandVT = Operand.getValueType();
11462  if (OperandVT.isVector()) {
11463  // A vector operand; extract a single element.
11464  EVT OperandEltVT = OperandVT.getVectorElementType();
11465  Operands[j] = getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, OperandEltVT,
11466  Operand, getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
11467  } else {
11468  // A scalar operand; just use it as is.
11469  Operands[j] = Operand;
11470  }
11471  }
11472 
11473  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
11474  default: {
11475  Scalars.push_back(getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, EltVT, Operands,
11476  N->getFlags()));
11477  break;
11478  }
11479  case ISD::VSELECT:
11480  Scalars.push_back(getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, EltVT, Operands));
11481  break;
11482  case ISD::SHL:
11483  case ISD::SRA:
11484  case ISD::SRL:
11485  case ISD::ROTL:
11486  case ISD::ROTR:
11487  Scalars.push_back(getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, EltVT, Operands[0],
11488  getShiftAmountOperand(Operands[0].getValueType(),
11489  Operands[1])));
11490  break;
11491  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: {
11492  EVT ExtVT = cast<VTSDNode>(Operands[1])->getVT().getVectorElementType();
11493  Scalars.push_back(getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, EltVT,
11494  Operands[0],
11495  getValueType(ExtVT)));
11496  }
11497  }
11498  }
11499 
11500  for (; i < ResNE; ++i)
11501  Scalars.push_back(getUNDEF(EltVT));
11502 
11503  EVT VecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*getContext(), EltVT, ResNE);
11504  return getBuildVector(VecVT, dl, Scalars);
11505 }
11506 
11507 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> SelectionDAG::UnrollVectorOverflowOp(
11508  SDNode *N, unsigned ResNE) {
11509  unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode();
11510  assert((Opcode == ISD::UADDO || Opcode == ISD::SADDO ||
11511  Opcode == ISD::USUBO || Opcode == ISD::SSUBO ||
11512  Opcode == ISD::UMULO || Opcode == ISD::SMULO) &&
11513  "Expected an overflow opcode");
11514 
11515  EVT ResVT = N->getValueType(0);
11516  EVT OvVT = N->getValueType(1);
11517  EVT ResEltVT = ResVT.getVectorElementType();
11518  EVT OvEltVT = OvVT.getVectorElementType();
11519  SDLoc dl(N);
11520 
11521  // If ResNE is 0, fully unroll the vector op.
11522  unsigned NE = ResVT.getVectorNumElements();
11523  if (ResNE == 0)
11524  ResNE = NE;
11525  else if (NE > ResNE)
11526  NE = ResNE;
11527 
11528  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> LHSScalars;
11529  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> RHSScalars;
11530  ExtractVectorElements(N->getOperand(0), LHSScalars, 0, NE);
11531  ExtractVectorElements(N->getOperand(1), RHSScalars, 0, NE);
11532 
11533  EVT SVT = TLI->getSetCCResultType(getDataLayout(), *getContext(), ResEltVT);
11534  SDVTList VTs = getVTList(ResEltVT, SVT);
11535  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> ResScalars;
11536  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> OvScalars;
11537  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NE; ++i) {
11538  SDValue Res = getNode(Opcode, dl, VTs, LHSScalars[i], RHSScalars[i]);
11539  SDValue Ov =
11540  getSelect(dl, OvEltVT, Res.getValue(1),
11541  getBoolConstant(true, dl, OvEltVT, ResVT),
11542  getConstant(0, dl, OvEltVT));
11543 
11544  ResScalars.push_back(Res);
11545  OvScalars.push_back(Ov);
11546  }
11547 
11548  ResScalars.append(ResNE - NE, getUNDEF(ResEltVT));
11549  OvScalars.append(ResNE - NE, getUNDEF(OvEltVT));
11550 
11551  EVT NewResVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*getContext(), ResEltVT, ResNE);
11552  EVT NewOvVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*getContext(), OvEltVT, ResNE);
11553  return std::make_pair(getBuildVector(NewResVT, dl, ResScalars),
11554  getBuildVector(NewOvVT, dl, OvScalars));
11555 }
11556 
11557 bool SelectionDAG::areNonVolatileConsecutiveLoads(LoadSDNode *LD,
11558  LoadSDNode *Base,
11559  unsigned Bytes,
11560  int Dist) const {
11561  if (LD->isVolatile() || Base->isVolatile())
11562  return false;
11563  // TODO: probably too restrictive for atomics, revisit
11564  if (!LD->isSimple())
11565  return false;
11566  if (LD->isIndexed() || Base->isIndexed())
11567  return false;
11568  if (LD->getChain() != Base->getChain())
11569  return false;
11570  EVT VT = LD->getMemoryVT();
11571  if (VT.getSizeInBits() / 8 != Bytes)
11572  return false;
11573 
11574  auto BaseLocDecomp = BaseIndexOffset::match(Base, *this);
11575  auto LocDecomp = BaseIndexOffset::match(LD, *this);
11576 
11577  int64_t Offset = 0;
11578  if (BaseLocDecomp.equalBaseIndex(LocDecomp, *this, Offset))
11579  return (Dist * Bytes == Offset);
11580  return false;
11581 }
11582 
11583 /// InferPtrAlignment - Infer alignment of a load / store address. Return
11584 /// std::nullopt if it cannot be inferred.
11585 MaybeAlign SelectionDAG::InferPtrAlign(SDValue Ptr) const {
11586  // If this is a GlobalAddress + cst, return the alignment.
11587  const GlobalValue *GV = nullptr;
11588  int64_t GVOffset = 0;
11589  if (TLI->isGAPlusOffset(Ptr.getNode(), GV, GVOffset)) {
11590  unsigned PtrWidth = getDataLayout().getPointerTypeSizeInBits(GV->getType());
11591  KnownBits Known(PtrWidth);
11592  llvm::computeKnownBits(GV, Known, getDataLayout());
11593  unsigned AlignBits = Known.countMinTrailingZeros();
11594  if (AlignBits)
11595  return commonAlignment(Align(1ull << std::min(31U, AlignBits)), GVOffset);
11596  }
11597 
11598  // If this is a direct reference to a stack slot, use information about the
11599  // stack slot's alignment.
11600  int FrameIdx = INT_MIN;
11601  int64_t FrameOffset = 0;
11602  if (FrameIndexSDNode *FI = dyn_cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(Ptr)) {
11603  FrameIdx = FI->getIndex();
11604  } else if (isBaseWithConstantOffset(Ptr) &&
11605  isa<FrameIndexSDNode>(Ptr.getOperand(0))) {
11606  // Handle FI+Cst
11607  FrameIdx = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(Ptr.getOperand(0))->getIndex();
11608  FrameOffset = Ptr.getConstantOperandVal(1);
11609  }
11610 
11611  if (FrameIdx != INT_MIN) {
11612  const MachineFrameInfo &MFI = getMachineFunction().getFrameInfo();
11613  return commonAlignment(MFI.getObjectAlign(FrameIdx), FrameOffset);
11614  }
11615 
11616  return std::nullopt;
11617 }
11618 
11619 /// GetSplitDestVTs - Compute the VTs needed for the low/hi parts of a type
11620 /// which is split (or expanded) into two not necessarily identical pieces.
11621 std::pair<EVT, EVT> SelectionDAG::GetSplitDestVTs(const EVT &VT) const {
11622  // Currently all types are split in half.
11623  EVT LoVT, HiVT;
11624  if (!VT.isVector())
11625  LoVT = HiVT = TLI->getTypeToTransformTo(*getContext(), VT);
11626  else
11627  LoVT = HiVT = VT.getHalfNumVectorElementsVT(*getContext());
11628 
11629  return std::make_pair(LoVT, HiVT);
11630 }
11631 
11632 /// GetDependentSplitDestVTs - Compute the VTs needed for the low/hi parts of a
11633 /// type, dependent on an enveloping VT that has been split into two identical
11634 /// pieces. Sets the HiIsEmpty flag when hi type has zero storage size.
11635 std::pair<EVT, EVT>
11636 SelectionDAG::GetDependentSplitDestVTs(const EVT &VT, const EVT &EnvVT,
11637  bool *HiIsEmpty) const {
11638  EVT EltTp = VT.getVectorElementType();
11639  // Examples:
11640  // custom VL=8 with enveloping VL=8/8 yields 8/0 (hi empty)
11641  // custom VL=9 with enveloping VL=8/8 yields 8/1
11642  // custom VL=10 with enveloping VL=8/8 yields 8/2
11643  // etc.
11644  ElementCount VTNumElts = VT.getVectorElementCount();
11645  ElementCount EnvNumElts = EnvVT.getVectorElementCount();
11646  assert(VTNumElts.isScalable() == EnvNumElts.isScalable() &&
11647  "Mixing fixed width and scalable vectors when enveloping a type");
11648  EVT LoVT, HiVT;
11649  if (VTNumElts.getKnownMinValue() > EnvNumElts.getKnownMinValue()) {
11650  LoVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*getContext(), EltTp, EnvNumElts);
11651  HiVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*getContext(), EltTp, VTNumElts - EnvNumElts);
11652  *HiIsEmpty = false;
11653  } else {
11654  // Flag that hi type has zero storage size, but return split envelop type
11655  // (this would be easier if vector types with zero elements were allowed).
11656  LoVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*getContext(), EltTp, VTNumElts);
11657  HiVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*getContext(), EltTp, EnvNumElts);
11658  *HiIsEmpty = true;
11659  }
11660  return std::make_pair(LoVT, HiVT);
11661 }
11662 
11663 /// SplitVector - Split the vector with EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR and return the
11664 /// low/high part.
11665 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue>
11666 SelectionDAG::SplitVector(const SDValue &N, const SDLoc &DL, const EVT &LoVT,
11667  const EVT &HiVT) {
11668  assert(LoVT.isScalableVector() == HiVT.isScalableVector() &&
11669  LoVT.isScalableVector() == N.getValueType().isScalableVector() &&
11670  "Splitting vector with an invalid mixture of fixed and scalable "
11671  "vector types");
11672  assert(LoVT.getVectorMinNumElements() + HiVT.getVectorMinNumElements() <=
11673  N.getValueType().getVectorMinNumElements() &&
11674  "More vector elements requested than available!");
11675  SDValue Lo, Hi;
11676  Lo =
11677  getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, LoVT, N, getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
11678  // For scalable vectors it is safe to use LoVT.getVectorMinNumElements()
11679  // (rather than having to use ElementCount), because EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR scales
11680  // IDX with the runtime scaling factor of the result vector type. For
11681  // fixed-width result vectors, that runtime scaling factor is 1.
11682  Hi = getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, HiVT, N,
11683  getVectorIdxConstant(LoVT.getVectorMinNumElements(), DL));
11684  return std::make_pair(Lo, Hi);
11685 }
11686 
11687 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> SelectionDAG::SplitEVL(SDValue N, EVT VecVT,
11688  const SDLoc &DL) {
11689  // Split the vector length parameter.
11690  // %evl -> umin(%evl, %halfnumelts) and usubsat(%evl - %halfnumelts).
11691  EVT VT = N.getValueType();
11692  assert(VecVT.getVectorElementCount().isKnownEven() &&
11693  "Expecting the mask to be an evenly-sized vector");
11694  unsigned HalfMinNumElts = VecVT.getVectorMinNumElements() / 2;
11695  SDValue HalfNumElts =
11696  VecVT.isFixedLengthVector()
11697  ? getConstant(HalfMinNumElts, DL, VT)
11698  : getVScale(DL, VT, APInt(VT.getScalarSizeInBits(), HalfMinNumElts));
11699  SDValue Lo = getNode(ISD::UMIN, DL, VT, N, HalfNumElts);
11700  SDValue Hi = getNode(ISD::USUBSAT, DL, VT, N, HalfNumElts);
11701  return std::make_pair(Lo, Hi);
11702 }
11703 
11704 /// Widen the vector up to the next power of two using INSERT_SUBVECTOR.
11705 SDValue SelectionDAG::WidenVector(const SDValue &N, const SDLoc &DL) {
11706  EVT VT = N.getValueType();
11707  EVT WideVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*getContext(), VT.getVectorElementType(),
11708  NextPowerOf2(VT.getVectorNumElements()));
11709  return getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, WideVT, getUNDEF(WideVT), N,
11710  getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
11711 }

11713 void SelectionDAG::ExtractVectorElements(SDValue Op,
11714  SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Args,
11715  unsigned Start, unsigned Count,
11716  EVT EltVT) {
11717  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
11718  if (Count == 0)
11719  Count = VT.getVectorNumElements();
11720  if (EltVT == EVT())
11721  EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
11722  SDLoc SL(Op);
11723  for (unsigned i = Start, e = Start + Count; i != e; ++i) {
11724  Args.push_back(getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, EltVT, Op,
11725  getVectorIdxConstant(i, SL)));
11726  }
11727 }

11739 
11740 bool BuildVectorSDNode::isConstantSplat(APInt &SplatValue, APInt &SplatUndef,
11741  unsigned &SplatBitSize,
11742  bool &HasAnyUndefs,
11743  unsigned MinSplatBits,
11744  bool IsBigEndian) const {
11745  EVT VT = getValueType(0);
11746  assert(VT.isVector() && "Expected a vector type");
11747  unsigned VecWidth = VT.getSizeInBits();
11748  if (MinSplatBits > VecWidth)
11749  return false;
11750 
11751  // FIXME: The widths are based on this node's type, but build vectors can
11752  // truncate their operands.
11753  SplatValue = APInt(VecWidth, 0);
11754  SplatUndef = APInt(VecWidth, 0);
11755 
11756  // Get the bits. Bits with undefined values (when the corresponding element
11757  // of the vector is an ISD::UNDEF value) are set in SplatUndef and cleared
11758  // in SplatValue. If any of the values are not constant, give up and return
11759  // false.
11760  unsigned int NumOps = getNumOperands();
11761  assert(NumOps > 0 && "isConstantSplat has 0-size build vector");
11762  unsigned EltWidth = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
11763 
11764  for (unsigned j = 0; j < NumOps; ++j) {
11765  unsigned i = IsBigEndian ? NumOps - 1 - j : j;
11766  SDValue OpVal = getOperand(i);
11767  unsigned BitPos = j * EltWidth;
11768 
11769  if (OpVal.isUndef())
11770  SplatUndef.setBits(BitPos, BitPos + EltWidth);
11771  else if (auto *CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(OpVal))
11772  SplatValue.insertBits(CN->getAPIntValue().zextOrTrunc(EltWidth), BitPos);
11773  else if (auto *CN = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(OpVal))
11774  SplatValue.insertBits(CN->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt(), BitPos);
11775  else
11776  return false;
11777  }
11778 
11779  // The build_vector is all constants or undefs. Find the smallest element
11780  // size that splats the vector.
11781  HasAnyUndefs = (SplatUndef != 0);
11782 
11783  // FIXME: This does not work for vectors with elements less than 8 bits.
11784  while (VecWidth > 8) {
11785  unsigned HalfSize = VecWidth / 2;
11786  APInt HighValue = SplatValue.extractBits(HalfSize, HalfSize);
11787  APInt LowValue = SplatValue.extractBits(HalfSize, 0);
11788  APInt HighUndef = SplatUndef.extractBits(HalfSize, HalfSize);
11789  APInt LowUndef = SplatUndef.extractBits(HalfSize, 0);
11790 
11791  // If the two halves do not match (ignoring undef bits), stop here.
11792  if ((HighValue & ~LowUndef) != (LowValue & ~HighUndef) ||
11793  MinSplatBits > HalfSize)
11794  break;
11795 
11796  SplatValue = HighValue | LowValue;
11797  SplatUndef = HighUndef & LowUndef;
11798 
11799  VecWidth = HalfSize;
11800  }
11801 
11802  SplatBitSize = VecWidth;
11803  return true;
11804 }
11805 
11806 SDValue BuildVectorSDNode::getSplatValue(const APInt &DemandedElts,
11807  BitVector *UndefElements) const {
11808  unsigned NumOps = getNumOperands();
11809  if (UndefElements) {
11810  UndefElements->clear();
11811  UndefElements->resize(NumOps);
11812  }
11813  assert(NumOps == DemandedElts.getBitWidth() && "Unexpected vector size");
11814  if (!DemandedElts)
11815  return SDValue();
11816  SDValue Splatted;
11817  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumOps; ++i) {
11818  if (!DemandedElts[i])
11819  continue;
11820  SDValue Op = getOperand(i);
11821  if (Op.isUndef()) {
11822  if (UndefElements)
11823  (*UndefElements)[i] = true;
11824  } else if (!Splatted) {
11825  Splatted = Op;
11826  } else if (Splatted != Op) {
11827  return SDValue();
11828  }
11829  }
11830 
11831  if (!Splatted) {
11832  unsigned FirstDemandedIdx = DemandedElts.countTrailingZeros();
11833  assert(getOperand(FirstDemandedIdx).isUndef() &&
11834  "Can only have a splat without a constant for all undefs.");
11835  return getOperand(FirstDemandedIdx);
11836  }
11837 
11838  return Splatted;
11839 }
11840 
11841 SDValue BuildVectorSDNode::getSplatValue(BitVector *UndefElements) const {
11842  APInt DemandedElts = APInt::getAllOnes(getNumOperands());
11843  return getSplatValue(DemandedElts, UndefElements);
11844 }
11845 
11846 bool BuildVectorSDNode::getRepeatedSequence(const APInt &DemandedElts,
11847  SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Sequence,
11848  BitVector *UndefElements) const {
11849  unsigned NumOps = getNumOperands();
11850  Sequence.clear();
11851  if (UndefElements) {
11852  UndefElements->clear();
11853  UndefElements->resize(NumOps);
11854  }
11855  assert(NumOps == DemandedElts.getBitWidth() && "Unexpected vector size");
11856  if (!DemandedElts || NumOps < 2 || !isPowerOf2_32(NumOps))
11857  return false;
11858 
11859  // Set the undefs even if we don't find a sequence (like getSplatValue).
11860  if (UndefElements)
11861  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumOps; ++I)
11862  if (DemandedElts[I] && getOperand(I).isUndef())
11863  (*UndefElements)[I] = true;
11864 
11865  // Iteratively widen the sequence length looking for repetitions.
11866  for (unsigned SeqLen = 1; SeqLen < NumOps; SeqLen *= 2) {
11867  Sequence.append(SeqLen, SDValue());
11868  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumOps; ++I) {
11869  if (!DemandedElts[I])
11870  continue;
11871  SDValue &SeqOp = Sequence[I % SeqLen];
11872  SDValue Op = getOperand(I);
11873  if (Op.isUndef()) {
11874  if (!SeqOp)
11875  SeqOp = Op;
11876  continue;
11877  }
11878  if (SeqOp && !SeqOp.isUndef() && SeqOp != Op) {
11879  Sequence.clear();
11880  break;
11881  }
11882  SeqOp = Op;
11883  }
11884  if (!Sequence.empty())
11885  return true;
11886  }
11887 
11888  assert(Sequence.empty() && "Failed to empty non-repeating sequence pattern");
11889  return false;
11890 }
11891 
11892 bool BuildVectorSDNode::getRepeatedSequence(SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Sequence,
11893  BitVector *UndefElements) const {
11894  APInt DemandedElts = APInt::getAllOnes(getNumOperands());
11895  return getRepeatedSequence(DemandedElts, Sequence, UndefElements);
11896 }

11922 int32_t
11923 BuildVectorSDNode::getConstantFPSplatPow2ToLog2Int(BitVector *UndefElements,
11924  uint32_t BitWidth) const {
11925  if (ConstantFPSDNode *CN =
11926  dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantFPSDNode>(getSplatValue(UndefElements))) {
11927  bool IsExact;
11928  APSInt IntVal(BitWidth);
11929  const APFloat &APF = CN->getValueAPF();
11930  if (APF.convertToInteger(IntVal, APFloat::rmTowardZero, &IsExact) !=
11931  APFloat::opOK ||
11932  !IsExact)
11933  return -1;
11934 
11935  return IntVal.exactLogBase2();
11936  }
11937  return -1;
11938 }

11940 bool BuildVectorSDNode::getConstantRawBits(
11941  bool IsLittleEndian, unsigned DstEltSizeInBits,
11942  SmallVectorImpl<APInt> &RawBitElements, BitVector &UndefElements) const {
11943  // Early-out if this contains anything but Undef/Constant/ConstantFP.
11944  if (!isConstant())
11945  return false;
11946 
11947  unsigned NumSrcOps = getNumOperands();
11948  unsigned SrcEltSizeInBits = getValueType(0).getScalarSizeInBits();
11949  assert(((NumSrcOps * SrcEltSizeInBits) % DstEltSizeInBits) == 0 &&
11950  "Invalid bitcast scale");
11951 
11952  // Extract raw src bits.
11953  SmallVector<APInt> SrcBitElements(NumSrcOps,
11954  APInt::getNullValue(SrcEltSizeInBits));
11955  BitVector SrcUndeElements(NumSrcOps, false);
11956 
11957  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumSrcOps; ++I) {
11958  SDValue Op = getOperand(I);
11959  if (Op.isUndef()) {
11960  SrcUndeElements.set(I);
11961  continue;
11962  }
11963  auto *CInt = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op);
11964  auto *CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op);
11965  assert((CInt || CFP) && "Unknown constant");
11966  SrcBitElements[I] = CInt ? CInt->getAPIntValue().trunc(SrcEltSizeInBits)
11967  : CFP->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt();
11968  }
11969 
11970  // Recast to dst width.
11971  recastRawBits(IsLittleEndian, DstEltSizeInBits, RawBitElements,
11972  SrcBitElements, UndefElements, SrcUndeElements);
11973  return true;
11974 }
11975 
11976 void BuildVectorSDNode::recastRawBits(bool IsLittleEndian,
11977  unsigned DstEltSizeInBits,
11978  SmallVectorImpl<APInt> &DstBitElements,
11979  ArrayRef<APInt> SrcBitElements,
11980  BitVector &DstUndefElements,
11981  const BitVector &SrcUndefElements) {
11982  unsigned NumSrcOps = SrcBitElements.size();
11983  unsigned SrcEltSizeInBits = SrcBitElements[0].getBitWidth();
11984  assert(((NumSrcOps * SrcEltSizeInBits) % DstEltSizeInBits) == 0 &&
11985  "Invalid bitcast scale");
11986  assert(NumSrcOps == SrcUndefElements.size() &&
11987  "Vector size mismatch");
11988 
11989  unsigned NumDstOps = (NumSrcOps * SrcEltSizeInBits) / DstEltSizeInBits;
11990  DstUndefElements.clear();
11991  DstUndefElements.resize(NumDstOps, false);
11992  DstBitElements.assign(NumDstOps, APInt::getNullValue(DstEltSizeInBits));
11993 
11994  // Concatenate src elements constant bits together into dst element.
11995  if (SrcEltSizeInBits <= DstEltSizeInBits) {
11996  unsigned Scale = DstEltSizeInBits / SrcEltSizeInBits;
11997  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumDstOps; ++I) {
11998  DstUndefElements.set(I);
11999  APInt &DstBits = DstBitElements[I];
12000  for (unsigned J = 0; J != Scale; ++J) {
12001  unsigned Idx = (I * Scale) + (IsLittleEndian ? J : (Scale - J - 1));
12002  if (SrcUndefElements[Idx])
12003  continue;
12004  DstUndefElements.reset(I);
12005  const APInt &SrcBits = SrcBitElements[Idx];
12006  assert(SrcBits.getBitWidth() == SrcEltSizeInBits &&
12007  "Illegal constant bitwidths");
12008  DstBits.insertBits(SrcBits, J * SrcEltSizeInBits);
12009  }
12010  }
12011  return;
12012  }
12013 
12014  // Split src element constant bits into dst elements.
12015  unsigned Scale = SrcEltSizeInBits / DstEltSizeInBits;
12016  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumSrcOps; ++I) {
12017  if (SrcUndefElements[I]) {
12018  DstUndefElements.set(I * Scale, (I + 1) * Scale);
12019  continue;
12020  }
12021  const APInt &SrcBits = SrcBitElements[I];
12022  for (unsigned J = 0; J != Scale; ++J) {
12023  unsigned Idx = (I * Scale) + (IsLittleEndian ? J : (Scale - J - 1));
12024  APInt &DstBits = DstBitElements[Idx];
12025  DstBits = SrcBits.extractBits(DstEltSizeInBits, J * DstEltSizeInBits);
12026  }
12027  }
12028 }
12029 
12030 bool BuildVectorSDNode::isConstant() const {
12031  for (const SDValue &Op : op_values()) {
12032  unsigned Opc = Op.getOpcode();
12033  if (Opc != ISD::UNDEF && Opc != ISD::Constant && Opc != ISD::ConstantFP)
12034  return false;
12035  }
12036  return true;
12037 }
12038 
12039 std::optional<std::pair<APInt, APInt>>
12040 BuildVectorSDNode::isConstantSequence() const {
12041  unsigned NumOps = getNumOperands();
12042  if (NumOps < 2)
12043  return std::nullopt;
12044 
12045  if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(getOperand(0)) ||
12046  !isa<ConstantSDNode>(getOperand(1)))
12047  return std::nullopt;
12048 
12049  unsigned EltSize = getValueType(0).getScalarSizeInBits();
12050  APInt Start = getConstantOperandAPInt(0).trunc(EltSize);
12051  APInt Stride = getConstantOperandAPInt(1).trunc(EltSize) - Start;
12052 
12053  if (Stride.isZero())
12054  return std::nullopt;
12055 
12056  for (unsigned i = 2; i < NumOps; ++i) {
12057  if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(getOperand(i)))
12058  return std::nullopt;
12059 
12060  APInt Val = getConstantOperandAPInt(i).trunc(EltSize);
12061  if (Val != (Start + (Stride * i)))
12062  return std::nullopt;
12063  }
12064 
12065  return std::make_pair(Start, Stride);
12066 }
12067 
12068 bool ShuffleVectorSDNode::isSplatMask(const int *Mask, EVT VT) {
12069  // Find the first non-undef value in the shuffle mask.
12070  unsigned i, e;
12071  for (i = 0, e = VT.getVectorNumElements(); i != e && Mask[i] < 0; ++i)
12072  /* search */;
12073 
12074  // If all elements are undefined, this shuffle can be considered a splat
12075  // (although it should eventually get simplified away completely).
12076  if (i == e)
12077  return true;
12078 
12079  // Make sure all remaining elements are either undef or the same as the first
12080  // non-undef value.
12081  for (int Idx = Mask[i]; i != e; ++i)
12082  if (Mask[i] >= 0 && Mask[i] != Idx)
12083  return false;
12084  return true;
12085 }

12087 // Returns the SDNode if it is a constant integer BuildVector
12088 // or constant integer.
12089 SDNode *SelectionDAG::isConstantIntBuildVectorOrConstantInt(SDValue N) const {
12090  if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(N))
12091  return N.getNode();
12092  if (ISD::isBuildVectorOfConstantSDNodes(N.getNode()))
12093  return N.getNode();
12094  // Treat a GlobalAddress supporting constant offset folding as a
12095  // constant integer.
12096  if (GlobalAddressSDNode *GA = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(N))
12097  if (GA->getOpcode() == ISD::GlobalAddress &&
12098  TLI->isOffsetFoldingLegal(GA))
12099  return GA;
12100  if ((N.getOpcode() == ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR) &&
12101  isa<ConstantSDNode>(N.getOperand(0)))
12102  return N.getNode();
12103  return nullptr;
12104 }
12105 
12106 // Returns the SDNode if it is a constant float BuildVector
12107 // or constant float.
12108 SDNode *SelectionDAG::isConstantFPBuildVectorOrConstantFP(SDValue N) const {
12109  if (isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(N))
12110  return N.getNode();
12111 
12112  if (ISD::isBuildVectorOfConstantFPSDNodes(N.getNode()))
12113  return N.getNode();
12114 
12115  if ((N.getOpcode() == ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR) &&
12116  isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(N.getOperand(0)))
12117  return N.getNode();
12118 
12119  return nullptr;
12120 }
12121 
12122 void SelectionDAG::createOperands(SDNode *Node, ArrayRef<SDValue> Vals) {
12123  assert(!Node->OperandList && "Node already has operands");
12124  assert(SDNode::getMaxNumOperands() >= Vals.size() &&
12125  "too many operands to fit into SDNode");
12126  SDUse *Ops = OperandRecycler.allocate(
12127  ArrayRecycler<SDUse>::Capacity::get(Vals.size()), OperandAllocator);
12128 
12129  bool IsDivergent = false;
12130  for (unsigned I = 0; I != Vals.size(); ++I) {
12131  Ops[I].setUser(Node);
12132  Ops[I].setInitial(Vals[I]);
12133  if (Ops[I].Val.getValueType() != MVT::Other) // Skip Chain. It does not carry divergence.
12134  IsDivergent |= Ops[I].getNode()->isDivergent();
12135  }
12136  Node->NumOperands = Vals.size();
12137  Node->OperandList = Ops;
12138  if (!TLI->isSDNodeAlwaysUniform(Node)) {
12139  IsDivergent |= TLI->isSDNodeSourceOfDivergence(Node, FLI, DA);
12140  Node->SDNodeBits.IsDivergent = IsDivergent;
12141  }
12142  checkForCycles(Node);
12143 }
12144 
12145 SDValue SelectionDAG::getTokenFactor(const SDLoc &DL,
12146  SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Vals) {
12147  size_t Limit = SDNode::getMaxNumOperands();
12148  while (Vals.size() > Limit) {
12149  unsigned SliceIdx = Vals.size() - Limit;
12150  auto ExtractedTFs = ArrayRef<SDValue>(Vals).slice(SliceIdx, Limit);
12151  SDValue NewTF = getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, ExtractedTFs);
12152  Vals.erase(Vals.begin() + SliceIdx, Vals.end());
12153  Vals.emplace_back(NewTF);
12154  }
12155  return getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, Vals);
12156 }
12157 
12158 SDValue SelectionDAG::getNeutralElement(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL,
12159  EVT VT, SDNodeFlags Flags) {
12160  switch (Opcode) {
12161  default:
12162  return SDValue();
12163  case ISD::ADD:
12164  case ISD::OR:
12165  case ISD::XOR:
12166  case ISD::UMAX:
12167  return getConstant(0, DL, VT);
12168  case ISD::MUL:
12169  return getConstant(1, DL, VT);
12170  case ISD::AND:
12171  case ISD::UMIN:
12172  return getAllOnesConstant(DL, VT);
12173  case ISD::SMAX:
12174  return getConstant(APInt::getSignedMinValue(VT.getSizeInBits()), DL, VT);
12175  case ISD::SMIN:
12176  return getConstant(APInt::getSignedMaxValue(VT.getSizeInBits()), DL, VT);
12177  case ISD::FADD:
12178  return getConstantFP(-0.0, DL, VT);
12179  case ISD::FMUL:
12180  return getConstantFP(1.0, DL, VT);
12181  case ISD::FMINNUM:
12182  case ISD::FMAXNUM: {
12183  // Neutral element for fminnum is NaN, Inf or FLT_MAX, depending on FMF.
12184  const fltSemantics &Semantics = EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT);
12185  APFloat NeutralAF = !Flags.hasNoNaNs() ? APFloat::getQNaN(Semantics) :
12186  !Flags.hasNoInfs() ? APFloat::getInf(Semantics) :
12187  APFloat::getLargest(Semantics);
12188  if (Opcode == ISD::FMAXNUM)
12189  NeutralAF.changeSign();
12190 
12191  return getConstantFP(NeutralAF, DL, VT);
12192  }
12193  }
12194 }
12195 
12196 void SelectionDAG::copyExtraInfo(SDNode *From, SDNode *To) {
12197  assert(From && To && "Invalid SDNode; empty source SDValue?");
12198  auto I = SDEI.find(From);
12199  if (I == SDEI.end())
12200  return;
12201 
12202  // Use of operator[] on the DenseMap may cause an insertion, which invalidates
12203  // the iterator, hence the need to make a copy to prevent a use-after-free.
12204  NodeExtraInfo Copy = I->second;
12205  SDEI[To] = std::move(Copy);
12206 }
12207 
12208 #ifndef NDEBUG
12209 static void checkForCyclesHelper(const SDNode *N,
12210  SmallPtrSetImpl<const SDNode*> &Visited,
12211  SmallPtrSetImpl<const SDNode*> &Checked,
12212  const llvm::SelectionDAG *DAG) {
12213  // If this node has already been checked, don't check it again.
12214  if (Checked.count(N))
12215  return;
12216 
12217  // If a node has already been visited on this depth-first walk, reject it as
12218  // a cycle.
12219  if (!Visited.insert(N).second) {
12220  errs() << "Detected cycle in SelectionDAG\n";
12221  dbgs() << "Offending node:\n";
12222  N->dumprFull(DAG); dbgs() << "\n";
12223  abort();
12224  }
12225 
12226  for (const SDValue &Op : N->op_values())
12227  checkForCyclesHelper(Op.getNode(), Visited, Checked, DAG);
12228 
12229  Checked.insert(N);
12230  Visited.erase(N);
12231 }
12232 #endif
12233 
12234 void llvm::checkForCycles(const llvm::SDNode *N,
12235  const llvm::SelectionDAG *DAG,
12236  bool force) {
12237 #ifndef NDEBUG
12238  bool check = force;
12239 #ifdef EXPENSIVE_CHECKS
12240  check = true;
12241 #endif // EXPENSIVE_CHECKS
12242  if (check) {
12243  assert(N && "Checking nonexistent SDNode");
12244  SmallPtrSet<const SDNode*, 32> visited;
12245  SmallPtrSet<const SDNode*, 32> checked;
12246  checkForCyclesHelper(N, visited, checked, DAG);
12247  }
12248 #endif // !NDEBUG
12249 }
12250 
12251 void llvm::checkForCycles(const llvm::SelectionDAG *DAG, bool force) {
12252  checkForCycles(DAG->getRoot().getNode(), DAG, force);
12253 }
